WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:08.920
Part 1 of The Custom House. Introductory to The Scarlet Letter by Nathaniel Hawthorne.

00:00:21.920 --> 00:00:32.680
The Custom House. Part 1. Introductory to The Scarlet Letter by Nathaniel Hawthorne.

00:00:32.820 --> 00:00:39.140
It is a little remarkable that though disinclined to talk over much of myself and my affairs

00:00:39.140 --> 00:00:45.080
at the fireside and to my personal friends, an autobiographical impulse should twice in

00:00:45.080 --> 00:00:49.360
my life have taken possession of me in addressing the public.

00:00:50.140 --> 00:00:56.320
The first time was three or four years since, when I favoured the reader inexcusably, and

00:00:56.320 --> 00:01:01.800
for no earthly reason that either the indulgent reader or the intrusive author could imagine,

00:01:02.400 --> 00:01:09.400
with a description of my way of life in the deep quietude of an old manse. And now, because

00:01:09.400 --> 00:01:14.700
beyond my deserts I was happy enough to find a listener or two on the former occasion,

00:01:14.700 --> 00:01:21.180
I again seize the public by the button and talk of my three years' experience in a custom

00:01:21.180 --> 00:01:28.300
house. The example of the famous PP, clerk of this parish, was never more faithfully

00:01:28.300 --> 00:01:34.240
followed. The truth seems to be, however, that when he casts his leaves forth upon the

00:01:34.240 --> 00:01:39.800
wind, the author addresses not the many who will fling aside his volume or never take

00:01:40.560 --> 00:01:46.080
but the few who will understand him better than most of his schoolmates and lifemates.

00:01:46.940 --> 00:01:52.720
Some authors, indeed, do far more than this, and indulge themselves in such confidential

00:01:52.720 --> 00:01:58.960
depths of revelation as could fittingly be addressed only and exclusively to the one

00:01:58.960 --> 00:02:04.680
heart and mind of perfect sympathy. As if the printed book, thrown at large on the wide

00:02:05.240 --> 00:02:10.960
were certain to find out the divided segment of the writer's own nature and complete his

00:02:10.960 --> 00:02:17.280
circle of existence by bringing him into communion with it. It is scarcely decorous, however,

00:02:17.300 --> 00:02:24.760
to speak all, even where we speak impersonally, but as thoughts are frozen and utterance benumbed

00:02:24.760 --> 00:02:30.620
unless the speaker stand in some true relation with his audience, it may be pardonable to

00:02:30.620 --> 00:02:36.460
imagine that a friend, a kind and apprehensive, though not the closest friend, is listening

00:02:36.460 --> 00:02:42.840
to our talk, and then, a native reserve being thawed by this genial consciousness, we may

00:02:42.840 --> 00:02:48.640
prate of the circumstances that lie around us and even of our self, but still keep the

00:02:48.640 --> 00:02:55.040
inmost me behind its veil. To this extent, and within these limits, an author, he thinks,

00:02:55.040 --> 00:03:01.000
may be autobiographical without violating either the reader's rights or his own.

00:03:02.320 --> 00:03:08.340
It will be seen, likewise, that this custom house sketch has a certain propriety of a kind

00:03:08.340 --> 00:03:14.220
always recognised in literature as explaining how a large portion of the following pages

00:03:14.220 --> 00:03:20.940
came into my possession and as offering proofs of the authenticity of a narrative therein contained.

00:03:21.500 --> 00:03:27.380
This, in fact, a desire to put myself in my true position as editor, or very little more,

00:03:27.740 --> 00:03:33.980
of the most prolix among the tales that make up my volume, this and no other is my true reason

00:03:33.980 --> 00:03:40.160
for assuming a personal relation with the public. In accomplishing the main purpose,

00:03:40.240 --> 00:03:46.660
it has appeared allowable by a few extra touches to give a faint representation of a mode of life

00:03:46.660 --> 00:03:51.720
not heretofore described, together with some of the characters that move in it,

00:03:51.920 --> 00:03:54.740
among whom the author happened to make one.

00:03:56.200 --> 00:04:02.320
In my native town of Salem, at the head of what, half a century ago, in the days of old King Derby,

00:04:02.440 --> 00:04:07.320
was a bustling wharf, but which is now burdened with decayed wooden warehouses,

00:04:07.740 --> 00:04:14.560
and exhibits few or no symptoms of a commercial life, except perhaps a bark or brig halfway down

00:04:14.560 --> 00:04:21.460
its melancholy length, discharging hides, or, nearer at hand, a Nova Scotia schooner,

00:04:21.620 --> 00:04:26.920
pitching out her cargo of firewood, at the head, I say, of this dilapidated wharf,

00:04:27.280 --> 00:04:33.360
which the tide often overflows, and along which, at the basin in the rear of the row of buildings,

00:04:33.560 --> 00:04:38.700
the track of many languid years is seen in a border of unthrifty grass.

00:04:39.260 --> 00:04:44.520
Here, with a view from its front windows, are down this not very enlivening prospect,

00:04:44.920 --> 00:04:49.380
and thence, across the harbour, stands a spacious edifice of brick.

00:04:50.340 --> 00:04:55.860
From the loftiest point of its roof, during precisely three and a half hours of each forenoon,

00:04:56.420 --> 00:05:02.540
floats or droops, in breeze or calm, the banner of the Republic, but with the thirteen stripes

00:05:02.540 --> 00:05:08.820
turned vertically instead of horizontally, and thus indicating that a civil and not a military

00:05:08.820 --> 00:05:16.680
post of Uncle Sam's government is here established. Its front is ornamented with a portico of half

00:05:16.680 --> 00:05:22.780
a dozen wooden pillars, supporting a balcony, beneath which a flight of wide granite steps

00:05:22.780 --> 00:05:29.840
descends towards the street. Over the entrance hovers an enormous specimen of the American eagle,

00:05:29.840 --> 00:05:35.380
with outspread wings, a shield before her breast, and, if I recollect to write,

00:05:35.580 --> 00:05:39.980
a bunch of intermingled thunderbolts and barbed arrows in each claw.

00:05:40.960 --> 00:05:45.940
With the customary infirmity of temper that characterises this unhappy fowl,

00:05:45.980 --> 00:05:51.780
she appears, by the fierceness of her beak and eye, and the general truculency of her attitude,

00:05:52.120 --> 00:05:57.960
to threaten mischief to the inoffensive community, and especially to warn all citizens,

00:05:57.960 --> 00:06:03.960
careful of their safety, against intruding on the premises which she overshadows with her wings.

00:06:05.180 --> 00:06:09.880
Nevertheless, vixenly as she looks, many people are seeking, at this very moment,

00:06:10.220 --> 00:06:15.360
to shelter themselves under the wing of the Federal Eagle, imagining, I presume,

00:06:15.440 --> 00:06:21.600
that her bosom has all the softness and snugness of an eiderdown pillow. But she has no great

00:06:21.600 --> 00:06:27.180
tenderness, even in her best of moods, and sooner or later, often a soon than late,

00:06:27.640 --> 00:06:32.400
is apt to fling off her nestlings with a scratch of her claw, a dab of her beak,

00:06:32.480 --> 00:06:39.660
or a rankling wound from her barbed arrows. The pavement round about the above described edifice,

00:06:39.760 --> 00:06:45.460
which we may as well name at once as the custom house of the port, has grass enough growing in

00:06:45.460 --> 00:06:52.140
its chinks to show that it has not, of late days, been worn by any multitudinous resort of business.

00:06:53.020 --> 00:06:58.180
In some months of the year, however, there often chances are forenoon when affairs move

00:06:58.180 --> 00:07:05.060
onward with a livelier tread. Such occasions might remind the elderly citizen of that period

00:07:05.060 --> 00:07:12.180
before the last war with England, when Salem was a port by itself, not scorned as she is now by her

00:07:12.180 --> 00:07:18.580
merchants and ship-owners, who permit her wharves to crumble to ruin while their ventures go to

00:07:18.580 --> 00:07:25.000
swell needlessly and imperceptibly the mighty flood of commerce at New York or Boston.

00:07:26.120 --> 00:07:30.200
On some such morning, when three or four vessels happen to have arrived at once,

00:07:30.380 --> 00:07:35.800
usually from Africa or South America, or to be on the verge of their departure thitherward,

00:07:36.160 --> 00:07:41.080
there is the sound of frequent feet passing briskly up and down the granite steps.

00:07:42.180 --> 00:07:47.220
Here, before his own wife has greeted him, you may greet the sea-flushed ship-master,

00:07:47.500 --> 00:07:52.660
Justin Port, with his vessel's papers under his arm in a tarnished tin box.

00:07:53.220 --> 00:07:57.880
Here, too, comes his owner, cheerful or sombre, gracious or in the sulks,

00:07:58.140 --> 00:08:03.580
according as his scheme of the now-accomplished voyage has been realized in merchandise that

00:08:03.580 --> 00:08:10.160
will readily be turned to gold, or has buried him under a bulk of in-commodities such as nobody

00:08:10.160 --> 00:08:16.760
will care to rid him of. Here, likewise, the germ of the wrinkled-browed, grizzly-bearded,

00:08:17.120 --> 00:08:23.300
careworn merchant, we have the smart young clerk, who gets the taste of traffic as a wolf-cub does

00:08:23.300 --> 00:08:28.840
a blud, and already sends adventures in his master's ships when he had better be sailing

00:08:28.840 --> 00:08:34.880
mimic boats upon a mill-pond. Another figure in the scene is the outward-bound sailor,

00:08:34.880 --> 00:08:41.360
in quest of a protection, or the recently arrived one, pale and feeble, seeking a passport to the

00:08:41.360 --> 00:08:47.700
hospital. Nor must we forget the captains of the rusty little schooners that bring firewood from

00:08:47.700 --> 00:08:53.440
the British provinces, a rough-looking set of tarpaulins, without the alertness of the

00:08:53.440 --> 00:08:59.780
Yankee aspect, but contributing an item of no slight importance to our decaying trade.

00:09:00.620 --> 00:09:06.560
Cluster all these individuals together, as they sometimes were, with other miscellaneous ones to

00:09:06.560 --> 00:09:11.920
diversify the group, and for the time being it made the Custom-House a stirring scene.

00:09:12.440 --> 00:09:17.540
More frequently, however, on ascending the steps, you would discern, in the entry,

00:09:17.580 --> 00:09:22.420
if it were summer-time, or in their appropriate rooms, if wintry or inclement weather,

00:09:22.900 --> 00:09:27.780
a row of venerable figures, sitting in old-fashioned chairs which were tipped on

00:09:27.780 --> 00:09:34.640
their hind legs back against the wall. Oftentimes they were asleep, but occasionally might be heard

00:09:34.640 --> 00:09:40.640
talking together, in voices between speech and a snore, and with that lack of energy that

00:09:40.640 --> 00:09:46.720
distinguishes the occupants of alms-houses, and all other human beings who depend for subsistence

00:09:46.720 --> 00:09:53.640
on charity, on monopolised labour, or on anything else but their own independent exertions.

00:09:55.080 --> 00:10:01.780
These old gentlemen, seated, like Matthew, at the receipt of custom, but not very liable to be

00:10:01.780 --> 00:10:06.800
summoned thence, like him, for apostolic errands, were Custom-House officers.

00:10:08.480 --> 00:10:13.560
Furthermore, on the left hand, as you enter the front door, is a certain room, or office,

00:10:13.680 --> 00:10:19.820
about fifteen feet square, and of a lofty height, with two of its arched windows commanding a view

00:10:19.820 --> 00:10:25.760
of the aforesaid dilapidated wharf, and the third looking across a narrow lane, and along

00:10:25.760 --> 00:10:31.720
a portion of Derby Street. All three give glimpses of the shops of grocers, block-makers,

00:10:32.080 --> 00:10:38.020
slop-sellers and ship-chandlers, around the doors of which are generally to be seen laughing and

00:10:38.020 --> 00:10:44.640
gossiping clusters of old salts and such other wharf-rats as haunt the whopping of a seaport.

00:10:45.580 --> 00:10:52.160
The room itself is cobwebbed and dingy with old paint. Its floor is strewn with grey sand,

00:10:52.200 --> 00:10:57.740
in a fashion that has elsewhere fallen into long disuse, and it is easy to conclude,

00:10:57.760 --> 00:11:03.240
from the general slovenliness of the place, that this is a sanctuary into which woman-kind,

00:11:03.380 --> 00:11:08.520
with her tools of magic, the broom and mop, has very infrequent access.

00:11:09.480 --> 00:11:15.240
In the way of furniture there is a stove with a voluminous funnel, an old pine desk with a

00:11:15.240 --> 00:11:21.660
three-legged stool beside it, two or three wooden bottom chairs exceedingly decrepit and infirm,

00:11:21.900 --> 00:11:28.580
and, not to forget the library, on some shelves a score or two of volumes of the Acts of Congress,

00:11:29.020 --> 00:11:35.200
and a bulky digest of the revenue laws. A tin pipe ascends through the ceiling,

00:11:35.200 --> 00:11:39.920
and forms a medium of vocal communication with other parts of the edifice.

00:11:40.580 --> 00:11:46.940
And here, some six months ago, pacing from corner to corner, or lounging on the long-legged stool,

00:11:47.100 --> 00:11:52.700
with his elbow on the desk and his eyes wandering up and down the columns of the morning newspaper,

00:11:53.240 --> 00:11:58.660
you might have recognised, honoured reader, the same individual who welcomed you into his

00:11:58.660 --> 00:12:04.400
cheery little study, where the sunshine glimmered so pleasantly through the willow branches on the

00:12:04.400 --> 00:12:10.740
western side of the old manse. But now, should you go thither to seek him, you would inquire in

00:12:10.740 --> 00:12:17.600
vain for the loco-foco surveyor. The besom of reform has swept him out of office, and a

00:12:17.600 --> 00:12:21.800
worthier successor wears his dignity and pockets his emoluments.

00:12:23.240 --> 00:12:29.140
This old town of Salem, my native place, though I have dwelt much away from it both in boyhood

00:12:29.140 --> 00:12:35.440
and mature years, possesses, or did possess, a hold on my affections, the force of which

00:12:35.440 --> 00:12:42.180
I have never realised during my seasons of actual residence here. Indeed, so far as its physical

00:12:42.180 --> 00:12:48.260
aspect is concerned, with its flat, unvaried surface, covered chiefly with wooden houses,

00:12:48.640 --> 00:12:54.280
few or none of which pretend to architectural beauty, its irregularity, which is neither

00:12:54.280 --> 00:13:01.000
picturesque nor quaint, but only tame, its long and lazy street lounging wearisomely

00:13:01.000 --> 00:13:06.380
through the whole extent of the peninsula, with Gallows Hill and New Guinea at one end,

00:13:06.560 --> 00:13:11.800
and a view of the Arms House at the other. Such being the features of my native town,

00:13:11.960 --> 00:13:18.140
it would be quite as reasonable to form a sentimental attachment to a disarranged checkerboard.

00:13:18.900 --> 00:13:24.880
And yet, though invariably happiest elsewhere, there is within me a feeling for old Salem,

00:13:25.320 --> 00:13:29.340
which, in lack of a better phrase, I must be content to call affection.

00:13:30.040 --> 00:13:35.320
The sentiment is probably assignable to the deep and aged roots which my family has struck

00:13:35.320 --> 00:13:41.200
into the soil. It is now nearly two centuries and a quarter since the original Britain,

00:13:41.660 --> 00:13:46.640
the earliest emigrant of my name, made his appearance in the wild and forest-bordered

00:13:46.640 --> 00:13:52.680
settlement, which has since become a city. And here his descendants have been born and died,

00:13:53.040 --> 00:13:58.220
and have mingled their earthy substance with the soil, until no small portion of it must

00:13:58.220 --> 00:14:04.360
necessarily be akin to the mortal frame, wherewith, for a little while, I walk the streets.

00:14:05.020 --> 00:14:11.180
In part, therefore, the attachment which I speak of is the mere sensuous sympathy of dust for dust.

00:14:11.740 --> 00:14:18.060
Few of my countrymen can know what it is, nor, as frequent transplantation is perhaps better

00:14:18.060 --> 00:14:25.180
for the stock, need they consider it desirable to know. But the sentiment has likewise its moral

00:14:25.180 --> 00:14:31.200
quality. The figure of that first ancestor, invested by family tradition with a dim and

00:14:31.200 --> 00:14:36.660
dusky grandeur, was present to my boyish imagination as far back as I can remember.

00:14:37.480 --> 00:14:41.840
It still haunts me, and induces a sort of home feeling with the past,

00:14:42.240 --> 00:14:46.060
which I scarcely claim in reference to the present phase of the town.

00:14:46.500 --> 00:14:51.940
I seem to have a stronger claim to a residence here on account of this grave, bearded,

00:14:52.080 --> 00:14:58.040
sable-cloaked, and steeple-crowned progenitor, who came so early with his Bible and his sword,

00:14:58.520 --> 00:15:03.700
and trod the unworn street with such a stately port, and made so large a figure,

00:15:03.700 --> 00:15:10.200
as a man of war and peace, a stronger claim than for myself, whose name is seldom heard,

00:15:10.320 --> 00:15:17.360
and my face hardly known. He was a soldier, legislator, judge. He was a ruler in the church.

00:15:17.500 --> 00:15:24.120
He had all the puritanic traits, both good and evil. He was likewise a bitter persecutor,

00:15:24.240 --> 00:15:30.000
as witnessed the Quakers, who have remembered him in their histories, and relate an incident of his

00:15:30.000 --> 00:15:35.420
hard severity towards a woman of their sect, which will last longer, it is to be feared,

00:15:35.780 --> 00:15:42.280
than any record of his better deeds, although these were many. His son, too, inherited the

00:15:42.280 --> 00:15:48.180
persecuting spirit, and made himself so conspicuous in the martyrdom of the witches, that their blood

00:15:48.180 --> 00:15:55.080
may fairly be said to have left a stain upon him. So deep a stain, indeed, that his old dry bones in

00:15:55.080 --> 00:16:00.980
Charter Street burial ground must still retain it, if they have not crumbled utterly to dust.

00:16:02.120 --> 00:16:07.360
I know not whether these ancestors of mine bethought themselves to repent, and ask pardon of

00:16:07.360 --> 00:16:12.980
heaven for their cruelties, or whether they are now groaning under the heavy consequences of them

00:16:12.980 --> 00:16:19.160
in another state of being. At all events, I, the present writer, as their representative,

00:16:19.160 --> 00:16:25.160
hereby take shame upon myself for their sakes, and pray that any curse incurred by them,

00:16:25.300 --> 00:16:31.040
as I have heard, and as the dreary unprosperous condition of the race for many a long year back

00:16:31.040 --> 00:16:38.220
would argue to exist, may be now and henceforth removed. Doubtless, however, either of these

00:16:38.220 --> 00:16:43.740
stern and black-browed Puritans would have thought it quite a sufficient retribution for his sins,

00:16:43.740 --> 00:16:50.340
that after so long a lapse of years the old trunk of the family tree, with so much venerable moss

00:16:50.340 --> 00:16:58.100
upon it, should have borne as its topmost bough an idler like myself. No aim that I have ever

00:16:58.100 --> 00:17:04.380
cherished would they recognise as laudable. No success of mine, if my life beyond its domestic

00:17:04.380 --> 00:17:10.580
scope had ever been brightened by success, would they deem otherwise than worthless, if not

00:17:10.580 --> 00:17:17.200
positively disgraceful. What is he, murmurs one grey shadow of my forefathers to the other,

00:17:17.480 --> 00:17:23.860
a writer of story books? What kind of a business in life, what mode of glorifying God or being

00:17:23.860 --> 00:17:31.080
serviceable to mankind in his day and generation, may that be? Why, the degenerate fellow might as

00:17:31.080 --> 00:17:37.420
well have been a fiddler. Such are the compliments banded between my great-grandsires and myself

00:17:37.420 --> 00:17:42.380
across the gulf of time. And yet, let them scorn me as they will,

00:17:42.580 --> 00:17:46.600
strong traits of their nature have intertwined themselves with mine.

00:17:47.720 --> 00:17:53.760
Planted deep in the town's earliest infancy and childhood by these two earnest and energetic men,

00:17:54.220 --> 00:18:01.620
the race has ever since subsisted here, always too in respectability, never, so far as I have known,

00:18:01.620 --> 00:18:07.020
disgraced by a single unworthy member, but seldom or never, on the other hand,

00:18:07.160 --> 00:18:13.080
after the first two generations, performing any memorable deed, or so much as putting forward

00:18:13.080 --> 00:18:19.980
acclaim to public notice. Gradually they have sunk almost out of sight, as old houses, here and there

00:18:19.980 --> 00:18:25.440
about the streets, get covered halfway to the eaves by the accumulation of new soil.

00:18:26.000 --> 00:18:29.820
From father to son, for above a hundred years they followed the sea,

00:18:30.300 --> 00:18:35.980
a grey-headed shipmaster in each generation, retiring from the quarterdeck to the homestead,

00:18:36.280 --> 00:18:42.460
while a boy of fourteen took the hereditary place before the mast, confronting the salt spray and

00:18:42.460 --> 00:18:49.240
the gale, which had blustered against his sire and grandsire. The boy also, in due time,

00:18:49.240 --> 00:18:55.340
passed from the foc'sle to the cabin, spent a tempestuous manhood, and returned from his world

00:18:55.340 --> 00:19:01.640
wanderings to grow old and die and mingle his dust with the natal earth. This long connection

00:19:01.640 --> 00:19:07.720
of a family with one spot, as its place of birth and burial, creates a kindred between the human

00:19:07.720 --> 00:19:13.780
being and the locality, quite independent of any charm in the scenery or moral circumstances

00:19:13.780 --> 00:19:20.860
that surround him. It is not love, but instinct. The new inhabitant who came himself from a foreign

00:19:20.860 --> 00:19:27.620
land, or whose father or grandfather came, has little claim to be called a Salemite. He has no

00:19:27.620 --> 00:19:34.000
conception of the oyster-like tenacity with which an old settler, over whom his third century is

00:19:34.000 --> 00:19:40.480
creeping, clings to the spot where his successive generations have been embedded. It is no matter

00:19:40.480 --> 00:19:46.480
that the place is joyless for him, that he is weary of the old wooden houses, the mud and dust,

00:19:46.880 --> 00:19:53.580
the dead level of sight and sentiment, the chill east wind and the chillest of social atmospheres.

00:19:53.960 --> 00:19:59.620
All these, and whatever faults besides, he may see or imagine, and nothing to the purpose.

00:20:00.320 --> 00:20:05.860
The spell survives, and just as powerfully as if the natal spot were an earthly paradise.

00:20:06.500 --> 00:20:12.740
So has it been in my case. I felt it almost as a destiny to make Salem my home,

00:20:13.000 --> 00:20:18.320
so that the mould of features and cast of character which had all along been familiar here.

00:20:19.020 --> 00:20:24.820
Ever, as one representative of the race lay down in his grave, another assuming, as it were,

00:20:24.940 --> 00:20:30.860
his century march along the main street, might still in my little day be seen and recognised

00:20:30.860 --> 00:20:36.860
in the old town. Nevertheless, this very sentiment is an evidence that the connection

00:20:36.860 --> 00:20:43.720
which has become an unhealthy one should at last be severed. Human nature will not flourish any

00:20:43.720 --> 00:20:51.060
more than a potato if it be planted and replanted for too long a series of generations in the same

00:20:51.060 --> 00:20:57.260
worn-out soil. My children have had other birthplaces, and so far as their fortunes

00:20:57.260 --> 00:21:02.200
may be within my control shall strike their roots into unaccustomed earth.

00:21:03.520 --> 00:21:09.360
On emerging from the old manse, it was chiefly this strange, indolent, unjoyous attachment for

00:21:09.360 --> 00:21:15.780
my native town that brought me to fill a place in Uncle Sam's brick edifice, when I might as well,

00:21:15.780 --> 00:21:22.940
or better, have gone somewhere else. My doom was on me. It was not the first time, nor the second,

00:21:22.940 --> 00:21:29.820
that I had gone away, as it seemed, permanently, but yet returned like the bad hapenny, or as if

00:21:29.820 --> 00:21:36.260
Salem were for me the inevitable centre of the universe. So one fine morning I ascended the

00:21:36.260 --> 00:21:41.240
flight of granite steps with the president's commission in my pocket, and was introduced

00:21:41.240 --> 00:21:47.980
to the corps of gentlemen who were to aid me in my weighty responsibility as chief executive officer

00:21:47.980 --> 00:21:55.940
of the Custom House. I doubt greatly, or rather I do not doubt at all, whether any public

00:21:55.940 --> 00:22:01.520
functionary of the United States, either in the civil or military line, has ever had such a

00:22:01.520 --> 00:22:08.620
patriarchal body of veterans under his orders as myself. The whereabouts of the oldest inhabitant

00:22:08.620 --> 00:22:14.040
was at once settled when I looked at them. For upwards of twenty years before this epoch,

00:22:14.040 --> 00:22:19.640
the independent position of the collector had kept the Salem Custom House out of the whirlpool

00:22:19.640 --> 00:22:26.180
of political vicissitude, which makes the tenure of office generally so fragile. A soldier,

00:22:26.380 --> 00:22:32.320
New England's most distinguished soldier, he stood firmly on the pedestal of his gallant services,

00:22:32.760 --> 00:22:39.300
and himself secure in the wise liberality of the successive administrations through which he had

00:22:39.300 --> 00:22:45.560
office, he had been the safety of his subordinates in many an hour of danger and heart-quake.

00:22:46.140 --> 00:22:52.560
General Miller was radically conservative, a man over whose kindly nature habit had no slight

00:22:52.560 --> 00:22:59.100
influence, attaching himself strongly to familiar faces, and with difficulty moved to change,

00:22:59.400 --> 00:23:03.000
even when change might have brought unquestionable improvement.

00:23:03.000 --> 00:23:10.380
Thus, on taking charge of my department, I found few but aged men. They were ancient sea captains

00:23:10.380 --> 00:23:16.580
for the most part, who, after being tossed on every sea and standing up sturdily against life's

00:23:16.580 --> 00:23:23.500
tempestuous blast, had finally drifted into this quiet nook, where, with little to disturb them

00:23:23.500 --> 00:23:29.580
except the periodical terrors of a presidential election, they, one and all, acquired a new lease

00:23:29.580 --> 00:23:35.740
of existence. Though by no means less liable than their fellow men to age and infirmity,

00:23:36.040 --> 00:23:42.080
they had evidently some talisman or other that kept death at bay. Two or three of their number,

00:23:42.080 --> 00:23:48.300
as I was assured, being gouty and rheumatic, or perhaps bedridden, never dreamt of making

00:23:48.300 --> 00:23:54.460
their appearance at the Custom House during a large part of the year, but, after a torpid winter,

00:23:54.460 --> 00:24:01.380
would creep out into the warm sunshine of May or June, go lazily about what they termed duty,

00:24:01.760 --> 00:24:05.760
and at their own leisure and convenience, betake themselves to bed again.

00:24:06.480 --> 00:24:12.420
I must plead guilty to the charge of abbreviating the official breath of more than one of these

00:24:12.420 --> 00:24:18.740
venerable servants of the Republic. They were allowed on my representation to rest from their

00:24:18.740 --> 00:24:24.780
arduous labours, and soon afterwards, as if their sole principle of life had been zeal for their

00:24:24.780 --> 00:24:32.180
country's service, as I verily believe it was, withdrew to a better world. It is a pious

00:24:32.180 --> 00:24:37.840
consolation to me that through my interference a sufficient space was allowed them for repentance

00:24:37.840 --> 00:24:44.000
of the evil and corrupt practices, into which, as a matter of course, every Custom House officer

00:24:44.000 --> 00:24:50.080
must be supposed to fall. Neither the front nor the back entrance of the Custom House

00:24:50.080 --> 00:24:58.020
opens on the road to paradise. The greater part of my officers were weak. It was well for their

00:24:58.020 --> 00:25:03.300
venerable brotherhood that the new surveyor was not a politician, and though a faithful Democrat

00:25:03.300 --> 00:25:09.140
in principle, neither received nor held his office with any reference to political services.

00:25:09.140 --> 00:25:15.540
Had it been otherwise, had an active politician been put into this influential post to assume

00:25:15.540 --> 00:25:20.880
the easy task of making head against a Whig collector whose infirmities withheld him from

00:25:20.880 --> 00:25:26.620
the personal administration of his office, hardly a man of the old corps would have drawn the breath

00:25:26.620 --> 00:25:32.640
of official life within a month after the exterminating angel had come up the Custom House steps.

00:25:33.660 --> 00:25:39.120
According to the received code in such matters, it would have been nothing short of duty in a

00:25:39.120 --> 00:25:44.040
politician to bring every one of those white heads under the axe of the guillotine.

00:25:44.960 --> 00:25:50.760
It was plain enough to discern that the old fellows dreaded some such discourtesy at my hands.

00:25:51.320 --> 00:25:57.060
It pained, and at the same time amused me, to behold the terrors that attended my advent,

00:25:57.620 --> 00:26:04.700
to see a furrowed cheek, weather-beaten by half a century of storm, turn ashy pale at the glance of

00:26:04.700 --> 00:26:11.300
harmless an individual as myself. To detect, as one or another addressed me, the tremor of a voice

00:26:11.300 --> 00:26:16.240
which in long past days had been wont to bellow through a speaking trumpet,

00:26:16.780 --> 00:26:23.380
hoarsely enough to frighten Boreas himself to silence. They knew these excellent old persons

00:26:23.380 --> 00:26:29.560
that by all established rule, and as regarded some of them, weighted by their own lack of efficiency

00:26:29.560 --> 00:26:35.040
for business, they ought to have given place to younger men, more orthodox in politics,

00:26:35.200 --> 00:26:40.720
and altogether fitter than themselves to serve our common uncle. I knew it too,

00:26:40.720 --> 00:26:46.560
but could never quite find in my heart to act upon the knowledge, much and deservedly to my

00:26:46.560 --> 00:26:52.140
own discredit therefore, and considerably to the detriment of my official conscience.

00:26:52.340 --> 00:26:58.460
They continued, during my incumbency, to creep about the wharves and loiter up and down the

00:26:58.460 --> 00:27:04.600
house steps. They spent a good deal of time also asleep in their accustomed corners,

00:27:05.040 --> 00:27:11.080
with their chairs tilted back against the wall, awaking, however, once or twice in a forenoon,

00:27:11.440 --> 00:27:18.260
to bore one another with the several thousandth repetition of old sea stories and mouldy jokes

00:27:18.260 --> 00:27:22.360
that had grown to be passwords and counter-signs among them.

00:27:23.280 --> 00:27:29.620
The discovery was soon made, I imagine, that the new Surveyor had no great harm in him. So,

00:27:29.640 --> 00:27:33.720
with lightsome hearts, and the happy consciousness of being usefully employed,

00:27:34.020 --> 00:27:39.360
in their own behalf at least, if not for our beloved country, these good old gentlemen went

00:27:39.360 --> 00:27:44.460
through the various formalities of office. Sugaciously, under their spectacles,

00:27:44.520 --> 00:27:49.580
did they peep into the holds of vessels. Mighty was their fuss about little matters,

00:27:49.580 --> 00:27:55.340
and marvellous sometimes, the obtuseness that allowed greater ones to slip between their

00:27:55.340 --> 00:28:01.320
fingers. Whenever such a mischance occurred, when a wagonload of valuable merchandise had been

00:28:01.320 --> 00:28:06.960
smuggled ashore, at noonday perhaps, and directly beneath their unsuspicious noses,

00:28:07.040 --> 00:28:12.640
nothing could exceed the vigilance and alacrity with which they proceeded to lock and double-lock,

00:28:13.020 --> 00:28:18.100
and secure with tape and sealing-wax all the avenues of the delinquent vessel.

00:28:18.780 --> 00:28:24.500
Instead of a reprimand for their previous negligence, the case seemed rather to require

00:28:24.500 --> 00:28:30.980
a eulogium on their praiseworthy caution, after the mischief had happened, a grateful recognition

00:28:30.980 --> 00:28:36.040
of the promptitude of their zeal, the moment that there was no longer any remedy.

00:28:37.320 --> 00:28:43.540
Unless people are more than commonly disagreeable, it is my foolish habit to contract a kindness for

00:28:43.540 --> 00:28:50.080
them. The better part of my companion's character, if it have a better part, is that which usually

00:28:50.080 --> 00:28:57.840
comes uppermost in my regard, and forms the type whereby I recognise the man. As most of these old

00:28:57.840 --> 00:29:04.000
custom house-officers had good traits, and as my position in reference to them, being paternal and

00:29:04.000 --> 00:29:09.820
protective, was favourable to the growth of friendly sentiments, I soon grew to like them all.

00:29:10.160 --> 00:29:16.660
It was pleasant in the summer forenoons, when the fervent heat that almost liquefied the rest of the

00:29:16.660 --> 00:29:23.680
human family merely communicated a genial warmth to their half-torpid systems. It was pleasant to

00:29:23.680 --> 00:29:28.880
hear them chatting in the back entry, a row of them all tipped against the wall as usual,

00:29:29.320 --> 00:29:35.340
while the frozen witticisms of past generations were thawed out and came bubbling with laughter

00:29:35.340 --> 00:29:42.180
from their lips. Externally, the jollity of aged men has much in common with the mirth of children.

00:29:42.720 --> 00:29:48.020
The intellect, any more than a deep sense of humour, has little to do with the matter. It

00:29:48.020 --> 00:29:54.160
is, with both, a gleam that plays upon the surface, and imparts a sunny and cheery aspect

00:29:54.160 --> 00:30:01.520
to light to the green branch and grey mouldering trunk. In one case, however, it is real sunshine.

00:30:01.520 --> 00:30:06.700
In the other, it more resembles the phosphorescent glow of decaying wood.

00:30:07.640 --> 00:30:12.280
It would be sad injustice, the reader must understand, to represent all my excellent

00:30:12.280 --> 00:30:18.620
old friends as in their dotage. In the first place, my co-editors were not invariably old,

00:30:19.140 --> 00:30:23.920
though were men among them in their strength and prime of marked ability and energy,

00:30:24.200 --> 00:30:29.500
and altogether superior to the sluggish and dependent mode of life on which their evil

00:30:29.500 --> 00:30:35.040
stars had cast them. Then, moreover, the white locks of age were sometimes found to be the

00:30:35.040 --> 00:30:40.600
thatch of an intellectual tenement in good repair. But as respects the majority of my

00:30:40.600 --> 00:30:45.220
corps of veterans, there would be no wrong done, if I characterise them generally,

00:30:45.600 --> 00:30:51.400
as a set of wearisome old souls who had gathered nothing worth preservation from their varied

00:30:51.400 --> 00:30:57.380
experience of life. They seemed to have flung away all the golden grain of practical wisdom

00:30:57.380 --> 00:31:03.140
which they had enjoyed so many opportunities of harvesting, and most carefully to have stored

00:31:03.140 --> 00:31:09.280
their memories with the husks. They spoke with far more interest and unction of their morning's

00:31:09.280 --> 00:31:15.540
breakfast, or yesterday's, today's, or tomorrow's dinner, than of the shipwreck of forty or fifty

00:31:15.540 --> 00:31:20.840
years ago, and all the world's wonders which they had witnessed with their youthful eyes.

00:31:22.120 --> 00:31:27.680
The father of the Custom House, the patriarch not only of this little squad of officials,

00:31:28.160 --> 00:31:34.020
but, I am bold to say, of the respectable body of tide-waiters all over the United States,

00:31:34.440 --> 00:31:41.200
was a certain permanent inspector. He might truly be termed a legitimate son of the revenue system,

00:31:41.500 --> 00:31:47.880
died in the wool, or rather born in the purple, since his sire, a revolutionary colonel and

00:31:47.880 --> 00:31:54.300
collector of the port, had created an office for him, and appointed him to fill it, at a period

00:31:54.300 --> 00:32:00.660
of the early ages which few living men can now remember. This inspector, when I first knew him,

00:32:00.700 --> 00:32:06.640
was a man of four score years or thereabouts, and certainly one of the most wonderful specimens of

00:32:06.640 --> 00:32:13.640
winter green that you would be likely to discover in a lifetime search. With his florid cheek,

00:32:13.640 --> 00:32:19.960
his compact figure smartly arrayed in a bright buttoned blue coat, his brisk and vigorous step,

00:32:20.040 --> 00:32:26.500
and his hale and hearty aspect, altogether he seemed, not young indeed, but a kind of new

00:32:26.500 --> 00:32:33.000
contrivance of mother nature in the shape of man, whom age and infirmity had no business to touch.

00:32:33.700 --> 00:32:37.840
His voice and laugh, which perpetually re-echoed through the Custom House,

00:32:37.840 --> 00:32:42.540
had nothing of the tremulous quaver and cackle of an old man's utterance.

00:32:42.920 --> 00:32:48.580
They came strutting out of his lungs like the crow of a cock, or the blast of a clarion.

00:32:49.400 --> 00:32:53.460
Looking at him merely as an animal, and there was very little else to look at,

00:32:53.680 --> 00:32:59.300
he was a most satisfactory object from the thorough helpfulness and wholesomeness of his system,

00:32:59.720 --> 00:33:06.720
and his capacity, at that extreme age, to enjoy all, or nearly all, the delights which he had

00:33:06.720 --> 00:33:14.200
aimed at or conceived of. The careless security of his life in the Custom House on a regular income,

00:33:14.540 --> 00:33:18.120
and with but slight and infrequent apprehensions of removal,

00:33:18.560 --> 00:33:22.460
had no doubt contributed to make time pass lightly over him.

00:33:23.480 --> 00:33:29.560
The original and more potent causes, however, lay in the rare perfection of his animal nature,

00:33:29.940 --> 00:33:34.400
the moderate proportion of intellect, and the very trifling admixture of

00:33:34.400 --> 00:33:40.480
moral and spiritual ingredients, these latter qualities indeed being in barely enough measure

00:33:40.480 --> 00:33:46.160
to keep the old gentleman from walking on all thaws. He possessed no power of thought,

00:33:46.280 --> 00:33:52.940
no depth of feeling, no troublesome sensibilities, nothing in short but a few commonplace instincts,

00:33:53.380 --> 00:33:58.680
which, aided by the cheerful temper that grew inevitably out of his physical well-being,

00:33:59.160 --> 00:34:04.000
did duty very respectably and to general acceptance in lieu of a heart.

00:34:04.940 --> 00:34:10.640
He had been the husband of three wives, all long since dead, the father of twenty children,

00:34:10.780 --> 00:34:16.420
most of whom, at every age of childhood or maturity, had likewise returned to dust.

00:34:17.240 --> 00:34:22.780
Here, one would suppose, might have been sorrow enough to imbue the sunniest disposition through

00:34:22.780 --> 00:34:30.800
and through with a sable tinge, not so with our old inspector. One brief sigh sufficed to

00:34:30.800 --> 00:34:36.780
carry off the entire burden of these dismal reminiscences. The next moment he was as ready

00:34:36.780 --> 00:34:42.280
for sport as any unbreached infant, far readier than the collector's junior clerk,

00:34:42.640 --> 00:34:46.920
who at nineteen years was much the elder and graver man of the two.

00:34:47.940 --> 00:34:52.040
I used to watch and study this patriarchal personage with, I think,

00:34:52.420 --> 00:34:57.460
livelier curiosity than any other form of humanity there presented to my notice.

00:34:57.460 --> 00:35:04.560
He was in truth a rare phenomenon, so perfect in one point of view, so shallow, so delusive,

00:35:04.720 --> 00:35:12.500
so impalpable, such an absolute non-entity in every other. My conclusion was that he had no soul,

00:35:12.660 --> 00:35:19.520
no heart, no mind, nothing, as I have already said, but instincts, and yet withal so cunningly had

00:35:19.520 --> 00:35:24.700
the few materials of his character been put together that there was no painful perception

00:35:24.700 --> 00:35:29.940
of deficiency, but on my part an entire contentment with what I found in him.

00:35:30.560 --> 00:35:35.940
It might be difficult, and it was so, to conceive how he should exist hereafter,

00:35:36.220 --> 00:35:40.660
so earthy and sensuous did he seem, but surely his existence here,

00:35:41.160 --> 00:35:46.420
admitting that it was to terminate with his last breath, had been not unkindly given,

00:35:46.780 --> 00:35:51.740
with no higher moral responsibilities than the beasts of the field, but with a larger

00:35:51.740 --> 00:35:56.980
scope of enjoyment than theirs, and with all their blessed immunity from the dreariness

00:35:56.980 --> 00:36:04.180
and duskiness of age. One point in which he had vastly the advantage over his four-footed brethren

00:36:04.180 --> 00:36:09.500
was his ability to recollect the good dinners which it had made no small portion of the

00:36:09.500 --> 00:36:15.900
happiness of his life to eat. His gourmandism was a highly agreeable trait, and to hear him

00:36:15.900 --> 00:36:23.260
meat was as appetizing as a pickle or an oyster, as he possessed no higher attribute,

00:36:23.700 --> 00:36:29.520
and neither sacrificed nor vitiated any spiritual endowment. By devoting all his energies and

00:36:29.520 --> 00:36:36.020
ingenuities to subserve the delight and profit of his more, it always pleased and satisfied me to

00:36:36.020 --> 00:36:42.560
hear him expatiate on fish, poultry, and butcher's meat, and the most eligible methods of preparing

00:36:42.560 --> 00:36:48.660
them for the table. His reminiscences of good cheer, however ancient the date of the actual

00:36:48.660 --> 00:36:54.360
banquet, seemed to bring the savour of pig or turkey under one's very nostrils. There

00:36:54.360 --> 00:36:59.380
were flavours on his palate that had lingered there not less than sixty or seventy years,

00:36:59.580 --> 00:37:04.860
and were still apparently as fresh as that of the mutton chop which he had just devoured for

00:37:04.860 --> 00:37:11.800
his breakfast. I have heard him smack his lips over dinners, every guest at which, except himself,

00:37:11.800 --> 00:37:18.760
had long been food for worms. It was marvellous to observe how the ghosts of bygone meals were

00:37:18.760 --> 00:37:25.340
continually rising up before him, not in anger or retribution, but as if grateful for his former

00:37:25.340 --> 00:37:32.320
appreciation, and seeking to reduplicate an endless series of enjoyment at once shadowy and

00:37:32.320 --> 00:37:39.740
sensual. A tenderloin of beef, a hind-quarter of veal, a spare rib of pork, a particular chicken,

00:37:39.740 --> 00:37:46.240
or a remarkably praiseworthy turkey, which had perhaps adorned his board in the days of the Elder

00:37:46.240 --> 00:37:52.040
Adams, would be remembered, while all the subsequent experience of our race, and all the

00:37:52.040 --> 00:37:58.040
events that brightened or darkened his individual career, had gone over him with as little permanent

00:37:58.040 --> 00:38:04.580
effect as the passing breeze. The chief tragic event of the old man's life, so far as I could

00:38:04.580 --> 00:38:10.820
judge, was his mishap with a certain goose which lived and died some twenty or forty years ago,

00:38:11.280 --> 00:38:17.760
a goose of most promising figure, but which at table proved so inveterately tough that the

00:38:17.760 --> 00:38:23.360
carving knife would make no impression on its carcass, and it could only be divided with an axe

00:38:23.360 --> 00:38:30.520
and handsaw. But it is time to quit this sketch, on which, however, I should be glad to dwell at

00:38:31.320 --> 00:38:37.720
length, because of all men whom I have ever known, this individual was fittest to be a custom house

00:38:37.720 --> 00:38:44.820
officer. Most persons, owing to causes which I may not have space to hint at, suffer moral detriment

00:38:44.820 --> 00:38:51.700
from this peculiar mode of life. The old inspector was incapable of it, and were he to continue in

00:38:51.700 --> 00:38:58.100
office to the end of time, would be just as good as he was then, and sit down to dinner with just

00:38:58.100 --> 00:39:05.100
good an appetite. There is one likeness without which my gallery of custom house portraits would

00:39:05.100 --> 00:39:11.640
be strangely incomplete, but which my comparatively few opportunities for observation enable me to

00:39:11.640 --> 00:39:18.340
sketch only in the merest outline. It is that of the collector, our gallant old general, who after

00:39:18.340 --> 00:39:24.460
his brilliant military service, subsequently to which he had ruled over a wild western territory,

00:39:24.460 --> 00:39:30.620
had come hither, twenty years before, to spend the decline of his varied and honourable life.

00:39:31.360 --> 00:39:36.680
The brave old soldier had already numbered, nearly all quite, his three score years and ten,

00:39:37.080 --> 00:39:42.360
and was pursuing the remainder of his earthly march, burdened with infirmities which even

00:39:42.360 --> 00:39:48.380
the martial music of his own spirit-stirring recollections could do little towards lightning.

00:39:49.040 --> 00:39:55.100
The stat was palsied now that had been foremost in the charge. It was only with the assistance

00:39:55.100 --> 00:40:01.160
of a servant, and by leaning his hand heavily on the iron balustrade, that he could slowly and

00:40:01.160 --> 00:40:07.740
painfully ascend the custom house steps, and with a torsion progress across the floor attain his

00:40:07.740 --> 00:40:14.560
customary chair beside the fireplace. There he used to sit, gazing with a somewhat dim serenity

00:40:14.560 --> 00:40:20.620
of aspect, at the figures that came and went, amid the rustle of papers, the administering of

00:40:20.620 --> 00:40:26.540
oaths, the discussion of business, and the casual talk of the office, all which sounds and

00:40:26.540 --> 00:40:32.860
circumstances seemed but indistinctly to impress his senses, and hardly to make their way into his

00:40:32.860 --> 00:40:40.280
inner sphere of contemplation. His countenance in this repose was mild and kindly. If his notice

00:40:40.280 --> 00:40:45.000
were sought, an expression of courtesy and interest gleamed out upon his features,

00:40:45.420 --> 00:40:50.340
proving that there was light within him, and that it was only the outward medium of the

00:40:50.340 --> 00:40:56.180
intellectual lamp that obstructed the rays in their passage. The closer you penetrated to the

00:40:56.180 --> 00:41:01.840
substance of his mind, the sounder it appeared. When no longer called upon to speak or listen,

00:41:02.200 --> 00:41:08.120
either of which operations cost him an evident effort, his face would briefly subside into its

00:41:08.120 --> 00:41:14.060
former, not uncheerful, quietude. It was not painful to behold this look, for though dim,

00:41:14.460 --> 00:41:20.640
it had not the imbecility of decaying age. The framework of his nature, originally strong and

00:41:20.640 --> 00:41:27.160
massive, was not yet crumbled into ruin. To observe and define his character, however,

00:41:27.300 --> 00:41:33.980
under such disadvantages, was as difficult a task as to trace out and build up anew in imagination

00:41:33.980 --> 00:41:40.820
an old fortress like Teconderoga, from a view of its grey and broken ruins. Here and there,

00:41:40.940 --> 00:41:46.740
perchance, the walls may remain almost complete, but elsewhere may be only a shapeless mound,

00:41:46.920 --> 00:41:53.140
cumbrous with its very strength, and overgrown through long years of peace and neglect with grass

00:41:53.140 --> 00:41:59.900
and alien weeds. Nevertheless, looking at the old warrior with affection, for slight as was the

00:41:59.900 --> 00:42:06.380
between us, my feeling towards him, like that of all bipeds and quadrupeds who knew him,

00:42:06.560 --> 00:42:12.100
might not improperly be termed so. I could discern the main points of his portrait.

00:42:12.380 --> 00:42:18.340
It was marked with the noble and heroic qualities which showed it to be not by a mere accident,

00:42:18.520 --> 00:42:25.560
but of good right, that he had won a distinguished name. His spirit could never, I conceive, have

00:42:25.560 --> 00:42:31.560
been characterised by an uneasy activity. It must, at any period of his life, have required

00:42:31.560 --> 00:42:38.020
an impulse to set him in motion, but once stirred up with obstacles to overcome and an adequate

00:42:38.020 --> 00:42:44.420
object to be attained, it was not in the man to give out or fail. The heat that had formerly

00:42:44.420 --> 00:42:49.900
pervaded his nature, and which was not yet extinct, was never of the kind that flashes

00:42:49.900 --> 00:42:56.540
and flickers in a blaze, but rather a deep red glow, as of iron in a furnace. Weight,

00:42:56.840 --> 00:43:03.540
solidity, firmness, this was the expression of his repose, even in such decay as had crept

00:43:03.540 --> 00:43:10.020
untimely over him at the period of which I speak. But I could imagine even then, that under some

00:43:10.020 --> 00:43:15.520
excitement which should go deeply into his consciousness, roused by a trumpet-peel loud

00:43:15.520 --> 00:43:21.920
to awaken all of his energies that were not dead, but only slumbering. He was yet capable

00:43:21.920 --> 00:43:28.040
of flinging off his infirmities like a sick man's gown, dropping the staff of age to seize a

00:43:28.040 --> 00:43:35.020
battle-sword, and starting up once more a warrior. And, in so intense a moment, his demeanour would

00:43:35.020 --> 00:43:40.600
have still been calm. Such an exhibition, however, was but to be pictured in fancy,

00:43:40.600 --> 00:43:48.000
not to be anticipated nor desired. What I saw in him, as evidently as the indestructible ramparts

00:43:48.000 --> 00:43:54.560
of old Ticonderoga, already cited as the most appropriate simile, were the features of stubborn

00:43:54.560 --> 00:44:00.220
and ponderous endurance, which might well have amounted to obstancy in his earlier days,

00:44:00.680 --> 00:44:06.000
of integrity that, like most of his other endowments, lay in a somewhat heavy mass,

00:44:06.000 --> 00:44:12.700
and was just as unmalleable and unmanageable as a tonne of iron ore, and of benevolence,

00:44:12.940 --> 00:44:19.380
which, fiercely as he led the bayonets on at Chippewa or Fort Erie, I take to be of quite

00:44:19.380 --> 00:44:25.580
as genuine a stamp as what actuates any or all the polemical philanthropists of the age.

00:44:26.180 --> 00:44:31.880
He had slain men with his own hand, for aught I know. Certainly they had fallen like blades of

00:44:31.880 --> 00:44:37.780
grass at the sweep of the scythe, before the charge to which his spirit imparted its triumphant

00:44:37.780 --> 00:44:44.260
energy. But, be that as it might, there was never in his heart so much cruelty as would have brushed

00:44:44.260 --> 00:44:51.060
the down off a butterfly's wing. I have not known the man to whose innate kindness I would more

00:44:51.060 --> 00:44:58.120
confidently make an appeal. Many characteristics, and those too which contribute not the least

00:44:58.120 --> 00:45:04.900
to impart resemblance in a sketch, must have vanished or been obscured before I met the general.

00:45:05.840 --> 00:45:12.220
All merely graceful attributes are usually the most evanescent, nor does nature adorn the human

00:45:12.220 --> 00:45:18.180
ruin with blossoms of new beauty that have their roots and proper nutriment only in the chinks and

00:45:18.180 --> 00:45:24.080
crevices of decay as she sows wall-flowers over the ruined fortress of Tikonderoga.

00:45:24.640 --> 00:45:31.380
Still, even in respect of grace and beauty, there were points well worth noting. A ray of

00:45:31.380 --> 00:45:36.580
humour now and then would make its way through the veil of dim obstruction and

00:45:36.580 --> 00:45:43.280
glimmer pleasantly upon our faces. A trait of native elegance seldom seen in the masculine

00:45:43.280 --> 00:45:49.080
character after childhood or early youth was shown in the general's fondness for the sight

00:45:49.080 --> 00:45:56.260
and fragrance of flowers. An old soldier might be supposed to prize only the bloody laurel on his

00:45:56.260 --> 00:46:02.400
brow, but here was one who seemed to have a young girl's appreciation of the floral tribe.

00:46:03.040 --> 00:46:08.820
There, beside the fireplace, the brave old general used to sit, while the surveyor, though seldom

00:46:08.820 --> 00:46:14.800
when it could be avoided, taking upon himself the difficult task of engaging him in conversation,

00:46:14.800 --> 00:46:21.120
was fond of standing at a distance and watching his quiet and almost slumberous countenance.

00:46:21.720 --> 00:46:27.520
He seemed away from us, although we saw him but a few yards off, remote though we passed close

00:46:27.520 --> 00:46:33.180
beside his chair, unattainable though we might have stretched forth our hands and touched his own.

00:46:33.800 --> 00:46:39.220
It might be that he lived a more real life within his thoughts than amid the inappropriate

00:46:39.220 --> 00:46:45.160
environment of the collector's office. The evolutions of the parade, the tumult of the

00:46:45.160 --> 00:46:51.400
battle, the flourish of old heroic music heard thirty years before, such scenes and sounds

00:46:51.400 --> 00:46:57.900
perhaps were all alive before his intellectual sense. Meanwhile the merchants and ship-masters,

00:46:58.400 --> 00:47:05.140
the spruce clerks and uncouth sailors entered and departed. The bustle of this commercial and

00:47:05.140 --> 00:47:10.960
custom-house life kept up its little murmur round about him, and neither with the men nor

00:47:10.960 --> 00:47:17.700
their affairs did the general appear to sustain the most distant relation. He was as much out of

00:47:17.700 --> 00:47:23.800
place as an old sword, now rusty, but which had flashed once in the battle's front and showed

00:47:23.800 --> 00:47:29.380
still a bright gleam along its blade, would have been among the ink-stands, paper-folders and

00:47:29.380 --> 00:47:36.920
mahogany rulers on the deputy-collector's desk. There was one thing that much aided me in renewing

00:47:36.920 --> 00:47:43.740
and recreating the stalwart soldier of the Niagara frontier, the man of true and simple energy.

00:47:44.220 --> 00:47:50.840
It was the recollection of those memorable words of his, I'll try, sir, spoken on the very verge

00:47:50.840 --> 00:47:57.240
of a desperate and heroic enterprise, and breathing the soul and spirit of New England hardyhood,

00:47:57.240 --> 00:48:04.440
comprehending all perils and encountering all. If in our country valour were rewarded by heraldic

00:48:04.440 --> 00:48:10.340
honour, this phrase, which it seems so easy to speak, but which only he with such a task of

00:48:10.340 --> 00:48:16.940
danger and glory before him has ever spoken, would be the best and fittest of all mottos for

00:48:16.940 --> 00:48:23.860
the general's shield of arms. It contributes greatly towards a man's moral and intellectual health

00:48:23.860 --> 00:48:29.960
to be brought into habits of companionship with individuals unlike himself, who care little for

00:48:29.960 --> 00:48:35.300
his pursuits and whose sphere and abilities he must go out of himself to appreciate.

00:48:36.480 --> 00:48:42.140
The accidents of my life have often afforded me this advantage, but never with more fullness and

00:48:42.140 --> 00:48:52.160
variety than during my continuance in office. There was one man especially the observation of

00:48:52.160 --> 00:48:58.480
his gifts were emphatically those of a man of business, prompt, acute, clear-minded,

00:48:58.960 --> 00:49:04.200
with an eye that saw through all perplexities and a faculty of arrangement that made them

00:49:04.200 --> 00:49:11.100
vanish as by the waving of an enchanter's wand. Bred up from boyhood in the custom house,

00:49:11.300 --> 00:49:17.120
it was his proper field of activity, and the many intricacies of business so harassing to the

00:49:17.120 --> 00:49:23.300
loper presented themselves before him with the regularity of a perfectly comprehended system.

00:49:24.300 --> 00:49:31.220
In my contemplation he stood as the ideal of his class. He was indeed the custom house in himself,

00:49:31.620 --> 00:49:36.840
or at all events the mainspring that kept its variously revolving wheels in motion.

00:49:37.660 --> 00:49:43.300
For in an institution like this, where its officers are appointed to subserve their own

00:49:43.300 --> 00:49:49.040
and convenience, and seldom with a leading reference to their fitness for the duty to be

00:49:49.040 --> 00:49:55.500
performed, they must perforce seek elsewhere the dexterity which is not in them. Thus,

00:49:55.680 --> 00:50:01.900
by an inevitable necessity, as a magnet attracts steel filings, so did our man of business draw

00:50:01.900 --> 00:50:08.260
to himself the difficulties which everybody met with, with an easy condescension and a kind

00:50:08.260 --> 00:50:13.760
of forbearance towards our stupidity, which, to his order of mind, must have seemed little short

00:50:13.760 --> 00:50:19.720
of crime, would he forthwith, by the merest touch of his finger, make the incomprehensible

00:50:19.720 --> 00:50:26.100
as clear as daylight. The merchants valued him not less than we, his esoteric friends.

00:50:26.800 --> 00:50:32.340
His integrity was perfect, it was a law of nature with him rather than a choice or a principle,

00:50:32.340 --> 00:50:38.440
nor can it be otherwise than the main condition of an intellect so remarkably clear and accurate

00:50:38.440 --> 00:50:44.860
as his, to be honest and regular in the administration of affairs. A stain on his

00:50:44.860 --> 00:50:50.300
conscience as to anything that came within the range of his vocation would trouble such a man

00:50:50.300 --> 00:50:56.380
very much in the same way, though to a far greater degree, than an error in the balance of an account

00:50:56.380 --> 00:51:03.040
or an ink blot on the fair page of a book of record. Here, in a word, and it is a rare

00:51:03.040 --> 00:51:09.440
instance in my life, I had met with a person thoroughly adapted to the situation which he held.

00:51:22.292 --> 00:51:28.612
THE CUSTOM HOUSE PART II. INTRODUCTORY TO THE SCARLET LETTER.

00:51:42.792 --> 00:51:48.752
THE CUSTOM HOUSE PART II. INTRODUCTORY TO THE SCARLET LETTER.

00:51:53.352 --> 00:51:58.912
Such were some of the people with whom I now found myself connected. I took it in good

00:51:58.912 --> 00:52:11.352
part at the hands of Providence that I was thrown into a position so little akin to my

00:52:11.952 --> 00:52:17.952
of toil and impracticable schemes with the dreamy brethren of Brook Farm, after living

00:52:17.952 --> 00:52:23.432
for three years within the subtile influence of an intellect like Emerson's, after those

00:52:23.432 --> 00:52:31.132
wild free days on the Assebeth indulging fantastic speculations beside our fires of fallen boughs,

00:52:31.232 --> 00:52:37.032
with Ellery Channing, after talking with Thorough about pine trees and Indian relics in his

00:52:38.132 --> 00:52:43.732
After growing fastidious by sympathy with the classic refinement of Hillard's culture,

00:52:44.372 --> 00:52:50.312
after becoming imbued with poetic sentiment at Longfellow's Hearthstone, it was time at

00:52:50.312 --> 00:52:55.852
length that I should exercise other faculties of my nature and nourish myself with food

00:52:55.852 --> 00:53:07.012
for which I had hitherto had little appetite. Even the old inspector was desirable as a

00:53:07.012 --> 00:53:12.952
I looked upon it as an evidence in some measure of a system naturally well balanced and lacking

00:53:12.952 --> 00:53:19.932
no essential part of a thorough organisation, that with such associates to remember I could

00:53:19.932 --> 00:53:25.692
mingle at once with men of altogether different qualities and never murmur at the change.

00:53:26.772 --> 00:53:32.812
Literature, its exertions and objects, were now of little moment in my regard. I cared

00:53:32.812 --> 00:53:39.252
not at this period for books, they were apart from me. Nature, except it were human nature,

00:53:39.632 --> 00:53:45.452
the nature that is developed in earth and sky, was in one sense hidden from me, and

00:53:45.452 --> 00:53:51.552
all the imaginative delight wherewith it had been spiritualised passed away out of my mind.

00:53:52.592 --> 00:53:59.712
A gift, a faculty, if it had not departed, was suspended and inanimate within me. There

00:53:59.712 --> 00:54:04.472
would have been something sad and unutterably dreary in all this had I not been conscious

00:54:04.472 --> 00:54:10.572
that it lay at my own option to recall whatever was valuable in the past. It might be true

00:54:10.572 --> 00:54:16.252
indeed that this was a life which could not, with impunity, be lived too long, else it

00:54:16.252 --> 00:54:21.892
might make me permanently other than I had been, without transforming me into any shape

00:54:21.892 --> 00:54:27.912
which it would be worth my while to take. But I never considered it as other than a

00:54:27.912 --> 00:54:34.532
transitory life. There was always a prophetic instinct, a low whisper in my ear, that within

00:54:34.532 --> 00:54:40.232
no long period and whenever a new change of custom should be essential to my good, a change

00:54:40.232 --> 00:54:40.972
would come.

00:54:42.172 --> 00:54:47.492
Meanwhile, there I was, a surveyor of the revenue, and so far as I have been able to

00:54:47.492 --> 00:54:54.172
understand as good a surveyor as need be. A man of thought, fancy and sensibility, had

00:54:54.172 --> 00:54:59.332
only ten times the surveyor's proportion of those qualities, may at any time be a man

00:54:59.332 --> 00:55:05.512
of affairs, if he will only choose to give himself the trouble. My fellow officers and

00:55:05.512 --> 00:55:10.152
the merchants and sea captains with whom my official duties brought me into any manner

00:55:10.152 --> 00:55:15.312
of connection, viewed me in no other light and probably knew me in no other character.

00:55:15.912 --> 00:55:20.912
None of them, I presume, had ever read a page of my indicting, or would have cared a fig

00:55:20.912 --> 00:55:26.352
them more for me, if they had read them all. Nor would it have mended the matter in the

00:55:26.352 --> 00:55:32.152
least had those same unprofitable pages been written with a pen like that of Burns or of

00:55:32.152 --> 00:55:39.672
Chaucer, each of whom was a custom house officer in his day as well as I. It is a good lesson,

00:55:39.812 --> 00:55:45.632
though it may often be a hard one, for a man who has dreamt of literary fame and of making

00:55:45.632 --> 00:55:52.612
rank among the world's dignitaries by such means, to step aside out of the narrow circle in which

00:55:52.612 --> 00:55:58.552
his claims are recognised, and to find how utterly devoid of significance, beyond that circle,

00:55:58.952 --> 00:56:06.012
is all that he achieves and all he aims at. I know not that I especially needed the lesson,

00:56:06.112 --> 00:56:13.032
either in the way of warning or rebuke, but at any rate I learnt it thoroughly. Nor, it gives me

00:56:13.032 --> 00:56:19.012
pleasure to reflect, did the truth, as it came home to my perception, ever cost me a pang,

00:56:19.132 --> 00:56:25.972
or require to be thrown off in a sigh. In the way of literary talk, it is true the naval officer,

00:56:26.332 --> 00:56:31.172
an excellent fellow who came into office with me and went out only a little later,

00:56:31.732 --> 00:56:36.532
would often engage me in a discussion about one or the other of his favourite topics,

00:56:36.532 --> 00:56:42.972
Napoleon or Shakespeare. The collector's junior clerk, too, a young gentleman who,

00:56:42.972 --> 00:56:47.392
it was whispered, occasionally covered a sheet of Uncle Sam's letter-paper with what,

00:56:47.732 --> 00:56:54.192
at the distance of a few yards, looked very much like poetry, used now and then to speak to me of

00:56:54.192 --> 00:57:00.972
books, as matters with which I might possibly be conversant. This was my all-of-lettered intercourse,

00:57:00.972 --> 00:57:08.392
and it was quite sufficient for my necessities. No longer seeking nor caring that my name should

00:57:08.392 --> 00:57:14.572
be blazoned abroad on title pages, I smiled to think that it had now another kind of vogue.

00:57:15.212 --> 00:57:21.232
The custom-house marker imprinted it, with a stencil and black paint, on pepper-bags and

00:57:21.232 --> 00:57:28.872
baskets of annatto and cigar-boxes and bales of all kinds of dutyable merchandise, in testimony

00:57:28.872 --> 00:57:34.172
that these commodities had paid the impost and gone regularly through the office.

00:57:35.452 --> 00:57:41.492
Born on such queer vehicle of fame, a knowledge of my existence, so far as a name conveys it,

00:57:41.852 --> 00:57:46.852
was carried where it had never been before, and I hope will never go again.

00:57:48.152 --> 00:57:54.652
But the past was not dead. Once in a great while the thoughts, that had seemed so vital and so

00:57:54.652 --> 00:58:01.652
effective, yet had been put to rest so quietly, revived again. One of the most remarkable

00:58:01.652 --> 00:58:07.452
occasions when the habit of bygone days awoke in me was that which brings it within the law

00:58:07.452 --> 00:58:11.972
of literary propriety to offer the public the sketch which I am now writing.

00:58:12.632 --> 00:58:18.092
In the second story of the custom-house there is a large room in which the brickwork and

00:58:18.092 --> 00:58:23.372
naked rafters have never been covered with panelling and plaster. The edifice,

00:58:23.372 --> 00:58:28.332
originally projected on a scale adapted to the old commercial enterprise of the port,

00:58:28.852 --> 00:58:33.412
and with an idea of subsequent prosperity destined never to be realised,

00:58:33.932 --> 00:58:37.712
contains far more space than its occupants know what to do with.

00:58:38.752 --> 00:58:44.612
This airy hall, therefore, over the collector's apartments, remains unfinished to this day,

00:58:45.072 --> 00:58:52.032
and in spite of the aged cobwebs that festoon its dusky beams, appears still to await the labour of

00:58:52.032 --> 00:58:59.452
carpenter and mason. At one end of the room, in a recess, were a number of barrels, piled

00:58:59.452 --> 00:59:06.032
one upon another, containing bundles of official documents. Large quantities of similar rubbish

00:59:06.032 --> 00:59:12.372
lay lumbering the floor. It was sorrowful to think how many days and weeks and months and years of

00:59:12.372 --> 00:59:18.512
toil had been wasted on these musty papers, which were now only an encumbrance on earth,

00:59:18.512 --> 00:59:24.492
and were hidden away in this forgotten corner, never more to be glanced at by human eyes.

00:59:25.472 --> 00:59:31.272
But then what reams of other manuscripts, filled not with the dullness of official formalities,

00:59:31.672 --> 00:59:36.372
but with the thought of inventive brains and the rich effusion of deep hearts,

00:59:36.772 --> 00:59:42.172
had gone equally to oblivion, and that, moreover, without serving a purpose in their day,

00:59:42.172 --> 00:59:48.512
as these heaped-up papers had, and, saddest of all, without purchasing for their writers

00:59:48.512 --> 00:59:54.092
the comfortable livelihood which the clerks of the Custom House had gained by these worthless

00:59:54.092 --> 01:00:01.652
scratchings of the pen. Yet not altogether worthless, perhaps, as materials of local history.

01:00:02.252 --> 01:00:06.732
Here, no doubt, statistics of the former commerce of Salem might be discovered,

01:00:06.732 --> 01:00:14.092
and memorials of her princely merchants, old King Derby, old Billy Grey, old Simon Forrester,

01:00:14.432 --> 01:00:20.232
and many another magnate in his day, whose powdered head, however, was scarcely in the tomb before

01:00:20.232 --> 01:00:25.952
his mountain pile of wealth began to dwindle. The founders of the greater part of the families

01:00:25.952 --> 01:00:31.952
which now composed the aristocracy of Salem might here be traced from the petty and obscure

01:00:31.952 --> 01:00:37.272
beginning of their traffic, at periods generally much posterior to the Revolution,

01:00:38.132 --> 01:00:44.432
upward to what their children look upon as long-established rank. Prior to the Revolution

01:00:44.432 --> 01:00:49.412
there is a dearth of records, the earlier documents and archives of the Custom House

01:00:49.412 --> 01:00:54.852
having, probably, been carried off to Halifax, when all the King's officials accompanied the

01:00:54.852 --> 01:01:00.832
British army in its flight from Boston. It has often been a matter of regret with me,

01:01:00.832 --> 01:01:05.872
for going back, perhaps, to the days of the Protectorate, those papers must have contained

01:01:05.872 --> 01:01:12.352
many references to forgotten or remembered men, and to antique customs, which would have affected

01:01:12.352 --> 01:01:17.772
me with the same pleasure as when I used to pick up Indian arrowheads in the field near the old

01:01:17.772 --> 01:01:24.832
manse. But one idle and rainy day, it was my fortune to make a discovery of some little

01:01:24.832 --> 01:01:31.512
interest, poking and burrowing into the heaped-up rubbish in the corner, unfolding one and another

01:01:31.512 --> 01:01:36.972
document, and reading the names of vessels that had long ago founded at sea or rotted at the

01:01:36.972 --> 01:01:43.912
wharves, and those of merchants never heard of now on change, nor very readily decipherable on

01:01:43.912 --> 01:01:50.592
their mossy tombstones. Glancing at such matters with the saddened, weary, half-reluctant interests

01:01:50.592 --> 01:01:57.152
which we bestow on the corpse of dead activity, and exerting my fancy, sluggish with little use,

01:01:57.552 --> 01:02:03.932
to raise up from these dry bones an image of the old town's brighter aspect when India was a new

01:02:03.932 --> 01:02:10.692
region, and only Salem knew the way thither, I chanced to lay my hand on a small package carefully

01:02:10.692 --> 01:02:17.632
done up in a piece of ancient yellow parchment. This envelope had the air of an official record

01:02:17.632 --> 01:02:24.492
of some period long past when clerks engrossed their stiff and formal chirography on more

01:02:24.492 --> 01:02:30.732
substantial materials than at present. There was something about it that quickened an instinctive

01:02:30.732 --> 01:02:36.952
curiosity, and made me undo the faded red tape that tied up the package, with the sense that

01:02:36.952 --> 01:02:42.792
a treasure would here be brought to light. Unbending the rigid folds of the parchment cover,

01:02:42.792 --> 01:02:48.932
I found it to be a commission, under the hand and seal of Governor Shirley, in favour of one

01:02:48.932 --> 01:02:55.372
Jonathan Pugh, the Surveyor of His Majesty's Customs for the Port of Salem, in the province of

01:02:55.372 --> 01:03:01.952
Massachusetts Bay. I remembered to have read, probably in Felt's Annals, a notice of the

01:03:01.952 --> 01:03:08.952
decease of Mr. Surveyor Pugh about four score years ago, and likewise in a newspaper of recent

01:03:08.952 --> 01:03:15.392
account of the digging up of his remains in the little graveyard of St. Peter's Church during

01:03:15.392 --> 01:03:22.072
the renewal of that edifice. Nothing, if I rightly call to mind, was left of my respected predecessor,

01:03:22.592 --> 01:03:28.872
save an imperfect skeleton, and some fragments of apparel, and a wig of majestic frizzle,

01:03:28.992 --> 01:03:33.912
which, unlike the head that it once adorned, was in very satisfactory preservation.

01:03:34.512 --> 01:03:39.212
But on examining the papers, which the parchment commission served to envelop,

01:03:39.432 --> 01:03:44.992
I found more traces of Mr. Pugh's mental part, and the internal operations of his head,

01:03:45.392 --> 01:03:49.192
than the frizzled wig had contained of the venerable skull itself.

01:03:49.872 --> 01:03:55.192
They were documents, in short, not official, but of a private nature, or at least written

01:03:55.192 --> 01:04:01.072
in his private capacity, and apparently with his own hand. I could account for their being

01:04:01.072 --> 01:04:06.152
included in the heap of custom-house lumber, only by the fact that Mr. Pugh's death had

01:04:06.152 --> 01:04:11.452
happened suddenly, and that these papers, which he probably kept in his official desk,

01:04:11.472 --> 01:04:16.852
had never come to the knowledge of his heirs, or were supposed to relate to the business of

01:04:16.852 --> 01:04:22.772
the revenue. On the transfer of the archives to Halifax, this package, proving to be of no

01:04:22.772 --> 01:04:27.732
public concern, was left behind, and had remained ever since unopened.

01:04:28.692 --> 01:04:34.032
The ancient surveyor, being little molested, I suppose, at that early day, with business

01:04:34.032 --> 01:04:39.952
pertaining to his office, seems to have devoted some of his many leisure hours to researches

01:04:39.952 --> 01:04:46.792
as a local antiquarian, and other inquisitions of a similar nature. These supplied material for

01:04:46.792 --> 01:04:56.492
petty activity to a mind that would otherwise have been eaten up with rust. A portion of his

01:04:56.492 --> 01:05:03.352
entitled main street included in the present volume. The remainder may perhaps be applied

01:05:03.352 --> 01:05:10.112
to purposes equally valuable hereafter, or not impossibly may be worked up, so far as they go,

01:05:10.352 --> 01:05:16.132
into a regular history of Salem, should my veneration for the natal soil ever impel me

01:05:16.132 --> 01:05:22.572
to so pious a task. Meanwhile they shall be at the command of any gentleman inclined and competent

01:05:22.572 --> 01:05:25.972
to take the unprofitable labour off my hands.

01:05:27.412 --> 01:05:32.772
As a final disposition I contemplate depositing them with the Essex Historical Society.

01:05:33.772 --> 01:05:37.192
But the object that most drew my attention in the mysterious package

01:05:37.192 --> 01:05:43.612
was a certain affair of fine red cloth, much worn and faded. There were traces about it

01:05:43.612 --> 01:05:49.672
of gold embroidery, which, however, was greatly frayed and defaced, so that none or very little

01:05:49.672 --> 01:05:55.252
of the glitter was left. It had been wrought, as was easy to perceive, with wonderful skill

01:05:55.252 --> 01:06:00.692
of needlework, and the stitch, as I am assured by ladies conversant with such mysteries,

01:06:01.172 --> 01:06:07.152
gives evidence of a now forgotten art, not to be recovered even by the process of picking out the

01:06:07.152 --> 01:06:14.632
threads. This rag of scarlet cloth, for time and wear, and a sacrilegious moth, had reduced it to

01:06:14.632 --> 01:06:21.292
little other than a rag, on careful examination assumed the shape of a letter. It was the capital

01:06:21.292 --> 01:06:28.212
letter A. By an accurate measurement, each limb proved to be precisely three inches and a quarter

01:06:28.212 --> 01:06:34.092
in length. It had been intended, there could be no doubt, as an ornamental article of dress,

01:06:34.512 --> 01:06:41.772
but how it was to be worn, or what rank, honour and dignity in by-pass times were signified by it,

01:06:41.772 --> 01:06:47.012
was a riddle which, so evanescent are the fashions of the world in these particulars,

01:06:47.292 --> 01:06:54.612
I saw little hope of solving. And yet it strangely interested me. My eyes fastened themselves upon

01:06:54.612 --> 01:07:01.052
the old scarlet letter, and would not be turned aside. Certainly there was some deep meaning in

01:07:01.052 --> 01:07:06.712
it, most worthy of interpretation, and which, as it were, streamed forth from the mystic symbol,

01:07:06.712 --> 01:07:13.052
subtly communicating itself to my sensibilities, but evading the analysis of my mind.

01:07:14.572 --> 01:07:20.852
While thus perplexed and cogitating among other hypotheses whether the letter might not have been

01:07:20.852 --> 01:07:26.812
one of those decorations which the white men used to contrive in order to take the eyes of Indians,

01:07:27.352 --> 01:07:33.672
I happened to place it on my breast. It seemed to me, the reader may smile, but must not doubt my

01:07:34.402 --> 01:07:41.232
It seemed to me, then, that I experienced a sensation not altogether physical, yet almost so,

01:07:41.572 --> 01:07:46.852
as of burning heat, and as if the letter were not of red cloth, but red-hot iron.

01:07:47.592 --> 01:07:51.272
I shuddered, and involuntarily let it fall upon the floor.

01:07:52.572 --> 01:07:58.122
In the absorbing contemplation of the scarlet letter, I had hitherto neglected to examine a

01:07:58.122 --> 01:08:04.522
small roll of dingy paper around which it had been twisted. This I now opened, and had the

01:08:04.522 --> 01:08:11.382
satisfaction to find, recorded by the old surveyor's pen, a reasonably complete explanation of the whole

01:08:11.382 --> 01:08:17.242
affair. There were several full-scap sheets containing many particulars respecting the life

01:08:17.242 --> 01:08:22.882
and conversation of one Hester Prynne, who appeared to have been rather a noteworthy

01:08:23.322 --> 01:08:29.082
in the view of our ancestors. She had flourished during a period between the early days of

01:08:29.082 --> 01:08:35.602
Massachusetts and the close of the seventeenth century. Aged persons, alive in the time of Mr

01:08:35.602 --> 01:08:41.762
Surveyor Pugh, and from whose oral testimony he had made up his narrative, remembered her in their

01:08:41.762 --> 01:08:49.162
youth as a very old but not decrepit woman, of a stately and solemn aspect. It had been her habit,

01:08:49.162 --> 01:08:54.622
from an almost immemorial date, to go about the country as a kind of voluntary nurse,

01:08:55.122 --> 01:09:01.142
and doing whatever miscellaneous good she might, taking upon herself likewise to give advice in

01:09:01.142 --> 01:09:07.562
all matters, especially those of the heart. By which means, as a person of such propensities

01:09:07.562 --> 01:09:14.462
inevitably must, she gained from many people the reverence due to an angel, but, I should imagine,

01:09:14.462 --> 01:09:21.202
was looked upon by others as an intruder and a nuisance. Prying farther into the manuscript,

01:09:21.682 --> 01:09:27.062
I found the record of other doings and sufferings of this singular woman, for the most of which the

01:09:27.062 --> 01:09:32.742
reader is referred to the story entitled The Scarlet Letter, and it should be borne carefully

01:09:32.742 --> 01:09:39.122
in mind that the main facts of that story are authorised and authenticated by the document of

01:09:39.862 --> 01:09:46.802
Pugh. The original papers, together with the scarlet letter itself, a most curious relic,

01:09:47.062 --> 01:09:52.902
are still in my possession, and shall be freely exhibited to whomsoever, induced by the great

01:09:52.902 --> 01:09:59.642
interest of the narrative, may desire a sight of them. I must not be understood as affirming,

01:09:59.922 --> 01:10:05.222
that in the dressing up of the tale, and imagining the motives and modes of passion that influence

01:10:05.222 --> 01:10:10.782
the characters who figure in it, I have invariably confined myself within the limits of the old

01:10:10.782 --> 01:10:17.302
surveyor's half a dozen sheets of full scap. On the contrary, I have allowed myself, as to such

01:10:17.302 --> 01:10:23.382
points, nearly or altogether as much licence as if the facts had been entirely of my own invention.

01:10:24.122 --> 01:10:31.242
What I contend for is the authenticity of the outline. This incident recalled my mind in some

01:10:31.242 --> 01:10:37.782
degree to its old track. There seemed to be here the groundwork of a tale. It impressed me as if the

01:10:37.782 --> 01:10:44.162
ancient surveyor, in his garb of a hundred years gone by, and wearing his immortal wig, which was

01:10:44.162 --> 01:10:50.122
buried with him, but did not perish in the grave, had met me in the deserted chamber of the custom

01:10:50.122 --> 01:10:56.662
house. In his port was the dignity of one who had borne his majesty's commission, and who was

01:10:56.662 --> 01:11:03.522
therefore illuminated by a ray of the splendour that shone so dazzlingly about the throne. How

01:11:03.522 --> 01:11:10.142
unlike, alas, the hang-dog look of a republican official, who, as the servant of the people,

01:11:10.282 --> 01:11:17.562
feels himself less than the least, and below the lowest of his masters. With his own ghostly hand,

01:11:17.682 --> 01:11:24.522
the obscurely seen but majestic figure had imparted to me the scarlet symbol, and the little role of

01:11:24.522 --> 01:11:30.922
the planetary manuscript. With his own ghostly voice he had exhorted me on the sacred consideration

01:11:30.922 --> 01:11:37.622
of my filial duty and reverence towards him, who might reasonably regard himself as my official

01:11:37.622 --> 01:11:42.922
ancestor, to bring his mouldy and moth-eaten lucubrations before the public.

01:11:44.342 --> 01:11:49.882
Do this, said the ghost of Mr. Surveyor Pugh emphatically, nodding the head that looked so

01:11:49.882 --> 01:11:56.542
imposing within its memorable wig. Do this, and the profit shall be all your own. You will shortly

01:11:56.542 --> 01:12:02.522
need it, for it is not in your days as it was in mine, when a man's office was a life-lease,

01:12:02.742 --> 01:12:08.862
and often times an heirloom. But I charge you, in this matter of old mistress Prynne, give to your

01:12:08.862 --> 01:12:15.162
predecessor's memory the credit which will be rightfully its due. And I said to the ghost of

01:12:15.162 --> 01:12:22.222
Mr. Surveyor Pugh, I will. On Hester Prynne's story, therefore, I bestowed much thought.

01:12:22.862 --> 01:12:28.822
It was the subject of my meditations for many an hour, while pacing to and fro across my room,

01:12:29.162 --> 01:12:34.722
or traversing with a hundred-fold repetition the long extent from the front door of the custom

01:12:34.722 --> 01:12:40.762
house to the side entrance and back again. Great were the weariness and annoyance of the old

01:12:40.762 --> 01:12:46.302
inspector, and the wares and gauges, whose slumbers were disturbed by the unmercifully

01:12:46.302 --> 01:12:52.942
lengthened tramp of my passing and returning footsteps. Remembering their own former habits,

01:12:53.022 --> 01:12:58.902
they used to say that the Surveyor was walking the quarter-deck. They probably fancied that my sole

01:12:58.902 --> 01:13:04.062
object, and indeed the sole object for which a sane man could ever put himself into voluntary

01:13:04.062 --> 01:13:10.862
motion, was to get an appetite for dinner. And to say the truth, an appetite, sharpened by the

01:13:10.862 --> 01:13:17.342
east wind that generally blew along the passage, was the only valuable result of so much indefatigable

01:13:17.342 --> 01:13:24.622
exercise. So little adapted is the atmosphere of a custom house to the delicate harvest of fancy

01:13:24.622 --> 01:13:31.502
and sensibility that had I remained there through ten presidencies yet to come, I doubt whether the

01:13:32.202 --> 01:13:38.942
scarlet letter would ever have been brought before the public eye. My imagination was a tarnished

01:13:38.942 --> 01:13:45.382
mirror. It would not reflect, or only with miserable dimness, the figures with which I did my best to

01:13:45.382 --> 01:13:51.602
people it. The characters of the narrative would not be warmed and rendered malleable by any heat

01:13:51.602 --> 01:13:57.942
that I could kindle at my intellectual forge. They would take neither the glow of passion nor the

01:13:57.942 --> 01:14:03.922
tenderness of sentiment, but retained all the rigidity of dead corpses, and stared me in the

01:14:03.922 --> 01:14:10.682
face with a fixed and ghastly grin of contemptuous defiance. What have you to do with us? that

01:14:10.682 --> 01:14:16.382
expression seemed to say. The little power you might once have possessed over the tribe of

01:14:16.382 --> 01:14:22.862
unrealities is gone. You have bartered it for a pittance of the public gold. Go then and earn

01:14:22.862 --> 01:14:30.062
your wages. In short, the almost torpid creatures of my own fancy twitted me with imbecility,

01:14:30.322 --> 01:14:37.082
and not without fair occasion. It was not merely during the three hours and a half which Uncle Sam

01:14:37.082 --> 01:14:42.462
claimed as his share of my daily life that this wretched numbness held possession of me.

01:14:43.102 --> 01:14:48.862
It went with me on my seashore walks and rambles into the country. Whenever, which was seldom and

01:14:48.862 --> 01:14:55.462
reluctantly, I bestirred myself to seek that invigorating charm of nature, which used to give

01:14:55.462 --> 01:15:01.202
me such freshness and activity of thought the moment that I stepped across the threshold of

01:15:01.202 --> 01:15:08.462
the old manse. The same torpor as regarded the capacity for intellectual effort accompanied me

01:15:08.462 --> 01:15:15.202
home and weighed upon me in the chamber which I most absurdly termed my study. Nor did it quit me

01:15:15.202 --> 01:15:21.182
when late at night I sat in the deserted parlour, lighted only by the glimmering coal fire and the

01:15:21.182 --> 01:15:28.182
moon, striving to picture forth imaginary scenes which the next day might flow out on the brightening

01:15:28.182 --> 01:15:35.422
page in many-hued description. If the imaginative faculty refused to act at such an hour, it might

01:15:35.422 --> 01:15:42.162
well be deemed a hopeless case. Moonlight in a familiar room, falling so white upon the carpet

01:15:42.162 --> 01:15:48.962
and showing all its figures so distinctly, making every object so minutely visible yet so unlike a

01:15:48.962 --> 01:15:55.562
morning or noontide visibility, is a medium the most suitable for a romance writer to get acquainted

01:15:55.562 --> 01:16:01.542
with his elusive guests. There is the little domestic scenery of the well-known apartment,

01:16:01.762 --> 01:16:08.842
the chairs with each its separate individuality, the centre table sustaining a work basket, a volume

01:16:08.842 --> 01:16:15.322
or two, and an extinguished lamp. The sofa, the bookcase, the picture on the wall, all these

01:16:15.322 --> 01:16:22.102
details so completely seen are so spiritualised by the unusual light that they seem to lose their

01:16:22.102 --> 01:16:29.262
actual substance and become things of intellect. Nothing is too small or too trifling to undergo

01:16:29.262 --> 01:16:36.522
this change and acquire dignity thereby. A child's shoe, the doll seated in her little wicker carriage,

01:16:36.522 --> 01:16:41.462
the hobby-horse, whatever in a word has been used or played with during the day,

01:16:41.802 --> 01:16:48.322
is now invested with a quality of strangeness and remoteness, though still almost as vividly present

01:16:48.322 --> 01:16:54.642
as by daylight. Thus, therefore, the floor of our familiar room has become a neutral territory

01:16:54.642 --> 01:17:00.942
somewhere between the real world and fairyland, where the actual and the imaginary may meet,

01:17:00.942 --> 01:17:07.642
and each imbue itself with the nature of the other. Ghosts might enter here without affrighting

01:17:07.642 --> 01:17:14.202
us. It would be too much in keeping with the scene to excite surprise were we to look about

01:17:14.202 --> 01:17:20.842
us and discover a form, beloved but gone hence, now sitting quietly in a streak of this magic

01:17:20.842 --> 01:17:26.562
moonshine, with an aspect that would make us doubt whether it had returned from afar

01:17:26.562 --> 01:17:33.442
or had never once stirred from our fireside. The somewhat dim coal-fire has an essential

01:17:33.442 --> 01:17:39.942
influence in producing the effect which I would describe. It throws its unobtrusive tinge

01:17:39.942 --> 01:17:45.542
throughout the room with a faint ruddiness upon the walls and ceiling and a reflected gleam from

01:17:45.542 --> 01:17:51.442
the polish of the furniture. This warmer light mingles itself with the cold spirituality of the

01:17:51.442 --> 01:17:56.822
and communicates, as it were, a heart and sensibilities of human tenderness

01:17:56.822 --> 01:18:03.722
to the forms which fancy summons up. It converts them from snow images into men and women.

01:18:04.742 --> 01:18:10.482
Glancing at the looking-glass, we behold, deep within its haunted verge, the smouldering glow

01:18:10.482 --> 01:18:16.902
of the half-extinguished anthracite, the white moonbeams on the floor, and a repetition of all

01:18:16.902 --> 01:18:22.122
gleam and shadow of the picture, with one removed farther from the actual and nearer

01:18:22.122 --> 01:18:28.142
to the imaginative. Then, at such an hour, and with this scene before him, if a man sitting

01:18:28.142 --> 01:18:34.502
all alone cannot dream strange things and make them look like truth, he need never try to write

01:18:34.502 --> 01:18:41.782
romances. But for myself, during the whole of my custom-house experience, moonlight and sunshine

01:18:41.782 --> 01:18:48.002
and the glow of firelight were just alike in my regard, and neither of them was of one wit more

01:18:48.002 --> 01:18:54.242
availed than the twinkle of a tallow candle. An entire class of susceptibilities and a gift

01:18:54.242 --> 01:19:00.642
connected with them, of no great richness or value but the best I had, was gone from me.

01:19:01.722 --> 01:19:06.162
It is my belief, however, that had I attempted a different order of composition,

01:19:06.642 --> 01:19:10.942
my faculties would not have been found so pointless and inefficacious.

01:19:11.782 --> 01:19:17.362
I might, for instance, have contented myself with writing out the narratives of a veteran shipmaster,

01:19:17.702 --> 01:19:21.682
one of the inspectors, whom I should be most ungrateful not to mention,

01:19:22.102 --> 01:19:26.642
since scarcely a day passed that he did not stir me to laughter and admiration

01:19:26.642 --> 01:19:34.082
by his marvellous gifts as a storyteller. Could I have preserved the picturesque force of his style

01:19:34.082 --> 01:19:38.642
and the humorous colouring which nature taught him how to throw over his descriptions,

01:19:38.642 --> 01:19:43.082
the result, I honestly believe, would have been something new in literature,

01:19:43.662 --> 01:19:50.042
or I might readily have found a more serious task. It was a folly, with the materiality of this

01:19:50.042 --> 01:19:56.242
daily life pressing so intrusively upon me, to attempt to fling myself back into another age,

01:19:56.562 --> 01:20:02.322
or to insist on creating the semblance of a world out of airy matter, when, at every moment,

01:20:02.322 --> 01:20:09.442
the impalpable beauty of my soap-bubble was broken by the rude contact of some actual circumstance.

01:20:10.522 --> 01:20:15.742
The wiser effort would have been to diffuse thought and imagination through the opaque

01:20:15.742 --> 01:20:22.422
substance of to-day, and thus to make it a bright transparency, to spiritualise the burden that

01:20:22.422 --> 01:20:29.102
began to weigh so heavily, to seek, resolutely, the true and indestructible value that lay hidden

01:20:29.102 --> 01:20:35.462
in the petty and wearisome incidents and ordinary characters, with which I was now conversant.

01:20:36.002 --> 01:20:41.962
The fault was mine. The page of life that was spread out before me seemed dull and commonplace,

01:20:42.042 --> 01:20:48.602
only because I had not fathomed its deeper import. A better book than I shall ever write was there,

01:20:48.922 --> 01:20:54.922
leaf after leaf, presenting itself to me, just as it was written out by the reality of the flitting

01:20:55.402 --> 01:21:01.902
and vanishing as fast as written, only because my brain wanted the insight and my hand the cunning

01:21:01.902 --> 01:21:09.502
to transcribe it. At some future day, it may be, I shall remember a few scattered fragments and

01:21:09.502 --> 01:21:15.302
broken paragraphs, and write them down, and find the letters turned to gold upon the page.

01:21:16.282 --> 01:21:21.842
These perceptions have come too late. At the instant, I was only conscious that what would

01:21:21.842 --> 01:21:27.882
have been a pleasure once was now a hopeless toil. There was no occasion to make much moan

01:21:27.882 --> 01:21:34.322
about this state of affairs. I had ceased to be a writer of tolerably poor tales and essays,

01:21:34.442 --> 01:21:42.142
and had become a tolerably good surveyor of the customs. That was all. But, nevertheless,

01:21:42.442 --> 01:21:48.222
it is anything but agreeable to be haunted by a suspicion that one's intellect is dwindling away,

01:21:48.222 --> 01:21:54.562
or exhaling without your consciousness like ether out of a file, so that, at every glance,

01:21:54.582 --> 01:22:01.242
you find a smaller and less volatile residuum. Of the fact there could be no doubt, and examining

01:22:01.242 --> 01:22:06.862
myself and others, I was led to conclusions in reference to the effect of public office on the

01:22:06.862 --> 01:22:13.862
character not very favourable to the mode of life in question. In some other form, perhaps, I may

01:22:13.862 --> 01:22:21.042
develop these effects. Suffice it here to say that a Custom House Officer of long continuance

01:22:21.042 --> 01:22:26.762
can hardly be a very praiseworthy or respectable personage for many reasons.

01:22:27.842 --> 01:22:33.742
One of them, the tenure by which he holds his situation, and another, the very nature of his

01:22:33.742 --> 01:22:43.842
business, which, though I trust an honest one, is of such a sort that he does not share in the

01:22:43.842 --> 01:22:49.582
I believe to be observable, more or less, in every individual who has occupied the position,

01:22:50.082 --> 01:22:56.202
is that, while he leans on the mighty arm of the Republic, his own proper strength departs from him.

01:22:56.702 --> 01:23:01.862
He loses, in an extent proportion to the weakness or force of his original nature,

01:23:02.362 --> 01:23:08.082
the capability of self-support. If he possess an unusual share of native energy,

01:23:08.082 --> 01:23:14.462
or the innovating magic of place do not operate too long upon him, his forfeited powers may be

01:23:14.462 --> 01:23:21.282
redeemable. The ejected officer, fortunate in the unkindly shove that sends him forth betimes

01:23:21.282 --> 01:23:27.642
to struggle amid a struggling world, may return to himself and become all that he has ever been.

01:23:28.082 --> 01:23:33.922
But this seldom happens. He usually keeps his ground just long enough for his own ruin,

01:23:33.922 --> 01:23:39.762
and is then thrust out, with sinews all unstrung, to totter along the difficult

01:23:39.762 --> 01:23:47.042
footpath of life as best he may. Conscious of his own infirmity, that his tempered steel and

01:23:47.042 --> 01:23:53.402
elasticity are lost, he, forever afterwards, looks wistfully about him in quest of support

01:23:53.402 --> 01:24:00.542
external to himself. His pervading and continual hope, a hallucination, which, in the face of all

01:24:00.542 --> 01:24:06.862
discouragement and making light of impossibilities, haunts him while he lives, and, I fancy, like the

01:24:06.862 --> 01:24:13.562
convulsive throws of the cholera, torments him for a brief space after death, is that finally,

01:24:13.562 --> 01:24:20.342
and in no long time, by some happy coincidence of circumstances, he shall be restored to office.

01:24:20.982 --> 01:24:26.882
This faith, more than anything else, steals the pith and availability out of whatever enterprise

01:24:26.882 --> 01:24:32.742
he may dream of undertaking. Why should he toil and moil, and be at so much trouble,

01:24:32.822 --> 01:24:38.342
to pick himself up out of the mud, when, in a little while hence, the strong arm of his uncle

01:24:38.342 --> 01:24:44.862
will raise and support him? Why should he work for his living here, or go to dig gold in California,

01:24:45.302 --> 01:24:51.302
when he is so soon to be made happy at monthly intervals with a little pile of glittering coin

01:24:51.302 --> 01:24:58.342
out of his uncle's pocket? It is sadly curious to observe how slight a taste of office suffices

01:24:58.342 --> 01:25:05.622
to infect a poor fellow with this singular disease. Uncle Sam's gold, meaning no disrespect to the

01:25:05.622 --> 01:25:11.782
worthy old gentleman, has, in this respect, a quality of enchantment like that of the devil's

01:25:11.782 --> 01:25:17.922
wages. Whoever touches it should look well to himself, or he may find the bargain to go hard

01:25:17.922 --> 01:25:25.222
against him, involving, if not his soul, yet many of its better attributes, its sturdy force,

01:25:25.342 --> 01:25:31.262
its courage and constancy, its truth, its self-reliance, and all that gives the emphasis

01:25:31.262 --> 01:25:38.462
to manly character. Here was a fine prospect in the distance, not that the surveyor brought the

01:25:38.462 --> 01:25:45.042
lesson home to himself, or admitted that he could be so utterly undone, either by continuance in

01:25:45.042 --> 01:25:51.722
Yet my reflections were not the most comfortable. I began to grow melancholy and restless,

01:25:52.122 --> 01:25:57.462
continually prying into my mind to discover which of its poor properties were gone,

01:25:57.682 --> 01:26:03.722
and what degree of detriment had already accrued to the remainder. I endeavoured to calculate how

01:26:03.722 --> 01:26:09.462
much longer I could stay in the custom house and yet go forth a man. To confess the truth,

01:26:09.462 --> 01:26:15.342
it was my greatest apprehension, as it would never be a measure of policy to turn out so quiet an

01:26:15.342 --> 01:26:20.482
individual as myself, and it being hardly in the nature of a public officer to resign.

01:26:21.022 --> 01:26:26.842
It was my chief trouble, therefore, that I was likely to grow grey and decrepit in the surveyership,

01:26:26.982 --> 01:26:39.442
and become much such another animal as the old inspector. Might it not, in the tedious

01:26:39.442 --> 01:26:45.502
to make the dinner hour the nucleus of the day, and to spend the rest of it as an old dog spends

01:26:45.502 --> 01:26:52.442
it, asleep in the sunshine or the shade. A dreary look forward this for a man who felt it to be the

01:26:52.442 --> 01:26:58.162
best definition of happiness, to live throughout the whole range of his faculties and sensibilities.

01:26:58.922 --> 01:27:03.122
But all this while I was giving myself very unnecessary alarm.

01:27:03.902 --> 01:27:08.842
Providence had meditated better things for me than I could possibly imagine for myself.

01:27:09.882 --> 01:27:15.462
A remarkable event of the third year of my surveyership, to adopt the tone of PP,

01:27:16.082 --> 01:27:21.622
was the election of General Taylor to the Presidency. It is essential in order to form

01:27:21.622 --> 01:27:27.822
a complete estimate of the advantages of official life, to view the incumbent at the incoming of a

01:27:27.822 --> 01:27:34.442
hostile administration. His position is then one of the most singularly irksome and in every

01:27:34.442 --> 01:27:41.362
contingency disagreeable that a wretched mortal can possibly occupy, with seldom an alternative

01:27:41.362 --> 01:27:47.882
of good on either hand, although what presents itself to him as the worst event may very probably

01:27:47.882 --> 01:27:55.882
be the best. But it is a strange experience to a man of pride and sensibility, to know that his

01:27:55.882 --> 01:28:01.982
interests are within the control of individuals who neither love nor understand him, and by whom,

01:28:01.982 --> 01:28:07.122
since one or the other must needs happen, he would rather be injured than obliged.

01:28:07.922 --> 01:28:13.582
Strange too for one who has kept his calmness throughout the contest to observe the blood

01:28:13.582 --> 01:28:19.362
thirstiness that is developed in the hour of triumph, and to be conscious that he is himself

01:28:19.362 --> 01:28:25.842
among its objects. There are few uglier traits of human nature than this tendency, which I now

01:28:25.842 --> 01:28:31.462
witnessed in men no worse than their neighbours, to grow cruel merely because they possessed the

01:28:31.462 --> 01:28:37.962
power of inflicting harm. If the guillotine as applied to office holders were a literal fact

01:28:37.962 --> 01:28:43.762
instead of one of the most active metaphors, it is my sincere belief that the active members

01:28:43.762 --> 01:28:48.982
of the victorious party were sufficiently excited to have chopped off all our heads,

01:28:49.362 --> 01:28:55.022
and have thanked heaven for the opportunity. It appears to me, who have been a calm and curious

01:28:55.022 --> 01:29:01.022
observer as well in victory as defeat, that this fierce and bitter spirit of malice and revenge

01:29:01.022 --> 01:29:06.902
has never distinguished the many triumphs of my own party as it now did that of the Whigs.

01:29:07.442 --> 01:29:13.002
The Democrats take the offices as a general rule because they need them, and because the practice

01:29:13.002 --> 01:29:18.562
of many years has made it the law of political warfare which, unless a different system be

01:29:18.562 --> 01:29:24.562
proclaimed, it will weakness and cowardice to murmur at. But the long habit of victory has made

01:29:24.562 --> 01:29:30.682
them generous. They know how to spare when they see occasion, and when they strike the axe may be

01:29:30.682 --> 01:29:37.422
sharp indeed, but its edge is seldom poisoned with ill-will, nor is it their custom ignominiously

01:29:37.422 --> 01:29:44.342
to kick the head which they have just struck off. In short, and pleasant as was my predicament,

01:29:44.522 --> 01:29:51.522
at best I saw much reason to congratulate myself that I was on the losing side, rather than the

01:29:51.522 --> 01:29:59.082
triumphant one. If heretofore I had been none of the warmest of partisans, I began now at this

01:29:59.082 --> 01:30:06.282
season of peril and adversity to be pretty acutely sensible with which party my predilections lay,

01:30:06.982 --> 01:30:12.542
nor was it without something like regret and shame that, according to a reasonable calculation

01:30:12.542 --> 01:30:18.762
of chances, I saw my own prospect of retaining office to be better than those of my Democratic

01:30:18.762 --> 01:30:26.722
brethren. But who can see an inch into futurity beyond his nose? My own head was the first that

01:30:26.722 --> 01:30:33.382
fell. The moment when a man's head drops off is seldom or never, I am inclined to think,

01:30:33.662 --> 01:30:38.882
precisely the most agreeable of his life. Nevertheless, like the greater part of our

01:30:38.882 --> 01:30:44.762
misfortunes, even so serious a contingency brings its remedy and consolation with it,

01:30:44.962 --> 01:30:51.222
if the sufferer will but make the best, rather than the worst, of the accident which has befallen him.

01:30:51.222 --> 01:30:57.522
In my particular case the consolatory topics were close at hand, and indeed had suggested

01:30:57.522 --> 01:31:02.882
themselves to my meditations a considerable time before it was requisite to use them.

01:31:03.622 --> 01:31:07.922
In view of my previous weariness of office and vague thoughts of resignation,

01:31:08.502 --> 01:31:14.282
my fortune somewhat resembled that of a person who should entertain an idea of committing suicide,

01:31:14.282 --> 01:31:19.162
and, altogether beyond his hopes, meet with a good hap to be murdered.

01:31:19.982 --> 01:31:26.562
In the Custom House, as before in the Old Manse, I had spent three years, a time long enough to

01:31:26.562 --> 01:31:32.622
rest a weary brain, long enough to break off old intellectual habits and make room for new ones,

01:31:32.942 --> 01:31:38.682
long enough and too long to have lived in an unnatural state, doing what was really of no

01:31:38.682 --> 01:31:44.202
advantage nor delight to any human being, and withholding myself from toil that would

01:31:44.202 --> 01:31:51.542
at least have stilled an unquiet impulse in me. Then, moreover, as regarded his unceremonious

01:31:51.542 --> 01:31:57.322
ejectment, the late Surveyor was not altogether ill-pleased to be recognised by the Whigs as an

01:31:57.322 --> 01:32:04.062
enemy, since his inactivity in political affairs, his tendency to roam at will in that broad and

01:32:04.062 --> 01:32:09.962
quiet field where all mankind may meet, rather than confine himself to those narrow paths

01:32:09.962 --> 01:32:15.642
where brethren of the same household must diverge from one another, had sometimes made it

01:32:15.642 --> 01:32:22.242
questionable with his brother Democrats whether he was a friend. Now, after he had won the Crown

01:32:22.242 --> 01:32:28.022
of Martyrdom, though with no longer a head to wear it on, the point might be looked upon as

01:32:28.822 --> 01:32:35.082
Finally, little heroic as he was, it seemed more decorous to be overthrown in the downfall of the

01:32:35.082 --> 01:32:41.062
party with which he had been content to stand, than to remain a forlorn survivor when so many

01:32:41.062 --> 01:32:47.102
worthier men were falling, and at last, after subsisting for four years on the mercy of a

01:32:47.102 --> 01:32:53.902
hostile administration, to be compelled then to define his position anew and claim the yet more

01:32:53.902 --> 01:33:01.022
humiliating mercy of a friendly one. Meanwhile the press had taken up my affair and kept me

01:33:01.022 --> 01:33:07.442
for a week or two, careering through the public prints in my decapitated state like Irving's

01:33:07.442 --> 01:33:14.482
headless horseman, ghastly and grim and longing to be buried as a politically dead man ought.

01:33:15.242 --> 01:33:21.902
So much for my figurative self. The real human being, all this time with his head safely on his

01:33:21.902 --> 01:33:28.002
shoulders, had brought himself to the comfortable conclusion that everything was for the best, and

01:33:28.002 --> 01:33:34.762
making an investment in ink, paper and steel pens, had opened his long disused writing desk,

01:33:34.922 --> 01:33:41.842
and was again a literary man. Now it was that the lucubrations of my ancient predecessor,

01:33:42.062 --> 01:33:49.242
Mr. Surveyor Pugh, came into play. Rusty through long idleness, some little space was requisite

01:33:49.242 --> 01:33:55.522
before my intellectual machinery could be brought to work upon the tale with an effect in any degree

01:33:55.522 --> 01:34:01.402
satisfactory. Even yet, though my thoughts were ultimately much absorbed in the task,

01:34:01.742 --> 01:34:08.582
it wears to my eye a stern and sombre aspect, too much ungladdened by genial sunshine,

01:34:08.982 --> 01:34:14.562
too little relieved by the tender and familiar influences which soften almost every scene of

01:34:15.122 --> 01:34:19.922
real life, and undoubtedly should soften every picture of them.

01:34:21.122 --> 01:34:26.642
This uncaptivating effect is perhaps due to the period of hardly accomplished revolution

01:34:26.642 --> 01:34:33.222
and still seething turmoil in which the story shaped itself. It is no indication, however,

01:34:33.322 --> 01:34:39.082
of a lack of cheerfulness in the writer's mind, for he was happier while straying through the gloom of

01:34:40.142 --> 01:34:46.522
fantasies than at any time since he had quitted the old manse. Some of the briefer articles which

01:34:46.522 --> 01:34:51.802
contribute to make up the volume have likewise been written since my involuntary withdrawal

01:34:51.802 --> 01:34:56.882
from the toils and honours of public life, and the remainders are gleaned from annuals and

01:34:56.882 --> 01:35:03.042
magazines of such antique date that they have gone round the circle and come back to novelty again.

01:35:03.982 --> 01:35:09.242
Keeping up the metaphor of the political guillotine, the whole may be considered as

01:35:09.242 --> 01:35:15.362
the posthumous papers of a decapitated surveyor, and the sketch which I am now bringing to a close,

01:35:15.682 --> 01:35:20.022
if too autobiographical for a modest person to publish in his lifetime,

01:35:20.562 --> 01:35:24.542
will readily be excused in a gentleman who writes from beyond the grave.

01:35:25.102 --> 01:35:30.642
Peace be with all the world, my blessing on my friends, my forgiveness to my enemies,

01:35:30.642 --> 01:35:37.662
for I am in the realm of quiet. The life of the Custom House lies like a dream behind me.

01:35:37.982 --> 01:35:43.782
The old Inspector, who by the by, I regret to say, was overthrown and killed by a horse some

01:35:43.782 --> 01:35:50.202
time ago, else he would certainly have lived for ever, he and all those other venerable personages

01:35:50.202 --> 01:35:56.342
who sat with him at the receipt of Custom are but shadows in my view, white-headed and wrinkled

01:35:56.342 --> 01:36:02.902
images, which my fancy used to sport with, and has now flung aside for ever. The Merchants,

01:36:03.122 --> 01:36:09.242
Pingree, Phillips, Shepherd, Upton, Kimble, Bertram, Hunt, these and many other names,

01:36:09.302 --> 01:36:14.622
which had such a classic familiarity for my ear six months ago, these men of traffic,

01:36:14.762 --> 01:36:20.672
who seem to occupy so important a position in the world, how little time has it required to

01:36:20.672 --> 01:36:27.432
disconnect me from them all, not merely an act but recollection. It is with an effort that I

01:36:27.432 --> 01:36:33.932
recall the figures and appellations of these few. Soon, likewise, my old native town will loom upon

01:36:33.932 --> 01:36:40.232
me through the haze of memory, a mist brooding over and around it, as if it were no portion of

01:36:40.232 --> 01:36:45.952
the real earth but an overgrown village in cloudland, with only imaginary inhabitants to

01:36:45.952 --> 01:36:52.972
its wooden houses and walk its homely lanes, and the unpicturesque prolixity of its main street.

01:36:54.012 --> 01:37:00.872
Henceforth it ceases to be a reality of my life. I am a citizen of somewhere else. My good townspeople

01:37:00.872 --> 01:37:07.152
will not much regret me. For, though it has been as dear an object as any in my literary efforts

01:37:07.152 --> 01:37:12.742
to be of some importance in their eyes, and to win myself a pleasant memory in this abode and

01:37:12.742 --> 01:37:19.142
place of so many of my forefathers, there has never been for me the genial atmosphere which a

01:37:19.142 --> 01:37:26.262
literary man requires in order to ripen the best harvest of his mind. I shall do better among other

01:37:26.262 --> 01:37:32.182
faces, and these familiar ones, it need hardly be said, will do just as well without me.

01:37:33.042 --> 01:37:39.062
It may be, however, all transporting and triumphant thought that the great-grandchildren

01:37:39.062 --> 01:37:44.342
of the present race may sometimes think kindly of the scribbler of bygone days,

01:37:44.722 --> 01:37:49.782
when the antiquary of days to come, among the sites memorable in the town's history,

01:37:50.162 --> 01:37:53.402
shall point out the locality of the town pump.

01:37:55.642 --> 01:37:59.042
End of part two of the Custom House

01:38:32.884 --> 01:38:34.084
THE PRISON DOOR

01:38:35.024 --> 01:38:40.384
A throng of bearded men, in sad-coloured garments and grey, steepled crowned hats, intermixed

01:38:40.384 --> 01:38:44.484
with women, some wearing hoods, and others bare-headed, was assembled in front of a wooden

01:38:44.484 --> 01:38:48.844
edifice, the door of which was heavily timbered with oak, and studded with iron spikes.

01:38:49.864 --> 01:38:54.584
The founders of a new colony, whatever utopia of human virtue and happiness they might originally

01:38:54.584 --> 01:38:59.124
project, have invariably recognised it among their earliest practical necessities to allot

01:38:59.844 --> 01:39:03.784
soil as a cemetery, and another portion as the site of a prison.

01:39:04.504 --> 01:39:08.944
In accordance with this rule, it may safely be assumed that the forefathers of Boston

01:39:08.944 --> 01:39:13.904
had built the first prison house somewhere in the vicinity of Corn Hill, almost as seasonably

01:39:13.904 --> 01:39:19.044
as they marked out the first burial ground, on Isaac Johnson's lot, and round about his

01:39:19.044 --> 01:39:23.784
grave, which subsequently became the nucleus of all the congregated sepulchres in the

01:39:23.784 --> 01:39:25.264
old churchyard of King's Chapel.

01:39:25.884 --> 01:39:30.404
Certain it is that some fifteen or twenty years after the settlement of the town, the

01:39:30.404 --> 01:39:34.884
wooden jail was already marked with weather stains and other indications of age, which

01:39:34.884 --> 01:39:38.164
gave a yet darker aspect to its beetle-browned and gloomy front.

01:39:38.984 --> 01:39:43.004
The rust on the ponderous ironwork of its oak and door looked more antique than anything

01:39:43.004 --> 01:39:44.004
else in the New World.

01:39:44.524 --> 01:39:47.904
Like all that pertains to crime, it seemed never to have known a youthful era.

01:39:48.644 --> 01:39:53.044
Before this ugly edifice, and between it and the wheel track of the street, was a grass

01:39:53.044 --> 01:39:58.544
plot, much overgrown with burdock, pigweed, apple-pern, and such unsightly vegetation,

01:39:58.904 --> 01:40:03.224
which evidently found something congenial in the soil that had so early borne the black

01:40:03.224 --> 01:40:06.204
flower of civilized society, a prison.

01:40:07.024 --> 01:40:11.484
But on one side of the portal, and rooted almost at the threshold, was a wild rose bush

01:40:11.484 --> 01:40:16.644
covered, in this month of June, with its delicate gems, which might be imagined to offer their

01:40:16.644 --> 01:40:20.624
fragrance and fragile beauty to the prisoner as he went in, and to the condemned criminal

01:40:20.624 --> 01:40:22.204
as he came forth to his doom.

01:40:22.784 --> 01:40:26.584
In token that the deep heart of nature could pity and be kind to him.

01:40:27.304 --> 01:40:31.564
This rose bush, by a strange chance, has been kept alive in history.

01:40:32.184 --> 01:40:36.324
But whether it had merely survived out of the stern old wilderness so long after the

01:40:36.324 --> 01:40:41.264
fall of the gigantic pines and oaks that originally overshadowed it, or whether, as there is fair

01:40:41.264 --> 01:40:45.624
authority for believing, it had sprung up under the footsteps of the sainted Anne Hutchinson

01:40:45.624 --> 01:40:49.144
as she entered the prison door, we shall not take upon us to determine.

01:40:49.824 --> 01:40:53.644
Finding it so directly on the threshold of our narrative, which is now about to issue

01:40:53.644 --> 01:40:58.064
from that inauspicious portal, we could hardly do otherwise than pluck one of its flowers

01:40:58.064 --> 01:40:59.584
and present it to the reader.

01:41:00.204 --> 01:41:05.184
It may serve, let us hope, to symbolize some sweet moral blossom that may be found along

01:41:05.184 --> 01:41:10.584
the track, or relieve the darkening clothes of a tale of human frailty and sorrow.

01:41:14.364 --> 01:41:16.084
The Prison Door

01:41:19.044 --> 01:41:22.424
who could be found at jrwmcdonald.com

01:41:37.167 --> 01:41:39.447
Recorded by James R. W. MacDonald

01:41:40.087 --> 01:41:43.187
The Scarlet Letter by Nathaniel Hathorne

01:41:43.767 --> 01:41:46.947
The Marketplace

01:41:47.847 --> 01:41:59.867
The grass plot before the jail and prison lane on a certain summer morning, not less than two centuries ago, was occupied by a pretty large number of the inhabitants of Boston, all with their eyes intently fastened on the iron-clamped oak and door.

01:42:00.407 --> 01:42:10.147
Amongst any other population, or at a later period in the history of New England, the grim rigidity that petrified the bearded physiognomies of these good people would have argued some awful business in hand.

01:42:10.147 --> 01:42:19.187
It could have been token nothing short of an anticipated execution of some noted culprit, on whom the sentence of a legal tribunal had but confirmed the verdict of public sentiment.

01:42:20.027 --> 01:42:26.207
But, in that early severity of the Puritan character, an inference of this kind could not so indubitably be drawn.

01:42:26.647 --> 01:42:34.107
It might be that a sluggish bond-servant or an undutiful child, whom his parents had given over to the civil authority, was to be corrected at the whipping post.

01:42:34.107 --> 01:42:47.887
It might be that an antinomian, a Quaker, or other heterodox religionist, was to be scourged out of the town, or an idle or vagrant Indian, whom the white man's fire-water had made riotous about the streets, was to be driven with stripes into the shadow of the forest.

01:42:47.887 --> 01:42:56.587
It might be, too, that a witch, like old Mistress Hibbins, the bitter-tempered widow of the magistrate, was to die upon the gallows.

01:42:57.047 --> 01:43:05.847
In either case, there was very much the same solemnity of demeanour on the part of the spectators as befitted a people among whom religion and law were almost identical,

01:43:06.227 --> 01:43:14.227
and in whose character both were so thoroughly interfused that the mildest and severest acts of public discipline were alike made venerable and awful.

01:43:14.887 --> 01:43:20.967
Meager, indeed, and cold was the sympathy that a transgressor might look for from such bystanders at the scaffold.

01:43:21.847 --> 01:43:32.447
On the other hand, a penalty which in our days would infer a degree of mocking infamy and ridicule might then be invested with almost as stern a dignity as the punishment of death itself.

01:43:33.467 --> 01:43:41.067
It was a circumstance to be noted on the summer morning, when our story begins its course, that the women of whom there were several in the crowd

01:43:41.067 --> 01:43:46.287
appeared to take a peculiar interest in whatever penal infliction might be expected to ensue.

01:43:46.687 --> 01:43:54.947
The age had not so much refinement that any sense of impropriety restrained the wearers of petticoat and farthingale from stepping forth into the public ways

01:43:54.947 --> 01:44:01.407
and wedging their not-so-unsubstantial bodies, if occasion were, into the throng nearest to the scaffold at an execution.

01:44:02.327 --> 01:44:10.727
Morally, as well as materially, there was a coarser fibre in those wives and maidens of old English birth and breeding than in their fair descendants,

01:44:11.167 --> 01:44:14.027
separated from them by a series of six or seven generations.

01:44:14.747 --> 01:44:24.447
For throughout that chain of ancestry, every successive mother had transmitted to her child a fainter bloom, a more delicate and briever beauty, and a slighter physical frame.

01:44:24.447 --> 01:44:32.867
If not character of less force and solidity than her own, the women who were now standing about the prison door stood within less than half a century of the period

01:44:32.867 --> 01:44:37.867
when the man like Elizabeth had been the not altogether unsuitable representative of the sex.

01:44:38.547 --> 01:44:46.427
They were her countrywomen, and the beef and ale of their native land, with a moral diet not a whit more refined, entered largely into their composition.

01:44:46.427 --> 01:44:55.767
The bright morning sun, therefore, shone on broad shoulders and well-developed busts, and on round and ruddy cheeks that had ripened in the far-off island

01:44:55.767 --> 01:44:59.687
and had hardly yet grown paler or thinner in the atmosphere of New England.

01:45:00.087 --> 01:45:11.827
There was, moreover, a boldness and rotundity of speech among these matrons, as most of them seemed to be, that would startle us at the present day, whether in respect to its purport or its volume of tone.

01:45:11.827 --> 01:45:18.507
Good wives, said a hard-featured dame of fifty, I'll tell ye a piece of my mind, it would be greatly.

01:45:19.327 --> 01:45:29.007
For the public behoof, if we women, being of mature age and church members and good repute, should have the handling of such a malfactress as this Hester Prynne, what think ye gossips?

01:45:29.867 --> 01:45:34.147
If the hussy stood up for judgment for us five, what are now here in a not together?

01:45:34.587 --> 01:45:37.827
Would she come off with such a sentence as the worshipful magistrates have awarded?

01:45:40.207 --> 01:45:50.167
People say, said another, that the Reverend Master Dimmesdale, her godly pastor, takes it very grievously to heart that such a scandal should have come upon his congregation.

01:45:51.067 --> 01:45:57.187
The magistrates are good-fearing gentlemen, but merciful morevermuch that is the truth, added a third autumnal matron.

01:45:57.587 --> 01:46:01.807
At the very least they should have put the brand of a hot iron on Hester Prynne's forehead.

01:46:02.427 --> 01:46:11.547
Madam Hester would have winced at that, I warn me, but she, the naughty baggage, little will she care what they put upon the bodice of her gown.

01:46:11.987 --> 01:46:19.267
Why, look you, she may cover it with a brooch, or such like heathenish adornment, and so walk the streets as brave as ever.

01:46:20.267 --> 01:46:29.207
Ah, but, interposed more softly, a young wife, holding a child by the hand, let her cover the marks as she will, the pain of it will be always in her heart.

01:46:29.967 --> 01:46:42.247
What do we talk of marks and brands, whether on the bodice of her gown, or the flesh of her forehead, cried another female, the ugliest as well as the most pitiless of these, self-constituted judges?

01:46:42.727 --> 01:46:49.707
This woman has brought shame upon us all, and ought to die. Is there not law for it? Truly there is.

01:46:50.367 --> 01:46:58.807
Both in the scripture and the statute book, then let the magistrates who have made it of no effect thank themselves if their own wives and daughters go astray.

01:46:59.807 --> 01:47:07.607
Mercy on us, good wife, exclaimed a man in the crowd. Is there no virtue in woman, save that springs from a wholesome fear of the gallows?

01:47:08.567 --> 01:47:15.287
That is the hardest word yet. Hush now, gossips for the lock is turning in the prison door, and here comes Mistress Prynne herself.

01:47:15.287 --> 01:47:28.807
The door of the jail being flung open from within there appeared, in the first place, like a black shadow emerging into sunshine, the grim and grisly presence of the town beetle, with a sword by his side, and his staff of office in his hand.

01:47:29.347 --> 01:47:41.687
This personage prefigured and represented in his aspect the whole dismal severity of the puritanic code of law, which it was his business to administer in its final and closest application to the offender.

01:47:41.687 --> 01:47:59.027
Stretching forth the official staff in his left hand, he laid his right upon the shoulder of a young woman, whom he thus drew forward, until, on the threshold of the prison door, she repelled him by an action marked with natural dignity and force of character, and stepped into the open air as if by her own free will.

01:47:59.027 --> 01:48:16.267
She bore in her arms a child, a baby of some three months old, who winked and turned aside its little face from the too vivid light of day, because of its existence, heretofore, had brought its acquaintance only with the gray twilight of a dungeon or other darksome apartment of the prison.

01:48:16.267 --> 01:48:33.427
When the young woman, the mother of this child, stood fully revealed before the crowd, it seemed to be her first impulse to clasp the infant closely to her bosom, not so much by an impulse of motherly affection, as that she might thereby conceal a certain token, which was wrought or fastened into her dress.

01:48:33.427 --> 01:48:48.547
In a moment, however, wisely judging that one token of her shame would but poorly serve to hide another, she took the baby on her arm, and with a burning blush, and yet a haughty smile, and a glance that would not be abashed, looked around at her townspeople and neighbours.

01:48:48.547 --> 01:48:57.627
On the breast of her gown, in fine red cloth surrounded with an elaborate embroidery and fantastic flourishes of gold thread, appeared the letter A.

01:48:58.127 --> 01:49:17.367
It was so artistically done, and with so much fertility and gorgeous luxuriance of fancy, that it had all the effect of a last and fitting decoration to the apparel which she wore, and which was of a splendour in accordance with the state of the age, but greatly beyond what was allowed by the sumptuary regulations of the colony.

01:49:17.967 --> 01:49:37.687
The young woman was tall, with a figure of perfect elegance on a large scale. She had dark and abundant hair, so glossy that it threw off the sunshine with a gleam, and a face which, besides being beautiful from regularity of feature and richness of complexion, had the impressiveness belonging to a marked brow and deep black eyes.

01:49:37.687 --> 01:49:58.207
She was ladylike, too, after the manner of the feminine gentility of those days, characterised by a certain state of dignity, rather than by the delicate evanescence and indescribable grace which is now recognised as its indication, and never had Hester Prynne appeared more ladylike in the antique interpretation of the term.

01:49:58.207 --> 01:50:15.307
Then as she issued from the prison, those who had before known her, and had expected to behold her dimmed and obscured by a disastrous cloud, were astonished, and even startled, to perceive how her beauty shone out, and made a halo of the misfortune and ignominy in which she was enveloped.

01:50:15.307 --> 01:50:34.487
It may be true that, to a sensitive observer, there was something exquisitely painful in it. Her attire, which indeed she had wrought for the occasion in prison, and had moulded much after her own fancy, seemed to express the attitude of her spirit, the desperate recklessness of her mood, by its wild and picturesque peculiarity.

01:50:34.487 --> 01:51:02.607
But the point which drew all eyes, and, as it were, transfigured the wearer, so that both men and women who had been familiarly acquainted with Hester Prynne, were now impressed as if they had beheld her for the first time, was the scarlet letter, so fantastically embroidered and illuminated upon her bosom, it had the effect of a spell, taking her out of the ordinary relations with humanity, and enclosing her in a sphere by herself.

01:51:03.547 --> 01:51:24.747
She hath good skill at her needle, that's certain, remarked one of her female spectators. But did ever a woman before this brazen hussy contrive such a way of showing it? Why, gossips, what is it but to laugh in the face of our cuddly magistrates and make a pride out of what they, worthy gentlemen, meant for a punishment?

01:51:25.547 --> 01:51:41.387
It were well, muttered the most iron-visaged of the old dames, if we stripped Madame Hester's rich gown off her dainty shoulders, and as for the red letter, which she hath stitched so curiously, I'll bestow a rag of mine own rheumatic flannel to make a fitter one.

01:51:41.387 --> 01:51:52.267
Oh, peace, neighbour's peace, whispered their youngest companion. Do not let her hear you, not a stitch in that embroidered letter, but she has felt it in her heart.

01:51:53.327 --> 01:52:09.527
The grim beetle now made a gesture with his staff. Make way, good people, make way in the king's name, cried he. Open a passage, and I promise ye, Mistress Payne shall be set where man, woman, and child may have a fair sight of her brave apparel from this time till an hour past meridian.

01:52:09.527 --> 01:52:19.407
A blessing on the righteous colony of the Massachusetts, where iniquity is dragged out into the sunshine. Come along, Madame Hester, and show your scarlet letter in the market place.

01:52:20.887 --> 01:52:34.387
Elaine was forthwith opened through the crowd of spectators. Proceeded by the beetle, and attended by an irregular procession of stern-browed men and unkindly-visaged women, Hester Prynne set forth toward the place appointed for her punishment.

01:52:34.387 --> 01:52:50.047
A crowd of eager and curious schoolboys understanding little of the matter in hand, except that it gave them a half holiday, ran before her progress, turning their heads continually to stare into her face, and at the winking baby in her arms, and at the ignominious letter on her breast.

01:52:50.047 --> 01:53:05.907
It was no great distance in those days from the prison door to the market place, measured by the prisoner's experience, however. It might be reckoned a journey of some length, for haughty as her demeanor was, she perchance underwent an agony from every footstep of those thronged to see her.

01:53:06.647 --> 01:53:24.167
As if her heart had been flung into the street for them all to spurn and trample upon, in our nature, however, there is a provision, alike marvellous and merciful, that the sufferer should never know the intensity of what he endures by its present torture, but chiefly by the pain that rankles afterward.

01:53:25.267 --> 01:53:39.947
With almost a serene deportment, therefore, Hester Prynne passed through this portion of her ordeal, and came to a sort of scaffold at the western extremity of the market place. It stood nearly beneath the eaves of Boston's earliest church, and appeared to be a fixture there.

01:53:39.947 --> 01:53:59.947
In fact, this scaffold constituted a portion of a penal machine, which now, for two or three generations past, has been merely historical and traditionary among us, but was held in the old time to be an effectual and agent in the promotion of good citizenship, as ever was the guillotine among the terrorists of France.

01:53:59.947 --> 01:54:14.187
It was, in short, the platform of the pillory, and above it rose the framework that the instrument of discipline so fashioned as to confine the human head in its tight grasp, and thus hold it up to the public gaze.

01:54:14.187 --> 01:54:35.687
The very ideal of ignominy was embodied and made manifest in the contrivance of wood and iron. There can be no outrage, methinks, against our common nature, wheter it be the delinquencies of the individual, no outrage more flagrant than to forbid the culprit to hide his face for shame, as it was the essence of this punishment to do.

01:54:35.687 --> 01:54:54.867
In Hester Prynne's instance, however, as not unfrequently in other cases, her sentence bore that she should stand a certain time upon the platform, but without undergoing that gripe about the neck and confinement of the head, the proneness to which was the most devilish characteristic of this ugly engine.

01:54:54.867 --> 01:55:04.407
Knowing well her part, she ascended a flight of wooden steps, and was thus displayed to the surrounding multitude, at about the height of a man's shoulders above the street.

01:55:06.687 --> 01:55:31.407
Had there been a papist among the crowd of Puritans, he might have seen in this beautiful woman so picturesque in her attire and mien, and with the infant at her bosom, an object to remind him of the image of divine maternity, which so many illustrious painters have vied with one another to represent, something which should remind him, indeed, but only by contrast, of that sacred image of sinless motherhood whose infant was to redeem the world.

01:55:31.407 --> 01:55:45.267
Here, there was the taint of deepest sin in the most sacred quality of human life, working such effect that the world was only the darker for this woman's beauty, and the more lost for the infant that she had borne.

01:55:46.847 --> 01:55:57.987
The scene was not without a mixture of awe, such as must always invest the spectacle of guilt and shame in a fellow creature, before society shall have grown corrupt enough to smile instead of shuddering at it.

01:55:57.987 --> 01:56:16.047
The witnesses of Hester Prynne's disgrace had not yet passed beyond their simplicity. They were stern enough to look upon her death, had that been the sentence, without a murmur at its severity, but had none of the heartlessness of another social state which would find only a theme for jest in an exhibition like the present.

01:56:16.047 --> 01:56:34.367
Even had there been a disposition to turn the matter into ridicule, it must have been repressed and overpowered by the solemn presence of men no less dignified than the governor, and several of his councillors, a judge, a general, and the ministers of the town, all of whom sat or stood in a balcony of the meeting house looking down upon the platform.

01:56:34.367 --> 01:56:47.247
When such personages could constitute a part of the spectacle without risking the majesty or reverence of rank and office, it was safely to be inferred that the infliction of a legal sentence would have an earnest and effectual meaning.

01:56:48.147 --> 01:57:00.347
Accordingly, the crowd was sombre and grave. The unhappy culprit sustained herself as best a woman might, under the heavy weight of a thousand unrelenting eyes, all fastened upon her and concentrated at her bosom.

01:57:00.347 --> 01:57:15.147
It was almost intolerable to be borne. Of an impulsive and passionate nature, she had fortified herself to encounter the stings and venomous stabs of public contumely, wreaking itself in every variety of insult.

01:57:15.147 --> 01:57:26.727
But there was a quality so much more terrible in the solemn mood of the popular mind that she longed rather to behold all those rigid countenances contorted with scornful merriment, and herself the object.

01:57:27.347 --> 01:57:39.387
Had a roar of laughter burst from the multitude, each man, each woman, each little shrill-voiced child contributing their individual parts, Hester Prynne might have repaid them all with a bitter and disdainful smile.

01:57:39.387 --> 01:57:52.527
But under the leaden infliction, which it was her doom to endure, she felt at moments as if she must need shriek out with the full power of her lungs and cast herself from the scaffold down upon the ground, or else go mad at once.

01:57:52.527 --> 01:58:04.427
Yet there were intervals when the whole scene in which she was the most conspicuous object seemed to vanish from her eyes, or at least glimmered indistinctly before them, like a mass of imperfectly shaped and spectral images.

01:58:04.727 --> 01:58:14.167
Her mind, and especially her memory, was preternaturally active, and kept bringing up other scenes than this roughly hewn street of a little town on the edge of the western wilderness.

01:58:14.167 --> 01:58:41.707
Other faces then were lowering upon her from beneath the brims of those steeple-crowned hats. Reminiscences, most trifling and immaterial, passages of infancy in school days, sports, childish quarrels, and the little domestic traits of her maiden years, came swarming back upon her, intermingled with recollections of whatever was gravest in her subsequent life, one picture precisely as vivid as another, as if all were of similar importance, or all alike, a play.

01:58:42.767 --> 01:58:53.507
Possibly it was an instinctive device of her spirit to relieve itself by the exhibitions of these phantasmagoric forms from the cruel weight and hardness of the reality.

01:58:54.107 --> 01:59:17.367
Be that as it might, the scaffold of the pillory was a point of view that revealed to Hester Prynne the entire track along which she had been treading since her happy infancy. Standing on that miserable eminence, she saw again her native village in Old England in her paternal home, a decayed house of grey stone, with a poverty-stricken aspect but retaining a half-obliterated shield of arms over the portal.

01:59:18.147 --> 01:59:40.967
In token of antique gentility, she saw her father's face, with its bold brow and revered white beard that flowed over the old-fashioned Elizabethan ruff, her mother's too, with a look of heedful and anxious love which it always wore in her remembrance, and which, even since her death, had so often laid the impediment of a gentle remonstrance in her daughter's pathway.

01:59:40.967 --> 01:59:49.367
She saw her own face, glowing with girlish beauty and illuminating all the interior of the dusky mirror in which she had been wont to gaze at.

01:59:50.327 --> 02:00:03.367
There she beheld another countenance of a man well stricken in years, a pale, thin, scholar-like visage, with eyes dim and bleared by the lamplight that had served them to pour over many ponderous books.

02:00:03.367 --> 02:00:21.327
Yet those same bleared optics had a strange penetrating power when it was their owner's purpose to read the human soul. This figure of the study and the cloister, as Hester Prynne's womanly fancy failed not to recall, was slightly deformed, with the left shoulder a trifle higher than the right.

02:00:22.127 --> 02:00:48.967
Next rose before her, in her memory's picture gallery, the intricate and narrow thoroughfares, the tall grey houses, the huge cathedrals, and the public edifices, ancient in date and quaint in architecture of a continental city where new life had awaited her, still in connection with the misshapen scholar, a new life, but feeding itself on time-worn materials like a tuft of green moss on a crumbling wall.

02:00:49.807 --> 02:01:13.587
Lastly, in lieu of these shifting scenes, came back the rude marketplace of the Puritan settlement, with all the townspeople assembled, and levelling their stern regards at Hester Prynne, yes, at herself, who stood on the scaffold of the pillory, an infant on her arm, and the letter A, in scarlet, fantastically embroidered with gold, thread upon her bosom.

02:01:14.527 --> 02:01:35.827
Could it be true? She clutched the child so fiercely to her breast that it sent forth a cry. She turned her eyes downward at the scarlet letter, and even touched it with her finger, to assure herself that the infant and the shame were real. Yes, these were her realities. All else had vanished.

02:01:43.587 --> 02:01:46.967
who can be found at jrwmcdonald.com

02:02:16.482 --> 02:02:21.322
From this intense consciousness of being the object of severe and universal observation,

02:02:21.322 --> 02:02:27.362
the wear of the scarlet flare was at length relieved by the surging on outskirts of the crowd,

02:02:27.722 --> 02:02:32.922
a fear which irresistibly took possession of our thoughts. An Indian, in his native car,

02:02:32.982 --> 02:02:38.582
was standing there. But red men were not so infrequent visitors of the English settlements

02:02:38.582 --> 02:02:45.042
that one of them would have attracted any notice from Esther Pryne at such a time. Much less would

02:02:45.042 --> 02:02:51.782
he have excluded all other objects and ideas from our mind. By the Indian side, and evidently

02:02:51.782 --> 02:02:57.902
sustaining companionship with him, stood a white man, clad in a strange disarray of civilised and

02:02:57.902 --> 02:03:05.382
savage costume. He was small in stature, with a furred visage, which as yet could hardly be

02:03:05.382 --> 02:03:11.542
termed aged. There was a remarkable intelligence in its features, as of a person who had so

02:03:11.542 --> 02:03:16.802
cultivated his mental part that he could not fail to mould the physical to itself and become

02:03:16.802 --> 02:03:23.942
manifest by unmistakable tokens. Although, by a seemingly careless arrangement of his

02:03:23.942 --> 02:03:29.862
heterogeneous garb, he had endeavoured to conceal or abate the peculiarity, it was sufficiently

02:03:29.862 --> 02:03:36.122
evident to Esther Pryne that one of this man's shoulder rose higher than the other. Again,

02:03:36.122 --> 02:03:41.422
at the first instant of perceiving that thin visage and slight formative figure,

02:03:41.882 --> 02:03:46.302
she pressed her infant to a bosom with so convulsive a force that the poor babe uttered

02:03:46.302 --> 02:03:53.242
another cry of pain. But mother did not seem to hear it. At his arrival in the marketplace,

02:03:53.842 --> 02:03:59.922
and some time before she saw him, the stranger had bent his eyes on Esther Pryne. It was careless

02:03:59.922 --> 02:04:05.942
at first, like a man chiefly accustomed to look inward and to whom external matters are of little

02:04:05.942 --> 02:04:12.322
value and import, unless they were relation to something within his mind. Very soon, however,

02:04:12.582 --> 02:04:18.522
his look became keen and penetrative. A writhing horror twisted itself across its features,

02:04:18.962 --> 02:04:25.802
like a snake gliding swiftly over them and making one little pause, with all its dreaded

02:04:25.802 --> 02:04:32.082
intervolutions in open sight. Its face darkened with some powerful emotion, which, nevertheless,

02:04:32.082 --> 02:04:38.242
he so instantaneously controlled by an effort of his will that, save at a single moment,

02:04:38.662 --> 02:04:45.682
its expression might have passed for calmness. After a brief space, the convulsion grew almost

02:04:45.682 --> 02:04:52.202
imperceptible and finally subsided into the depth of his nature. When he found the eyes of Esther

02:04:52.202 --> 02:04:58.322
Pryne fastened on his own and saw that she appeared to recognize him, he slowly and calmly

02:04:58.322 --> 02:05:02.862
raised his finger, made a gesture with it in the air, and laid it on his lips.

02:05:04.222 --> 02:05:09.302
Then, touching the shoulder of a townsman who stood near to him, he addressed him in a formal

02:05:09.302 --> 02:05:10.502
and courteous manner.

02:05:11.882 --> 02:05:19.242
I pray you, good sir, said he. Who is this woman, and wherefore is she here set up to public shame?

02:05:20.842 --> 02:05:25.822
You must need to be a stranger in this region, friend, answered the townsman,

02:05:25.822 --> 02:05:29.022
looking curiously at the questioner and his savage companion.

02:05:29.962 --> 02:05:33.942
Else you'd surely have heard of Mr. Esther Pryne and her evildoings.

02:05:34.682 --> 02:05:39.762
She hath raised a great scandal, I promise you, in Godlymaster Dimsdale's church.

02:05:41.042 --> 02:05:48.242
You say truly, replied the other. I am a stranger, and have been a wanderer, surely against my will.

02:05:48.762 --> 02:05:54.782
I have met with grievous mischiefs by sea and land, and have been long held in bonds among the

02:05:54.782 --> 02:06:00.742
distant folk of Southworth, and am now brought hithered by this Indian to be redeemed out of my

02:06:00.742 --> 02:06:07.442
captivity. Will it please you, therefore, to tell me of Esther Pryne's, if I have her name rightly,

02:06:08.122 --> 02:06:11.922
of this woman's offences, and what was brought her to yonder scaffold?

02:06:13.142 --> 02:06:18.802
Truly, friend, and methinks it must clad in your heart, after your troubles and sojourn

02:06:18.802 --> 02:06:21.642
in the wilderness, said the townsman.

02:06:22.442 --> 02:06:28.902
To find yourself at length in a land where iniquity is surged out and punished in sight of rulers and

02:06:28.902 --> 02:06:36.462
people, as here in our goodly New England. Yonder woman, sir, you must know, was the wife of a

02:06:36.462 --> 02:06:43.002
certain learned man, English by birth, but who had long ago dwelt in Amsterdam. When some good

02:06:43.002 --> 02:06:49.702
time had gone, he was minded to cross over and cast in his lot with those of the Massachusetts.

02:06:50.302 --> 02:06:55.662
To this purpose he sent his wife before him, remaining himself to look after some necessary

02:06:55.662 --> 02:07:02.402
affairs. Mary, good sir, in some two years or less than the woman has been a dweller here in

02:07:02.402 --> 02:07:08.482
Boston, no tidings have come from this learned gentleman, Master Pryme. And this young wife,

02:07:08.662 --> 02:07:11.422
look you, being left to her own misguidance.

02:07:13.242 --> 02:07:21.782
Ah, ah, I conceive you, said stranger with a bitter smile. So, lured the man as you speak of,

02:07:22.062 --> 02:07:28.102
should have learned this too in his books. And who, by your favour, sir, may be the father of

02:07:28.102 --> 02:07:34.182
Yonder babe? It is some three or four months old, I should judge, which Master Pryme is holding in

02:07:34.182 --> 02:07:42.422
arms. Of a truth, friend, that mirror remains a riddle, and Daniel will shall expound it is yet

02:07:42.422 --> 02:07:49.722
a wanting, answered the townsman. Madam Esser absolutely refused to speak, and magistrates have

02:07:49.722 --> 02:07:55.462
laid their heads together in vain. Peradventure the guilty one stands looking on at this sad

02:07:55.462 --> 02:08:03.362
spectacle, unknown of men, and forgetting that God sees him. The learned man, absurd strange

02:08:03.362 --> 02:08:07.362
with another smile, should come himself to look into the mystery.

02:08:08.862 --> 02:08:13.502
It behelps him well if he be still in life, responded the townsman.

02:08:14.722 --> 02:08:21.082
Now, good sir, our master such as magistrates see, the thinking themselves that this woman is

02:08:21.082 --> 02:08:27.682
youthful and fair, and that was so strongly tempted to her fall, and that, moreover, as it most likely,

02:08:27.942 --> 02:08:32.782
her husband may be at the bottom of the sea, they have not been bold to put in force the

02:08:32.782 --> 02:08:39.262
extremity of our Raja's law against her. The penalty thereof is death. But in their great mercy

02:08:39.262 --> 02:08:44.822
and tenderness of heart, they have doomed Mr. Pryme to stand only a space of three hours on the

02:08:44.822 --> 02:08:50.722
platform of the pillory, and then, and thereafter, for the reminder of her natural life to a remark

02:08:50.722 --> 02:08:58.522
of shame upon her bosom. A wise sentence, remarked the stranger, gravely bowing his head.

02:08:59.242 --> 02:09:04.582
Thus she will be a living sermon against sin until the ignominious letter be engraved upon

02:09:04.582 --> 02:09:10.822
her tombstones. It irks me, nevertheless, that a partner of her iniquity should not at least

02:09:10.822 --> 02:09:17.642
stand uncareful by her side. But he will be known. He will be known. He will be known.

02:09:18.202 --> 02:09:23.222
He bowed courteously to the communicative townsman, and whispering a few words to his Indian

02:09:23.222 --> 02:09:29.602
attendant, they both made their way through the crowd. While they passed, Mr. Pryme had been

02:09:29.602 --> 02:09:35.562
standing on her pedestal, still with a fixed gaze towards the stranger, so fixed a gaze that,

02:09:35.562 --> 02:09:40.942
at moments of intense absorption, all other objects in the visible world seemed to vanish,

02:09:41.462 --> 02:09:47.242
leaving only him and her. Such an interview, perhaps, would have been more terrible than

02:09:47.242 --> 02:09:52.382
ever to meet him as she now did, with hot midday sun burning down upon her face,

02:09:52.382 --> 02:09:59.122
and lighting up its shame. With scarlet token of infamy on her breast, with sin-born infant in her

02:09:59.122 --> 02:10:04.662
arms, with a whole pupil drawn forth as to a festival, staring at features that should have

02:10:04.662 --> 02:10:10.822
been seen only in the quiet gleam of the fireside, in happy shadow of a home, or beneath a metrony

02:10:10.822 --> 02:10:17.022
veiled church. Dreadful as it was, she was conscious of a shelter in the presence of these thousand

02:10:17.022 --> 02:10:23.242
witnesses. It was better to stand thus, with so many between him and her, than to greet him face to

02:10:23.242 --> 02:10:30.322
face, they too alone. She fled for refuge, as it were, to the public exposure, and dreaded the

02:10:30.322 --> 02:10:35.582
moment when his protection should be withdrawn from her. Involving this thought, she scarcely

02:10:35.582 --> 02:10:41.382
heard a voice behind her until it had repeated her name more than once, in a loud and solemn tone,

02:10:41.382 --> 02:10:43.382
audible to the whole multitude.

02:10:45.502 --> 02:10:52.522
Hark! anon to me, Esther Pryne! said the voice. It was already be noticed that directly over the

02:10:52.522 --> 02:10:58.442
platform on which Esther Pryne stood was a kind of balcony, or open gallery, appended to the

02:10:58.442 --> 02:11:03.722
meeting-house. It was the place where his proclamations were on to be made, amidst an

02:11:03.722 --> 02:11:09.422
assemblage of the magistracy, with old ceremonial that attended such public observances in those

02:11:09.422 --> 02:11:15.802
days. Here, to witness the scene which we are describing, said Governor Bellingham himself,

02:11:15.942 --> 02:11:22.242
with four sergeants about his chair, bearing alberts, as a guard of honour. He wore a dark

02:11:22.242 --> 02:11:27.482
feather on his head, a border of embroidery on his cloak, and a black velvet tunic beneath.

02:11:28.362 --> 02:11:32.342
Gentleman advanced in ears, with a hard experience written in his wrinkles.

02:11:33.462 --> 02:11:38.402
He was not ill-fitted to be the head and representative of a community which owned

02:11:38.402 --> 02:11:43.962
its origins and progress, and its present state of development, not to the impulse of youth,

02:11:44.362 --> 02:11:49.442
but to the stern and tempered energy of manhood, and some sagacity of age,

02:11:50.342 --> 02:11:54.682
accomplishing so much, precisely because it imagined and hoped so little.

02:11:55.482 --> 02:12:01.002
The other eminent characters, by whom the chief ruler was surrounded, were distinguished by a

02:12:01.002 --> 02:12:07.442
dignity of men, belonging to a period when forms of authority were felt to possess sacredness of

02:12:07.442 --> 02:12:15.722
institutions. They were doubtless good men, just and sage, but, out of the old human family,

02:12:16.182 --> 02:12:20.562
it would not have been easy to select the same number of wise and virtuous persons,

02:12:20.882 --> 02:12:24.422
who should be less capable of sitting in judgement on an earring woman's heart,

02:12:25.022 --> 02:12:30.702
and disentangling its mesh of good and evil, than sages of richest aspects towards whom a

02:12:30.702 --> 02:12:37.782
prime now turned her face. She seemed conscious, indeed, that whatever sympathy she might expect

02:12:37.782 --> 02:12:43.462
lay in the large and unwarmer heart of the multitude, for, as she lifted her eyes towards

02:12:43.462 --> 02:12:49.662
the balcony, the unhappy woman grew pale and trembled. The voice which had called her

02:12:49.662 --> 02:12:55.762
attentions was that of the reverend and famous John Wilson, the eldest clergyman of Boston,

02:12:55.762 --> 02:12:59.202
a great scholar, like most of his contemporaries in the profession,

02:12:59.642 --> 02:13:04.802
and with all a man of kind and genial spirit. This last attribute, however,

02:13:05.222 --> 02:13:10.602
had been less carefully developed than his intellectual gifts, and was, in truth, rather

02:13:10.602 --> 02:13:17.082
a mere shame than self-congratulation with him. There he stood, with the border of greased locks

02:13:17.082 --> 02:13:22.602
beneath his skullcap, while his grey eyes, accustomed to the shaded light of his study,

02:13:22.602 --> 02:13:29.502
were winking, like those of Esther's infant, in the unadulterated sunshine. He looked like the

02:13:29.502 --> 02:13:35.682
darkly engraved portrait which is he prefixed to all volumes of sermons, and had no more right than

02:13:35.682 --> 02:13:41.462
one of those portraits would have to step forth, as he now did, and meddle with the question of

02:13:41.462 --> 02:13:47.762
human guilt, passion and anguish. Esther praying, said the clergyman,

02:13:48.402 --> 02:13:53.682
I have striven with my young brother here, under whose preaching of the word you have

02:13:53.682 --> 02:14:00.282
been privileged to sit. Here Mr. Wilson laid his hand on the shoulder of a pale young man beside him.

02:14:01.002 --> 02:14:07.382
I have sought, I say, to persuade this godly youth that he should deal with you, here in the

02:14:07.382 --> 02:14:13.362
faith of heaven, and before these wise and upright rulers, and in hearing of old people,

02:14:13.362 --> 02:14:19.862
as touching the violence and blackness of your sin. Knowing your natural temper better than I,

02:14:20.302 --> 02:14:24.762
he could better judge what arguments to use, whether of tenderness or terror,

02:14:25.182 --> 02:14:30.002
such as might prevail over your hardness and obstinacity, and so much that you should no

02:14:30.002 --> 02:14:36.202
longer hide the name of him who tempted you to this grievous fall. But he opposes to me,

02:14:36.802 --> 02:14:43.102
with the young man's over-softness, albeit wise beyond his years, that it were wronging the very

02:14:43.102 --> 02:14:48.222
nature of a human to force her to lay open her heart's secrets in such broad daylight,

02:14:48.462 --> 02:14:55.402
and in presence of so great a multitude. Truly, as I sought to convince him, the shame lay in the

02:14:55.402 --> 02:15:01.882
commission of the sin, and not in showing of it forth. What say you to it, once again, brother

02:15:01.882 --> 02:15:07.402
Dimmesdale? Must it be thou, or I, that shall deal with this poor sinner's soul?

02:15:08.422 --> 02:15:13.042
There was a murmur amongst the dignified and revered occupants of the balcony,

02:15:13.762 --> 02:15:19.382
and Governor Bellingham gave expression to its porport, speaking in an authoritative voice,

02:15:19.622 --> 02:15:23.742
although chambered in respect towards the youthful clergyman whom he addressed.

02:15:25.402 --> 02:15:31.862
Good master Dimmesdale, said he, the responsibility of this woman's soul lies greatly with you.

02:15:31.862 --> 02:15:36.862
It behoves you, therefore, to exhort her to repentance and to covession,

02:15:37.162 --> 02:15:39.322
as a proof and consequence thereof.

02:15:41.382 --> 02:15:46.682
The directness of this appeal drew the eyes of the whole crowd upon Reverend Mr. Dimmesdale,

02:15:47.242 --> 02:15:51.302
young clergyman who had come from one of the great English universities,

02:15:51.782 --> 02:15:57.262
bringing all the learning of the age into our wild forest land. His eloquence and religious

02:15:57.262 --> 02:16:02.762
fervour had already given the earnest of high eminence in this profession. He was a person of

02:16:02.762 --> 02:16:10.102
very striking aspect, with a white, lofty and impending brow, large brown melancholic eyes,

02:16:10.422 --> 02:16:15.742
and a mouth which, unless when he forcibly compressed it, was apt to be tremulous,

02:16:16.102 --> 02:16:20.222
expressing both nervous sensibility and the vast power of self-restraint.

02:16:21.702 --> 02:16:26.682
Notwithstanding his high native gifts and scholar-like attainments, there was an error

02:16:26.682 --> 02:16:33.182
to his young minister, an apprehensive, a startled, a half-frightened look, as of a being

02:16:33.182 --> 02:16:39.122
who felt himself quite astray, and at a loss in the pathway of human existence, and could only be

02:16:39.122 --> 02:16:46.842
at ease in some seclusion of his own. Therefore, so far as duties would permit, it rode in shadowy by

02:16:46.842 --> 02:16:54.042
path, and thus kept itself simple and childlike coming forth, when occasion was, with a freshness

02:16:54.042 --> 02:17:00.322
and fragrance and due purity of thought, which, as many people said, affected them like the speech

02:17:00.322 --> 02:17:07.382
of an angel. Such was the young man whom the Reverend Mr. Wilson and the Governor had introduced

02:17:07.382 --> 02:17:13.442
to openly to the public notice, bidding him speak, in the earring of all men, to that mystery of a

02:17:13.442 --> 02:17:19.742
woman's soul so sacred even in its pollution. The trying nature of his position drove the blood from

02:17:19.742 --> 02:17:22.322
his cheek, and made his lips tremulous.

02:17:24.282 --> 02:17:30.982
Speak to the woman, my brother, said Mr. Wilson. It is a moment to her soul, and therefore,

02:17:31.322 --> 02:17:37.042
as the worshipful Governor says, moments to thin own, in whose charge hers is,

02:17:38.262 --> 02:17:44.382
exalted to confess the truth. The Reverend Mr. Dimmesdale bent his head in silent prayer,

02:17:44.662 --> 02:17:47.062
as it seemed, and then came forward.

02:17:50.242 --> 02:17:56.482
Esther Pryne, said he, leaning over the balcony, and looking down steadfastly into her eyes.

02:17:57.362 --> 02:18:02.922
Thou hearest what this good man says, and seest the accountability under which I labor.

02:18:03.662 --> 02:18:10.462
If thou feelest it to be for thy soul's peace, and that thy earthly punishment will thereby

02:18:10.462 --> 02:18:16.722
be made more effectual to salvation, I charge thee to speak out the name of thy fellow sinner

02:18:16.722 --> 02:18:23.402
and fellow sufferer. Be not silent from any mistaken pity and tenderness for him. For,

02:18:23.782 --> 02:18:29.982
believe me, Esther, though he were to step down from a high place, and stand there beside thee,

02:18:30.202 --> 02:18:36.462
on thy pedestal of shame, yet better were it so than to hide the guilty heart through life.

02:18:37.022 --> 02:18:42.882
What could thou silence do for him? Except tempt him, yeah, compel him, as it were,

02:18:42.882 --> 02:18:50.902
to add hypocrisy to sin. Heaven hath granted thee an open ignominy, that thereby thou mayest

02:18:50.902 --> 02:18:57.842
work out an open triumph over the evil within thee and sorrow without. Take heed how thou

02:18:57.842 --> 02:19:05.402
deniest to him, who, perchance, hath not courage to grasp it for himself, the bitter but wholesome

02:19:05.402 --> 02:19:11.962
cup that is now presented to thy lips. The young pastor's voice was tremulous sweet,

02:19:11.962 --> 02:19:17.442
rich, deep and broken. The feeling that it so evidently manifested,

02:19:17.842 --> 02:19:22.822
rather than the direct purport of the words, caused it to vibrate within all hearts,

02:19:23.122 --> 02:19:29.102
and brought listeners into one accord of sympathy. Even the poor baby at Esther's bosom was affected

02:19:29.102 --> 02:19:34.542
by the same influence, for it directed easy through the vacant gaze towards Mr. Dimmesdale,

02:19:34.962 --> 02:19:41.362
and held up its little arms with a half-pleased, half-plaintive murmur. So powerful seemed the

02:19:41.362 --> 02:19:46.842
appeal that people could not believe but that Esther Pryne would speak out a guilty name,

02:19:46.882 --> 02:19:52.142
or else that the guilty one himself, in whatever high or lowly place he stood,

02:19:52.902 --> 02:19:59.222
would be drawn forth by an inward and inevitable necessity and compelled to ascend the scaffold.

02:20:00.602 --> 02:20:01.982
Esther shook her head.

02:20:03.962 --> 02:20:10.142
Woman, transgress not beyond the limits of Heaven's mercy, cried Reverend Mr. Wilson,

02:20:10.142 --> 02:20:16.722
more harshly than before. That little baby has been gifted with a voice to second and

02:20:16.722 --> 02:20:22.602
confirm the counsel which thou hast heard. Speak out a name that, and thy repentance,

02:20:23.082 --> 02:20:25.942
may avail to take the scarlet letter off thy breast.

02:20:27.502 --> 02:20:34.442
Never, replied Esther Pryne, looking, not at Mr. Wilson, but into the deep and troubled eyes

02:20:34.442 --> 02:20:40.302
of the younger clergyman. It is too deeply branded. He cannot take it off,

02:20:41.042 --> 02:20:43.942
and would that I might endure his agony as well as mine.

02:20:46.282 --> 02:20:52.842
Speak, woman, said another voice, coolly and sternly, proceeding from the crowd about the

02:20:52.842 --> 02:21:01.502
scaffold. Speak, and give a child a father. I will not speak, answered Esther, turning pale

02:21:02.102 --> 02:21:08.582
but responding to this voice, which she too surely recognized. And my child must seek a Heavenly

02:21:08.582 --> 02:21:16.842
Father. She shall never know an earthly one. She will not speak, murmured Mr. Dimmesdale, who,

02:21:17.182 --> 02:21:22.202
leaning over the balcony with his hand upon his heart, had waited the result of his appeal.

02:21:23.062 --> 02:21:29.362
He now drew back with a long respiration, round to a strength and generosity of a woman's heart.

02:21:29.362 --> 02:21:30.862
She will not speak.

02:21:32.202 --> 02:21:35.682
Discerning the impracticable state of the poor sculprit's mind,

02:21:36.102 --> 02:21:39.962
the elder clergyman, who had carefully prepared himself for the occasion,

02:21:40.622 --> 02:21:44.362
addressed to the multitude the discursive scene in all its branches,

02:21:44.862 --> 02:21:51.082
but with continual reference to the ignominious letter. So forcibly did he dwell upon this symbol,

02:21:51.482 --> 02:21:55.702
for the hour or more during which his periods were rolling over the people's heads,

02:21:55.702 --> 02:21:58.942
that it assumed new cherubs in their imagination,

02:21:59.342 --> 02:22:03.562
and seemed to derive its scarlet hue from the flames of the infernal pit.

02:22:04.502 --> 02:22:09.742
Esther Prine, meanwhile, kept her place upon the pedestal of shame, with glazed eyes,

02:22:10.062 --> 02:22:15.142
and an air of weary indifference. She had borne that morning all that nature could endure,

02:22:15.642 --> 02:22:21.022
and as her temperament was not of the order that escapes from too intense suffering by a swoon,

02:22:21.022 --> 02:22:25.882
her spirit could only shelter itself beneath a stony crust of incessibility,

02:22:26.462 --> 02:22:30.662
while the faculties of animal life remained entire. In this state,

02:22:31.042 --> 02:22:37.222
the voice of the preacher thundered remorselessly, but unavailingly, upon her ears. The infant,

02:22:37.362 --> 02:22:42.102
during the later portion of her ordeal, pursed the air with its wailing and screams.

02:22:42.742 --> 02:22:47.402
She strove to hush it mechanically, but seemed scarcely to sympathize with its trouble.

02:22:48.122 --> 02:22:51.882
With the same hard meaner, she was led back to prison,

02:22:52.142 --> 02:22:57.642
and vanished from the public gaze within its air-clamped portal. It was whispered by those

02:22:57.642 --> 02:23:04.082
who peered after her that Scarlet Lara threw a lurid gleam along the dark passageway of the interior.

02:23:43.021 --> 02:23:47.961
After a return to the prison, a surfer was found to be in a state of nervous excitement

02:23:47.961 --> 02:23:53.621
that demanded constant watchfulness, lest she should perpetrate violence on herself

02:23:53.621 --> 02:23:57.001
or do some half-francid mischief to the poor babe.

02:23:57.921 --> 02:24:03.061
As night approached, it proving impossible to quell her insubordination by rebuke of

02:24:03.061 --> 02:24:08.561
threats of punishment, Master Brackett, the jailer, thought fit to introduce a physician.

02:24:09.761 --> 02:24:14.301
He described him as a man of skill in all Christian modes of physical science,

02:24:14.301 --> 02:24:20.621
and likewise familiar with whatever the savage people could teach in respect to medicinal herbs

02:24:20.621 --> 02:24:26.701
and roots that grew in the forest. To say the truth, there was much need of professional

02:24:26.701 --> 02:24:33.401
assistance, not merely for Esther herself, but still more urgently for the child, who,

02:24:33.681 --> 02:24:39.101
drawing his sustenance from the maternal bosom, seemed to have drunk in it with all the turmoil,

02:24:39.101 --> 02:24:43.021
the anguish and despair which pervaded the mother's system.

02:24:43.841 --> 02:24:48.021
It now breathed in convulsions of pain, and was a forcible type,

02:24:48.321 --> 02:24:53.321
in its little frame of the moral agony which Esther Pryne had borne throughout the day.

02:24:54.641 --> 02:24:59.001
Closely following the jailer into the dismal apartment, appeared that individual,

02:24:59.461 --> 02:25:04.281
a singular aspect whose presence in the crowd had been of such steep interest to the wearer

02:25:04.281 --> 02:25:09.681
of the scarlet letter. He was lodged in the prison, not as suspected of any offence,

02:25:10.401 --> 02:25:15.341
but as the most convenient and suitable mode of disposing of him, until the magistrate

02:25:15.341 --> 02:25:20.981
should have conferred with Indian seshamores respecting his ransom. His name was announced

02:25:20.981 --> 02:25:27.401
as Roger Schillingworth. The jailer, after hushering him into the room, remained a moment,

02:25:27.941 --> 02:25:33.721
marveling at comparative quiet that followed his entrance, for Esther Pryne had immediately

02:25:33.721 --> 02:25:37.721
become as still as death, although the child continued to moan.

02:25:38.621 --> 02:25:43.621
''Pry thee, friend, leave me alone with my patients,'' said the practitioner.

02:25:44.561 --> 02:25:50.501
''Trust me, good jailer, you shall briefly have peace in your house, and, I promise you,

02:25:50.801 --> 02:25:57.481
Mistress Pryne shall be more amiable to just authority than you may have found her here before.''

02:25:59.501 --> 02:26:04.661
''Nay, if your horseship can accomplish that,'' answered Master Brackett,

02:26:05.141 --> 02:26:12.021
''I shall own you for a man of skill indeed. Fairly, do man hath been like a possessed one,

02:26:12.261 --> 02:26:17.081
and there lacks little that I should take in hand to drive Satan out of her with stripes.''

02:26:18.501 --> 02:26:23.001
The stranger that entered the room had a characteristic quietitude of the profession

02:26:23.001 --> 02:26:28.921
to which he announced himself as belonging. Nor did this demeanor change when the withdrawal

02:26:28.921 --> 02:26:34.721
of the prison keeper left him face to face with the woman, whose observed notice of him in the

02:26:34.721 --> 02:26:41.821
crowd had intimated so close a relation between himself and her. His first care was given to the

02:26:41.821 --> 02:26:48.981
child, whose cries, indeed, as she lay reading on the trundled bed, made it a peremptory necessity

02:26:48.981 --> 02:26:54.921
to postpone all other business to the task of suiting her. He examined the infant carefully,

02:26:55.321 --> 02:27:00.521
and then proceeded to unclasp a leathern case, which he took from the niece's dress.

02:27:01.421 --> 02:27:06.801
It appeared to contain medical preparations, one of which he mingled with a cup of water.

02:27:08.201 --> 02:27:15.381
''My old studies in alchemy,'' absurd he, ''and my sojourn, for above a year past,

02:27:15.381 --> 02:27:20.761
among a pupil well versed in the kindly properties of simples, have made a better

02:27:20.761 --> 02:27:27.241
physician of me than many that claimed medical degree. Here, woman, the child is yours,

02:27:27.521 --> 02:27:34.521
she is none of mine. Neither will she recognize my voice or aspect as a father's. Administer this

02:27:34.521 --> 02:27:42.501
drug, therefore, with thine own hand.'' As to repel the offered medicine, at the same time,

02:27:42.501 --> 02:27:45.661
he gave me to strongly mark the prehension into his face.

02:27:46.401 --> 02:27:50.861
''Wouldst thou avenge thyself on the innocent babe?'' whispered she.

02:27:52.281 --> 02:27:56.981
''Foolish woman,'' responded the physician, half coldly, half soothingly.

02:27:58.021 --> 02:28:03.821
''What should hail me to harm this misbegotten and miserable babe? The medicine is potent for good,

02:28:04.401 --> 02:28:10.201
and were it my child, yeah, my own, as well as thine, I could do no better for it.''

02:28:11.441 --> 02:28:17.661
As she still hesitated, being in fact in so reasonable a state of mind, he took the infant

02:28:17.661 --> 02:28:24.441
in his arms and himself administered the drug. It soon proved his efficacy, and redeemed Litch's

02:28:24.441 --> 02:28:31.841
pledge. The mounted little patient subsided, its convulsive tossing gradually ceased, and in a few

02:28:31.841 --> 02:28:38.121
moments, as is the custom of young children after relief from pain, it sank into a profound and dewy

02:28:38.121 --> 02:28:44.741
slumber. The physician, as he had a fair right to be turned, next bestowed his attention on the

02:28:44.741 --> 02:28:52.101
mother. With calm and intense scrutiny, he felt her pulse, looked into her eyes, a gaze that made

02:28:52.101 --> 02:28:59.261
her heart shrink and shudder, because so familiar, and yet so strange and cold, and, finally,

02:28:59.661 --> 02:29:03.681
satisfied with his investigation, proceeded to mingle another drug.

02:29:05.461 --> 02:29:11.881
''I know not left nor in the panthe,'' remarked he, ''but I have learned many new secrets in the

02:29:11.881 --> 02:29:18.361
wilderness, and here is one of them, a recipe that an Indian taught me, in the quiet of some lessons

02:29:18.361 --> 02:29:25.381
of my own, that was all asparacelsus. Drink it. It may be less soothing than a sinless conscience,

02:29:25.681 --> 02:29:32.561
that I cannot give thee, but it will come to swell and heaving of thy passion, like oil thrown on the

02:29:32.561 --> 02:29:40.781
tempestuous sea.'' He presented the cup to Esther, who received it with a slow, earnest look into

02:29:40.781 --> 02:29:46.921
his face, not precisely a look of fear, yet full of doubt and questioning as to what his purpose

02:29:46.921 --> 02:29:55.801
might be. She looked also at her slumbering child. ''I have thought of death,'' said she,

02:29:55.801 --> 02:29:59.861
''I have wished for it, would even have prayed for it,

02:30:00.081 --> 02:30:06.381
retweeted such as I should pray for anything. Yet, if death be in this cup,

02:30:06.781 --> 02:30:13.541
I bid thee think again, here thy behold is me coiffed. See, it is even now at my lips.''

02:30:14.981 --> 02:30:19.401
''Drink, then,'' replied he, still with the same cool composure.

02:30:20.381 --> 02:30:26.301
''Thus thou know me so little, Esther Prine, or my purposes won't be so shallow.

02:30:27.001 --> 02:30:32.141
Even if I imagine a scheme of vengeance, what could I do better for my object than to let thy

02:30:32.141 --> 02:30:39.441
live, than to give thy medicines against all harm and peril of life, so that this burning shame may

02:30:39.441 --> 02:30:46.461
still blaze upon thy bosom?'' As he spoke, he laid his long forefinger on scarlet leather,

02:30:46.461 --> 02:30:53.521
which her width seemed scorched into Esther's breast, as if it had been red hot. He noticed

02:30:53.521 --> 02:31:00.301
that her involuntarily gestured and smiled. ''Leave, therefore, and bear about thy doom with thee,

02:31:00.521 --> 02:31:06.061
in the eyes of men and women, in the eyes of him whom thou didst call thy husband,

02:31:06.541 --> 02:31:12.201
in the eyes of yonder child, and, that thou mayest live, take off this drug.''

02:31:13.981 --> 02:31:20.801
Without further exhalation or delay, Esther Prine drained the cup, and, at notion of demand of skill,

02:31:21.381 --> 02:31:26.781
seated herself on the bed, where the child was sleeping, while he drew the only chair

02:31:26.781 --> 02:31:33.061
which the room afforded, and took his own seat beside her. She could not but tremble at these

02:31:33.061 --> 02:31:40.941
preparations, for she felt that, having now done all that humanity or principle, or, if so it were,

02:31:40.941 --> 02:31:45.741
a refined cruelty impaled him to do for the life of physical suffering,

02:31:46.321 --> 02:31:51.481
he was next to treat with her as the man whom she had most deeply and irreparably injured.

02:31:53.601 --> 02:32:02.301
''Hester,'' said he, ''I ask not wherefore, nor how, thou hast fallen into the pits, or, say,

02:32:02.561 --> 02:32:09.481
rather, thou hast ascended to the pedestal of infamy on which I found thee. The reason is not

02:32:09.481 --> 02:32:16.781
hard to seek. It was my folly and thy weakness. I, a man of thought, the bookwarden of great

02:32:16.781 --> 02:32:23.081
labouries, a man already in decay, having given my best years to feed the hungry dream of knowledge,

02:32:23.861 --> 02:32:30.241
what had I to do with youth and beauty like thine own? Mishappen from my birth hour. How

02:32:30.241 --> 02:32:36.821
could I delude myself with the idea that intellectual gifts might reveal physical deformity in a young

02:32:36.821 --> 02:32:45.261
girl's fantasy? Men call me wise. If sages were ever wise in their own behove, I might have foreseen

02:32:45.261 --> 02:32:51.661
all this. I might have known that, as I came out of the vast and dismal forest and entered this

02:32:51.661 --> 02:32:56.901
settlement of Christian men, the very first object to meet my eyes would be thyself,

02:32:57.101 --> 02:33:06.801
Hester Pryne, standing up, a statue of ignominy before the people. Nay, from the moment when he

02:33:06.801 --> 02:33:13.181
gathered, a married pair, I might have beheld the bell-fire of that scarlet letter blazing at

02:33:13.181 --> 02:33:21.841
the end of our path. Thou knowest, said Hester, for, depressed as she was, she could not endure

02:33:21.841 --> 02:33:36.781
this last quiet step at the token of her shame. Thou knowest that I was frank with thee. I felt

02:33:36.781 --> 02:33:43.441
but, up to that epoch of my life, I had lived in vain. The world had been so cheerless.

02:33:43.981 --> 02:33:49.821
My heart was a habitation large enough for many guests, but lonely and chill, and without the

02:33:49.821 --> 02:33:58.241
household fire. I longed to kindle one. It seemed not so wild a dream, old as I was, and sombre as

02:33:58.241 --> 02:34:05.721
I was, and mishappen as I was. That simple bliss, which is scattered far and wide, for all mankind

02:34:05.721 --> 02:34:13.961
to gather up, might yet be mine. And so, Hester, I drew thee into my heart, into its innermost

02:34:13.961 --> 02:34:18.801
chamber, and thought to warm thee by the warmth which thy presence made there.

02:34:20.301 --> 02:34:30.601
I have greatly wronged thee, murmured Hester. We have wronged each other, answered he. Mine was

02:34:30.601 --> 02:34:36.221
wrong, when I betrayed thy putting youth into a false and unnatural relation with my decay.

02:34:36.941 --> 02:34:42.261
Therefore, as a man who has not thought and philosophied in vain, I seek no vengeance,

02:34:42.761 --> 02:34:48.561
plot no evil against thee. Between thee and me, the scale hangs fairly balanced.

02:34:49.181 --> 02:34:54.681
But, Hester, the man leaves who has wronged us both. Who is he?

02:34:55.761 --> 02:35:03.681
Ask me not, replied Hester Pryne, looking firmly into his face. That thou shalt never know.

02:35:05.461 --> 02:35:11.821
Never, sayest thou? Rejoin he with a smile of dark and self-relying intelligence.

02:35:12.641 --> 02:35:19.361
Never know him. Believe me, Hester, there are few things, whether in the outward world, or,

02:35:19.361 --> 02:35:25.141
to a certain depth, in the invisible sphere of thought, few things hidden from the man

02:35:25.141 --> 02:35:32.061
who devotes himself earnestly and unreservedly to the solution of a mystery. Thou mayest cover

02:35:32.061 --> 02:35:39.381
up thy secret from the Pryme Altitude. Thou mayest conceal it, too, from ministers and magistrates,

02:35:39.921 --> 02:35:44.741
even as thou didst this day, when they sought to wrench the name out of thy heart,

02:35:44.741 --> 02:35:51.461
and give thee a partner on thy pedestal. But, as for me, I come to the inquest with other

02:35:51.461 --> 02:35:56.701
senses than they possess. I shall seek this man, as I have thought through sin books,

02:35:57.061 --> 02:36:02.401
as I have sought goals in alchemy. There is a sympathy that will make me conscious of him.

02:36:02.861 --> 02:36:09.781
I shall see him tremble. I shall feel myself shudder suddenly and unwares. Sooner or later,

02:36:09.781 --> 02:36:16.821
he must needs be mine. The eyes of the wrinkled scholar glowed so intensely upon her

02:36:16.821 --> 02:36:20.441
that, as to Pryne, clasped her hand over her heart,

02:36:20.781 --> 02:36:26.861
dreading lest he should read secret there at once. Thou wilt not reveal his name.

02:36:27.761 --> 02:36:34.761
Not lest he is mine, resumed he, with a look of confidence, as if destiny were at one with him.

02:36:35.341 --> 02:36:39.601
He bears no layer of infamy wrought into his garment, as thou dost,

02:36:40.041 --> 02:36:46.281
but I shall read it on his heart. Yet fear not for him. Think not that I shall interfere

02:36:46.281 --> 02:36:52.621
with heaven's own method of retribution, or, to my own loss, betray him to the grip of human love.

02:36:53.701 --> 02:36:59.921
Neither do thou imagine that I shall contrive hard against his life, no, nor against his fame,

02:36:59.921 --> 02:37:07.361
if, as I judge, he be a man of fair repute. Let him live. Let him hide himself in outward

02:37:07.361 --> 02:37:11.281
honour, if he may. Not lest he shall be mine.

02:37:12.681 --> 02:37:19.841
Thy acts are like mercy, said Esther, bewildered and appalled, but thy words interpret thee as a

02:37:19.841 --> 02:37:28.861
terror. One thing. Thou that was my life, I wouldn't join upon thee, continued the scholar.

02:37:29.501 --> 02:37:36.821
Thou hast kept secret of thy paramour. Keep likewise mine. There are none in this land that

02:37:36.821 --> 02:37:43.741
know me. Bring not to any human soul that thou didst ever call me husband. Here, on this wild

02:37:43.741 --> 02:37:50.541
outskirt of the earth, I shall pitch my tent. For, elsewhere a wanderer and isolated from human

02:37:50.541 --> 02:37:57.281
interests, I find here a woman, a man, a child, amongst whom and myself there exists the closest

02:37:57.281 --> 02:38:04.841
ligaments, no matter whether of love or hate, no matter whether of right or wrong. Thou and thine,

02:38:05.321 --> 02:38:12.121
Esther Pryne, belong to me. My home is where thou art and where he is. But betray me not.

02:38:14.401 --> 02:38:21.281
Wherefore dost thou desire it? inquired Esther, shrinking, she hardly knew why, from the secret

02:38:21.281 --> 02:38:26.521
bound. Why not denounce thyself openly and cast me off at once?

02:38:28.201 --> 02:38:33.621
It may be, he replied, because I will not encounter the dishonour that

02:38:34.221 --> 02:38:41.061
besmirches the husband of a faithless woman. It may be for other reasons. Enough. It is my purpose

02:38:41.061 --> 02:38:46.901
to live and die unknown. Let therefore thy husband be to the world as one already dead,

02:38:46.901 --> 02:38:53.841
and of whom no tidings shall ever come. Recognise me not by word, by sign, by look.

02:38:54.601 --> 02:39:00.761
Breed not the secret above all to the man thou houghtest of. Should thou fail me in this,

02:39:01.081 --> 02:39:07.401
beware. His fame, his position, his life will be in my hands. Beware.

02:39:08.161 --> 02:39:18.101
I'll keep thy secret, and I have his, said Esther, swear it, rejoin he, and she took to oath.

02:39:19.481 --> 02:39:25.601
And now, Mistress Pryne, said old Roger Chillingworth, as he was hereafter to be

02:39:25.601 --> 02:39:33.361
named, I leave thee alone, alone with thy infant and scarlet letter. Who is it, Esther,

02:39:33.361 --> 02:39:37.361
doth thou sentence by indeed to wear the token in thy sleep?

02:39:38.121 --> 02:39:41.181
Art thou not afraid of nightmares and hideous dreams?

02:39:42.681 --> 02:39:49.021
Why dost thou smile so at me? inquired Esther, troubled at the expression of his eyes.

02:39:50.021 --> 02:39:54.441
Art thou like the black man that hunts the forest round about us,

02:39:54.961 --> 02:39:58.501
as thou entice me into a bond that will prove the ruin of my soul?

02:39:59.541 --> 02:40:05.521
Not thy soul, he answered with another smile. No, not thine.

02:40:18.067 --> 02:40:35.267
5. HESTER AT HER NEEDLE

02:40:35.267 --> 02:40:38.627
Hester Prynne's term of confinement was now at an end.

02:40:39.607 --> 02:40:44.367
The prison door was thrown open, and she came forth into the sunshine, which, falling on

02:40:44.367 --> 02:40:49.947
all alike, seemed to her sick and morbid heart, as if meant for no other purpose than to reveal

02:40:49.947 --> 02:40:52.227
the scarlet letter on her breast.

02:40:53.187 --> 02:40:57.527
Perhaps there was a more real torture in her first unattended footsteps from the threshold

02:40:57.527 --> 02:41:02.267
of the prison than even in the procession and spectacle that had been described, where

02:41:02.267 --> 02:41:07.227
she was made the common infamy at which all mankind was summoned to point its finger.

02:41:07.947 --> 02:41:13.167
Then she was supported by an unnatural tension of the nerves, and by all the combative energy

02:41:13.167 --> 02:41:18.227
of her character which enabled her to convert the scene into a kind of lurid triumph, it

02:41:18.227 --> 02:41:24.607
was moreover a separate and insulated event, to occur but once in her lifetime, and to

02:41:24.607 --> 02:41:28.807
meet which, therefore reckless of economy, she might call up the vital strength that

02:41:28.807 --> 02:41:31.847
she would have sufficed for many quiet years.

02:41:33.167 --> 02:41:38.567
The very law that condemned her, a giant of stern features but with vigor to support as

02:41:38.567 --> 02:41:46.687
in his iron arm, had held her up through the terrible ordeal of her ignominy, but now, with

02:41:46.687 --> 02:41:51.767
the unattended walk from her prison door, became the daily custom, that she must either

02:41:51.767 --> 02:41:57.147
sustain and carry it forward by the ordinary resources of her nature or sink beneath it.

02:41:57.807 --> 02:42:01.167
She could no longer borrow from the future to help her through the present grief.

02:42:01.787 --> 02:42:06.947
Tomorrow would bring its own trial with it, so would the next day, so would the next,

02:42:06.947 --> 02:42:09.247
each its own trial.

02:42:09.907 --> 02:42:16.087
And yet, the very same that was now so unutterably grievous to be born, the days of the far-off

02:42:16.087 --> 02:42:21.527
future would toil onward, still with the same burden for her to take up and bear along with

02:42:21.527 --> 02:42:27.127
her, but never to fling down, for the accumulating days and added years would pile up their

02:42:27.127 --> 02:42:29.527
misery upon the heap of shame.

02:42:30.367 --> 02:42:35.227
Without them all, giving up her individuality, she would become the general symbol at which

02:42:35.227 --> 02:42:40.047
the preacher and the moralist might point, and in which they might vivify and embody

02:42:40.047 --> 02:42:43.427
their images of a woman's frailty and sinful passion.

02:42:44.207 --> 02:42:48.367
Thus, the young and pure would be taught to look at her with the scarlet letter flaming

02:42:48.367 --> 02:42:54.767
on her breast, at her, the child of the honorable parents, at her, the mother of the babe that

02:42:54.767 --> 02:43:00.667
would hereafter be a woman, at her, who had once been innocent as the figure, the body,

02:43:00.667 --> 02:43:02.647
the reality of sin.

02:43:03.167 --> 02:43:09.147
And over her grave, the infamy at which she must carry thither would be her only monument.

02:43:09.727 --> 02:43:14.127
It may seem marvelous that, with the world before her, kept by no restrictive clause

02:43:14.127 --> 02:43:19.187
or her condemnation within the limits of the Puritan settlement, so remote and so obscure,

02:43:19.707 --> 02:43:24.387
free to return to her birthplace or to any other European land, and there hide her character

02:43:24.387 --> 02:43:29.507
and identity under a new exterior as completely as if emerging into another state of being,

02:43:29.507 --> 02:43:34.607
and having also the passage of the dark, inscrutable forest open to her, where the

02:43:34.607 --> 02:43:39.527
wildness of her nature might assimilate itself with the people's customs in life or alien

02:43:39.527 --> 02:43:41.267
from the law that had condemned her.

02:43:41.747 --> 02:43:46.347
It may seem marvelous that this woman should still call that place her home, where, and

02:43:46.347 --> 02:43:49.287
where only, she must needs to be the type of shame.

02:43:50.227 --> 02:43:56.427
But there is a fatality, a feeling so irresistible and inevitable, that it has the force of doom,

02:43:56.427 --> 02:44:03.067
which almost invariably compels human beings to linger around and haunt, ghost-like, the spot

02:44:03.067 --> 02:44:07.787
where some great and marked event has given the color to her lifetime, and still the more

02:44:07.787 --> 02:44:14.087
irresistibly, the darker the tinge that saddens it. Her sin, her ignominy, were the roots which

02:44:14.087 --> 02:44:20.027
she had struck into the soil. It was as if new birth, with stronger assimilations than the first,

02:44:20.367 --> 02:44:25.447
had converted the forest land still so uncongenial to every other pilgrim and wanderer,

02:44:25.447 --> 02:44:32.247
into Hester Prynne's wild and dreary but lifelong home. All other scenes of earth, even that village

02:44:32.247 --> 02:44:37.347
of rural England, where happy infancy and stainless maidenhood seemed yet to be her

02:44:37.347 --> 02:44:42.847
and her mother's keeping, like garments put off long ago, were foreign to her in comparison.

02:44:43.307 --> 02:44:48.027
The chain that bound her here was made of iron links and galling in her inmost soul,

02:44:48.147 --> 02:44:54.227
but could never be broken. It might be, too, doubtless it was so, although she hid the

02:44:54.227 --> 02:44:58.727
secret from herself and grew pale whenever it struggled out of her heart, like a serpent

02:44:58.727 --> 02:45:03.687
from its hole. It might be that another feeling kept her within the scene and pathway that had

02:45:03.687 --> 02:45:09.387
been so fatal. There dwelt, there trod the feet of one with whom she deemed herself connected

02:45:09.387 --> 02:45:14.707
in a union that, unrecognized on earth, would bring them together before the bar of final judgment,

02:45:15.247 --> 02:45:20.167
and make that their marriage altar for a joint futurity of endless retribution.

02:45:21.287 --> 02:45:27.767
Over and over again the tempester of souls had thrust this idea upon Hester's contemplation,

02:45:28.227 --> 02:45:33.927
and laughed at the passionate and desperate joy at which she seized and then strove to cast it from

02:45:33.927 --> 02:45:40.527
her. She barely looked the idea in the face and hastened to bar it from its dungeon. What she

02:45:40.527 --> 02:45:50.147
compelled herself to believe, what, finally, she reasoned upon as her motive to continuing a

02:45:50.147 --> 02:45:56.287
delusion. Here, she said to herself, had been the scene of her guilt, and here should be the

02:45:56.287 --> 02:46:02.627
scene of her earthly punishment. And so, perchance, the torture of her daily shame would at length

02:46:02.627 --> 02:46:09.707
purge her soul and work out another purity than that which she had lost, more saint-like because

02:46:09.707 --> 02:46:16.887
the result of martyrdom. Hester Prynne, therefore, did not flee. On the outskirts of town, within the

02:46:16.887 --> 02:46:22.907
peninsula, but not in close vicinity to any other habitation, there was a small thatched cottage.

02:46:23.607 --> 02:46:28.347
It had been built by an earlier settler and abandoned because the soil about it was too

02:46:28.347 --> 02:46:33.747
sterile for cultivation. While its comparative remoteness put it out of the sphere of social

02:46:33.747 --> 02:46:38.967
activity which already marked the habits of the immigrants, it stood on the shore looking across

02:46:38.967 --> 02:46:45.367
the basin of the sea at the forest-covered hills toward the west. A clump of scrubby trees such as

02:46:45.367 --> 02:46:50.827
grew on the peninsula did not so much conceal the cottage from view, as seemed to denote that there

02:46:50.827 --> 02:46:57.727
was some object which would fain have been, or at least ought to be, concealed. In this little

02:46:57.727 --> 02:47:03.067
lonesome dwelling, with some slender means that she possessed, and by the license of the magistrates

02:47:03.067 --> 02:47:09.227
who still kept an inquisitorial watch over her, Hester established herself with her infant child.

02:47:10.067 --> 02:47:14.067
A mystic's shadow on the suspicion immediately attached itself to the spot.

02:47:14.067 --> 02:47:19.087
Children, too young to comprehend wherefore this woman should be shut out from the sphere of human

02:47:19.087 --> 02:47:24.267
charities, would creep nigh enough to behold her plying her needle at the cottage window,

02:47:24.567 --> 02:47:29.567
or standing in the doorway, or laboring in her little garden, or coming forth along the pathway

02:47:29.567 --> 02:47:34.427
that led townward, and discerning that scarlet letter on her breast would scamper off with a

02:47:34.427 --> 02:47:41.547
strange, contagious fear. Loneliness was Hester's situation, and without a friend on earth who dared

02:47:41.547 --> 02:47:48.087
to show himself, she, however, incurred even no risk of want. She possessed an art that sufficed

02:47:48.087 --> 02:47:54.247
even in a land that afforded comparatively little scope for its exercise, to supply food for her

02:47:54.247 --> 02:48:01.367
thriving infant and herself. It was the art, then as now, almost the only one within a woman's grasp,

02:48:01.727 --> 02:48:08.707
of needlework. She bore on her breast, in the curiously embroidered letter, a specimen of her

02:48:08.707 --> 02:48:14.227
delicate and imaginative skill, of which the dames of a court might gladly have availed themselves,

02:48:14.527 --> 02:48:20.527
to add the richer and more spiritual adornment of human ingenuity to their fabrics of silk and gold.

02:48:21.447 --> 02:48:26.127
Here, indeed, in the sable simplicity that generally characterized the puritanic modes of

02:48:26.127 --> 02:48:30.547
dress, there might be an infrequent call for the finer productions of her handiwork.

02:48:30.907 --> 02:48:35.547
Yet the taste of the age, demanding whatever was elaborate in compositions of this kind,

02:48:35.547 --> 02:48:41.647
did not fail to extend its influence over our stern progenitors, who had cast behind them so

02:48:41.647 --> 02:48:47.127
many fashions which it might seem harder to dispense with. Public ceremonies, such as the

02:48:47.127 --> 02:48:52.527
ordinations, the installation of magistrates, and all that could give magistrate to the forms in

02:48:52.527 --> 02:48:58.167
which a new government manifested itself to the people, were as a matter of policy marked by a

02:48:58.167 --> 02:49:06.047
and well-conducted ceremonial ensemble, but yet a studied magnificence. Deep ruffs, painfully

02:49:06.047 --> 02:49:11.387
wrought bands, and gorgeously embroidered gloves were all deemed necessary to the official state

02:49:11.387 --> 02:49:17.807
of men, assuming the reins of power, and were readily allowed to individuals dignified by rank

02:49:17.807 --> 02:49:24.647
or wealth, even while sumptuary laws forbade these and similar extravagances to the plebeian order.

02:49:24.647 --> 02:49:30.787
In the array of funerals, too, whether for the apparel of the dead body, or to typify by manifold

02:49:30.787 --> 02:49:36.947
emblematic devices of sable cloth and snowy lawn, the sorrow of the survivors, there was a frequent

02:49:36.947 --> 02:49:43.207
and characteristic demand for such labor as Hester Primm could supply. Baby linen, for babies,

02:49:43.727 --> 02:49:49.227
then wore robes of state, afforded still another possibility of toil and emolument.

02:49:49.927 --> 02:49:55.187
By degrees, nor very slowly, her handiwork became what would now be termed the fashion.

02:49:55.787 --> 02:50:01.507
Whether from commiseration for women of so miserable a destiny, or from the morbid curiosity that gives

02:50:01.507 --> 02:50:07.447
a fictitious value even to common or worthless things, or by whatever other intangible circumstances

02:50:07.447 --> 02:50:13.447
was then, as now sufficient to bestow on some persons what others might seek in vain, or,

02:50:13.447 --> 02:50:18.687
because Hester really filled a gap which must otherwise have remained vacant, it is certain

02:50:18.687 --> 02:50:24.947
that she had ready and fairly requited employment for many hours as she saw fit to occupy with her

02:50:24.947 --> 02:50:31.747
needle. Vanity, it may be, chose to mortify itself by putting on for ceremonials of pomp and state

02:50:31.747 --> 02:50:37.467
the garments that had been wrought by her sinful hands. Her needlework was seen on the ruff of the

02:50:37.467 --> 02:50:43.167
governor, military men wore it on their scarves, and the minister on his band. It decked the baby's

02:50:43.167 --> 02:50:49.047
little cap. It was shut up to be mild-wet and moldered away in the coffins of the dead.

02:50:49.767 --> 02:50:54.067
But it is not recorded that, in a single instance, her skill was called in aid to

02:50:54.067 --> 02:50:57.807
embroider the white veil which was to cover the pure blushes of a bride.

02:50:58.927 --> 02:51:04.567
The exception indicated the ever-relentless vigor with which society frowned upon her sin.

02:51:05.547 --> 02:51:11.527
Hester sought not to acquire anything beyond a substance, but the plainest and most ascetic

02:51:11.527 --> 02:51:17.687
description for herself and a simple abundance for her child. Her own dress was of the coarsest

02:51:17.687 --> 02:51:25.007
materials and the most somber hue, with only that of one ornament, the scarlet letter, which it was

02:51:25.007 --> 02:51:30.387
her doom to wear. The child's attire, on the other hand, was distinguished by a fanciful,

02:51:30.867 --> 02:51:36.847
or we might rather say a fantastic ingenuity, which served indeed to heighten the airy charm

02:51:36.847 --> 02:51:42.087
that earlier began to develop itself in the little girl, but which appeared to also have

02:51:42.087 --> 02:51:48.027
a deeper meaning. We may speak further of it hereafter. Except for the small expenditure

02:51:48.027 --> 02:51:54.807
and decoration on her infant, Hester bestowed on her some hurtful means and charity on wretches

02:51:54.807 --> 02:51:59.967
less miserable than herself, and who not unfrequently insulted the hand that fed them.

02:52:00.647 --> 02:52:04.947
Much of the time which she might readily have applied to the better efforts of her art,

02:52:04.947 --> 02:52:10.547
she employed in making coarse garments for the poor. It is probable that there was an idea of

02:52:10.547 --> 02:52:15.367
penance in the mode of an occupation, and that she offered up a real sacrifice of enjoyment

02:52:15.367 --> 02:52:21.707
in devoting so many hours to such rude handiwork. She added in her nature a rich, voluptuous,

02:52:21.787 --> 02:52:26.307
oriental characteristic, a taste for the gorgeously beautiful, which save in the

02:52:26.307 --> 02:52:31.487
exquisite productions of her needle, found nothing else in all the possibilities of her life to

02:52:31.487 --> 02:52:37.607
exercise itself upon. Women derive a pleasure incomprehensible for the other sex from the

02:52:37.607 --> 02:52:42.947
delicate toil of the needle. To Hester Prynne, it might have been a mode of expressing, and

02:52:42.947 --> 02:52:48.927
therefore soothing, the passion of her life. Like all other joys, she rejected it as a sin.

02:52:49.507 --> 02:52:55.327
This morbid meddling of conscience with an immaterial matter betoken, it is to be feared,

02:52:55.327 --> 02:53:01.707
no genuine and steadfast penance, but something doubtful, something that might be deeply wrong

02:53:01.707 --> 02:53:07.727
beneath. In this manner, Hester Prynne came to have a part to perform in the world. With her

02:53:07.727 --> 02:53:13.587
native energy of character and rare capacity, it could not entirely cast her off, although it had

02:53:13.587 --> 02:53:19.007
set a mark upon her more intolerable to a woman's heart than that which branded the brow of Cain.

02:53:19.927 --> 02:53:24.927
In all her intercourse with society, however, there was nothing that made her feel as if she

02:53:24.927 --> 02:53:31.027
belonged to it. Every gesture, every word, and even the silence of those with whom she came in

02:53:31.027 --> 02:53:38.127
contact, inquired, and often expressed, that she was banished, and as much as alone as if she

02:53:38.127 --> 02:53:43.887
inhabited another sphere, but communicated with the common nature by other organs and senses than

02:53:43.887 --> 02:53:50.847
the rest of humankind. She stood apart from moral interests, yet close beside them, long a ghost

02:53:50.847 --> 02:53:57.107
revisits the familiar fireside and can no longer make itself seen or felt, nor more smile with the

02:53:57.107 --> 02:54:02.787
household joy, nor mourn with the kindred sorrow, or should it succeed in manifesting its forbidden

02:54:02.787 --> 02:54:09.847
sympathy, awakening only terror and horrible repugnance. These emotions, in fact, and its

02:54:09.847 --> 02:54:14.927
bitter scorn besides, seem to be the sole portion that she retained in the universal heart.

02:54:15.487 --> 02:54:20.827
It was not an age of delicacy, and her position, although she understood it well and was in little

02:54:20.827 --> 02:54:26.627
danger of forgetting it, was often brought before her vivid self-perception, like a new anguish,

02:54:26.927 --> 02:54:33.627
by the rudest touch upon the tenderest spot. The poor, as we have already said, whom she sought out

02:54:33.627 --> 02:54:38.767
to be the objects of her bounty, reviled the hand that was stretched forth to secure them.

02:54:39.587 --> 02:54:43.967
Dames of elevated rank likewise, whose doors she entered in the way of her occupation,

02:54:44.487 --> 02:54:48.967
were accustomed to distil drops of bitterness into her heart, sometimes through the alchemy

02:54:48.967 --> 02:54:55.287
of quiet malice by which women can concoct a subtle poison from ordinary trifles, and sometimes

02:54:55.287 --> 02:55:01.387
also by a coarser expression that fell upon the sufferer's defenseless breast like a rough blow

02:55:01.387 --> 02:55:07.427
upon an ulcerated wound. Custer had schooled herself long and well. She never responded to

02:55:07.427 --> 02:55:12.807
these attacks, save by a flush of crimson that rose irreflexibly over the pale cheek,

02:55:12.807 --> 02:55:19.307
and again subsided into the depths of her bosom. She was patient, a martyr indeed, but she

02:55:19.307 --> 02:55:24.847
forbear to pray for her enemies, lest, in spite of her forgiving aspirations, the words of the

02:55:24.847 --> 02:55:30.687
blessing should stubbornly twist themselves into a curse. Continually, and in a thousand other ways,

02:55:30.767 --> 02:55:35.487
did she feel the innumerable frauds of anguish that had been so cunningly contrived for her by

02:55:35.487 --> 02:55:41.467
the undying, the ever-active sentence of the Puritan Tribunal. Clergymen paused in the street

02:55:41.467 --> 02:55:46.467
to address words of exhortation that brought a crowd with its mingled grin and frown around the

02:55:46.467 --> 02:55:52.527
poor, sinful woman. If she entered a church trusting to share the Sabbath smile of the

02:55:52.527 --> 02:55:57.187
Universal Father, it was often her mishap to find herself the text of the discourse.

02:55:57.587 --> 02:56:02.647
She grew to have a dread of children, for they had imbibed from their parents a vague idea of

02:56:02.647 --> 02:56:08.467
something horrible in this dreary woman, gliding silently through the town, with never any companion

02:56:08.467 --> 02:56:14.467
but only one child. Therefore, first allowing her to pass, they pursued her at a distance with

02:56:14.467 --> 02:56:20.387
shrill cries and the utterance of a word that had no distinct report to their own minds, but was

02:56:20.387 --> 02:56:26.067
nonetheless terrible to her, as proceeding from the lips that babbled it unconsciously.

02:56:26.767 --> 02:56:32.387
It seemed to argue so wide a diffusion of her shame that all nature knew of it. It could have

02:56:32.387 --> 02:56:37.287
caused her no deeper pain had the leaves of the trees whispered the dark story among themselves,

02:56:37.287 --> 02:56:42.067
and the summer breeze murmured about it, had the wintry blast shrieked it aloud.

02:56:43.027 --> 02:56:48.467
Another peculiar torture was felt in the gaze of the new eye. When strangers looked curiously at

02:56:48.467 --> 02:56:54.127
the scarlet letter, and none ever failed to do so, they branded it afresh into Hester's soul,

02:56:54.387 --> 02:56:59.567
so that oftentimes she could scarcely refrain, it always did refrain, from covering the symbol

02:56:59.567 --> 02:57:04.907
with her hand. But then again an accustomed eye had likewise its own anguish to inflict.

02:57:05.547 --> 02:57:12.147
At its cool stare the familiarity was intolerable. From first to last and short, Hester Prynne had

02:57:12.147 --> 02:57:18.027
always this dreadful agony in feeling a human eye upon the token. The spot never grew callous,

02:57:18.067 --> 02:57:23.667
it seemed, on the contrary, to grow more sensitive with daily torture. But sometimes,

02:57:23.867 --> 02:57:30.067
once in many days or perchance in many months, she felt an eye, a human eye, upon the ignominious

02:57:30.067 --> 02:57:36.927
brand that seemed to give a momentary relief as if half her agony were shared. The next instant,

02:57:37.307 --> 02:57:43.207
back at all rushed again, with still a deeper throb of pain, for in that brief interval she

02:57:43.207 --> 02:57:51.287
had sinned anew. Had Hester sinned alone? Her imagination was somehow affected, and, had she

02:57:51.287 --> 02:57:57.727
been of softer moral and intellectual fibre, would have been still more so by the strange and solitary

02:57:57.727 --> 02:58:03.567
anguish of her life. Walking to and fro with those lonely footsteps in the little world with

02:58:03.567 --> 02:58:10.107
which she had outwardly connected, and now and then appeared to Hester, if altogether fancy,

02:58:10.327 --> 02:58:17.167
it was nevertheless too impotent to be resisted. She felt, or fancied then, that the scarlet letter

02:58:17.167 --> 02:58:23.027
had endowed her with a new sense. She shuddered to believe, yet could not help believing, that it

02:58:23.027 --> 02:58:28.867
gave her a sympathetic knowledge of the hidden sin in our hearts. She was terror-stricken by

02:58:28.867 --> 02:58:34.687
the revelations that were thus made. What were they? Could they be other than the insidious

02:58:34.687 --> 02:58:40.147
whispers of the bad angel, who would fain have pursued the struggling woman, as yet only half

02:58:40.147 --> 02:58:46.367
his victim? That the outward guise of purity was but a lie, and that, if truth were everywhere to

02:58:46.367 --> 02:58:52.707
be shown, a scarlet letter would blaze forth on many a bosom besides Hester Prince? Or must

02:58:52.707 --> 02:59:00.367
she receive those intimidations, so obscure, yet so distant, as truth? In all her miserable experience

02:59:00.367 --> 02:59:06.527
there was nothing else so awful and so loathsome as this sense. Perplexed as well as shocked her

02:59:06.527 --> 02:59:13.347
by the irreverent opportunities of the occasions that brought it into vivid action. Sometimes the

02:59:13.347 --> 02:59:19.187
red infamy upon her breast would give a sympathetic thrive, if she passed near a venerable minister or

02:59:19.877 --> 02:59:26.707
the model of piety and justice, to whom the age of antique reverence looked up as to a mortal man

02:59:26.707 --> 02:59:33.467
in fellowship with angels. What evil thing is at hand, would Hester say to herself, lifting her

02:59:33.467 --> 02:59:38.587
reluctant eyes, there would be nothing a human within the scope of view, save the form of the

02:59:38.587 --> 02:59:45.727
earthly saint? Again, the mystic sisterhood would contumishly assert itself as she met the sanctified

02:59:45.727 --> 02:59:52.027
crown of some matron, who, according to the rumor of all tongues, had kept cold snow within her bosom

02:59:52.527 --> 02:59:58.567
throughout life. That unsung snow in the matron's bosom, in the burning Shema and Hester Prince,

02:59:59.067 --> 03:00:04.827
would had the two in common, or once more the electric thrill would give her warning. Behold,

03:00:05.027 --> 03:00:10.487
Hester here is a companion. And looking up, she would detect the eyes of a young maiden glancing

03:00:10.487 --> 03:00:16.087
at the scarlet letter, shyly and aside, and quickly averted with a faint, chill crimson in

03:00:16.087 --> 03:00:22.047
her cheeks, as if her purity were somewhat sullied by the momentary glance. O fiend,

03:00:22.287 --> 03:00:28.567
whose talisman was of that fatal symbol, wouldst thou leave nothing, whether in youth or age,

03:00:28.707 --> 03:00:34.907
for this poor sinner to revere? Such loss of faith is ever one of the saddest results of sin.

03:00:34.907 --> 03:00:40.247
Be it accepted as proof that all was not corrupt in this poor victim of her own frailty,

03:00:40.747 --> 03:00:45.567
and man's hard law, that Hester Prince yet struggled to believe that no fellow mortal

03:00:45.567 --> 03:00:52.427
was guilty like herself. The vulgar, who in their dreary old times were always contributing a

03:00:52.427 --> 03:00:57.247
grotesque horror to what interested their imaginations, had a story about the scarlet

03:00:57.247 --> 03:01:03.367
letter, which we might readily work up into a terrific legend. They averred that the symbol

03:01:03.367 --> 03:01:10.127
was not a mere scarlet cloth tinged in an earthly dye pot, but was the red hot with infernal fire,

03:01:10.287 --> 03:01:15.587
and could be seen glowing all alight whenever Hester Prince walked abroad in the night time.

03:01:16.207 --> 03:01:21.827
And we must need say it seared Hester's bosom so deeply, that perhaps there was more truth in that

03:01:21.827 --> 03:01:30.227
rumor than our modern incredulity would be inclined to admit. End of of the scarlet letter.

03:01:33.367 --> 03:01:34.207
you

03:01:45.266 --> 03:01:54.026
VI. Pearl.

03:01:55.126 --> 03:02:00.026
We have as yet hardly spoken of the infant, that little creature whose innocent life had

03:02:00.026 --> 03:02:05.726
sprung, by the inscrutable decree of Providence, a lovely and immortal flower out of the rank

03:02:05.726 --> 03:02:07.706
luxuriance of a guilty passion.

03:02:08.266 --> 03:02:12.966
How strange it seemed to the sad woman, as she watched the growth and the beauty that

03:02:12.966 --> 03:02:18.526
became every day more brilliant, and the intelligence that threw its quivering sunshine over the

03:02:18.526 --> 03:02:20.206
tiny features of this child.

03:02:20.666 --> 03:02:27.326
Her pearl, for so had Tester called her, not as a name expressive of her aspect, which

03:02:27.326 --> 03:02:32.726
had nothing of the calm, white, unimpassioned luster that would be indicated by the comparison.

03:02:33.306 --> 03:02:39.246
But she named the infant Pearl, as being of great price, purchased with all she had, her

03:02:39.246 --> 03:02:40.546
mother's only treasure.

03:02:41.186 --> 03:02:47.806
How strange, indeed, man had marked this woman's sin by a scarlet letter, which had such potent

03:02:47.806 --> 03:02:53.506
and disastrous efficacy that no human sympathy could reach her, save it were sinful like

03:02:53.506 --> 03:02:54.146
herself.

03:02:54.746 --> 03:02:59.986
God, as a direct consequence of the sin which man thus punished, had given her a lovely

03:02:59.986 --> 03:03:05.766
child, whose place was on that same dishonoured bosom to connect her parent for ever with

03:03:05.766 --> 03:03:10.806
the race and descent of mortals, and to be finally a blessed soul in heaven.

03:03:11.486 --> 03:03:15.726
Yet these thoughts affected Hester Prynne less with hope than apprehension.

03:03:16.126 --> 03:03:18.066
She knew that her deed had been evil.

03:03:18.566 --> 03:03:21.926
She could have no faith, therefore, that its result would be good.

03:03:22.456 --> 03:03:27.586
Day after day she looked fearfully into the child's expanding nature, ever dreading to

03:03:27.586 --> 03:03:32.566
detect some dark and wild peculiarity that should correspond with the guiltiness to which

03:03:32.566 --> 03:03:33.646
she owed her being.

03:03:34.506 --> 03:03:36.406
Certainly there was no physical defect.

03:03:36.826 --> 03:03:42.466
By its perfect shape, its vigor, and its natural dexterity in the use of all its untried limbs,

03:03:42.946 --> 03:03:47.606
the infant was worthy to have been brought forth in Eden, worthy to have been left there

03:03:47.606 --> 03:03:51.946
to be the plaything of the angels after the world's first parents were driven out.

03:03:52.426 --> 03:03:57.686
The child had a native grace which does not invariably co-exist with faultless beauty.

03:03:58.486 --> 03:04:03.806
Its attire, however simple, always impressed the beholder as if it were the very garb that

03:04:03.806 --> 03:04:05.586
precisely became it best.

03:04:06.126 --> 03:04:09.186
But little Pearl was not clad in rustic weeds.

03:04:10.486 --> 03:04:16.166
Her mother, with a morbid purpose, that may be better understood hereafter, had bought

03:04:16.166 --> 03:04:21.706
the richest tissues that could be procured, and allowed her imaginative faculty its full

03:04:21.706 --> 03:04:26.446
play in the arrangement and decoration of the dresses which the child wore before the

03:04:26.446 --> 03:04:27.266
public eye.

03:04:28.166 --> 03:04:33.606
So magnificent was the small figure when thus arrayed, and such was the splendor of Pearl's

03:04:33.606 --> 03:04:38.626
own proper beauty, shining through the gorgeous robes which might have extinguished a paler

03:04:38.626 --> 03:04:44.606
loveliness, that there was an absolute circle of radiance around her, on the darksome cottage

03:04:44.606 --> 03:04:51.606
And yet a russet gown, torn and soiled with the child's rude play, made a picture of her

03:04:51.606 --> 03:04:52.646
just as perfect.

03:04:53.186 --> 03:04:56.886
Pearl's aspect was imbued with a spell of infinite variety.

03:04:57.526 --> 03:05:03.266
In this one child there were many children, comprehending the full scope between the wildflower

03:05:03.266 --> 03:05:08.906
prettiness of a peasant baby, and the pomp, in little, of an infant princess.

03:05:09.606 --> 03:05:14.926
Throughout all, however, there was a trait of passion, a certain depth of hue which she

03:05:14.926 --> 03:05:21.186
never lost, and if in any of her changes she had grown fainter or paler, she would have

03:05:21.186 --> 03:05:24.566
ceased to be herself, it would have been no longer Pearl.

03:05:25.626 --> 03:05:30.906
This outward mutability indicated, and did not more than fairly express, the various

03:05:30.906 --> 03:05:32.566
properties of her inner life.

03:05:32.886 --> 03:05:39.086
Her nature appeared to possess depth, too, as well as variety, but, or else Hester's

03:05:39.086 --> 03:05:44.246
fears deceived her, it lacked reference and adaptation to the world into which she was

03:05:44.246 --> 03:05:44.586
born.

03:05:45.046 --> 03:05:47.726
The child could not be made amenable to rules.

03:05:48.266 --> 03:05:53.526
In giving her existence a great law had been broken, and the result was a being whose elements

03:05:53.526 --> 03:05:59.106
were perhaps beautiful and brilliant, but all in disorder, or with an order peculiar

03:05:59.106 --> 03:06:04.546
to themselves, amidst which the point of variety and arrangement was difficult or

03:06:04.546 --> 03:06:06.066
impossible to be discovered.

03:06:07.166 --> 03:06:11.906
Hester could only account for the child's character, and even then most vaguely and

03:06:11.906 --> 03:06:16.986
imperfectly, by recalling what she herself had been during that momentous period, while

03:06:16.986 --> 03:06:22.466
Pearl was imbibing her soul from the spiritual world, and her bodily frame from its material

03:06:22.466 --> 03:06:23.026
of earth.

03:06:23.426 --> 03:06:28.586
The mother's impassioned state had been the medium through which were transmitted into

03:06:28.586 --> 03:06:35.126
the unborn infant the rays of its moral life, and, however white and clear originally, they

03:06:35.126 --> 03:06:41.126
had taken the deep stains of crimson and gold, the fiery luster, the black shadow, and the

03:06:41.126 --> 03:06:43.866
untempered light of the intervening substance.

03:06:44.786 --> 03:06:50.226
Above all, the warfare of Hester's spirit at that epoch was perpetuated in Pearl.

03:06:50.786 --> 03:06:56.786
She could recognize her wild, desperate, defiant mood, the flightiness of her temper, and even

03:06:56.786 --> 03:07:01.686
some of the very cloud-shapes of gloom and despondency that had brooded in her heart.

03:07:02.206 --> 03:07:07.766
They were now illuminated by the morning radiance of a young child's disposition, but, later

03:07:07.766 --> 03:07:12.766
in the day of earthly existence, might be prolific of the storm and whirlwind.

03:07:13.566 --> 03:07:18.666
The discipline of the family in those days was of a far more rigid kind than now.

03:07:19.206 --> 03:07:24.426
The frown, the harsh rebuke, the frequent application of the rod enjoined by scriptural

03:07:24.426 --> 03:07:29.866
authority, were used not merely in the way of punishment for actual offenses, but as

03:07:29.866 --> 03:07:34.326
a wholesome regimen for the growth and promotion of all childish virtues.

03:07:35.566 --> 03:07:41.526
Hester Prynne, nevertheless, the loving mother of this one child, ran little risk of erring

03:07:41.526 --> 03:07:47.086
on the side of undue severity, mindful, however, of her own errors and misfortunes.

03:07:47.566 --> 03:07:53.026
She early sought to impose a tender but strict control over the infant immortality that was

03:07:53.026 --> 03:07:54.226
committed to her charge.

03:07:54.686 --> 03:07:56.666
But the task was beyond her skill.

03:07:57.226 --> 03:08:01.866
After testing both smiles and frowns, and proving that neither mode of treatment possessed

03:08:01.866 --> 03:08:07.466
any calculable influence, Hester was ultimately compelled to stand aside and permit the child

03:08:07.466 --> 03:08:09.866
to be swayed by her own impulses.

03:08:10.446 --> 03:08:14.946
Physical compulsion or restraint was effectual, of course, while it lasted.

03:08:15.466 --> 03:08:20.546
As to any other kind of discipline, whether addressed to her mind or heart, little Pearl

03:08:20.546 --> 03:08:24.786
might or might not be within its reach in accordance with the caprice that ruled the

03:08:24.786 --> 03:08:25.126
moment.

03:08:25.766 --> 03:08:30.546
Her mother, while Pearl was yet an infant, grew acquainted with a certain peculiar look

03:08:30.546 --> 03:08:35.906
that warned her when it would be labor thrown away to insist, persuade, or plead.

03:08:37.266 --> 03:08:43.766
It was a look so intelligent, yet inexplicable, perverse, sometimes so malicious, but generally

03:08:43.766 --> 03:08:48.946
accompanied by a wild flow of spirits, that Hester could not help questioning at such

03:08:48.946 --> 03:08:51.586
moments whether Pearl was a human child.

03:08:52.346 --> 03:08:58.026
She seemed rather an airy sprite, which, after playing its fantastic sports for a little

03:08:58.026 --> 03:09:02.486
while upon the cottage floor, would flit away with a mocking smile.

03:09:03.146 --> 03:09:09.406
Whenever that look appeared in her wild, bright, deeply black eyes, it invested her with a

03:09:09.406 --> 03:09:11.766
strange remoteness and intangibility.

03:09:12.386 --> 03:09:17.046
It was as if she were hovering in the air, and might vanish like a glimmering light,

03:09:17.046 --> 03:09:21.166
that comes we know not whence, and goes we know not whither.

03:09:21.926 --> 03:09:27.666
Beholding it, Hester was constrained to rush towards the child, to pursue the little elf

03:09:27.666 --> 03:09:33.906
in the flight which she invariably began, to snatch her to her bosom with a close pressure

03:09:33.906 --> 03:09:39.946
and earnest kisses, not so much from overflowing love as to assure herself that Pearl was flesh

03:09:39.946 --> 03:09:42.326
and blood and not utterly delusive.

03:09:42.886 --> 03:09:48.806
But Pearl's laugh, when she was caught, though full of merriment and music, made her mother

03:09:48.806 --> 03:09:50.346
more doubtful than before.

03:09:51.926 --> 03:09:57.206
Heart-smitten at this bewildering and baffling spell that so often came between herself and

03:09:57.206 --> 03:10:02.926
her sole treasure, whom she had bought so dear, and who was all her world, Hester sometimes

03:10:02.926 --> 03:10:04.646
burst into passionate tears.

03:10:05.126 --> 03:10:10.326
Then, perhaps, for there was no foreseeing how it might affect her, Pearl would frown

03:10:10.326 --> 03:10:15.766
and clench her little fist, and harden her small features into a stern, unsympathizing

03:10:15.766 --> 03:10:17.526
look of discontent.

03:10:18.066 --> 03:10:23.966
Not seldom she would laugh anew and louder than before, like a thing incapable and unintelligent

03:10:23.966 --> 03:10:25.046
of human sorrow.

03:10:25.386 --> 03:10:31.186
Or, but this more rarely happened, she would be convulsed with rage of grief and sob out

03:10:31.186 --> 03:10:36.686
her love for her mother in broken words, and seem intent on proving that she had a heart

03:10:36.686 --> 03:10:37.866
by breaking it.

03:10:39.026 --> 03:10:43.726
Yet Hester was hardly safe in confiding herself to that gusty tenderness.

03:10:44.186 --> 03:10:46.546
It passed as suddenly as it came.

03:10:47.886 --> 03:10:53.046
Brooding over all these matters, the mother felt like one who has evoked a spirit, but,

03:10:53.066 --> 03:10:59.666
by some irregularity in the process of conjuration, has failed to win the master word that should

03:10:59.666 --> 03:11:03.006
control this new and incomprehensible intelligence.

03:11:03.806 --> 03:11:08.126
Her only real comfort was when the child lay in the placidity of sleep.

03:11:09.026 --> 03:11:15.306
Then she was sure of her, and tasted hours of quiet, sad, delicious happiness, until,

03:11:15.306 --> 03:11:20.686
perhaps with that perverse expression glimmering from beneath her opening lids, little Pearl

03:11:20.686 --> 03:11:21.446
awoke.

03:11:22.386 --> 03:11:28.086
How soon, and with what strange rapidity indeed, did Pearl arrive at an age that was capable

03:11:28.086 --> 03:11:32.946
of social intercourse beyond the mother's ever-ready smile and nonsense words.

03:11:33.466 --> 03:11:38.006
And then what a happiness would it have been could Hester Prynne have heard her clear birdlike

03:11:38.006 --> 03:11:43.766
voice mingling with the uproar of other childish voices, and have distinguished and unraveled

03:11:43.766 --> 03:11:49.546
her own darling's tones amid all the entangled outcry of a group of sportive children.

03:11:50.426 --> 03:11:51.946
But this could never be.

03:11:51.946 --> 03:11:55.506
Pearl was a born outcast of the infantile world.

03:11:56.026 --> 03:12:02.126
An imp of evil, emblem and product of sin, she had no right among christened infants.

03:12:02.826 --> 03:12:08.306
Nothing was more remarkable than the instinct, as it seemed, with which the child comprehended

03:12:08.306 --> 03:12:09.186
her loneliness.

03:12:10.166 --> 03:12:16.106
The destiny that had drawn an inviolable circle round about her, the whole peculiarity in

03:12:16.106 --> 03:12:19.066
short of her position in respect to other children.

03:12:19.746 --> 03:12:24.166
Never since her release from prison had Hester met the public gaze without her.

03:12:24.406 --> 03:12:30.166
In all her walks about the town, Pearl, too, was there, first as the babe in arms, and

03:12:30.166 --> 03:12:35.806
afterwards as the little girl, small companion of her mother, holding a forefinger with her

03:12:35.806 --> 03:12:41.746
whole grasp, and tripping along, at the rate of three or four footsteps, to one of Hester's.

03:12:42.706 --> 03:12:47.546
She saw the children of the settlement on the grassy margin of the street, or at the

03:12:47.546 --> 03:12:53.466
domestic thresholds, distorting themselves in such grim fashions as the puritanic nurture

03:12:53.466 --> 03:12:59.786
would permit, playing at going to church, perchance, or at scourging Quakers, or taking

03:12:59.786 --> 03:13:05.306
scalps in a sham fight with the Indians, or scaring one another with freaks of imitative

03:13:05.306 --> 03:13:06.146
witchcraft.

03:13:07.326 --> 03:13:11.326
Pearl saw and gazed intently, but never sought to make acquaintance.

03:13:11.706 --> 03:13:14.086
If spoken to, she would not speak again.

03:13:14.446 --> 03:13:19.306
If the children gathered about her as they sometimes did, Pearl would grow positively

03:13:19.306 --> 03:13:26.626
terrible in her puny wrath, snatching up stones to fling at them with shrill, incoherent exclamations

03:13:26.626 --> 03:13:31.806
that made her mother tremble, because they had so much the sound of a witch's anathemas

03:13:31.806 --> 03:13:33.606
in some unknown tongue.

03:13:34.966 --> 03:13:40.226
The truth was that the little puritans, being of the most intolerant brood that ever lived,

03:13:40.226 --> 03:13:46.966
had got a vague idea of something outlandish, unearthly, or at variance with ordinary fashions,

03:13:47.246 --> 03:13:52.326
in the mother and the child, and therefore scorned them in their hearts, and not infrequently

03:13:52.326 --> 03:13:54.186
reviled them with their tongues.

03:13:55.266 --> 03:13:59.866
Pearl felt the sentiment, and requited it with the bitterest hatred that can be supposed

03:13:59.866 --> 03:14:01.846
to rankle in a childish bosom.

03:14:02.446 --> 03:14:07.546
These outbreaks of a fierce temper had a kind of value, and even comfort for the mother,

03:14:08.166 --> 03:14:13.246
because there was at least an intelligible earnestness in the mood, instead of the fitful

03:14:13.246 --> 03:14:17.086
caprice that so often thwarted her in the child's manifestations.

03:14:17.646 --> 03:14:23.006
It appalled her, nevertheless, to discern here again a shadowy reflection of the evil

03:14:23.006 --> 03:14:24.666
that had existed in herself.

03:14:25.786 --> 03:14:32.106
All this enmity and passion had Pearl inherited, by inalienable right, out of Hester's heart.

03:14:32.506 --> 03:14:37.346
Mother and daughter stood together in the same circle of seclusion from human society,

03:14:38.306 --> 03:14:43.426
and in the nature of the child seemed to be perpetuated those unquiet elements that had

03:14:43.426 --> 03:14:49.126
distracted Hester Prynne before Pearl's birth, but had since begun to be soothed away by

03:14:49.126 --> 03:14:51.566
the softening influences of maternity.

03:14:52.846 --> 03:14:58.886
At home, within and around her mother's cottage, Pearl wanted not a wide and various circle

03:14:58.886 --> 03:14:59.766
of acquaintance.

03:15:00.226 --> 03:15:06.066
The spell of life went forth from her ever-creative spirit, and communicated itself to a thousand

03:15:06.066 --> 03:15:10.066
objects as a torch kindles a flame wherever it may be applied.

03:15:10.766 --> 03:15:16.786
The unlikeliest materials—a stick, a bunch of rags, a flower—were the puppets of Pearl's

03:15:16.786 --> 03:15:22.526
witchcraft, and, without undergoing any outward change, became spiritually adapted to whatever

03:15:22.526 --> 03:15:25.326
drama occupied the stage of her inner world.

03:15:26.166 --> 03:15:32.966
Her one baby voice served a multitude of imaginary personages, old and young, to talk with all.

03:15:33.506 --> 03:15:39.506
The pine trees, aged, black and solemn, and flinging groans and other melancholy utterances

03:15:39.506 --> 03:15:43.946
on the breeze, needed little transformation to figure as Puritan elders.

03:15:44.686 --> 03:15:50.006
The ugliest weeds of the garden were their children, whom Pearl smote down and uprooted

03:15:50.006 --> 03:15:51.286
most unmercifully.

03:15:51.986 --> 03:15:57.386
It was wonderful, the vast variety of forms into which she threw her intellect with no

03:15:57.386 --> 03:16:03.386
continuity indeed but darting up and dancing, always in a state of preternatural activity,

03:16:03.926 --> 03:16:09.626
soon sinking down, as if exhausted by so rapid and feverish a tide of life, and succeeded

03:16:09.626 --> 03:16:12.386
by other shapes of a similar wild energy.

03:16:13.286 --> 03:16:18.186
It was like nothing so much as the phantasmagoric play of the northern lights.

03:16:18.526 --> 03:16:24.086
In the mere exercise of the fancy, however, and the sportiveness of a growing mind, there

03:16:24.086 --> 03:16:29.026
might be a little more than was observable in other children of bright faculties, except

03:16:29.026 --> 03:16:34.426
as Pearl, in the dearth of human playmates, was thrown more upon the visionary throng

03:16:34.426 --> 03:16:35.426
which she created.

03:16:35.846 --> 03:16:41.086
The singularity lay in the hostile feelings with which the child regarded all these offsprings

03:16:41.086 --> 03:16:42.886
of her own heart and mind.

03:16:43.486 --> 03:16:48.726
She never created a friend, but seemed always to be sowing broadcast the dragon's teeth

03:16:48.726 --> 03:16:53.366
whence sprung a harvest of armed enemies against whom she rushed to battle.

03:16:53.926 --> 03:16:59.666
It was inexpressibly sad, then what depth of sorrow to a mother, who felt in her own

03:16:59.666 --> 03:17:05.966
heart the cause, to observe in one so young this constant recognition of an adverse world,

03:17:06.566 --> 03:17:11.426
and so fierce a training of the energies that were to make good her cause in the contest

03:17:11.426 --> 03:17:13.086
that must ensue.

03:17:14.586 --> 03:17:19.706
Gazing at Pearl, Hester Prynne often dropped her work upon her knees, and cried out with

03:17:19.706 --> 03:17:24.086
an agony which she would fain have hidden, but which made utterance for itself betwee

03:17:24.086 --> 03:17:30.246
speech and a groan, O Father in heaven, if thou art still my father, what is this being

03:17:30.246 --> 03:17:32.026
which I have brought into the world?

03:17:32.526 --> 03:17:37.566
And Pearl, overhearing the ejaculation, or aware through some more subtle channel of

03:17:37.566 --> 03:17:42.586
those throbs of anguish, would turn her vivid and beautiful little face upon her mother,

03:17:43.186 --> 03:17:46.386
smile with sprite-like intelligence, and resume her play.

03:17:47.986 --> 03:17:51.746
One peculiarity of the child's deportment remains yet to be told.

03:17:52.126 --> 03:17:57.606
The very first thing which she had noticed in her life was, what, not the mother's smile,

03:17:57.746 --> 03:18:03.386
responding to it as other babies do, by that faint embryo smile of the little mouth remembered

03:18:03.386 --> 03:18:08.546
so doubtfully afterwards, and with such fond discussion whether it were indeed a smile,

03:18:08.966 --> 03:18:14.786
by no means, but that first object of which Pearl seemed to become aware was, shall we

03:18:14.786 --> 03:18:17.826
say it, the scarlet letter on Hester's bosom.

03:18:18.346 --> 03:18:24.166
One day, as her mother stooped over the cradle, the infant's eyes had been caught by the glimmering

03:18:24.166 --> 03:18:28.886
of the gold embroidery about the letter, and putting up her little hand, she grasped at

03:18:28.886 --> 03:18:34.486
it, smiling, not doubtfully, but with a decided gleam that gave her face the look of a much

03:18:34.486 --> 03:18:35.386
older child.

03:18:36.446 --> 03:18:42.406
Then, gasping for breath, did Hester Prynne clutch the fatal token, instinctively endeavouring

03:18:42.406 --> 03:18:47.866
to tear it away, so infinite was the torture inflicted by the intelligent touch of Pearl's

03:18:47.866 --> 03:18:48.686
baby hand.

03:18:49.406 --> 03:18:54.546
Again, as if her mother's agonized gesture were meant only to make sport for her, did

03:18:54.546 --> 03:18:57.106
little Pearl look into her eyes and smile.

03:18:57.566 --> 03:19:03.386
From that epoch, except when the child was asleep, Hester had never felt a moment's safety,

03:19:03.606 --> 03:19:05.766
not a moment's calm enjoyment of her.

03:19:06.406 --> 03:19:11.606
Weeks, it is true, would sometimes elapse, during which Pearl's gaze might never once

03:19:11.606 --> 03:19:17.106
be fixed upon the scarlet letter, but then again it would come at unawares, like the

03:19:17.106 --> 03:19:22.666
stroke of sudden death, and always with that peculiar smile and odd expression of the eyes.

03:19:24.106 --> 03:19:29.206
Once this freakish, elvish cast came into the child's eyes while Hester was looking

03:19:29.206 --> 03:19:35.106
at her own image in them, as mothers are fond of doing, and suddenly, for women in solitude

03:19:35.106 --> 03:19:39.746
and with troubled hearts, are pestered with unaccountable delusions, she fancied that

03:19:39.746 --> 03:19:45.026
she beheld, not her own miniature portrait, but another face in the small black mirror

03:19:45.026 --> 03:19:46.046
of Pearl's eye.

03:19:46.366 --> 03:19:52.426
It was a face, fiend-like, full of smiling malice, yet bearing the semblance of features

03:19:52.426 --> 03:19:57.446
that she had known full well, though seldom with a smile, and never with malice in them.

03:19:57.866 --> 03:20:03.606
It was as if an evil spirit possessed the child, and had just then peeped forth in mockery.

03:20:04.226 --> 03:20:09.866
Many a time afterwards had Hester been tortured, though less vividly, by the same illusion.

03:20:11.386 --> 03:20:16.546
In the afternoon of a certain summer's day, after Pearl grew big enough to run about,

03:20:16.886 --> 03:20:22.386
She amused herself with gathering handfuls of wildflowers, and flinging them, one by

03:20:22.386 --> 03:20:27.406
one, at her mother's bosom, dancing up and down like a little elf whenever she hit the

03:20:27.406 --> 03:20:28.126
scarlet letter.

03:20:28.886 --> 03:20:33.646
Hester's first motion had been to cover her bosom with her clasped hands, but whether

03:20:33.646 --> 03:20:38.906
from pride or resignation, or a feeling that her penance might best be wrought out by this

03:20:38.906 --> 03:20:45.586
unutterable pain, she resisted the impulse, and sat erect, pale as death, looking sadly

03:20:45.586 --> 03:20:47.726
into little Pearl's wild eyes.

03:20:48.426 --> 03:20:53.826
Still came the battery of flowers, almost invariably hitting the mark, and covering

03:20:53.826 --> 03:20:58.966
the mother's breast with hurts for which she could find no balm in this world, nor knew

03:20:58.966 --> 03:21:00.326
how to seek it in another.

03:21:00.946 --> 03:21:06.866
At last, her shot being all expended, the child stood still and gazed at Hester with

03:21:06.866 --> 03:21:12.566
that little laughing image of a fiend peeping out, or, whether it peeped or no, her mother

03:21:12.566 --> 03:21:16.326
imagined it from the unsearchable abyss of her black eyes.

03:21:16.786 --> 03:21:18.766
"'Child, what art thou?' cried the mother.

03:21:19.086 --> 03:21:21.666
"'Oh, I am your little Pearl,' answered the child.

03:21:22.286 --> 03:21:26.626
But while she said it, Pearl laughed, and began to dance up and down with the humorsome

03:21:26.626 --> 03:21:31.526
gesticulation of a little imp, whose next freak might be to fly up the chimney.

03:21:32.086 --> 03:21:35.186
"'Art thou, my child, in very truth?' asked Hester.

03:21:35.726 --> 03:21:41.066
Nor did she put the question altogether idly, but for the moment, with a portion of genuine

03:21:41.066 --> 03:21:46.606
earnestness, for such was Pearl's wonderful intelligence that her mother half doubted

03:21:46.606 --> 03:21:51.426
whether she were not acquainted with the secret spell of her existence, and might not now

03:21:51.426 --> 03:21:52.366
reveal herself.

03:21:53.286 --> 03:21:57.486
"'Yes, I am little Pearl,' repeated the child, continuing her antics.

03:21:57.766 --> 03:22:02.786
"'Thou art not, my child, thou art no Pearl of mine,' said the mother half playfully,

03:22:02.906 --> 03:22:07.586
for it was often the case that a sportive impulse came over her in the midst of her

03:22:07.586 --> 03:22:08.446
deepest suffering.

03:22:08.446 --> 03:22:11.886
"'Tell me, then, what thou art, and who sent thee hither?'

03:22:12.826 --> 03:22:17.906
"'Tell me, mother,' said the child seriously, coming up to Hester and pressing herself close

03:22:17.906 --> 03:22:18.486
to her knees.

03:22:18.726 --> 03:22:20.246
"'Do thou tell me?'

03:22:20.806 --> 03:22:23.786
"'Thy heavenly father sent thee,' answered Hester Prynne.

03:22:24.406 --> 03:22:29.006
But she said it with a hesitation that did not escape the acuteness of the child, whether

03:22:29.006 --> 03:22:34.486
moved only by her ordinary freakishness, or because an evil spirit prompted her, she put

03:22:34.486 --> 03:22:37.606
her small forefinger, and touched the scarlet letter.

03:22:38.166 --> 03:22:42.686
"'He did not send me,' cried she positively, "'I have no heavenly father.'

03:22:43.286 --> 03:22:48.306
"'Hush, Pearl, hush, thou must not talk so,' answered the mother, suppressing a groan.

03:22:48.346 --> 03:22:50.426
"'He sent us all into the world.

03:22:50.546 --> 03:22:52.666
He sent even me, thy mother.

03:22:53.306 --> 03:22:59.806
"'Then, much more thee, or if not, thou strange and elfish child, whence didst thou come?'

03:22:59.806 --> 03:23:04.466
"'Tell me, tell me,' repeated Pearl, no longer seriously, but laughing and

03:23:04.466 --> 03:23:07.806
tapering about the floor, "'It is thou that must tell me.'

03:23:07.806 --> 03:23:13.126
But Hester could not resolve the query, being herself in a dismal labyrinth of doubt.

03:23:14.266 --> 03:23:19.346
She remembered, betwixt a smile and a shudder, the talk of the neighbouring townspeople,

03:23:19.506 --> 03:23:25.446
who, seeking vainly elsewhere for the child's paternity, and observing some of her odd attributes,

03:23:25.826 --> 03:23:31.286
had given out that poor little Pearl was a demon offspring, such as ever since old Catholic

03:23:31.286 --> 03:23:36.946
had occasionally been seen on earth through the agency of their mother's sin, and to promote

03:23:36.946 --> 03:23:38.686
some foul and wicked purpose.

03:23:39.226 --> 03:23:44.526
Luther, according to the scandal of his monkish enemies, was a brat of that hellish breed.

03:23:45.026 --> 03:23:50.586
Nor was Pearl the only child to whom this inauspicious origin was assigned among the

03:23:50.586 --> 03:23:51.986
New England Puritans.

03:24:25.051 --> 03:24:25.571
VII.

03:24:26.231 --> 03:24:27.811
The Governor's Hall.

03:24:29.111 --> 03:24:33.431
Hester Prynne went one day to the mansion of Governor Bellingham, with a pair of gloves

03:24:33.431 --> 03:24:38.371
which he had fringed and embroidered to his order, and which were to be worn on some great

03:24:38.371 --> 03:24:43.511
occasion of state, for, though the chances of a popular election had caused this former

03:24:43.511 --> 03:24:49.971
ruler to descend a step or two from the highest rank, he still held an honourable and influential

03:24:49.971 --> 03:24:52.711
place among the colonial magistracy.

03:24:54.571 --> 03:24:59.611
Another and far more important reason than the delivery of a pair of embroidered gloves

03:24:59.611 --> 03:25:05.651
impelled Hester at this time to seek an interview with a personage of so much power and activity

03:25:05.651 --> 03:25:07.231
in the affairs of the settlement.

03:25:08.011 --> 03:25:12.731
It had reached her ears that there was a design on the part of some of the leading inhabitants

03:25:12.731 --> 03:25:18.811
cherishing the more rigid order of principles in religion and government, to deprive her

03:25:18.811 --> 03:25:19.651
of her child.

03:25:21.111 --> 03:25:26.651
On the supposition that Pearl, as already hinted, was of demon origin, these good people

03:25:26.651 --> 03:25:31.671
not unreasonably argued that a Christian interest in the mother's soul required them

03:25:31.671 --> 03:25:34.451
to remove such a stumbling block from her path.

03:25:35.111 --> 03:25:40.151
If the child, on the other hand, were really capable of moral and religious growth, and

03:25:40.151 --> 03:25:45.611
possessed the elements of ultimate salvation, then surely it would enjoy all the fairer

03:25:45.611 --> 03:25:51.471
prospects of these advantages by being transferred to wiser and better guardianship than Hester

03:25:51.471 --> 03:25:52.251
Prynne's.

03:25:52.821 --> 03:25:57.831
Among those who promoted the design, Governor Bellingham was said to be one of the most

03:25:57.831 --> 03:25:58.211
busy.

03:25:58.751 --> 03:26:04.271
It may appear singular and, indeed, not a little ludicrous, that an affair of this kind,

03:26:04.371 --> 03:26:10.471
which in later days would have been referred to no higher jurisdiction than that of the

03:26:10.471 --> 03:26:16.111
select men of the town, should then have been a question publicly discussed, and on which

03:26:16.111 --> 03:26:18.251
statesmen of eminence took sides.

03:26:18.851 --> 03:26:24.671
At that epoch of pristine simplicity, however, matters of even slighter public interest,

03:26:24.711 --> 03:26:30.071
and of far less intrinsic weight than the welfare of Hester and her child, were strangely

03:26:30.071 --> 03:26:34.331
mixed up with the deliberations of legislators and acts of state.

03:26:35.051 --> 03:26:40.111
The period was hardly, if at all, earlier than that of our story, when a dispute concerning

03:26:40.111 --> 03:26:46.311
the right of property in a pig not only caused a fierce and bitter contest in the legislative

03:26:46.311 --> 03:26:52.331
body of the colony, but resulted in an important modification of the framework itself of the

03:26:52.331 --> 03:26:52.871
legislature.

03:26:54.771 --> 03:26:59.811
Full of concern, therefore, but so conscious of her own right that it seemed scarcely an

03:26:59.811 --> 03:27:05.471
unequal match between the public on one side and a lonely woman, backed by the sympathies

03:27:05.471 --> 03:27:10.231
of nature on the other, Hester Prynne set forth from her solitary cottage.

03:27:10.911 --> 03:27:13.331
Little Pearl, of course, was her companion.

03:27:13.331 --> 03:27:19.351
She was now of an age to run lightly along by her mother's side, and, constantly in motion,

03:27:19.851 --> 03:27:24.771
from morn till sunset, could have accomplished a much longer journey than that before her.

03:27:25.311 --> 03:27:30.451
Often, nevertheless, more from caprice than necessity, she demanded to be taken up in

03:27:30.451 --> 03:27:36.031
arms, but was soon as imperious to be let down again, and frisked onward before Hester

03:27:36.031 --> 03:27:40.031
on the grassy pathway, with many a harmless trip and tumble.

03:27:40.711 --> 03:27:46.571
We have spoken of Pearl's rich and luxuriant beauty, a beauty that shone with deep and

03:27:46.571 --> 03:27:53.611
vivid tints, a bright complexion, eyes possessing intensity both of depth and glow, and hair

03:27:53.611 --> 03:27:59.211
already of a deep glossy brown, and which, in after years, would be nearly akin to black.

03:27:59.811 --> 03:28:02.311
There was fire in her and throughout her.

03:28:02.611 --> 03:28:06.651
She seemed the unpremeditated offshoot of a passionate moment.

03:28:07.151 --> 03:28:12.491
Her mother, in contriving the child's garb, had allowed the gorgeous tendencies of her

03:28:12.491 --> 03:28:18.791
imagination their full play, arraying her in a crimson velvet tunic of a peculiar cut,

03:28:19.431 --> 03:28:23.431
abundantly embroidered in fantasies and flourishes of gold thread.

03:28:23.951 --> 03:28:29.451
So much strength of colouring, which must have given a wane and pallid aspect to cheeks

03:28:29.451 --> 03:28:34.891
of a fainter bloom, was admirably adapted to Pearl's beauty, and made her the very

03:28:34.891 --> 03:28:38.471
brightest little jet of flame that ever danced upon the earth.

03:28:39.751 --> 03:28:44.651
But it was a remarkable attribute of this garb, and indeed of the child's whole appearance,

03:28:45.071 --> 03:28:50.671
that irresistibly and inevitably reminded the beholder of the token which Hester Prynne

03:28:50.671 --> 03:28:52.891
was doomed to wear upon her bosom.

03:28:53.451 --> 03:28:58.771
It was the scarlet letter in another form, the scarlet letter endowed with life.

03:28:59.271 --> 03:29:05.031
The mother herself, as if the red ignominy were so deeply scorched into her brain that

03:29:05.031 --> 03:29:11.211
all her conceptions assumed its form, had carefully wrought out the similitude, lavishing

03:29:11.211 --> 03:29:16.971
many hours of morbid ingenuity to create an analogy between the object of her affection

03:29:16.971 --> 03:29:19.351
and the emblem of her guilt and torture.

03:29:19.891 --> 03:29:25.531
But in truth Pearl was the one as well as the other, and only in consequence of that

03:29:25.531 --> 03:29:31.871
identity had Hester contrived so perfectly to represent the scarlet letter in her appearance.

03:29:33.171 --> 03:29:38.671
As the two wayfarers came within the precincts of the town, the children of the Puritans

03:29:38.671 --> 03:29:43.431
looked up from their play, or what passed for play with those somber little urchins,

03:29:43.931 --> 03:29:46.071
and spoke gravely one to another.

03:29:46.471 --> 03:29:51.651
Behold verily there is the woman of the scarlet letter, and of a truth moreover, there is

03:29:51.651 --> 03:29:54.731
likeness of the scarlet letter running along by her side.

03:29:55.311 --> 03:29:57.671
Come therefore and let us fling mud at them.

03:29:58.551 --> 03:30:04.091
But Pearl, who was a dauntless child, after frowning, stamping her foot, and shaking her

03:30:04.091 --> 03:30:08.691
little hand with a variety of threatening gestures, suddenly made a rush at the nod

03:30:08.691 --> 03:30:11.051
of her enemies, and put them all to flight.

03:30:11.811 --> 03:30:16.211
She resembled, in her fierce pursuit of them, an infant pestilence.

03:30:16.631 --> 03:30:22.511
The scarlet fever, or some such half-fledged angel of judgment, whose mission was to punish

03:30:22.511 --> 03:30:28.331
the sins of the rising generation, she screamed and shouted too with a terrific volume of

03:30:28.331 --> 03:30:32.891
sound, which doubtless caused the hearts of the fugitives to quake within them.

03:30:33.351 --> 03:30:39.151
The victory accomplished, Pearl returned quietly to her mother, and looked up, smiling, into

03:30:39.151 --> 03:30:39.891
her face.

03:30:41.071 --> 03:30:44.851
Without further adventure they reached the dwelling of Governor Bellingham.

03:30:44.851 --> 03:30:49.771
This was a large wooden house, built in a fashion of which there are specimens still

03:30:49.771 --> 03:30:56.091
extant in the streets of our older towns, now moss-grown, crumbling to decay, and melancholy

03:30:56.091 --> 03:31:01.251
at heart with the many sorrowful or joyful occurrences, remembered or forgotten, that

03:31:01.251 --> 03:31:04.391
have happened and passed away within their dusky chambers.

03:31:04.931 --> 03:31:09.911
Then, however, there was the freshness of the passing year on its exterior, and the

03:31:10.551 --> 03:31:16.011
gleaming forth from the sunny windows of a human habitation into which death had never

03:31:16.011 --> 03:31:16.491
entered.

03:31:17.151 --> 03:31:22.891
It had, indeed, a very cheery aspect, the walls being overspread with a kind of stucco

03:31:22.891 --> 03:31:28.951
in which fragments of broken glass were plentifully intermixed, so that, when the sunshine fell

03:31:28.951 --> 03:31:34.571
a slantwise over the front of the edifice, it glittered and sparkled as if diamonds had

03:31:34.571 --> 03:31:37.271
been flung against it by the double handful.

03:31:37.931 --> 03:31:43.331
The brilliancy might have fitted Aladdin's palace rather than the mansion of a grave

03:31:43.331 --> 03:31:44.771
old Puritan ruler.

03:31:45.651 --> 03:31:50.531
It was further decorated with strange and seemingly cabalistic figures and diagrams,

03:31:50.951 --> 03:31:55.871
suitable to the quaint taste of the age which had been drawn in the stucco when newly laid

03:31:55.871 --> 03:32:01.231
on, and had now grown hard and durable for the admiration of aftertimes.

03:32:02.531 --> 03:32:07.791
Pearl, looking at this bright wonder of a house, began to caper and dance, and imperatively

03:32:07.791 --> 03:32:12.831
required that the whole breadth of sunshine should be stripped off its front and given

03:32:12.831 --> 03:32:13.891
her to play with.

03:32:14.511 --> 03:32:18.391
"'No, my little Pearl,' said her mother, "'thou must gather thine own sunshine.

03:32:18.751 --> 03:32:20.831
I have none to give thee.'

03:32:20.831 --> 03:32:26.031
They approached the door, which was of an arched form, and flanked on each side by a

03:32:26.031 --> 03:32:31.651
narrow tower or projection of the edifice, in both of which were lattice windows, the

03:32:31.651 --> 03:32:34.091
wooden shutters to close over them at need.

03:32:34.891 --> 03:32:40.031
Lifting the iron hammer that hung at the portal, Hester Prynne gave a summons, which was answered

03:32:40.031 --> 03:32:45.411
by one of the governor's bond-servants, a free-born Englishman, but now a seven-year

03:32:45.411 --> 03:32:46.011
slave.

03:32:46.751 --> 03:32:51.431
During that term he was to be the property of his master, and as much a commodity of

03:32:51.431 --> 03:32:55.131
bargain and sale as an ox or a joint-stool.

03:32:55.711 --> 03:33:01.391
The serf wore the customary garb of serving-men at that period and long before, in the old

03:33:01.391 --> 03:33:03.351
hereditary halls of England.

03:33:04.151 --> 03:33:06.851
"'Is the worshipful Governor Bellingham within?'

03:33:06.851 --> 03:33:07.891
inquired Hester.

03:33:08.671 --> 03:33:13.531
"'Yea, forsooth,' replied the bond-servant, staring with wide open eyes at the scarlet

03:33:13.531 --> 03:33:17.971
letter, which, being a newcomer in the country, he had never before seen.

03:33:18.491 --> 03:33:23.411
Yea, his honourable worship is within, but he hath a godly minister or two with him,

03:33:23.411 --> 03:33:25.171
and likewise a liege.

03:33:25.711 --> 03:33:27.691
Yea may not see his worship now.'

03:33:29.451 --> 03:33:34.711
"'Nevertheless I will enter,' answered Hester Prynne, and the bond-servant, perhaps judging

03:33:34.711 --> 03:33:40.071
from the decision of her heir, and the glittering symbol in her bosom, that she was a great

03:33:40.071 --> 03:33:42.671
lady in the land, offered no opposition.

03:33:44.371 --> 03:33:50.071
So the mother and little Pearl were admitted into the hall of entrance, with many variations

03:33:50.071 --> 03:33:55.131
suggested by the nature of his building materials, diversity of climate, and a different mode

03:33:55.131 --> 03:34:00.891
of social life, Governor Bellingham had planned his new habitation after the residences of

03:34:00.891 --> 03:34:03.491
gentlemen of Ferris State in his native land.

03:34:04.291 --> 03:34:09.591
Here then was a wide and reasonably lofty hall, extending through the whole depth of

03:34:09.591 --> 03:34:15.051
the house and forming a medium of general communication more or less directly with all

03:34:15.051 --> 03:34:16.071
the other apartments.

03:34:16.071 --> 03:34:22.151
At one extremity this spacious room was lighted by the windows of the two towers, which formed

03:34:22.151 --> 03:34:24.951
a small recess on either side of the portal.

03:34:26.171 --> 03:34:31.591
At the other end, though partly muffled by a curtain, it was more powerfully illuminated

03:34:31.591 --> 03:34:37.371
by one of those embowed hall windows which we read of in old books, and which was provided

03:34:37.371 --> 03:34:39.311
with a deep and cushioned seat.

03:34:39.971 --> 03:34:46.411
Here on the cushion lay a folio tome probably of the Chronicles of England or other such

03:34:46.411 --> 03:34:52.371
substantial literature, even as, in our own days, we scatter gilded volumes on the center

03:34:52.371 --> 03:34:55.131
table to be turned over by the casual guest.

03:34:55.771 --> 03:35:00.451
The furniture of the hall consisted of some ponderous chairs, the backs of which were

03:35:00.451 --> 03:35:06.791
elaborately carved with wreaths of oaken flowers, and likewise a table in the same taste, the

03:35:06.791 --> 03:35:12.851
being of the Elizabethan age, or perhaps earlier, and heirlooms transferred hither from the

03:35:12.851 --> 03:35:14.211
governor's paternal home.

03:35:14.691 --> 03:35:19.911
On the table, in token that the sentiment of Old English hospitality had not been left

03:35:19.911 --> 03:35:25.991
behind, stood a large pewter tankard, at the bottom of which, had Hester or Pearl peeped

03:35:25.991 --> 03:35:30.731
into it, they might have seen the frothy remnant of a recent draught of ale.

03:35:32.031 --> 03:35:37.451
On the wall hung a row of portraits, representing the forefathers of the Bellingham lineage,

03:35:37.931 --> 03:35:42.871
some with armor on their breasts, and others with stately ruffs and robes of peace.

03:35:43.411 --> 03:35:48.651
All were characterized by the sternness and severity which old portraits so invariably

03:35:48.651 --> 03:35:54.291
put on, as if they were the ghosts, rather than the pictures of departed worthies, and

03:35:54.291 --> 03:36:00.391
gazing with harsh and intolerant criticism at the pursuits and enjoyments of living men.

03:36:02.231 --> 03:36:07.411
At about the center of the oaken panels that lined the hall was suspended a suit of mail,

03:36:07.831 --> 03:36:13.551
not like the pictures an ancestral relic, but of the most modern date, for it had been

03:36:13.551 --> 03:36:19.251
manufactured by a skilful armorer in London, the same year in which Governor Bellingham

03:36:19.251 --> 03:36:20.771
came over to New England.

03:36:20.771 --> 03:36:27.331
There was a steel headpiece, a cuirass, a gorget and greaves, and a pair of gauntlets

03:36:27.331 --> 03:36:29.051
and a sword hanging beneath.

03:36:29.831 --> 03:36:34.791
All and especially the helmet and breast-plate so highly burnished as to glow with white

03:36:34.791 --> 03:36:39.131
radiance, and scatter an illumination everywhere about upon the floor.

03:36:39.711 --> 03:36:44.951
This bright panoply was not meant for mere idle show, but had been worn by the governor

03:36:44.951 --> 03:36:50.071
on many a solemn muster and training-field, and had glittered moreover at the head of

03:36:50.071 --> 03:36:51.891
the regiment in the Pequod War.

03:36:52.331 --> 03:36:58.171
For though bred a lawyer, and accustomed to speak of Bacon, Coke, Noy, and Finch as his

03:36:58.171 --> 03:37:03.431
professional associates, the exigencies of this new country had transformed Governor

03:37:03.431 --> 03:37:07.751
Bellingham into a soldier, as well as a statesman and ruler.

03:37:09.471 --> 03:37:14.011
Little Pearl, who was as greatly pleased with the gleaming armor as she had been with the

03:37:14.011 --> 03:37:18.711
glittering frontispiece of the house, spent some time looking into the polished mirror

03:37:18.711 --> 03:37:19.791
of the breast-plate.

03:37:20.231 --> 03:37:22.131
"'Mother,' cried she, "'I see you here.

03:37:22.231 --> 03:37:22.631
Look!

03:37:23.911 --> 03:37:24.551
Look!'

03:37:24.551 --> 03:37:29.891
Hester looked by way of humouring the child, and she saw that, owing to the peculiar effect

03:37:29.891 --> 03:37:35.331
of this convex mirror, the scarlet letter was represented in exaggerated and gigantic

03:37:35.331 --> 03:37:39.831
proportions, so as to be greatly the most prominent feature of her appearance.

03:37:40.351 --> 03:37:43.411
In truth, she seemed absolutely hidden behind it.

03:37:43.831 --> 03:37:49.371
Pearl pointed upwards also at a similar picture in the headpiece, smiling at her mother with

03:37:49.371 --> 03:37:53.951
the elvish intelligence that was so familiar an expression to her small physiognomy.

03:37:54.651 --> 03:37:59.711
That look of naughty merriment was likewise reflected in the mirror, with so much breadth

03:37:59.711 --> 03:38:04.171
and intensity of effect that it made Hester Prynne feel as if it could not be the image

03:38:04.171 --> 03:38:09.631
of her own child, but of an imp who was seeking to mold itself into Pearl's shape.

03:38:10.751 --> 03:38:13.371
"'Come along, Pearl,' said she, drawing her away.

03:38:13.551 --> 03:38:15.611
"'Come and look into this fair garden.

03:38:15.731 --> 03:38:20.751
It may be we shall see flowers there—more beautiful ones than we find in the woods.'

03:38:20.751 --> 03:38:25.531
Pearl accordingly ran to the bow-window at the further end of the hall, and looked along

03:38:25.531 --> 03:38:30.691
the vista of a garden-walk, carpeted with closely shaven grass, and bordered with some

03:38:30.691 --> 03:38:33.031
rude and immature attempt at shrubbery.

03:38:33.371 --> 03:38:38.531
But the proprietor appeared already to have relinquished as hopeless the effort to perpetuate

03:38:38.531 --> 03:38:44.091
on this side of the Atlantic, in a hard soil, and amid the close struggle for subsistence,

03:38:44.511 --> 03:38:47.251
the native English taste for ornamental gardening.

03:38:48.051 --> 03:38:53.911
Cabages grew in plain sight, and a pumpkin-vine, rooted at some distance, had run across the

03:38:53.911 --> 03:38:59.151
intervening space and deposited one of its gigantic products directly beneath the hall-window,

03:38:59.251 --> 03:39:04.511
as if to warn the governor that this great lump of vegetable gold was as rich an ornament

03:39:04.511 --> 03:39:06.511
as New England earth would offer him.

03:39:06.511 --> 03:39:12.091
There were a few rose-bushes, however, and a number of apple-trees, probably the descendants

03:39:12.091 --> 03:39:18.671
of those planted by the reverend Mr. Blackstone, the first settler of the peninsula, that half-mythological

03:39:18.671 --> 03:39:22.771
personage who rides through our early annals seated on the back of a bull.

03:39:23.711 --> 03:39:28.511
Pearl, seeing the rose-bushes, began to cry for a red rose, and would not be pacified.

03:39:29.491 --> 03:39:32.071
"'Hush, child, hush!' said her mother earnestly.

03:39:32.071 --> 03:39:33.771
"'Do not cry, dear little Pearl.

03:39:33.871 --> 03:39:35.471
I hear voices in the garden.

03:39:35.631 --> 03:39:39.711
The governor is coming, and gentlemen along with him.'

03:39:39.711 --> 03:39:45.091
In fact, down the vista of the garden avenue, a number of persons were seen approaching

03:39:45.091 --> 03:39:46.191
towards the house.

03:39:46.711 --> 03:39:52.391
Pearl, in utter scorn of her mother's attempt to quiet her, gave an eldritch scream, and

03:39:52.391 --> 03:39:57.511
then became silent, not from any notion of obedience, but because the quick and mobile

03:39:57.511 --> 03:40:02.851
curiosity of her disposition was excited by the appearance of those new personages.

03:40:33.151 --> 03:40:38.291
Recorded by George Pilling. www.Storiesales.com

03:40:39.191 --> 03:40:44.331
The Scarlet Letter, Chapter 8, The Elf Child and the Minister

03:40:45.631 --> 03:40:52.931
Governor Bellingham, in a loose gown and easy cap, such as elderly gentlemen love to undo themselves with in their domestic privacy,

03:40:53.651 --> 03:40:59.051
walked foremost and appeared to be showing off his estate and expatiating on his projected improvements.

03:40:59.991 --> 03:41:05.771
The wide circumference of an elaborate ruff beneath his gray beard in the antiquated fashion of King James' reign

03:41:05.771 --> 03:41:09.771
caused his head to look not a little like that of John the Baptist in a charger.

03:41:10.371 --> 03:41:16.331
The impression made by his aspect, so rigid and severe, and frostbitten with more than autumnal age,

03:41:16.811 --> 03:41:22.611
was hardly in keeping with the appliances of worldly enjoyment wherewith he had evidently done his utmost to surround himself.

03:41:23.531 --> 03:41:31.671
But it is an error to suppose that our grave forefathers, though accustomed to speak and think of human existence as a state merely of trial and warfare,

03:41:32.271 --> 03:41:36.351
and though unfeignedly prepared to sacrifice goods and life at the behest of duty,

03:41:36.351 --> 03:41:43.691
made it a matter of conscience to reject such means of comfort or even luxury as lay fairly within their grasp.

03:41:44.771 --> 03:41:50.431
This creed was never taught, for instance, by the venerable Pastor John Wilson, whose beard, white as a snowdrift,

03:41:50.491 --> 03:41:57.811
was seen over Governor Bellingham's shoulder while its wearer suggested that pears and peaches might yet be naturalized in the New England climate

03:41:57.811 --> 03:42:02.811
and that purple grapes might possibly be compelled to flourish against the sunny garden wall.

03:42:03.431 --> 03:42:11.891
The old clergyman, nurtured at the rich bosom of the English Church, had a long-established and legitimate taste for all good and comfortable things,

03:42:12.271 --> 03:42:18.831
and however stern he might show himself in the pulpit or in his public reproof of such transgressions as that of Hester Prynne,

03:42:19.671 --> 03:42:27.071
still the genial benevolence of his private life had won him warmer affection than was accorded to any of his professional contemporaries.

03:42:28.191 --> 03:42:31.211
Behind the Governor and Mr. Wilson came two other guests.

03:42:31.771 --> 03:42:39.651
One, the Reverend Arthur Dimmesdale, whom the reader may remember as having taken a brief and reluctant part in the scene of Hester Prynne's disgrace,

03:42:39.991 --> 03:42:50.271
and, in close companionship with him, old Roger Chillingworth, a person of great skill in physics, who, for two or three years past, had been settled in the town.

03:42:50.271 --> 03:42:55.651
It was understood that this learned man was the physician as well as friend of the young minister,

03:42:56.171 --> 03:43:03.711
whose health had severely suffered of late by his too unreserved self-sacrifice to the labors and duties of the pastoral relation.

03:43:05.331 --> 03:43:13.851
The Governor, in advance of his visitors, ascended one or two steps, and, throwing open the leaves of the great hall window, found himself close to Little Pearl.

03:43:14.391 --> 03:43:18.551
The shadow of the curtain fell on Hester Prynne and partially concealed her.

03:43:19.531 --> 03:43:25.911
What have we here? said Governor Bellingham, looking with surprise at the scarlet little figure before him.

03:43:26.351 --> 03:43:35.451
Ay, profess, I have never seen the like since my days of vanity in old King James's time, when I was wont to esteem it in high favour to be admitted to a court-mask.

03:43:35.951 --> 03:43:41.951
There used to be a swarm of these small apparitions in holiday time, and we called them children of the Lord of Misrule.

03:43:42.411 --> 03:43:44.591
But how got such a guest into my hall?

03:43:46.151 --> 03:43:52.051
Ay, indeed, cried good old Mr. Wilson, what little bird of scarlet plumage may this be?

03:43:52.511 --> 03:44:00.651
Methinks I have seen just such figures when the sun has been shining through a richly painted window and tracing out the golden and crimson images across the floor.

03:44:01.271 --> 03:44:04.731
But that was in the old land. Pretty young one, who art thou?

03:44:04.971 --> 03:44:10.771
And what has ailed thy mother to betisen thee in this strange fashion? Art thou a Christian child? Ah?

03:44:10.771 --> 03:44:20.571
Dost thou know thy catechism? Or art thou one of those naughty elves or fairies whom we thought to have left behind us with other relics of papistry in merry old England?

03:44:21.851 --> 03:44:27.051
I am my mother's child, answered the scarlet vision, and my name is Pearl.

03:44:28.571 --> 03:44:39.471
Pearl? Ruby, rather, or Carl, or Red Rose, at the very least, judging from my hue, responded the old minister, putting forth his hand in vain attempt to pat little Pearl on the cheek.

03:44:39.471 --> 03:44:46.891
But where is this mother of thine? Ah, I see, he added, and turning to the governor, Bellingham whispered,

03:44:47.171 --> 03:44:54.311
This is the self-same child of whom we have held speech together, and behold, here the unhappy woman has to bring her mother.

03:44:55.771 --> 03:45:04.131
Sayest thou so? cried the governor. Nay, we might have judged that such a child's mother must need be a scarlet woman, and a worthy type of her of Babylon.

03:45:04.531 --> 03:45:07.951
But she comes at a good time, and we will look into this matter forthwith.

03:45:08.751 --> 03:45:12.731
Governor Bellingham stepped through the window into the hall, followed by his three guests.

03:45:14.191 --> 03:45:19.371
Hester Prynne, said he, fixing his naturally stern regard on the wearer of the scarlet letter,

03:45:19.711 --> 03:45:27.191
There hath been much question concerning thee of late. The point hath been weightily discussed whether we, that are of authority and influence,

03:45:27.331 --> 03:45:37.211
To well discharge our consciences by trusting in a mortal soul, such as there is in yonder child, to the guidance of one who has stumbled and fallen amid the pitfalls of this world.

03:45:37.211 --> 03:45:43.671
Speak thou, the child's own mother. Were it not, thinkest thou, for thy little one's temporal and eternal welfare,

03:45:43.991 --> 03:45:53.851
That she be taken out of thy charge, and clad soberly, and disciplined strictly, and instructed in the truths of heaven and earth, what canst thou do for the child in this kind?

03:45:54.731 --> 03:46:01.591
I can teach my little pearl what I have learned from this, answered Hester Prynne, laying her finger on the red token.

03:46:01.591 --> 03:46:06.411
Woman, it is thy badge of shame, replied the stern magistrate.

03:46:06.791 --> 03:46:12.131
It is because of the stain which that letter indicates that we would transfer thy child to other hands.

03:46:13.531 --> 03:46:20.011
Nevertheless, said the mother calmly, though growing more pale, this badge hath taught me.

03:46:20.531 --> 03:46:30.711
It daily teaches me. It is teaching me at this moment lessons whereof my child may be the wiser and better, albeit they can profit nothing to myself.

03:46:31.851 --> 03:46:37.271
We will judge warily, said Bellingham, and look well what we are about to do.

03:46:37.631 --> 03:46:46.491
Good Master Wilson, I pray you, examine this pearl, since that is her name, and see whether she hath had such Christian nurture as befits a child of her age.

03:46:47.431 --> 03:46:52.651
The old minister seated himself in an armchair, and made an effort to draw pearl betwixt his knees.

03:46:52.651 --> 03:46:59.611
But the child, unaccustomed to the touch of familiarity of any but her mother, escaped through the open window,

03:46:59.951 --> 03:47:06.411
and stood on the upper step looking like a wild tropical bird of rich plumage, ready to take flight into the upper air.

03:47:07.591 --> 03:47:15.591
Mr. Wilson, not a little astonished at this outbreak, for he was a grandfatherly sort of personage, and usually a vast favorite with children,

03:47:16.331 --> 03:47:18.571
assayed, however, to proceed with the examination.

03:47:19.611 --> 03:47:29.751
Pearl, said he with great solemnity, thou must take heed to instruction, that so in due season thou mayest wherein thy bosom the pearl of great price.

03:47:30.291 --> 03:47:32.971
Canst thou tell me, my child, who made thee?

03:47:33.991 --> 03:47:42.571
Now Pearl knew well enough who made her, for Hester Prynne, the daughter of a pious home, very soon after her talk with the child about her heavenly father,

03:47:42.571 --> 03:47:50.271
had begun to inform her of those truths which the human spirit, at whatever stage of immaturity, imbibes with such eager interest.

03:47:51.131 --> 03:47:58.671
Pearl, therefore, so large were the attainments of her three years' lifetime, could have borne a fair examination in the New England Primer,

03:47:59.031 --> 03:48:05.731
or the first column of the Westminster Catechisms, although unacquainted with the outward form of either of those celebrated works.

03:48:06.411 --> 03:48:15.751
But that perversity which all children have more or less of, and of which little Pearl had a tenfold portion, now, at the most inopportune moment,

03:48:16.111 --> 03:48:21.031
took a thorough possession of her, and closed her lips, or impelled her to speak words amiss.

03:48:21.471 --> 03:48:26.931
After putting her finger in her mouth, with many ungracious refusals to answer good Mr. Wilson's questions,

03:48:27.431 --> 03:48:34.551
the child finally announced that she had not been made at all, but had been plucked by her mother off a bush of wild roses that grew by the prison door.

03:48:35.491 --> 03:48:42.071
This fantasy was probably suggested by the near proximity of the governor's red roses, as Pearl stood outside of the window,

03:48:42.471 --> 03:48:46.571
together with the recollection of the prison rose bush which she had passed in coming hither.

03:48:48.411 --> 03:48:53.351
Old Roger Chillingworth, with a smile on his face, whispered something in the young clergyman's ear.

03:48:53.891 --> 03:49:01.771
Hester Prynne looked at the man of skill, and even then, with her fate hanging in the balance, was startled to perceive what a change had come over his features,

03:49:01.771 --> 03:49:11.291
how much uglier they were, how his dark complexion seemed to have grown duskier, and his figure more misshapen, since the days when she had familiarly known him.

03:49:11.831 --> 03:49:17.631
She met his eyes for an instant, but was immediately constrained to give all her attention to the scene now going forward.

03:49:18.871 --> 03:49:25.571
This is awful! cried the governor, slowly recovering from the astonishment into which Pearl's response had thrown him.

03:49:25.571 --> 03:49:36.011
Here is a child of three years old, and she cannot tell who made her. Without question she is equally in the dark as to her soul, its present depravity, and future destiny.

03:49:36.451 --> 03:49:38.691
Methinks, gentlemen, we need inquire no further.

03:49:39.651 --> 03:49:45.751
Hester caught hold of Pearl and drew her forcibly into her arms, confronting the old puritan magistrate with almost a fierce expression.

03:49:46.551 --> 03:49:58.191
Alone in the world, cast off by it, and with this sole treasure to keep her heart alive, she felt that she possessed indefeasible rights against the world, and was ready to defend them to the death.

03:49:59.051 --> 03:50:09.651
God gave me this child, cried she. He gave her in requital of all things else, which he had taken from me. She is my happiness. She is my torture nonetheless.

03:50:10.311 --> 03:50:25.011
Pearl keeps me here in life. Pearl punishes me too. See ye not, she is the scarlet letter, only capable of being loved, and so endowed with a millionfold the power of retribution for my sin? Ye shall not take her. I will die first.

03:50:25.771 --> 03:50:33.571
My poor woman, said the not unkind old minister, the child shall be well cared for, far better than thou can do it.

03:50:34.311 --> 03:50:41.571
God gave her into my keeping, repeated Hester Prynne, raising her voice almost to a shriek. I will not give her up.

03:50:42.131 --> 03:50:50.911
And here, by a sudden impulse, she turned to the young clergyman, Mr. Dimmesdale, at whom, up to this moment, she had seemed hardly so much as once to direct her eyes.

03:50:51.811 --> 03:51:01.631
Speak thou for me, cried she. Thou wast my pastor, and hadst charge of my soul, and knowest me better than these men can. I will not lose the child.

03:51:02.011 --> 03:51:17.331
Speak for me, thou knowest, for thou hast sympathies which these men lack. Thou knowest what is in my heart, and what are a mother's rights, and how much the stronger they are when that mother has but her child in the scarlet letter. Look thou to it. I will not lose the child. Look to it.

03:51:17.991 --> 03:51:34.331
At this wild and singular appeal, which indicated that Hester Prynne's situation had provoked her to little less than madness, the young minister at once came forward, pale, and holding his hand over his heart as was his custom whenever his peculiarly nervous temperament was thrown into agitation.

03:51:34.331 --> 03:51:49.451
He looked now more careworn and emaciated than as we described him at the scene of Hester's public ignominy, and whether it were his failing health or whatever the cause might be, his large dark eyes had a world of pain in their troubled and melancholy depth.

03:51:50.951 --> 03:52:06.411
There is truth in what she says, began the minister with a voice sweet, tremulous, but powerful, insomuch that the hall re-echoed, and the hollow armor rang with it. The truth in what Hester says, and in the feeling which inspires her.

03:52:06.411 --> 03:52:23.791
God gave her the child, and gave her too an instinctive knowledge of its nature and requirements, both seemingly so peculiar, which no other mortal being can possess. And moreover, is there not a quality of awful sacredness in the relation between this mother and this child?

03:52:24.751 --> 03:52:31.111
I? How is that, good Master Dimmesdale? interrupted the governor. Make it plain, I pray you.

03:52:31.871 --> 03:52:48.571
It must be even so, resumed the minister. For if we deem it otherwise, do we not thereby say that the Heavenly Father, the Creator of all flesh, hath lightly recognized the deed of sin, and made of no account the distinction between unhallowed lust and holy love?

03:52:48.571 --> 03:53:01.271
This child, of its father's guilt and its mother's shame, hath come from the hand of God, to work in many ways upon her heart, who plead so earnestly, and with such bitterness of spirit, the right to keep her.

03:53:01.271 --> 03:53:23.851
It was meant for a blessing, for the mother herself hath told us, for a retribution too, a torture to be felt at many an unthought of moment, a pang, a sting, an ever recurring agony, in the midst of a troubled joy. Has she not expressed this thought in the garb of the poor child, so forcibly reminding us of that red symbol which sears her bosom?

03:53:25.011 --> 03:53:31.611
Well said again, cried good Mr. Wilson. I feared the woman had no better thought than to make a multibank of a child.

03:53:32.411 --> 03:53:57.271
Oh no, not so, not so, continued Mr. Dimmesdale. She recognizes, believe me, the solemn miracle which God hath wrought in the existence of that child. And may she feel too, what methinks is the very truth, that this boon was meant, above all things else, to keep the mother's soul alive, and to preserve her from blacker depths of sin into which Satan might else have sought to plunge her.

03:53:57.271 --> 03:54:21.291
Therefore it is good for this poor sinful woman that she hath an infant immortality, a being capable of eternal joy or sorrow, confided to her care, to be trained up by her to righteousness, to remind her at every moment of her fall, but yet to teach her, as it were by the Creator's sacred pledge, that if she bring the child to heaven, the child also will bring its parent thither.

03:54:21.911 --> 03:54:33.391
Herein is the sinful mother happier than the sinful father, for Hester Prynne's sake then, and no less for the poor child's sake. Let us leave them as Providence hath seen fit to place them.

03:54:34.371 --> 03:54:40.851
You speak, my friend, with a strange earnestness, said old Roger Chillingworth, smiling at him.

03:54:41.551 --> 03:54:51.471
And there is weighty import in what my young brother hath spoken, added the Reverend Mr. Wilson. What say you, worshipful Master Bellingham? Hath he not pleaded well for the poor woman?

03:54:52.351 --> 03:55:17.771
Indeed, hath he, answered the magistrate, and hath adduced such arguments that we will even leave the matter as it now stands, so long, at least as there shall be no further scandal in the woman. Care must be had, nevertheless, to put the child to due and stated examination in the catechism, at thy hands, our Master Dimmesdale's. Moreover, at a proper season, the tithing men must take heed that she go both to school and to meeting.

03:55:18.671 --> 03:55:33.491
The young minister, on ceasing to speak, had withdrawn a few steps from the group, and stood with his face partially concealed in the heavy folds of the window curtains, while the shadow of his figure, which the sunlight cast upon the floor, was tremulous with the vehemence of his appeal.

03:55:34.131 --> 03:55:51.491
Pearl, that wild and flighty little elf, stole softly towards him, and taking his hand in the grasp of both her own, laid her cheek against it, a caress so tender and withal so unobtrusive, that her mother, who was looking on, asked herself, Is that my pearl?

03:55:52.091 --> 03:56:02.151
Yet she knew that there was love in the child's heart, although it mostly revealed itself in passion, and hardly twice in her lifetime had been softened by such gentleness as now.

03:56:02.811 --> 03:56:16.831
The minister, for save the long sought regards of woman, nothing is sweeter than those marks of childish preference, accorded spontaneously by a spiritual instinct, and therefore seeming to imply in us something truly worthy to be loved.

03:56:16.831 --> 03:56:34.751
The minister looked round, laid his hand on the child's head, hesitated an instant, and then kissed her brow. Little Pearl's unwanted mood of sentiment lasted no longer. She laughed, and went capering down the hall so airily that old Mr. Wilson raised a question whether even her tiptoes touched the floor.

03:56:36.151 --> 03:56:43.651
The little baggage hath witchcraft in her, I profess, said he to Mr. Dimmesdale. She needs no old woman's broomstick to fly withal.

03:56:44.571 --> 03:57:00.191
As strange child, remarked old Roger Chillingworth, it is easy to see the mother's part in her. Would it be beyond a philosopher's research, think ye, gentlemen, to analyze that child's nature, and from its make and mould to give shrewd guess at the father?

03:57:01.711 --> 03:57:22.571
Nay, it would be sinful in such a question to follow the clue of profane philosophy, said Mr. Wilson. Better to fast and pray upon it, and still better, it may be, to leave the mystery as we find it, unless Providence reveal it of its own accord. Thereby every good Christian man hath a title to show a father's kindness toward the poor deserted babe.

03:57:23.411 --> 03:57:45.191
The affair being so satisfactorily concluded, Hester Prynne, with pearl, departed from the house. As they descended the steps, it is averred that the lattice of a chamber window was thrown open, and forth into the sunny day was thrust the face of Mr. Sibyn's, Governor Bellingham's bitter-tempered sister, and the same who, a few years later, was executed as a witch.

03:57:45.971 --> 03:58:02.411
Hissed, hissed, said she, while her ill-omened physiognomy seemed to cast a shadow over the cheerful newness of the house. Will thou go with us to-night? There will be a merry company in the forest, and I will nigh promise the black man that comely Hester Prynne should make one.

03:58:03.431 --> 03:58:20.091
Make my excuse to him, so please you, answered Hester, with a triumphant smile. I must tarry at home, and keep watch over my little pearl. Had they taken her from me, I would willingly have gone with thee into the forest, and signed my name in the black man's book too, and that with mine own blood.

03:58:21.031 --> 03:58:26.071
We shall have thee there anon, said the witch-lady, frowning, as she drew back her head.

03:58:26.851 --> 03:58:44.691
But here, if we suppose this interview betwixt Mr. Sibyn's and Hester Prynne to be authentic and not a parable, was already an illustration of the young minister's argument against sundering the relation of a fallen mother to the offspring of her frailty. Even thus early had the child saved her from Satan's snare.

03:59:17.339 --> 03:59:21.819
Under the appellation of Roger Chillingworth, the reader will remember, was hidden another

03:59:21.819 --> 03:59:25.519
name, which its former wearer had resolved should never more be spoken.

03:59:26.099 --> 03:59:30.819
It has been related how, in the crowd that witnessed Hester Prynne's ignominious exposure,

03:59:31.119 --> 03:59:37.239
stood a man, elderly, travel-worn, who, just emerging from the perilous wilderness, beheld

03:59:37.239 --> 03:59:42.399
the woman, in whom he hoped to find embodied the warmth and cheerfulness of home, set up

03:59:42.399 --> 03:59:44.379
as a type of sin before the people.

03:59:44.979 --> 03:59:47.779
Her matrimonial frame was trodden under all men's feet.

03:59:48.419 --> 03:59:51.139
Infamy was babbling around her in the public marketplace.

03:59:51.879 --> 03:59:56.859
For her kindred, should the tidings ever reach them, and for the companions of her unspotted

03:59:56.859 --> 04:00:01.879
life, there remained nothing but the contagion of her dishonor, which would not fail to be

04:00:01.879 --> 04:00:06.699
distributed in strict accordance and proportion with the intimacy and sacredness of their

04:00:06.699 --> 04:00:07.839
previous relationship.

04:00:08.579 --> 04:00:14.259
Then why, since a choice was with themself, should the individual, whose connection with

04:00:14.259 --> 04:00:18.919
fallen woman had been the most intimate and sacred of them all, come forward to vindicate

04:00:18.919 --> 04:00:21.799
his claim to an inheritance so little desirable?

04:00:22.539 --> 04:00:25.979
He resolved not to be pilloried beside her on the pedestal of shame.

04:00:26.719 --> 04:00:32.159
Unknown to all but Hester Prynne, and possessing the lock and key of her silence, he chose

04:00:32.159 --> 04:00:38.099
to withdraw his name from the role of mankind, and, as regarded his former ties and interests,

04:00:38.239 --> 04:00:42.279
to vanish out of life as completely as if he indeed lay at the bottom of the ocean,

04:00:42.729 --> 04:00:45.239
with a rumor had long ago consigned him.

04:00:45.819 --> 04:00:50.799
This purpose, once effected, new interests would immediately spring up, and likewise

04:00:50.799 --> 04:00:56.879
a new purpose, dark, it is true, if not guilty, but of force enough to engage the full strength

04:00:56.879 --> 04:00:58.119
of his faculties.

04:00:59.439 --> 04:01:05.179
In pursuance of this resolve, he took up his residence in the Puritan town as Roger Chillingworth,

04:01:05.519 --> 04:01:09.559
without other introduction than the learning and intelligence of which he possessed more

04:01:09.559 --> 04:01:10.539
than a common measure.

04:01:11.259 --> 04:01:15.439
As his studies, at a previous period of his life, had made him extensively acquainted

04:01:15.439 --> 04:01:20.099
with the medical science of the day, it was as a physician that he presented himself,

04:01:20.499 --> 04:01:22.639
and as such was cordially received.

04:01:23.539 --> 04:01:28.239
Skillful men of the medical and chirurgical profession were of rare occurrence in the

04:01:28.239 --> 04:01:28.559
colony.

04:01:29.199 --> 04:01:33.459
They seldom, it would appear, partook of the religious zeal that brought other emigrants

04:01:33.459 --> 04:01:34.359
across the Atlantic.

04:01:34.859 --> 04:01:39.939
In their researches into the human frame, it may be that the higher and more subtle

04:01:39.939 --> 04:01:44.799
faculties of such men were materialized, and that they lost the spiritual view of

04:01:44.799 --> 04:01:49.799
existence amid the intricacies of that wondrous mechanism which seemed to involve art enough

04:01:49.799 --> 04:01:52.379
to comprise all of life within itself.

04:01:53.099 --> 04:01:57.719
At all events, the health of the good town of Boston, so far as medicine had ought to

04:01:57.719 --> 04:02:03.539
do with it, had hitherto lain in the guardianship of an aged deacon and apothecary whose piety

04:02:03.539 --> 04:02:08.439
and godly deportment were stronger testimonials in his favor than any that he could have produced

04:02:08.439 --> 04:02:09.659
in the shape of a diploma.

04:02:10.319 --> 04:02:15.179
The only surgeon was one who combined the occasional exercise of that noble art with

04:02:15.179 --> 04:02:17.379
the daily and habitual flourish of a razor.

04:02:18.099 --> 04:02:22.559
To such a professional body, Roger Chillingworth was a brilliant acquisition.

04:02:23.399 --> 04:02:28.579
He soon manifested his familiarity with the ponderous and imposing machinery of antique

04:02:28.579 --> 04:02:33.659
physics in which every remedy contained a multitude of far-fetched and heterogeneous

04:02:33.659 --> 04:02:39.959
has elaborately compounded as if the proposed result had been the elixir of life.

04:02:41.019 --> 04:02:46.359
In his Indian captivity, moreover, he had gained much knowledge of the properties of

04:02:46.359 --> 04:02:51.419
native herbs and roots, nor did he conceal from his patients that these simple medicines,

04:02:51.959 --> 04:02:56.979
nature's boon to the untutored savage, had quite as large a share of his own confidence

04:02:56.979 --> 04:03:02.719
as the European pharmacopoeia, with so many learned doctors, had spent centuries in elaborating.

04:03:04.279 --> 04:03:09.019
This learned stranger was exemplary as regarded at least the outward forms of a religious

04:03:09.019 --> 04:03:14.259
life, and early after his arrival had chosen for a spiritual guide the Reverend Mr. Dimmesdale.

04:03:14.899 --> 04:03:19.819
The young divine, whose scholar-like renown still lived in Oxford, was considered by his

04:03:19.819 --> 04:03:25.279
more fervent admirers as little less than a heavenly ordained apostle, destined, should

04:03:25.279 --> 04:03:30.659
he live and labor for the ordinary term of life to do as great deeds for the now feeble

04:03:30.659 --> 04:03:35.159
New England Church as the early Fathers had achieved for the infancy of the Christian

04:03:35.159 --> 04:03:35.459
faith.

04:03:36.319 --> 04:03:41.279
About this period, however, the health of Mr. Dimmesdale had evidently begun to fail.

04:03:41.839 --> 04:03:46.019
By those best acquainted with his habits, the paleness of the young minister's cheek

04:03:46.019 --> 04:03:52.019
was accounted for by his too earnest devotion to study, his scrupulous fulfillment of parochial

04:03:52.019 --> 04:03:57.479
duty, and more than all to the fasts and vigils of which he made a frequent practice

04:03:57.479 --> 04:04:02.939
in order to keep the grossness of this earthly state from clogging and obscuring his spiritual

04:04:02.939 --> 04:04:03.299
lamp.

04:04:04.039 --> 04:04:08.479
Some declared that if Mr. Dimmesdale were really going to die, it was cause enough that

04:04:08.479 --> 04:04:11.579
the world was not worthy to be any longer trodden by his feet.

04:04:12.359 --> 04:04:17.739
He himself, on the other hand, with characteristic humility, avowed his belief that if Providence

04:04:18.259 --> 04:04:23.379
to remove him, it would be because of his own unworthiness to perform its humblest mission

04:04:23.379 --> 04:04:24.119
here on earth.

04:04:24.679 --> 04:04:29.399
With all this difference of opinion as the cause of his decline, there could be no question

04:04:29.399 --> 04:04:30.059
of the fact.

04:04:31.079 --> 04:04:37.759
His form grew emaciated, his voice, though still rich and sweet, had a certain melancholy

04:04:37.759 --> 04:04:39.219
prophecy of decay in it.

04:04:39.399 --> 04:04:44.499
He was often observed, on any slight alarm or other sudden accident, to put his hand

04:04:44.499 --> 04:04:49.979
over his heart, with first a flush and then a paleness, indicative of pain.

04:04:51.479 --> 04:04:56.039
Such was the young clergyman's condition, and so imminent the prospect that his dawning

04:04:56.039 --> 04:05:00.979
light would be extinguished all untimely when Roger Chillingworth made his advent to the

04:05:00.979 --> 04:05:01.239
town.

04:05:01.899 --> 04:05:06.959
His first entry on the scene, few people could tell whence, dropping down, as it were, out

04:05:06.959 --> 04:05:11.879
of the sky or starting from the nether earth, had an aspect of mystery which was easily

04:05:11.879 --> 04:05:13.159
heightened to the miraculous.

04:05:13.639 --> 04:05:15.739
He was now known to be a man of skill.

04:05:16.119 --> 04:05:21.179
It was observed that he gathered herbs and the blossoms of wildflowers, and dug up roots

04:05:21.179 --> 04:05:25.739
and plucked off twigs from the forest trees like one acquainted with hidden virtues in

04:05:25.739 --> 04:05:27.619
what was valueless to common eyes.

04:05:28.159 --> 04:05:34.059
He was heard to speak of Sir Kenneth Dinkby and other famous men, whose scientific attainments

04:05:34.059 --> 04:05:39.259
were esteemed hardly less than supernatural, as having been his correspondents or associates.

04:05:39.899 --> 04:05:43.679
Why was such rank in the learned world had he come hither?

04:05:44.359 --> 04:05:48.499
What could he, whose fear was in great cities, be seeking in the wilderness?

04:05:49.299 --> 04:05:54.639
In answer to this query, a rumor gained ground, and however absurd, was entertained by some

04:05:54.639 --> 04:06:01.339
very sensible people, that heaven had wrought an absolute miracle by transporting an eminent

04:06:01.339 --> 04:06:06.679
doctor of physics from a German university bodily through the air and setting him down

04:06:06.679 --> 04:06:08.839
at the door of Mr. Dimmesdale's study.

04:06:10.439 --> 04:06:14.899
Individuals of wiser faith, indeed, who knew that heaven promotes its purposes without

04:06:14.899 --> 04:06:19.579
aiming at the stage effect of what is called miraculous interposition, were inclined to

04:06:19.579 --> 04:06:23.039
see a providential hand in Roger Chillingworth's so opportune arrival.

04:06:24.659 --> 04:06:29.939
This idea was countenanced by the strong interest which the physician ever manifested in the

04:06:29.939 --> 04:06:30.739
young clergyman.

04:06:31.079 --> 04:06:36.279
He attached himself to him as a parishioner, and sought to win a friendly regard and confidence

04:06:36.279 --> 04:06:38.319
from his naturally reserved sensibility.

04:06:38.939 --> 04:06:43.379
He expressed great alarm at his pastor's state of health, but was anxious to attempt

04:06:43.379 --> 04:06:48.299
the cure, and if early undertaken, seemed not despondent of a favorable result.

04:06:48.879 --> 04:06:54.999
The elders, the deacons, the motherly dames, and the young and fair maidens of Mr. Dimmesdale's

04:06:54.999 --> 04:06:59.999
flock were alike importunate that he should make trial of the physician's frankly offered

04:06:59.999 --> 04:07:00.379
skill.

04:07:01.419 --> 04:07:04.359
Mr. Dimmesdale gently repelled their entreaties.

04:07:05.219 --> 04:07:08.279
I need no medicine, said he.

04:07:09.539 --> 04:07:14.699
But how could the young minister say so, when with every successive Sabbath his cheek was

04:07:14.699 --> 04:07:20.259
paler and thinner, and his voice more tremulous than before, when it had now become a constant

04:07:20.259 --> 04:07:24.719
habit rather than a casual gesture to press his hand over his heart?

04:07:25.299 --> 04:07:26.899
Was he weary of his labors?

04:07:27.279 --> 04:07:28.619
Did he wish to die?

04:07:29.299 --> 04:07:33.659
These questions were solemnly propounded to Mr. Dimmesdale by the elder ministers of

04:07:33.659 --> 04:07:40.039
Boston and the deacons of his church, who, to use their own phrase, dealt with him on

04:07:40.039 --> 04:07:43.839
the sin of rejecting the aid which Providence so manifestly held out.

04:07:44.259 --> 04:07:48.239
He listened in silence, and finally promised to confer with the physician.

04:07:49.959 --> 04:07:55.999
Were it God's will, said the Reverend Mr. Dimmesdale, when, in fulfillment of this pledge,

04:07:56.059 --> 04:08:02.719
he requested old Roger Chillingworth's professional advice, I could well be content that my labors

04:08:02.719 --> 04:08:07.659
and my sorrows and my sins and my pains should shortly end with me.

04:08:08.279 --> 04:08:12.879
And what is earthly of them to be buried in my grave, and the spiritual go with me to

04:08:12.879 --> 04:08:18.379
my eternal state, rather than that you should put your skill to the proof in my behalf?

04:08:20.599 --> 04:08:26.659
Ah, replied Roger Chillingworth, with that quietness, which, whether imposed or natural,

04:08:27.039 --> 04:08:31.619
marked all his deportment, it is thus that a young clergyman is apt to speak.

04:08:32.339 --> 04:08:39.179
Youthful men, not having taken a deep route, give up their hold of life so easily, and

04:08:39.179 --> 04:08:44.439
saintly men who walk with God on earth would fain be away to walk with him on the golden

04:08:44.439 --> 04:08:45.979
pavements of the New Jerusalem.

04:08:47.139 --> 04:08:51.579
Nay, rejoined the young minister, putting his hand to his heart with a flush of pain

04:08:51.579 --> 04:08:56.959
flitting over his brow, were I worthier to walk there, I could be better content to toil

04:08:56.959 --> 04:08:57.539
here.

04:08:58.419 --> 04:09:02.639
Good men ever interpret themselves too meanly, said the physician.

04:09:04.859 --> 04:09:10.339
In this manner, the mysterious old Roger Chillingworth became the medical advisor of the Reverend

04:09:10.339 --> 04:09:11.379
Mr. Dimmesdale.

04:09:12.139 --> 04:09:17.459
As not only the disease interested the physician, but he was strongly moved to look into the

04:09:17.459 --> 04:09:23.239
character and qualities of the patient, these two men, so different in age, came gradually

04:09:23.239 --> 04:09:25.159
to spend much time together.

04:09:25.679 --> 04:09:29.859
For the sake of the minister's health, and to enable the leech to gather plants with

04:09:29.859 --> 04:09:35.439
healing balm in them, they took long walks on the seashore, or in the forest, mingling

04:09:35.439 --> 04:09:40.019
various walks with the splash and murmur of the waves and the solemn wind anthem among

04:09:40.019 --> 04:09:41.519
the treetops.

04:09:41.699 --> 04:09:46.379
Often, likewise, one was a guest of the other in his place of study and retirement.

04:09:46.879 --> 04:09:51.319
There was a fascination for the minister in the company of the man of science, in whom

04:09:51.319 --> 04:09:56.399
he recognized an intellectual cultivation of no moderate depth or scope, together with

04:09:56.399 --> 04:10:00.319
a range and freedom of ideas that he would have vainly looked for among the members of

04:10:00.319 --> 04:10:01.139
his own profession.

04:10:02.099 --> 04:10:07.359
In truth, he was startled, if not shocked, to find this attribute in the physician.

04:10:08.479 --> 04:10:14.539
Mr. Dimmesdale was a true priest, a true religionist, with a reverential sentiment largely developed,

04:10:15.019 --> 04:10:19.759
and an order of mind that impelled itself powerfully along the track of a creed and

04:10:19.759 --> 04:10:22.839
more its passage continually deeper with the lapse of time.

04:10:23.639 --> 04:10:27.519
In no state of society would he have been what is called a man of liberal views.

04:10:27.999 --> 04:10:32.879
It would always be essential to his piece to feel the pressure of a faith about him,

04:10:33.119 --> 04:10:36.259
support him, while it confined him with its iron framework.

04:10:37.999 --> 04:10:43.039
Not the less, however, though with a tremulous enjoyment, did he feel the occasional relief

04:10:43.039 --> 04:10:47.399
of looking at the universe through the medium of another kind of intellect than those with

04:10:47.399 --> 04:10:49.199
which he habitually held converse.

04:10:49.839 --> 04:10:55.039
It was as if a window were thrown open, admitting a freer atmosphere into the close and stifled

04:10:55.039 --> 04:11:00.479
study, whereas life was wasting itself away amid lamp light or obstructed by day beams,

04:11:00.979 --> 04:11:06.119
and the musty fragrance, be it sensual or moral, that exhales from books.

04:11:06.259 --> 04:11:10.879
But the air was too fresh and chill to be long-breathed with comfort, so the minister

04:11:10.879 --> 04:11:15.779
and the physician with him withdrew again within the limits of what their church defined

04:11:15.779 --> 04:11:17.059
as orthodox.

04:11:18.459 --> 04:11:23.859
Thus Roger Chillingworth scrutinized his patient carefully, both as he saw him in his ordinary

04:11:23.859 --> 04:11:28.619
life, keeping an accustomed pathway in the range of thoughts familiar to him, and as

04:11:28.619 --> 04:11:33.459
he appeared when thrown amidst other moral scenery, the novelty of which might call out

04:11:33.459 --> 04:11:35.459
something new to the surface of his character.

04:11:36.039 --> 04:11:41.119
He deemed it essential, it would seem, to know the man before attempting to do him good.

04:11:41.899 --> 04:11:46.739
Wherever there is a heart and an intellect, the diseases of the physical frame are tinged

04:11:46.739 --> 04:11:48.399
with the peculiarity of these.

04:11:49.139 --> 04:11:54.839
In Arthur Dimmesdale, thought and imagination were so active and sensibility so intense

04:11:54.839 --> 04:11:58.959
that the bodily infirmity would be likely to have its groundwork there.

04:12:00.179 --> 04:12:06.179
So Roger Chillingworth, the man of skill, the kind and friendly physician, strove to

04:12:06.179 --> 04:12:12.279
go deep into his patient's bosom, delving among his principles, prying into his recollections,

04:12:12.559 --> 04:12:17.139
and probing everything with a cautious touch, like a treasure-seeker in a dark cavern.

04:12:17.959 --> 04:12:22.479
Few secrets can escape an investigator who has an opportunity and license to undertake

04:12:22.479 --> 04:12:25.239
such a quest, and skill to follow it up.

04:12:25.979 --> 04:12:30.299
A man burdened with a secret should especially avoid the intimacy of his physician.

04:12:31.719 --> 04:12:38.159
If the latter possess native sagacity and a nameless something more, let us call it intuition.

04:12:38.639 --> 04:12:44.539
If he show no intrusive egotism nor disagreeable prominent characteristics of his own, if he

04:12:44.539 --> 04:12:49.739
have the power, which must be borne with him, to bring his mind into such affinity with

04:12:49.739 --> 04:12:54.339
his patients that this last shall unawares have spoken what he imagines of self only

04:12:54.339 --> 04:12:55.039
to have thought.

04:12:55.669 --> 04:13:01.579
If such revelations be received without tumult and acknowledged, not so often by an uttered

04:13:01.579 --> 04:13:06.999
sympathy as by silence and inarticulate breath, and here and there are word to indicate that

04:13:06.999 --> 04:13:13.119
all is understood, if to these qualifications of a confidant be joined the advantages afforded

04:13:13.119 --> 04:13:19.869
by his recognized character as a physician, then, at some inevitable moment, will the

04:13:19.869 --> 04:13:25.669
soul of the sufferer be dissolved and flow forth in a dark but transparent stream, bringing

04:13:25.669 --> 04:13:27.709
all its mysteries into the daylight.

04:13:29.349 --> 04:13:33.809
Roger Chillingworth possessed all or most of the attributes above enumerated.

04:13:34.389 --> 04:13:36.109
Nevertheless, time went on.

04:13:36.429 --> 04:13:41.229
A kind of intimacy, as we have said, grew up between these two cultivated minds, which

04:13:41.229 --> 04:13:45.329
had as wide a field as the whole sphere of human thought and study to meet upon.

04:13:45.889 --> 04:13:51.149
They discussed every topic of ethics and religion, of public affairs and private character,

04:13:51.509 --> 04:13:56.429
they talked much on both sides of matters that seemed personal to themselves, and yet

04:13:56.429 --> 04:14:02.269
no secret, such as the physician fancied must exist there, ever stole out of the minister's

04:14:02.269 --> 04:14:04.229
consciousness into his companion's ear.

04:14:05.009 --> 04:14:09.809
The latter had his suspicions, indeed, that even the nature of Mr. Dimmesdale's bodily

04:14:09.809 --> 04:14:12.229
disease had never been fairly revealed to him.

04:14:12.709 --> 04:14:14.269
It was a strange reserve.

04:14:14.889 --> 04:14:20.709
After a time, at a hint from Roger Chillingworth, the friends of Mr. Dimmesdale affected an

04:14:20.709 --> 04:14:25.289
arrangement by which the two were lodged in the same house, so that every ebb and flow

04:14:25.289 --> 04:14:29.609
of the minister's life-tide might pass on to the eye of his anxious and attached physician.

04:14:30.589 --> 04:14:35.209
There was much joy throughout the town when this greatly desirable object was attained.

04:14:36.109 --> 04:14:40.989
It was held to be the best possible measure for the young clergyman's welfare, unless,

04:14:40.989 --> 04:14:46.089
indeed, as often urged by such as felt authorized to do so, he had selected one of the many

04:14:46.089 --> 04:14:51.069
blooming damsels, spiritually devoted to him, to become his devoted wife.

04:14:51.789 --> 04:14:56.109
This latter step, however, there was no present prospect that Arthur Dimmesdale would be

04:14:56.109 --> 04:14:57.189
prevailed upon to take.

04:14:57.569 --> 04:15:02.609
He rejected all suggestions of the kind, as if priestly celibacy were one of his articles

04:15:02.609 --> 04:15:03.629
of church discipline.

04:15:04.549 --> 04:15:09.689
Doomed by his own choice, therefore, as Mr. Dimmesdale so evidently was, to eat his unsavory

04:15:09.689 --> 04:15:14.729
morsel always at another's board, and endure the life-long chill which must be his lot,

04:15:15.129 --> 04:15:20.629
who seeks to warm himself only at another's fireside, it truly seemed that this sagacious,

04:15:21.249 --> 04:15:27.029
experienced, benevolent old physician, with his concord of paternal and reverential love

04:15:27.029 --> 04:15:31.929
for the young pastor, was the very man of all mankind to be constantly within reach

04:15:31.929 --> 04:15:32.689
of his voice.

04:15:34.029 --> 04:15:39.529
The new abode of the two friends was with a pious widow of good social rank who

04:15:39.529 --> 04:15:43.909
dwelt in a house covering pretty nearly the site on which the venerable structure of King's

04:15:43.909 --> 04:15:45.189
Chapel has since been built.

04:15:46.189 --> 04:15:51.269
It had the graveyard, originally Isaac Johnson's home field, on one side, and so was well

04:15:51.269 --> 04:15:56.289
adapted to call up serious reflections suited to their respective employments in both

04:15:56.289 --> 04:15:57.869
minister and man of physics.

04:15:59.069 --> 04:16:03.409
The motherly care of the good widow assigned to Mr. Dimmesdale a front apartment with a

04:16:03.409 --> 04:16:09.329
sunny exposure and heavy window curtains to create noontide shadow when desirable.

04:16:09.529 --> 04:16:15.529
The walls were hung round with tapestry, said to be from the goblin looms, and at all events,

04:16:16.229 --> 04:16:20.889
representing the scriptural story of David in Bathsheba and Nathan the prophet, in colors

04:16:20.889 --> 04:16:26.349
still unfaded, but which made the fair woman of the scene almost as grimly picturesque as a woe

04:16:26.349 --> 04:16:27.589
denouncing seer.

04:16:28.589 --> 04:16:33.989
Here the pale clergyman piled up his library, rich with parchment-bound folios of the Fathers

04:16:33.989 --> 04:16:40.749
and the lore of the rabbis and monkish erudition of which the Protestant divines, even while they

04:16:40.749 --> 04:16:45.529
vilified and decried that class of writers, were yet constrained often to avail themselves.

04:16:46.249 --> 04:16:50.849
On the other side of the house, old Roger Chillingworth arranged his study and laboratory.

04:16:51.789 --> 04:16:57.589
Not such as a modern man of science would reckon even tolerably complete, but provided with a

04:16:57.589 --> 04:17:03.129
distilling apparatus and the means of compounding drugs and chemicals which the practiced alchemist

04:17:03.129 --> 04:17:04.769
knew well how to turn to purpose.

04:17:05.509 --> 04:17:11.489
With such commodiousness of situation, these two learned persons set themselves down, each in his

04:17:11.489 --> 04:17:17.009
own domain, yet familiarly passing from one apartment to the other, and bestowing a mutual

04:17:17.009 --> 04:17:20.289
and not incurious inspection into one another's business.

04:17:21.849 --> 04:17:25.989
And the Reverend Arthur Dimmesdale's best discerning friends, as we have intimated,

04:17:26.469 --> 04:17:30.889
very reasonably imagined that the hand of Providence had done all this for the purpose,

04:17:30.889 --> 04:17:37.229
besought in so many public and domestic and secret prayers of restoring the young minister to health.

04:17:38.889 --> 04:17:45.109
But, it must now be said, another portion of the community had latterly begun to take its own view

04:17:45.109 --> 04:17:49.189
of the relation betwixt Mr. Dimmesdale and the mysterious old physician.

04:17:49.989 --> 04:17:55.989
When an uninstructed multitude attempts to see with its eyes, it is exceedingly apt to be deceived.

04:17:56.789 --> 04:18:03.829
When, however, it forms its judgment, as it usually does, on the intuitions of its great and

04:18:03.829 --> 04:18:09.569
warm heart, the conclusions thus attained are often so profound and so unerring as to

04:18:09.569 --> 04:18:12.609
possess the character of truth supernaturally revealed.

04:18:13.489 --> 04:18:19.429
The people, in the case of which we speak, could justify its prejudice against Roger Chillingworth

04:18:19.429 --> 04:18:22.989
by no fact or argument worthy of serious refutation.

04:18:23.549 --> 04:18:28.749
There was an aged handicraftsman, it is true, who had been a citizen of London at the period

04:18:28.749 --> 04:18:34.609
of Sir Thomas Overby's murder, now some thirty years ago on. He testified to having seen the

04:18:34.609 --> 04:18:38.929
physician, under some other name, which the narrator of the story had now forgotten,

04:18:39.469 --> 04:18:44.249
in company with Dr. Foreman, the famous old conjurer who was implicated in the affair of

04:18:44.249 --> 04:18:49.609
Overbury. Two or three individuals hinted that the man of skill during his Indian captivity

04:18:49.609 --> 04:18:54.809
had enlarged his medical attainments by joining in the incantations of the savage priests

04:18:54.809 --> 04:18:59.669
who were universally acknowledged to be powerful enchanters, often performing

04:18:59.669 --> 04:19:02.989
seemingly miraculous cures by their skill in the black art.

04:19:04.529 --> 04:19:09.769
A large number, and many of these were persons of such sober sense and practical observation

04:19:09.769 --> 04:19:12.589
that their opinions would have been valuable in other matters,

04:19:13.389 --> 04:19:17.869
affirmed that Roger Chillingworth's aspect had undergone a remarkable change while he

04:19:17.869 --> 04:19:24.709
dwelt in town, and especially since his abode with Mr. Dimmesdale. At first, his expression had

04:19:24.709 --> 04:19:31.709
been calm, meditative, scholar-like. Now there was something ugly and evil in his face, which they

04:19:31.709 --> 04:19:37.229
had not previously noticed, and which grew still the more obvious to sight the oftener they looked

04:19:37.229 --> 04:19:43.369
upon him. According to the vulgar idea, the fire in his laboratory had been brought from the lower

04:19:43.369 --> 04:19:50.829
regions, and was fed with infernal fuel, and so, as might be expected, his visage was getting

04:19:50.829 --> 04:19:57.589
sooty with the smoke. To sum up the matter, it grew to be a widely diffused opinion that

04:19:57.589 --> 04:20:03.609
Reverend Arthur Dimmesdale, like many other personages of special sanctity in all ages of

04:20:03.609 --> 04:20:13.129
the Christian world, was haunted either by Satan himself or by Satan's emissary in the guise of

04:20:13.129 --> 04:20:19.269
divine permission for a season to burrow into the clergyman's intimacy and plot against his soul.

04:20:19.829 --> 04:20:23.829
No sensible man, it was confessed, could doubt on which side the victor would turn.

04:20:24.409 --> 04:20:28.909
The people looked, with an unshaken hope, to see the minister come forth out of the conflict

04:20:28.909 --> 04:20:34.149
transfigured with the glory which he would unquestionably win. Meanwhile, nevertheless,

04:20:34.349 --> 04:20:39.689
it was sad to think of the perchance mortal agony through which he must struggle toward his triumph.

04:20:41.549 --> 04:20:46.709
Alas, to judge from the gloom and terror in the depth of the poor minister's eyes,

04:20:47.269 --> 04:20:52.069
the battle was a sore one, and the victory anything but secure.

04:21:20.056 --> 04:21:24.296
The Scarlet Letter by Nathaniel Hawthorne

04:21:24.856 --> 04:21:28.736
The Leech and His Patient

04:21:31.176 --> 04:21:45.836
Old Roger Chillingworth, throughout life, had been calm in temperament, kindly, though not of warm affections, but ever, and in all his relations with the world, a pure and upright man.

04:21:45.836 --> 04:22:08.716
He had begun an investigation, as he imagined, with the severe and equal integrity of a judge, desirous only of truth, even as if the question involved no more than the air-drawn lines and figures of a geometrical problem, instead of human passions and wrongs inflicted on himself.

04:22:08.716 --> 04:22:24.596
But as he proceeded, a terrible fascination, a kind of fierce, though still calm, necessity, seized the old man within its grip, and never set him free again, until he had done all its bidding.

04:22:24.596 --> 04:22:50.176
He now dug into the poor clergyman's heart, like a miner searching for gold, or rather like a sexton delving into a grave, possibly in quest of a jewel that had been buried on the dead man's bosom, but likely to find nothing save mortality and corruption, alas for his own soul, if these were what he sought.

04:22:51.456 --> 04:23:10.436
Sometimes a light glimmered out of the physician's eyes, burning blue and ominous, like the reflection of a furnace, or, let us say, like one of those gleams of ghastly fire that darted from Bunyan's awful doorway in the hillside, and quivered on the pilgrim's face.

04:23:10.436 --> 04:23:18.036
The soil where this dark miner was working had perchance shown indications that encouraged him.

04:23:19.676 --> 04:23:36.136
This man, said he at one such moment to himself, pure as they deem him, all spiritual as he seems, hath inherited a strong animal nature from his father or his mother. Let us dig a little further in the direction of this vein.

04:23:36.136 --> 04:24:03.356
Then, after a long search into the minister's dim interior, and turning over many precious materials, in the shape of high aspirations for the welfare of his race, warm love of souls, pure sentiments, natural piety, strengthened by thought and study, and illuminated by revelation, all of which invaluable gold, was perhaps no better than rubbish to the seeker.

04:24:03.356 --> 04:24:08.616
He would turn back, discouraged, and begin his quest towards another point.

04:24:09.836 --> 04:24:28.576
He groped along as stealthily, with as cautious a tread and as wary an outlook, as a thief entering a chamber where a man lies only half asleep, or, it may be, broad awake, with a purpose to steal the very treasure which this man guards as the apple of his eye.

04:24:29.516 --> 04:24:42.776
In spite of his premeditated carefulness, the floor would now and then creak, his garments would rustle, the shadow of his presence in a forbidden proximity would be thrown across his victim.

04:24:42.776 --> 04:24:58.996
In other words, Mr. Dimmesdale, whose sensibility of nerve often produced the effect of spiritual intuition, would become vaguely aware that something inimical to his peace had thrust itself into relation with him.

04:24:58.996 --> 04:25:15.836
But old Roger Chillingworth, too, had perceptions that were almost intuitive, and when the minister threw his startled eyes towards him, there the physician sat, his kind, watchful, sympathising, but never intrusive friend.

04:25:16.816 --> 04:25:29.936
Yet Mr. Dimmesdale would perhaps have seen this individual's character more perfectly if a certain morbidness to which sick hearts are liable had not rendered him suspicious of all mankind.

04:25:29.936 --> 04:25:54.636
Trusting no man as his friend, he could not recognise his enemy when the latter actually appeared. He therefore still kept up a familiar intercourse with him, daily receiving the old physician in his study, or visiting the laboratory, and for recreation's sake watching the processes by which weeds were converted into drugs of potency.

04:25:55.836 --> 04:26:10.096
One day, leaning his forehead on his hand, and his elbow on the sill of the open window that looked towards the graveyard, he talked with Roger Chillingworth while the old man was examining a bundle of unsightly plants.

04:26:10.936 --> 04:26:28.436
Where, asked he, with a look askance at them, for it was the clergyman's peculiarity that he seldom, nowadays, looks straightforward at any object, whether human or inanimate. Where, my kind doctor, did you gather those herbs with such a dark, flabby leaf?

04:26:29.076 --> 04:26:47.616
Even here in the graveyard, here at hand, answered the physician, continuing his employment, they are new to me. I found them growing on a grave which bore no tombstone, no other memorial of the dead man save these ugly weeds that have taken upon themselves to keep him in remembrance.

04:26:47.616 --> 04:26:57.876
They grew out of his heart, and typify, it may be, some hideous secret that was buried with him, and which he had done better to confess during his lifetime.

04:26:59.056 --> 04:27:18.916
Perchance, said Mr. Dimmesdale, he earnestly desired it, but could not. And wherefore, rejoined the physician, wherefore not, since all the powers of nature call so earnestly for the confession of sin that these black weeds have sprung up out of a buried heart to make manifest an outspoken crime?

04:27:20.496 --> 04:27:36.736
That, good sir, is but a fantasy of yours, replied the minister. There can be, if I forebode aright, no power short of the Divine Mercy to disclose, whether by uttered words, or by type, or emblem, the secrets that may be buried in the human heart.

04:27:36.736 --> 04:27:46.096
The heart, making itself guilty of such secrets, must perforce hold them, until the day when all hidden things shall be revealed.

04:27:46.096 --> 04:28:00.456
Nor have I so read or interpreted holy writ as to understand that the disclosure of human thoughts and deeds, then to be made, is intended as a part of the retribution. That, surely, were a shallow view of it.

04:28:00.456 --> 04:28:15.636
No, these revelations, unless I greatly err, are meant merely to promote the intellectual satisfaction of all intelligent beings, who are stand waiting on that day to see the dark problem of this life made plain.

04:28:15.636 --> 04:28:34.056
A knowledge of men's hearts will be needful to the completest solution of that problem, and I conceive, moreover, that the hearts holding such miserable secrets as you speak of will yield them up at that last day, not with reluctance, but with a joy unutterable.

04:28:34.056 --> 04:28:46.796
Then why not reveal it here? asked Roger Chillingworth, glancing quietly aside at the minister. Why should not the guilty ones sooner avail themselves of this unutterable solace?

04:28:46.796 --> 04:29:03.836
They mostly do, said the clergyman, gripping hard at his breast, as if afflicted with an importunate throb of pain. Many, many a poor soul hath given its confidence to me, not only on the death-bed, but while strong in life and fair in reputation.

04:29:03.836 --> 04:29:32.896
And ever, after such an outpouring, oh, what a relief have I witnessed in those sinful brethren, even as in one who at last draws free air after a long stifling with his own polluted breath. How can it be otherwise? Why should a wretched man, guilty, we will say, of murder, prefer to keep the dead corpse buried in his own heart, rather than fling it forth at once and let the universe take care of it?

04:29:33.756 --> 04:29:38.236
Yet some men bury their secrets thus, observed the calm physician.

04:29:38.236 --> 04:29:49.676
True, there are such men, answered Mr Dimmesdale, but not to suggest more obvious reasons. It may be that they are kept silent by the very constitution of their nature.

04:29:50.356 --> 04:30:11.096
Or, can we not suppose it, guilty as they may be, retaining nevertheless zeal for God's glory and man's welfare, they shrink from displaying themselves black and filthy in the view of men, because, thenceforward, no good can be achieved by them, no evil of the past be redeemed by better service.

04:30:11.096 --> 04:30:26.336
So, to their own unutterable torment, they go about among their fellow creatures, looking pure as new-fallen snow, while their hearts are all speckled and spotted with iniquity of which they cannot rid themselves.

04:30:27.416 --> 04:30:39.816
These men deceive themselves, said Roger Chillingworth, with somewhat more emphasis than usual, and making a slight gesture with his forefinger. They fear to take up the shame that rightfully belongs to them.

04:30:40.316 --> 04:30:55.516
Their love for man, their zeal for God's service, these holy impulses may or may not coexist in their hearts with the evil inmates to which their guilt has unbarred the door, and which must needs propagate a hellish breed within them.

04:30:55.516 --> 04:31:12.056
But if they seek to glorify God, let them not lift heavenward their unclean hands. If they would serve their fellow men, let them do it by making manifest the power and reality of conscience in constraining them to penitential self-abasement.

04:31:12.056 --> 04:31:26.776
Would thou have me to believe, O wise and pious friend, that a false show can be better, can be more for God's glory or man's welfare than God's own truth? Trust me, such men deceive themselves.

04:31:27.456 --> 04:31:43.576
It may be so, said the young clergyman, indifferently, as waving a discussion that he considered irrelevant or unseasonable. He had a ready faculty, indeed, of escaping from any topic that agitated his too sensitive and nervous temperament.

04:31:44.096 --> 04:31:53.676
But now I would ask of my well-skilled physician whether, in good sooth, he deems me to have profited by his kindly care of this weak frame of mine.

04:31:54.556 --> 04:32:03.576
Before Roger Chillingworth could answer, they heard the clear, wild laughter of a young child's voice proceeding from the adjacent burial ground.

04:32:04.296 --> 04:32:14.656
Looking instinctively from the open window, for it was summertime, the minister beheld Hester Prynne and little Pearl passing along the footpath that traversed the enclosure.

04:32:14.656 --> 04:32:28.036
Pearl looked as beautiful as the day, but was in one of those moods of perverse merriment which, whenever they occurred, seemed to remove her entirely out of the sphere of sympathy or human contact.

04:32:28.596 --> 04:32:42.536
She now skipped irreverently from one grave to another, until, coming to the broad, flat, armorial tombstone of a departed worthy, perhaps of Isaac Johnson himself, she began to dance upon it.

04:32:42.536 --> 04:32:53.656
In reply to her mother's command and entreaty that she would behave more decorously, little Pearl paused to gather the prickly burrs from a tall burdock which grew beside the tomb.

04:32:54.376 --> 04:33:05.536
Taking a handful of these, she arranged them along the lines of the scarlet letter that decorated the maternal bosom, to which the burrs, as their nature was, tenaciously adhered.

04:33:06.596 --> 04:33:08.256
Hester did not pluck them off.

04:33:09.376 --> 04:33:14.716
Roger Chillingworth had by this time approached the window and smiled grimly down.

04:33:15.376 --> 04:33:28.556
There is no law nor reverence for authority, no regard for human ordinances or opinions, right or wrong, mixed up with that child's composition, remarked he, as much to himself as to his companion.

04:33:28.556 --> 04:33:35.056
I saw her the other day, bespatter the governor himself with water at the cattle-trough in Spring Lane.

04:33:35.616 --> 04:33:44.456
What in heaven's name is she? Is the imp altogether evil? Hath she affections? Hath she any discoverable principle of being?

04:33:45.376 --> 04:33:56.696
None, save the freedom of a broken law, answered Mr. Dimmesdale in a quiet way, as if he had been discussing the point within himself. Whether capable of good, I know not.

04:33:56.696 --> 04:34:10.036
The child probably overheard their voices, for looking up to the window with a bright but naughty smile of mirth and intelligence, she threw one of the prickly burrs at the reverent Mr. Dimmesdale.

04:34:10.816 --> 04:34:21.736
The sensitive clergyman shrank with nervous dread from the light missile. Detecting his emotion, Pearl clapped her little hands in the most extravagant ecstasy.

04:34:21.736 --> 04:34:33.656
Esther Prynne likewise had involuntarily looked up, and all these four persons, old and young, regarded one another in silence, till the child laughed aloud and shouted,

04:34:34.016 --> 04:34:46.016
Come away, mother, come away, or yonder old black man will catch you. He hath got hold of the minister already. Come away, mother, or he will catch you. But he cannot catch little Pearl.

04:34:46.916 --> 04:35:02.296
So she drew her mother away, skipping, dancing and frisking fantastically among the hillocks of the dead people, like a creature that had nothing in common with a bygone and buried generation, nor owned herself akin to it.

04:35:02.296 --> 04:35:15.956
It was as if she had been made afresh out of new elements, and must perforce be permitted to live her own life, and be a law unto herself, without her eccentricities being reckoned to her for a crime.

04:35:16.796 --> 04:35:28.656
There goes a woman, resumed Roger Chillingworth after a pause, who, be her demerits what they may, hath none of that mystery of hidden sinfulness which you deem so grievous to be born.

04:35:28.656 --> 04:35:34.436
Is Hester Prynne the less miserable, thank you, for that scarlet letter on her breast?

04:35:35.196 --> 04:35:56.416
I do verily believe it, answered the clergyman. Nevertheless, I cannot answer for her. There was a look of pain in her face, which I would gladly have been spared the sight of. But still me thinks, it must needs be better for the sufferer to be free to show his pain, as this poor woman hesteres, than to cover it up in his heart.

04:35:57.196 --> 04:36:03.596
There was another pause, and the physician began anew to examine and arrange the plants which he had gathered.

04:36:05.176 --> 04:36:18.156
You inquired of me a little time agone, said he at length, my judgment as touching your health. I did answer the clergyman, and would gladly learn it. Speak frankly, I pray you, be it for life or death.

04:36:19.076 --> 04:36:37.256
Freely then and plainly, said the physician, still busy with his plants, but keeping a wary eye on Mr. Dimmesdale. The disorder is a strange one, not so much in itself, nor as outwardly manifested, in so far at least as the symptoms have been laid open to my observation.

04:36:37.256 --> 04:36:59.676
Looking daily at you, my good sir, and watching the tokens of your aspect now for months gone by, I should deem you a man sore sick, it may be, yet not so sick, but that an instructed and watchful physician might well hope to cure you. But I know not what to say. The disease is what I seem to know, yet know it not.

04:36:59.676 --> 04:37:06.316
You speak in riddles, learned sir, said the pale minister, glancing aside out of the window.

04:37:07.796 --> 04:37:16.976
Then to speak more plainly, continued the physician, and I crave pardon, sir, should it seem to require pardon for this needful plainness of my speech.

04:37:16.976 --> 04:37:28.796
Let me ask as your friend, as one having charge under providence of your life and physical well-being, hath all the operations of this disorder been fairly laid open and recounted to me?

04:37:29.876 --> 04:37:37.016
How can you question it, asked the minister? Surely it were child's play to call in a physician and then hide the sore?

04:37:37.856 --> 04:37:59.416
You would tell me then that I know all, said Roger Chillingworth deliberately, and fixing an eye bright with intense and concentrated intelligence on the minister's face, be it so, but again, he to whom only the outward and physical evil is laid open, knoweth oftentimes but half the evil which he is called upon to cure.

04:37:59.416 --> 04:38:09.996
A bodily disease, which we look upon as whole and entire within itself, may after all be but a symptom of some ailment in the spiritual part.

04:38:11.116 --> 04:38:27.256
Your pardon once again, good sir, if my speech give the shadow of offence. You, sir, of all men whom I have known, are he whose body is the closest conjoined and imbued and identified, so to speak, with the spirit whereof it is the instrument.

04:38:28.316 --> 04:38:36.776
Then I need ask no further, said the clergyman, somewhat hastily rising from his chair. You deal not, I take it, in medicine for the soul.

04:38:38.416 --> 04:38:53.376
Thus a sickness, continued Roger Chillingworth, going on in an unaltered tone without heeding the interruption, but standing up and confronting the emaciated and white-cheeked minister with his low, dark and misshapen figure.

04:38:53.996 --> 04:39:12.596
A sickness, a sore place, if we may so call it, in your spirit, hath immediately its appropriate manifestation in your bodily frame. Would you therefore let your physician heal the bodily evil? How may this be, unless you first lay open to him the wound or trouble in your soul?

04:39:13.616 --> 04:39:30.776
No, not to thee, not to an earthly physician, cried Mr. Dimmesdale passionately, and turning his eyes full and bright and with a kind of fierceness on old Roger Chillingworth. Not to thee! But if it be the soul's disease, then do I commit myself to the one physician of the soul.

04:39:30.776 --> 04:39:46.876
He, if it stand with his good pleasure, can cure or he can kill. Let him do with me as, in his justice and wisdom, he shall see good. But who art thou that medallist in this matter, that dares thrust himself between the sufferer and his god?

04:39:47.976 --> 04:39:51.096
With a frantic gesture he rushed out of the room.

04:39:51.656 --> 04:40:18.856
It is as well to have made this step, said Roger Chillingworth to himself, looking after the minister with a grave smile. There is nothing lost. We shall be friends again and on. But see now how passion takes hold upon this man, and hurrieth him out of himself. As with one passion, so with another. He hath done a wild thing here now, this pious master Dimmesdale, in the hot passion of his heart.

04:40:19.776 --> 04:40:43.856
It proved not difficult to re-establish the intimacy of the two companions, on the same footing and in the same degree as heretofore. The young clergyman, after a few hours of privacy, was sensible that the disorder of his nerves had hurried him into an unseemly outbreak of temper, which there had been nothing in the physician's words to excuse or palliate.

04:40:43.856 --> 04:40:58.056
He marvelled indeed at the violence with which he had thrust back the kind old man, when merely proffering the advice which it was his duty to bestow, and which the minister himself had expressly sought.

04:40:58.056 --> 04:41:16.996
With these remorseful feelings, he lost no time in making the amplest apologies, and besought his friends still to continue the care which, if not successful in restoring him to health, had in all probability been the means of prolonging his feeble existence to that hour.

04:41:17.996 --> 04:41:45.156
Roger Chiningworth readily assented, and went on with his medical supervision of the minister, doing his best for him in all good faith, but always quitting the patient's apartment at the close of the professional interview, with a mysterious and puzzled smile upon his lips. This expression was invisible in Mr Dimmesdale's presence, but grew strongly evident as the physician crossed the threshold.

04:41:45.996 --> 04:41:59.316
A rare case, he muttered, I must needs look deeper into it. A strange sympathy betwixt soul and body. Were it only for art's sake, I must search this matter to the bottom.

04:41:59.316 --> 04:42:16.656
It came to pass, not long after the scene above recorded, that the Reverend Mr Dimmesdale, noonday, and entirely unawares, fell into a deep deep slumber, sitting in his chair, with a large black letter volume open before him on the table.

04:42:16.656 --> 04:42:37.896
It must have been a work of vast ability in the somniferous school of literature. The profound depth of the minister's repose was the more remarkable, inasmuch as he was one of those persons whose sleep ordinarily is as light, as fitful, and as easily scared away as a small bird hopping on a twig.

04:42:37.896 --> 04:42:51.716
To such an unwanted remoteness, however, had his spirit now withdrawn into itself, that he stirred not in his chair when old Roger Chillingworth, without any extraordinary precaution, came into the room.

04:42:52.536 --> 04:43:04.636
The physician advanced directly in front of his patient, laid his hand upon his bosom, and thrust aside the vestment, that hitherto had always covered it, even from the professional eye.

04:43:05.436 --> 04:43:34.616
Then, indeed, Mr Dimmesdale shuddered, and slightly stirred. After a brief pause, the physician turned away, but with what a wild look of wonder, joy, and honour, with what a ghastly rapture, as it were, too mighty to be expressed only by the eye and features, and therefore bursting forth through the whole ugliness of his figure, and making itself even riotously manifest by the extreme.

04:43:34.636 --> 04:43:55.696
He made extravagant gestures, with which he threw up his arms towards the ceiling, and stamped his foot upon the floor. Had a man seen old Roger Chillingworth at that moment of his ecstasy, he would have had no need to ask how Satan comports himself when a precious human soul is lost to heaven, and won into his kingdom.

04:43:56.456 --> 04:44:02.336
But what distinguished the physician's ecstasy from Satan's was the trait of wonder in it.

04:44:25.098 --> 04:44:28.918
The Scarlet Letter by Nathaniel Hawthorne

04:44:28.918 --> 04:44:33.418
The Interior of a Heart

04:44:34.818 --> 04:44:46.818
After the incident last described, the intercourse between the clergyman and the physician, though externally the same, was really of another character than it had previously been.

04:44:47.558 --> 04:44:52.918
The intellect of Roger Chillingworth had now a sufficiently plain path before it.

04:44:52.918 --> 04:44:57.758
It was not indeed precisely that which he had laid out for himself to tread.

04:44:58.338 --> 04:45:16.378
Calm, gentle, passionless as he appeared, there was yet, we fear, a quiet depth of malice hitherto latent but active now in this unfortunate old man, which led him to imagine a more intimate revenge than any mortal had ever wreaked upon an enemy.

04:45:16.378 --> 04:45:31.038
To make himself the one trusted friend, to whom should be confided all the fear, the remorse, the agony, the ineffectual repentance, the backward rush of sinful thoughts, expelled in vain.

04:45:31.618 --> 04:45:42.718
All that guilty sorrow, hidden from the world, whose great heart would have pitied and forgiven, to be revealed to him the pitiless, to him the unforgiving.

04:45:42.718 --> 04:45:50.978
All that dark treasure to be lavished on the very man to whom nothing else could so adequately pay the debt of vengeance.

04:45:53.798 --> 04:45:57.498
The clergyman's shy and sensitive reserve had bought this scheme.

04:45:57.498 --> 04:46:16.378
Roger Chillingworth, however, was inclined to be hardly, if at all, less satisfied with the aspect of affairs which Providence, using the avenger and his victim for its own purposes and perchance pardoning where it seemed most to punish, had substituted for his black devices.

04:46:17.758 --> 04:46:21.498
A revelation, he could almost say, had been granted to him.

04:46:21.498 --> 04:46:26.738
It mattered little for his object, whether celestial or from what other region.

04:46:27.458 --> 04:46:43.758
By its aid, in all the subsequent relations betwixt him and Mr. Dimmesdale, not merely the external presence, but the very inmost soul of the latter, seemed to be brought out before his eyes, so that he could see and comprehend its every movement.

04:46:44.838 --> 04:46:52.578
He became, thenceforth, not a spectator only, but a chief actor in the poor minister's interior world.

04:46:53.358 --> 04:46:55.718
He could play upon him as he chose.

04:46:56.438 --> 04:46:58.618
Would he arouse him with a throb of agony?

04:46:59.518 --> 04:47:01.438
The victim was forever on the rack.

04:47:01.758 --> 04:47:07.218
It needed only to know the spring that controlled the engine, and the physician knew it well.

04:47:07.218 --> 04:47:25.618
Would he startle him with sudden fear, as at the waving of a magician's wand up rose a thousand grisly phantoms, in many shapes of death or more awful shame, all flocking round the clergyman and pointing with their fingers at his breast?

04:47:26.438 --> 04:47:40.118
All this was accomplished with a subtlety so perfect that the minister, though he had constantly a dim perception of some evil influence watching over him, could never gain a knowledge of its actual nature.

04:47:40.118 --> 04:47:49.518
True, he looked doubtfully, fearfully, even at times with horror and the bitterness of hatred, at the deformed figure of the old physician.

04:47:50.218 --> 04:48:01.118
His gestures, his gait, his grizzled beard, his slightest and most indifferent acts, the very fashion of his garments, were odious in the clergyman's sight.

04:48:01.118 --> 04:48:09.938
A token implicitly to be relied on of a deeper antipathy in the breast of the latter than he was willing to acknowledge to himself.

04:48:10.558 --> 04:48:26.878
For, as it was impossible to assign a reason for such distrust and abhorrence, so Mr. Dimmesdale, conscious that the poison of one morbid spot was infecting his heart's entire substance, attributed all his presentiments to no other cause.

04:48:28.058 --> 04:48:38.918
He took himself to task for his bad sympathies in reference to Roger Chillingworth, disregarded the lesson that he should have drawn from them, and did his best to root them out.

04:48:38.918 --> 04:49:01.058
Unable to accomplish this, he nevertheless, as a matter of principle, continued his habits of social familiarity with the old man, and thus gave him constant opportunities for perfecting the purpose to which, poor forlorn creature that he was, and more wretched than his victim, the avenger had devoted himself.

04:49:01.938 --> 04:49:17.438
While thus suffering under bodily disease, and gnawed and tortured by some black trouble of the soul, and given over to the machinations of his deadliest enemy, the Reverend Mr. Dimmesdale had achieved a brilliant popularity in his sacred office.

04:49:18.398 --> 04:49:35.358
He won it indeed in great part by his sorrows. His intellectual gifts, his moral perceptions, his power of experiencing and communicating emotion, were kept in a state of preternatural activity by the prick and anguish of his daily life.

04:49:36.038 --> 04:49:45.618
His fame, though still on its upward slope, already overshadowed the soberer reputations of his fellow clergymen, eminent as several of them were.

04:49:45.618 --> 04:50:02.918
There are scholars among them who had spent more years in acquiring abstruse law connected with the divine profession than Mr. Dimmesdale had lived, and who might well, therefore, be more profoundly versed in such solid and valuable attainments than their youthful brother.

04:50:02.918 --> 04:50:24.438
There were men, too, of a sturdier texture of mind than his, and endowed with a far greater share of shrewd hard iron or granite understanding, which, duly mingled with a fair proportion of doctrinal ingredient, constitutes a highly respectable, efficacious and unamiable variety of the clerical species.

04:50:24.438 --> 04:50:48.398
There were others again, true saintly fathers, whose faculties had been elaborated by weary toil among their books, and by patient thought, and etherealized, moreover, by spiritual communications with the better world, into which their purity of life had almost introduced these holy personages, with their garments of mortality still clinging to them.

04:50:48.398 --> 04:51:06.558
All that they lacked was the gift that descended upon the chosen disciples at Pentecost in tongues of flame, symbolizing, it would seem, not the power of speech in foreign and unknown languages, but that of addressing the whole human brotherhood in the heart's native language.

04:51:06.558 --> 04:51:27.018
These fathers, otherwise so apostolic, lacked heaven's last and rarest attestation of their office, the tongue of flame. They would have vainly sought, had they ever dreamt of seeking, to express the highest truths through the humblest medium of familiar words and images.

04:51:27.018 --> 04:51:43.338
Their voices came down afar and indistinctly from the upper heights where they habitually dwelt. Not improbably, it was to this latter class of minister that Mr. Dimmesdale, by many of his traits of character, naturally belonged.

04:51:43.338 --> 04:51:57.718
To the high mountain peaks of faith and sanctity he would have climbed, had not the tendency been thwarted by the burden, whatever it might be, of crime or anguish, beneath which it was his doom to totter.

04:51:57.718 --> 04:52:07.618
It kept him down on a level with the lowest, him, the man of ethereal attributes, whose voice the angels might else have listened to and answered.

04:52:07.618 --> 04:52:29.058
But this very burden, it was, that gave him sympathies so intimate with the sinful brotherhood of mankind, so that his heart vibrated in unison with theirs, and received their pain into itself, and sent its own throb of pain through a thousand other hearts in gushes of sad, persuasive eloquence.

04:52:29.058 --> 04:52:45.938
Often it's persuasive, but sometimes terrible. The people knew not the power that moved them thus. They deemed the young clergyman a miracle of holiness. They fancied him the mouthpiece of heaven's messages of wisdom and rebuke and love.

04:52:45.938 --> 04:53:08.078
In their eyes the very ground on which he trod was sanctified. The virgins of his church grew pale around him, victims of a passion so imbued with religious sentiment that they imagined it to be all religion, and brought it openly in their white bosoms as their most acceptable sacrifice before the altar.

04:53:09.158 --> 04:53:29.458
The aged members of his flock, beholding Mr. Dimmesdale's frame so feeble, while they were themselves so rugged in their infirmity, believed that he would go heavenward before them, and enjoined it upon their children that their old bones should be buried close to their young pastor's holy grave.

04:53:29.458 --> 04:53:42.438
And all this time, perchance, when poor Mr. Dimmesdale was thinking of his grave, he questioned with himself whether the grass would ever grow on it, because an accursed thing must there be buried.

04:53:43.558 --> 04:54:02.238
It is inconceivable the agony with which this public veneration tortured him. It was his genuine impulse to adore the truth, and to reckon all things shadow-like, and utterly devoid of weight or value, that had not its divine essence as the life within their life.

04:54:02.238 --> 04:54:15.038
Then what was he, a substance, or the dimmest of all shadows? He longed to speak out from his own pulpit at the full height of his voice, and tell the people what he was.

04:54:15.038 --> 04:54:30.058
I, whom you behold in these black garments of the priesthood, I, who ascend the sacred desk and turn my pale face heavenward, taking upon myself to hold communion in your behalf with the Most High Omniscience,

04:54:30.058 --> 04:54:45.238
I, in whose daily life you discern the sanctity of Enoch, I, whose footsteps, as you suppose, leave a gleam along my earthly track, whereby the pilgrims that shall come after me may be guided to the regions of the blessed,

04:54:45.238 --> 04:55:05.318
I, who have laid the hand of baptism upon your children, I, who have breathed the parting prayer of your dying friends, to whom the amen sounded faintly from a world which they had quitted, I, your pastor, whom you so reverence and trust, am utterly a pollution and a lie.

04:55:06.038 --> 04:55:27.658
More than once Mr. Dimmesdale had gone into the pulpit with a purpose never to come down its steps until he should have spoken words like the above. More than once he had cleared his throat and drawn in the long, deep and tremulous breath which, when sent forth again, would come burdened with the black secret of his soul.

04:55:27.658 --> 04:55:56.198
More than once, nay, more than a hundred times, he had actually spoken, spoken, but how? He had told his hearers that he was altogether vile, a vile companion of the vilest, the worst of sinners, an abomination, a thing of unimaginable iniquity, and that the only wonder was that they did not see his wretched body shriveled up before their eyes by the burning wrath of the Almighty.

04:55:56.198 --> 04:56:13.218
Could there be plainer speech than this? Would not the people start up in their seats by a simultaneous impulse and tear him down out of the pulpit which he defiled? Not so indeed. They heard it all and did but reverence him the more.

04:56:13.218 --> 04:56:32.538
A little guessed what deadly purport lurked in those self-condemning words. The godly youth, said they among themselves, the saint on earth. Alas, if he discerned such sinfulness in his own white soul, what horrid spectacle would he behold in thine or mine?

04:56:32.538 --> 04:56:56.318
The minister well knew, subtle but remorseful hypocrite that he was, the light in which his vague confession would be viewed. He had striven to put a cheat upon himself by making the avowal of a guilty conscience, but had gained only one other sin and a self-acknowledged shame without the momentary relief of being self-deceived.

04:56:56.318 --> 04:57:15.098
He had spoken the very truth and transformed it into the veryest falsehood, and yet by the constitution of his nature he loved the truth and loathed the lie as few men ever did. Therefore, above all things else, he loathed his miserable self.

04:57:16.858 --> 04:57:34.158
His inward trouble drove him to practice his morn accordance with the old corrupted faith of Rome than with the better light of the church in which he had been born and bred. In Mr. Dimmesdale's secret closet, under lock and key, there was a bloody scourge.

04:57:34.158 --> 04:57:48.178
Oftentimes this Protestant and Puritan divine had plied it on his own shoulders, laughing bitterly at himself the while, and smiting so much the more pitilessly because of that bitter laugh.

04:57:48.178 --> 04:58:09.258
It was his custom, too, as it has been that of many other pious Puritans, to fast, not, however, like them, in order to purify the body and render it the fitter medium of celestial illumination, but rigorously until his knees trembled beneath him as an act of penance.

04:58:09.258 --> 04:58:31.858
He kept vigils likewise night after night, sometimes in utter darkness, sometimes with a glimmering lamp, and sometimes viewing his own face in a looking-glass by the most powerful light which he could throw upon it. He thus typified the constant introspection wherewith he tortured but could not purify himself.

04:58:31.858 --> 04:58:49.458
In these lengthened vigils his brain often reeled, and visions seemed to flit before him, perhaps seen doubtfully and by a faint light of their own, in the remote dimness of the chamber, or more vividly and close beside him within the looking-glass.

04:58:49.458 --> 04:59:06.458
Now it was a herd of diabolic shapes that grinned and mocked at the pale minister, and beckoned him away with them. Now a group of shining angels who flew upward heavily as sorrow-laden, but grew more ethereal as they rose.

04:59:07.798 --> 04:59:25.878
Now came the dead friends of his youth, and his white-bearded father with a saint-like frown, and his mother turning her face away as she passed by, ghost of a mother, thinnest fantasy of a mother, bethink she might yet have thrown a pitying glance towards her son.

04:59:25.878 --> 04:59:45.018
And now, through the chamber which these spectral thoughts had made so ghastly, glided Hester Prynne, leading along little Pearl, in her scarlet garb, and pointing her forefinger first at the scarlet letter on her bosom, and then at the clergyman's own breast.

04:59:45.018 --> 05:00:06.598
None of these visions ever quite deluded him. At any moment, by an effort of his will, he could discern substances through their misty lack of substance, and convince himself that they were not solid in their nature, like yonder table of carved oak, or that big square leather-bound and brazen-classed volume of divinity.

05:00:06.598 --> 05:00:29.478
But for all that, they were, in one sense, the truest and most substantial things which the poor minister now dealt with. It is the unspeakable misery of a life so false as his, that it steals the pith and substance out of whatever realities there are around us, and which were meant by Heaven to be the Spirit's joy and nutriment.

05:00:29.478 --> 05:00:46.138
To the untrue man, the whole universe is false. It is impalpable. It shrinks to nothing within his grasp. And he himself, insofar as he shows himself in a false light, becomes a shadow, or indeed ceases to exist.

05:00:46.138 --> 05:01:05.738
The only truth that continued to give Mr. Dimmesdale a real existence on this earth was the anguish in his inmost soul, and the undissembled expression of it in his aspect. Had he once found power to smile and wear a face of gaiety, there would have been no such man.

05:01:06.538 --> 05:01:32.338
On one of these ugly nights, which we have faintly hinted at, but foreborn to picture forth, the minister started from his chair. A new thought had struck him. There might be a moment's peace in it. Attiring himself with as much care as if it had been for public worship, and precisely in the same manner, he stole softly down the staircase, undid the door, and issued forth.

05:01:58.582 --> 05:02:01.562
The Scarlet Letter by Nathaniel Hawthorne

05:02:02.302 --> 05:02:06.562
The Minister's Vigil

05:02:07.262 --> 05:02:13.562
Walking in the shadow of a dream, as it were, and perhaps actually under the influence of a species of somnambulism,

05:02:14.702 --> 05:02:22.782
Mr. Dimmesdale reached the spot where, now so long since, Hester Prynne had lived through her first hours of public ignominy.

05:02:23.962 --> 05:02:30.222
The same platform or scaffold, black and weather-stained with the storm or sunshine of seven long years,

05:02:30.222 --> 05:02:39.502
and foot-worn too with the tread of many culprits who had since ascended it, remained standing beneath the balcony of the meeting-house.

05:02:41.042 --> 05:02:43.082
The Minister went up the steps.

05:02:44.222 --> 05:02:52.842
It was an obscure night in early May. An unwearied pool of cloud muffled the whole expanse of sky from zenith to horizon.

05:02:52.842 --> 05:03:01.562
If the same multitude which had stood as eyewitnesses while Hester Prynne sustained her punishment could now have been summoned forth,

05:03:02.002 --> 05:03:09.642
they would have discerned no face above the platform nor hardly the outline of a human shape in the dark grey of the midnight.

05:03:10.462 --> 05:03:14.482
But the town was all asleep. There was no peril of discovery.

05:03:14.482 --> 05:03:21.302
The Minister might stand there, if it so pleased him, until morning should redden in the east,

05:03:21.802 --> 05:03:29.742
without other risk than that the dank and chill night air would creep into his frame and stiffen his joints with rheumatism,

05:03:30.242 --> 05:03:38.222
and clog his throat with catar and cough, thereby defrauding the expectant audience of tomorrow's prayer and sermon.

05:03:38.842 --> 05:03:46.322
No eye could see him save that ever-waitful one which had seen him in his closet, wielding the bloody scourge.

05:03:46.742 --> 05:03:55.922
Why then had he come hither? Was it but the mockery of penitence? A mockery indeed, but in which his soul trifled with itself.

05:03:56.842 --> 05:04:02.882
A mockery at which angels blushed and wept, while fiends rejoiced with jeering laughter.

05:04:02.882 --> 05:04:08.642
He had been driven hither by the impulse of that remorse which dogged him everywhere,

05:04:09.202 --> 05:04:17.442
and whose own sister and closely linked companion was that cowardice which invariably drew him back with her tremulous grip,

05:04:17.902 --> 05:04:21.802
just when the other impulse had hurried him to the verge of a disclosure.

05:04:22.382 --> 05:04:28.362
Poor miserable man! What right had infirmity like his to burden itself with crime?

05:04:28.362 --> 05:04:35.282
Crime is for the iron-nerved who have their choice either to endure it or, if it pressed too hard,

05:04:35.422 --> 05:04:41.082
to exert their fierce and savage strength for a good purpose and fling it off at once.

05:04:42.002 --> 05:04:49.042
This feeble and most sensitive of spirits could do neither, yet continually did one thing or another

05:04:49.042 --> 05:04:56.802
which intertwined in the same inextricable knot the agony of heaven-defying guilt and vain repentance.

05:04:58.562 --> 05:05:06.822
And thus, while standing on the scaffold in this vain show of expiation, Mr. Dimmesdale was overcome with a great horror of mind,

05:05:07.242 --> 05:05:13.422
as if the universe was gazing at a scarlet token on his naked breast, right over his heart.

05:05:13.902 --> 05:05:21.342
On that spot, in very truth, there was, and there had long been, the gnawing and poisonous tooth of bodily pain.

05:05:21.342 --> 05:05:29.362
Without any effort of his will or power to restrain himself, he shrieked aloud an outcry that went peeling through the night

05:05:29.362 --> 05:05:34.842
and was beaten back from one house to another and reverberated from the hills in the background,

05:05:35.262 --> 05:05:44.342
as if a company of devils, detecting so much misery and terror in it, had made a plaything of the sound and were bandying it to and fro.

05:05:44.342 --> 05:05:49.662
"'It is done,' muttered the minister, covering his face with his hands.

05:05:50.002 --> 05:05:54.422
The whole town was awake and hurried forth and fined me here.

05:05:55.262 --> 05:05:57.042
But it was not so.

05:05:57.562 --> 05:06:03.642
The shriek had perhaps sounded with a far greater power to his own startled ears than it actually possessed.

05:06:04.462 --> 05:06:11.702
The town did not awake, or if it did, the drowsy slumberers mistook the cry either for something frightful in a dream

05:06:11.702 --> 05:06:19.762
or for the noise of witches, whose voices at that period were often heard to pass over the settlements or lonely cottages

05:06:19.762 --> 05:06:22.442
as they rode with Satan through the air.

05:06:23.282 --> 05:06:29.382
The clergyman, therefore, hearing no symptoms of disturbance, uncovered his eyes and looked about him.

05:06:30.182 --> 05:06:36.662
At one of the chamber windows of Governor Bellingham's mansion, which stood at some distance on the line of another street,

05:06:36.662 --> 05:06:46.102
he beheld the appearance of the old magistrate himself with a lamp in his hand, a white nightcap on his head, and a long white gown enveloping his figure.

05:06:47.082 --> 05:06:50.382
He looked like a ghost evoked unseasonably from the grave.

05:06:51.062 --> 05:06:53.322
The cry had evidently startled him.

05:06:54.142 --> 05:07:01.162
At another window of the same house, moreover, appeared old Mistress Hibbins, the governor's sister, also with a lamp,

05:07:01.162 --> 05:07:06.922
which even thus far off revealed the expression of her sour and discontented face.

05:07:08.542 --> 05:07:12.862
She thrust forth her head from the lattice and looked anxiously upward.

05:07:13.622 --> 05:07:18.962
Beyond the shadow of a doubt, this venerable witch-lady had heard Mr Dimmesdale's outcry

05:07:18.962 --> 05:07:27.582
and interpreted it, with its multitudinous echoes and reverberations, as the clamour of the fiends and night-hags

05:07:27.582 --> 05:07:31.582
with whom she was well known to make excursions in the forest.

05:07:32.902 --> 05:07:38.262
Detecting the gleam of Governor Bellingham's lamp, the old lady quickly extinguished her own and vanished.

05:07:39.082 --> 05:07:41.062
Possibly she went up among the clouds.

05:07:41.902 --> 05:07:44.562
The minister saw nothing further of her motions.

05:07:45.542 --> 05:07:56.222
The magistrate, after a wary observation of the darkness, into which nevertheless he could see but little further than he might into a millstone, retired from the window.

05:07:56.902 --> 05:07:59.662
The minister grew comparatively calm.

05:08:00.522 --> 05:08:07.982
His eyes, however, were soon greeted by a little glimmering light, which at first, a long way off, was approaching up the street.

05:08:08.682 --> 05:08:18.542
It threw a gleam of recognition on here a post and there a garden fence, and here a latticed windowpane and there a pump with its full trough of water,

05:08:18.922 --> 05:08:24.902
and here again an arched door of oak with an iron knocker and a rough log for the doorstep.

05:08:24.902 --> 05:08:37.302
The reverend Mr. Dimmesdale noted all these minute particulars, even while firmly convinced that the doom of his existence was stealing onward in the footsteps which he now heard,

05:08:37.822 --> 05:08:44.442
and that the gleam of the lantern would fall upon him in a few moments more and reveal his long-hidden secret.

05:08:45.342 --> 05:08:57.302
As the light drew nearer, he beheld, within its illuminated circle, his brother clergyman, or, to speak more accurately, his professional father, as well as highly valued friend,

05:08:57.802 --> 05:09:05.342
the reverend Mr. Wilson, who, as Mr. Dimmesdale now conjectured, had been praying at the bedside of some dying man.

05:09:05.342 --> 05:09:15.822
And so he had. The good old minister came freshly from the death chamber of Governor Winthrop, who had passed from earth to heaven within that very hour,

05:09:16.242 --> 05:09:24.522
and now surrounded, like the saint-like personage of olden times, with a radiant halo that glorified him amid this gloomy night of sin,

05:09:24.842 --> 05:09:33.342
as if the departed governor had left him an inheritance of his glory, or as if he had caught upon himself the distant shine of the celestial city,

05:09:33.342 --> 05:09:45.182
while looking thitherward to see the triumphant pilgrim pass within its gates. Now, in short, Goodfather Wilson was moving homeward, aiding his footsteps with a lighted lantern.

05:09:46.162 --> 05:09:56.022
The glimmer of this luminary suggested the above conceits to Mr. Dimmesdale, who smiled, and I almost laughed at them, and then wondered if he was going mad.

05:09:57.122 --> 05:10:07.262
As the reverend Mr. Wilson passed beside the scaffold, closely muffling his Geneva cloak about him with one arm, and holding the lantern before his breast with the other,

05:10:07.862 --> 05:10:10.762
the minister could hardly restrain himself from speaking.

05:10:11.842 --> 05:10:18.362
A good evening to you, venerable Father Wilson. Come up hither, I pray you, and pass a pleasant hour with me.

05:10:19.642 --> 05:10:30.542
Good heavens, had Mr. Dimmesdale actually spoken! For one instant he believed that these words had passed his lips, but they were uttered only within his imagination.

05:10:31.402 --> 05:10:43.162
The venerable Father Wilson continued to step slowly onward, looking carefully at the muddy pathway before his feet, and never once turning his head towards the guilty platform,

05:10:43.162 --> 05:10:47.882
when the light of the glimmering lantern had faded quite away.

05:10:48.722 --> 05:11:02.962
The minister discovered, by the faintness which came over him, that the last few moments had been a crisis of terrible anxiety, although his mind had made an involuntary effort to relieve itself by a kind of lurid playfulness.

05:11:04.402 --> 05:11:12.082
Shortly afterwards, the like grisly sense of the humorous again stole in among the solemn phantoms of his thought.

05:11:12.882 --> 05:11:21.362
He felt his limbs growing stiff with the unaccustomed chilliness of the night, and doubted whether he should be able to descend the steps of the scaffold.

05:11:21.982 --> 05:11:27.622
Morning would break and find him there. The neighborhood would begin to rouse itself.

05:11:28.382 --> 05:11:41.802
The earliest riser, coming forth in a dim twilight, would perceive a vaguely defined figure aloft on the place of shame, and half-crazed betwixt alarm and curiosity, would go knocking from door to door,

05:11:42.082 --> 05:11:48.682
summoning all the people to behold the ghost, as he needs must think it, of some defunct transgressor.

05:11:48.682 --> 05:12:06.162
A dusky tumult would flap its wings from one house to another. Then, the morning light still waxing stronger, old patriarchs would rise up in great haste, each in his flannel gown and matronly dames, without pausing to put off their night gear.

05:12:06.162 --> 05:12:19.242
The whole tribe of decorous personages, who had never heretofore been seen with a single hair of their heads awry, would start into public view with the disorder of a nightmare in their aspects.

05:12:19.242 --> 05:12:37.322
Old Governor Bellingham would come grimly forth, with his King James ruff fastened askew, and Mistress Hibbins, with some twigs of the forest clinging to her skirts, and looking sourer than ever, as having hardly got a wink of sleep after her night ride,

05:12:37.322 --> 05:12:49.162
and Goodfather Wilson too, after spending half the night at a deathbed, and liking ill to be disturbed thus early out of his dreams about the glorified saints.

05:12:49.162 --> 05:13:09.562
Hither likewise would come the elders and deacons of Mr Dimmesdale's church, and the young virgins who so idolized their minister, and had made a shrine for him in their white bosoms, which now, by the by, in their hurry and confusion, they would scantily have given themselves time to cover with their kerchiefs.

05:13:09.562 --> 05:13:32.642
All people in a word would come stumbling over their thresholds, and turning up their amazed and horror-stricken visages around the scaffold. Whom would they discern there with the red eastern light upon his brow? Whom but the Reverend Arthur Dimmesdale, half frozen to death, overwhelmed with shame, and standing where Hester Prynne had stood?

05:13:33.562 --> 05:13:57.822
Carried away by the grotesque horror of this picture, the minister, unawares and to his own infinite alarm, burst into a great peal of laughter. It was immediately responded to by a light, airy, childish laugh, in which, with a thrill of the heart, but he knew not whether of exquisite pain or pleasure as acute. He recognized the tones of Little Pearl.

05:13:58.722 --> 05:14:07.362
Pearl, Little Pearl, cried he, after a moment's pause, then suppressing his voice. Hester, Hester Prynne, are you there?

05:14:08.062 --> 05:14:20.622
Yes, it is Hester Prynne, she replied in a tone of surprise, and the minister heard her footsteps approaching from the sidewalk, along which she had been passing. It is I and my Little Pearl.

05:14:21.682 --> 05:14:25.622
Whence come you, Hester? asked the minister. What sent you hither?

05:14:25.622 --> 05:14:36.662
I have been watching at her death-bed, answered Hester Prynne, at Governor Winthrop's death-bed, and have taken his measure for a robe, and am now going homeward to my dwelling.

05:14:37.722 --> 05:14:50.102
Come up hither, Hester, thou and Little Pearl, said the Reverend Mr Dimmesdale. Ye have both been here before, but I was not with you. Come up hither once again, and we will stand all three together.

05:14:50.862 --> 05:14:59.962
She silently ascended the steps, and stood on the platform, holding Little Pearl by the hand. The minister felt for the child's other hand, and took it.

05:15:00.462 --> 05:15:18.382
The moment that he did so, there came what seemed a tumultuous rush of new life, other life than his own, pouring like a torrent into his heart, and hurrying through all his veins, as if the mother and the child were communicating their vital warmth to his half-torpid system.

05:15:18.382 --> 05:15:21.702
The three formed an electric chain.

05:15:22.942 --> 05:15:29.522
Minister, whispered Little Pearl, what wouldst thou say, child? asked Mr Dimmesdale.

05:15:30.522 --> 05:15:35.562
Wilt thou stand here with my mother and me to-morrow noontide? inquired Pearl.

05:15:36.762 --> 05:15:56.922
Nay, not so, my Little Pearl, answered the minister. For, with the new energy of the moment, all the dread of public exposure that had so long been the anguish of his life, had returned upon him, and he was already trembling at the conjunction in which, with the strange joy nevertheless, he now found himself.

05:15:56.922 --> 05:16:04.302
Not so, my child, I shall indeed stand with thy mother and thee one other day, but not to-morrow.

05:16:05.422 --> 05:16:10.402
Pearl laughed and attempted to pull away her hand, but the minister held it fast.

05:16:11.222 --> 05:16:13.802
A moment longer, my child, said he.

05:16:14.222 --> 05:16:20.342
But wilt thou promise, asked Pearl, to take my hand and mother's hand to-morrow noontide?

05:16:21.062 --> 05:16:24.442
Not then, Pearl, said the minister, but another time.

05:16:25.202 --> 05:16:27.922
And what other time? persisted the child.

05:16:28.702 --> 05:16:38.642
At the great judgment day, whispered the minister, and strangely enough, the sense that he was a professional teacher of the truth impelled him to answer the child so.

05:16:39.542 --> 05:16:48.902
Then and there, before the judgment seat, thy mother and thou and I must stand together, but the daylight of this world shall not see our meeting.

05:16:48.902 --> 05:16:50.962
Pearl laughed again.

05:16:51.802 --> 05:16:57.862
But before Mr. Dimmesdale had done speaking, a light gleamed far and wide over all the muffled sky.

05:16:58.342 --> 05:17:07.682
It was doubtless caused by one of those meteors which the night-watcher may so often observe burning out to waste in the vacant regions of the atmosphere.

05:17:08.242 --> 05:17:15.662
So powerful was its radiance that it thoroughly illuminated the dense medium of cloud betwixt the sky and earth.

05:17:15.662 --> 05:17:19.922
The great vault brightened like the dome of an immense lamp.

05:17:20.682 --> 05:17:31.782
It showed the familiar scene of the street with a distinctness of midday, but also with the awfulness that is always imparted to familiar objects by an unaccustomed light.

05:17:32.662 --> 05:17:36.702
The wooden houses with their jutting stories and quaint gable peaks.

05:17:37.422 --> 05:17:41.382
The doorsteps and thresholds with the early grass springing up about them.

05:17:41.842 --> 05:17:45.142
The garden plots, black with freshly turned earth.

05:17:45.142 --> 05:18:01.802
The wheel track, little worn, and even in the marketplace, margined with green on either side, all were visible, but with a singularity of aspect that seemed to give another moral interpretation to the things of this world than they had ever borne before.

05:18:01.802 --> 05:18:15.422
And there stood the minister with his hand over his heart, and Hester Prynne with the embroidered letter glimmering on her bosom, and Little Pearl herself a symbol and the connecting link between those two.

05:18:16.182 --> 05:18:28.122
They stood in the noon of that strange and solemn splendour, as if it were the light that is to reveal all secrets, and the daybreak that shall unite all who belong to one another.

05:18:28.122 --> 05:18:39.962
There was witchcraft in Little Pearl's eyes, and her face, as she glanced upward at the minister, wore that naughty smile which made its expression frequently so elvish.

05:18:40.622 --> 05:18:52.242
She withdrew her hand from Mr. Dimmesdale's, and pointed across the street, but he clasped both his hands over his breast, and cast his eyes towards the zenith.

05:18:52.962 --> 05:19:08.462
Nothing was more common in those days than to interpret all meteoric appearances and other natural phenomena that occurred with less regularity than the rise and set of sun and moon, as so many revelations from a supernatural source.

05:19:09.582 --> 05:19:23.562
Thus a blazing spear, a sword of flame, a bow or a sheaf of arrows seen in the midnight sky prefigured Indian warfare. Pestilence was known to have been foreboded by a shower of crimson light.

05:19:23.562 --> 05:19:38.202
We doubt whether any marked event for good or evil ever befell New England from its settlement down to revolutionary times, of which the inhabitants had not been previously warned by some spectacle of its nature.

05:19:39.402 --> 05:19:58.182
Not seldom it had been seen by multitudes. Oftener, however, its credibility rested on the faith of some lonely eyewitness, who beheld the wonder through the coloured, magnifying and distorted medium of his imagination, and shaped it more distinctly in his afterthought.

05:19:58.182 --> 05:20:14.322
It was indeed a majestic idea that the destiny of nations should be revealed in these awful hieroglyphics on the Cope of Heaven. A scroll so wide might not be deemed too expensive for Providence to write a people's doom upon.

05:20:14.322 --> 05:20:25.982
The belief was a favourite one with our forefathers, as betokening that their infant commonwealth was under a celestial guardianship of peculiar intimacy and strictness.

05:20:25.982 --> 05:20:35.082
But what shall we say when an individual discovers a revelation addressed to himself alone, on the same vast sheet of record?

05:20:35.082 --> 05:20:58.182
In such a case it could only be the symptom of a highly disordered mental state, when a man, rendered morbidly self-contemplative by long, intense and secret pain, had extended his egotism over the whole expanse of nature, until the firmament itself should appear no more than a fitting page for his soul's history and fate.

05:20:59.082 --> 05:21:14.902
We impute it therefore solely to the disease in his own eye and heart, that the minister, looking upward to the zenith, beheld there the appearance of an immense letter, the letter A, marked out in lines of dull red light.

05:21:14.902 --> 05:21:31.102
Not but the meteor may have shown itself at that point, burning duskily through a veil of cloud, but with no such shape as his guilty imagination gave it, or at least with so little definiteness that another's guilt might have seen another symbol in it.

05:21:31.102 --> 05:21:52.202
There was a singular circumstance that characterized Mr. Dimmesdale's psychological state at this moment. All the time that he gazed upward to the zenith, he was nevertheless perfectly aware that little Pearl was hinting her finger towards old Roger Chillingworth, who stood at no great distance from the scaffold.

05:21:52.202 --> 05:22:13.842
The minister appeared to see him with the same glance that discerned the miraculous letter. To his feature, as to all other objects, the meteoric light imparted a new expression, or it might well be that the physician was not careful then, as at all other times, to hide the malevolence with which he looked upon his victim.

05:22:13.842 --> 05:22:33.682
Certainly, if the meteor kindled up the sky and disclosed the earth with an awfulness that admonished Hester Prynne and the clergymen of the Day of Judgment, then might Roger Chillingworth have passed with them for the Arch Fiend, standing there with a smile and a scowl to claim his own.

05:22:33.682 --> 05:22:50.422
So vivid was the expression, or so intense the minister's perception of it, that it seemed still to remain painted on the darkness after the meteor had vanished, with an effect as if the street and all things else were at once annihilated.

05:22:51.822 --> 05:23:05.242
"'Who is that man, Hester?' gasped Mr Dimmesdale, overcome with terror. I shiver at him. Dost thou know the man? I hate him, Hester." She remembered her oath and was silent.

05:23:06.002 --> 05:23:16.422
"'I tell thee, my soul shivers at him,' muttered the minister again. Who is he? Who is he? Canst thou do nothing for me? I have a nameless horror of the man.'

05:23:17.782 --> 05:23:21.782
"'Minister,' said little Pearl, "'I can tell thee who he is.'

05:23:21.782 --> 05:23:29.642
"'Quickly then, child,' said the minister, bending his ear close to her lips, "'quickly, and as low as thou canst whisper.'"

05:23:29.642 --> 05:23:57.362
Pearl mumbled something into his ear that sounded indeed like human language, but was only such gibberish as children may be heard amusing themselves with by the hour together. At all events, if it involved any secret information in regard to old Roger Chillingworth, it was in a tongue unknown to the erudite clergyman, and did but increase the bewilderment of his mind. The elvish child then laughed aloud.

05:23:59.102 --> 05:24:02.022
"'Dost thou mock me now?' said the minister.

05:24:02.782 --> 05:24:11.362
"'Thou wast not bold. Thou wast not true,' answered the child. Thou wouldst not promise to take my hand and mother's hand to morrow noontide.'

05:24:12.902 --> 05:24:17.602
"'Worthy sir,' answered the physician, who had now advanced to the foot of the platform.

05:24:17.962 --> 05:24:21.242
"'Pious Master Dimmesdale, can this be you?'

05:24:21.242 --> 05:24:37.242
"'Well, well indeed. We men of study whose heads are in our books have need to be straightly looked after. We dream in our waking moments and walk in our sleep. Come, good sir, and my dear friend. I pray you, let me lead you home.'

05:24:37.842 --> 05:24:41.662
"'How knewst thou that I was here?' asked the minister fearfully.

05:24:42.142 --> 05:24:55.102
"'Barely and in good faith,' answered Roger Chillingworth, I knew nothing of the matter. I had spent the better part of the night at the bedside of the worshipful Governor Winthrop, doing what my poor skill might to give him ease.

05:24:55.702 --> 05:25:08.602
"'He going home to a better world, I likewise was on my way homeward when this light shone out. Come with me, I beseech you, reverend sir, else you will be poorly able to do Sabbath duty to-morrow.

05:25:09.382 --> 05:25:21.382
"'Aha, see now how they trouble the brain, these books, these books. You should study less, good sir, and take a little pastime, or these night whimsies will grow upon you.'

05:25:21.382 --> 05:25:34.602
"'I will go home with you,' said Mr. Dimmesdale. With a chill despondency, like one awakening, all nerveless from an ugly dream, he yielded himself to the physician and was led away.

05:25:35.402 --> 05:25:48.542
"'The next day, however, being the Sabbath, he preached a discourse which was held to be the richest and most powerful and the most replete with heavenly influences that had ever proceeded from his lips.

05:25:48.542 --> 05:26:02.922
"'Souls, it is said, more souls than one, were brought to the truth by the efficacy of that sermon, and vowed within themselves to cherish a holy gratitude towards Mr. Dimmesdale throughout the long hereafter.

05:26:02.922 --> 05:26:13.222
"'But as he came down the pulpit steps, the grey-bearded sexton met him holding up a black glove, which the minister recognized as his own.

05:26:13.682 --> 05:26:26.002
"'It was found,' said the sexton, this morning on the scaffold, where evildoers are set to public shame. Satan dropped it there, I take it, intending a scurrilous jest against your reverence.

05:26:26.002 --> 05:26:34.002
"'But indeed he was blind and foolish, as he ever and always is. A pure hand needs no glove to cover it.'

05:26:34.802 --> 05:26:46.722
"'Thank you, my good friend,' said the minister, gravely, but startled at heart, for so confused was his remembrance that he had almost brought himself to look at the events of the past night as visionary.

05:26:47.522 --> 05:27:00.102
"'Yes, it seems to me my glove, indeed. And since Satan saw fit to steal it, your reverence must needs handle him without gloves henceforward,' remarked the old sexton, grimly smiling.

05:27:00.102 --> 05:27:09.722
"'But did your reverence hear of the portent that was seen last night, a great red letter in the sky, the letter A, which we interpret to stand for Angel?

05:27:10.162 --> 05:27:18.922
"'For as our good Governor Winthrop was made an Angel this past night, it was doubtless held fit that there should be some notice thereof.'

05:27:18.922 --> 05:27:24.102
"'No,' answered the minister. I had not heard of it.'

05:27:35.742 --> 05:27:37.142
The End

05:28:00.895 --> 05:28:09.595
In her late, singular interview with Mr Dimmesdale, Hester Prynne was shocked at the condition to which she found the clergyman reduced.

05:28:10.415 --> 05:28:17.495
His nerve seemed absolutely destroyed. His moral force was abased into more than childish weakness.

05:28:18.015 --> 05:28:24.635
It grovelled helpless on the ground, even while his intellectual faculties retained their pristine strength,

05:28:24.635 --> 05:28:30.355
or had perhaps acquired a morbid energy which disease alone could have given them.

05:28:30.995 --> 05:28:40.135
With her knowledge of a train of circumstances hidden from all others, she could readily infer that besides the legitimate action of his own conscience,

05:28:40.715 --> 05:28:48.755
a terrible machinery had been brought to bear and was still operating on Mr Dimmesdale's well-being and repose.

05:28:48.755 --> 05:28:57.935
Knowing what this poor fallen man had once been, her whole soul was moved by the shuddering terror with which she had appealed to her,

05:28:58.015 --> 05:29:03.275
the outcast woman, for support against his instinctively discovered enemy.

05:29:04.215 --> 05:29:08.755
She decided, moreover, that he had a right to her utmost aid.

05:29:09.735 --> 05:29:18.395
Little accustomed in her long seclusion from society to measure her ideas of right and wrong by any standard external to herself,

05:29:18.395 --> 05:29:25.575
Esther saw, or seemed to see, that there lay a responsibility upon her in reference to the clergyman,

05:29:25.955 --> 05:29:29.535
which she owed to no other, nor to the whole world besides.

05:29:30.275 --> 05:29:39.015
The links that united her to the rest of humankind, links of flowers or silk or gold or whatever the material, had all been broken.

05:29:39.915 --> 05:29:45.595
Here was the iron link of mutual crime which neither he nor she could break.

05:29:45.595 --> 05:29:50.355
Like all other ties, it brought along with it its obligations.

05:29:52.155 --> 05:30:00.055
Hester Prynne did not now occupy precisely the same position in which we beheld her during the earlier periods of her ignominy.

05:30:00.975 --> 05:30:04.935
Years had come and gone. Pearl was now seven years old.

05:30:05.635 --> 05:30:14.275
Her mother, with the scarlet letter on her breast, glittering in its fantastic embroidery, had long been a familiar object to the townspeople.

05:30:15.215 --> 05:30:20.455
As is apt to be the case when a person stands out in any prominence before the community,

05:30:21.215 --> 05:30:26.655
and at the same time interferes neither with public nor individual interests and convenience,

05:30:27.415 --> 05:30:32.675
a species of general regard had ultimately grown up in reference to Hester Prynne.

05:30:33.355 --> 05:30:41.675
It is to the credit of human nature that, except where its selfishness is brought into play, it loves more readily than it hates.

05:30:42.315 --> 05:30:47.355
Hatred, by a gradual and quiet process, will even be transformed to love,

05:30:47.615 --> 05:30:54.035
unless the change be impeded by a continually new irritation of the original feeling of hostility.

05:30:55.275 --> 05:31:00.435
In this matter of Hester Prynne, there was neither irritation nor irksomeness.

05:31:01.055 --> 05:31:06.515
She never battled with the public, but submitted uncomplainingly to its worst usage.

05:31:07.115 --> 05:31:10.335
She made no claim upon it in requital for what she suffered.

05:31:10.335 --> 05:31:12.735
She did not weigh upon its sympathies.

05:31:14.475 --> 05:31:22.835
Then also the blameless purity of her life during all these years in which she had been set apart to infamy was reckoned largely in her favour.

05:31:23.575 --> 05:31:29.635
With nothing now to lose in the sight of mankind, and with no hope and seemingly no wish of gaining anything,

05:31:30.315 --> 05:31:35.935
it could only be a genuine regard for virtue that had brought back the poor wanderer to its paths.

05:31:35.935 --> 05:31:43.795
It was perceived, too, that while Hester never put forward even the humblest title to share in the world's privileges,

05:31:44.375 --> 05:31:51.495
further than to breathe the common air and earn daily bread for little Pearl and herself by the faithful labour of her hands,

05:31:52.055 --> 05:31:58.775
she was quick to acknowledge her sisterhood with the race of man whenever benefits were to be conferred.

05:31:58.775 --> 05:32:03.255
None so ready as she to give of her little substance to every demand of poverty,

05:32:03.755 --> 05:32:10.315
even though the bitter-hearted pauper threw back a jibe in requital of the food brought regularly to his door,

05:32:10.815 --> 05:32:15.575
or the garments wrought for him by the fingers that could have embroidered a monarch's robe.

05:32:17.115 --> 05:32:21.415
None so self-devoted as Hester when pestilence stalked through the town.

05:32:21.415 --> 05:32:29.995
In all seasons of calamity, indeed, whether general or of individuals, the outcast of society at once found her place.

05:32:30.795 --> 05:32:37.215
She came not as a guest, but as a rightful inmate into the household that was darkened by trouble,

05:32:37.755 --> 05:32:43.975
as if its gloomy twilight were a medium in which she was entitled to hold intercourse with her fellow-creature.

05:32:45.155 --> 05:32:49.775
There glimmered the embroidered letter, with comfort in its unearthly ray.

05:32:49.775 --> 05:32:54.315
Elsewhere the token of sin, it was the taper of the sick chamber.

05:32:55.355 --> 05:33:01.315
It had even thrown its gleam in the sufferer's hard extremity across the verge of time.

05:33:02.015 --> 05:33:06.955
It had shown him where to set his foot while the light of earth was fast becoming dim,

05:33:07.475 --> 05:33:09.935
and ere the light of futurity could reach him.

05:33:10.695 --> 05:33:14.755
In such emergencies Hester's nature showed itself warm and rich,

05:33:14.755 --> 05:33:22.255
a wellspring of human tenderness, unfailing to every real demand, and inexhaustible by the largest.

05:33:23.415 --> 05:33:28.575
Her breast, with its badge of shame, was but the softer pillow for the head that needed one.

05:33:29.455 --> 05:33:36.955
She was self-ordained a sister of mercy, or, we may rather say, the world's heavy hand had so ordained her,

05:33:37.175 --> 05:33:40.595
when neither the world nor she looked forward to this result.

05:33:41.395 --> 05:33:43.635
The letter was the symbol of her calling.

05:33:44.775 --> 05:33:49.275
Such helpfulness was found in her, so much power to do and power to sympathize,

05:33:50.315 --> 05:33:55.035
that many people refused to interpret the scarlet A by its original signification.

05:33:56.255 --> 05:34:00.835
They said it meant Abel, so strong was Hester Prynne, with a woman's strength.

05:34:01.515 --> 05:34:04.295
It was only the darkened house that could contain her.

05:34:04.915 --> 05:34:07.835
When sunshine came again, she was not there.

05:34:08.655 --> 05:34:10.955
Her shadow had faded across the threshold.

05:34:10.955 --> 05:34:17.835
The helpful inmate had departed without one backward glance to gather up the mead of gratitude,

05:34:18.295 --> 05:34:22.495
if any were in the hearts of those whom she had served so zealously.

05:34:24.075 --> 05:34:27.675
Meeting them in the street, she never raised her head to receive their greeting.

05:34:28.575 --> 05:34:33.955
If they were resolute to accost her, she laid her finger on the scarlet letter and passed on.

05:34:35.115 --> 05:34:38.455
This might be pride, but was so like humility,

05:34:39.015 --> 05:34:43.535
that it produced all the softening influence of the latter quality on the public mind.

05:34:44.315 --> 05:34:46.415
The public is despotic in its temper.

05:34:47.135 --> 05:34:52.295
It is capable of denying common justice when too strenuously demanded as a right.

05:34:53.115 --> 05:34:57.715
But quite as frequently, it awards more than justice when the appeal is made,

05:34:58.195 --> 05:35:02.195
as despots love to have it made, entirely to its generosity.

05:35:03.855 --> 05:35:07.595
Interpreting Hester Prynne's deportment as an appeal of this nature,

05:35:08.395 --> 05:35:12.635
society was inclined to show its former victim a more benign countenance

05:35:12.635 --> 05:35:16.955
than she cared to be favoured with, or perchance, than she deserved.

05:35:17.835 --> 05:35:21.035
The rulers and the wise and learned men of the community

05:35:21.035 --> 05:35:25.995
were longer in acknowledging the influence of Hester's good qualities than the people.

05:35:26.755 --> 05:35:29.835
The prejudices which they shared in common with the latter

05:35:29.835 --> 05:35:34.155
were fortified in themselves by an iron framework of reasoning

05:35:34.155 --> 05:35:38.175
that made it a far tougher labour to expel them.

05:35:39.135 --> 05:35:45.075
Day by day, nevertheless, their sour and rigid wrinkles were relaxing into something

05:35:45.075 --> 05:35:50.935
which, in the due course of years, might grow to be an expression of almost benevolence.

05:35:52.155 --> 05:35:55.575
Thus it was with the men of rank on whom their eminent position

05:35:55.575 --> 05:35:58.415
imposed the guardianship of the public morals.

05:36:00.015 --> 05:36:04.615
Individuals in private life, meanwhile, had quite forgiven Hester Prynne for her frailty.

05:36:05.515 --> 05:36:09.615
Nay more, they had begun to look upon the scarlet letter as the token,

05:36:10.115 --> 05:36:14.775
not of that one sin for which she had borne so long and dreary a penance,

05:36:15.175 --> 05:36:17.335
but of her many good deeds since.

05:36:17.955 --> 05:36:22.015
Do you see that woman with the embroidered badge, they would say to strangers?

05:36:22.375 --> 05:36:27.135
It is our Hester, the town's own Hester, who is so kind to the poor,

05:36:27.135 --> 05:36:31.375
so helpful to the sick, so comfortable to the afflicted.

05:36:32.035 --> 05:36:36.755
Then it is true the propensity of human nature to tell the very worst of itself,

05:36:37.295 --> 05:36:39.055
when embodied in the person of another,

05:36:39.295 --> 05:36:43.475
would constrain them to whisper the black scandal of bygone years.

05:36:44.475 --> 05:36:49.375
It was nonetheless a fact, however, that in the eyes of the very men who spoke thus,

05:36:49.855 --> 05:36:53.275
the scarlet letter had the effect of the cross on a nun's bosom.

05:36:54.715 --> 05:36:57.435
It imparted to the wearer a kind of sacredness,

05:36:58.135 --> 05:37:01.375
which enabled her to walk securely amid all peril.

05:37:02.475 --> 05:37:05.395
Had she fallen among thieves, it would have kept her safe.

05:37:06.535 --> 05:37:08.855
It was reported, and believed by many,

05:37:09.175 --> 05:37:11.815
that an Indian had drawn his arrow against the badge,

05:37:12.175 --> 05:37:15.755
and that the missile struck it and fell harmless to the ground.

05:37:17.635 --> 05:37:21.995
The effect of the symbol, or rather of the position in respect to society

05:37:21.995 --> 05:37:26.015
that was indicated by it, on the mind of Hester Prynne herself,

05:37:26.275 --> 05:37:27.895
was powerful and peculiar.

05:37:29.095 --> 05:37:32.255
All the light and graceful foliage of her character

05:37:32.255 --> 05:37:35.415
had been withered up by this red-hot brand,

05:37:36.075 --> 05:37:40.355
and had long ago fallen away, leaving a bare and harsh outline,

05:37:40.795 --> 05:37:42.275
which might have been repulsive,

05:37:42.475 --> 05:37:46.175
had she possessed friends or companions to be repelled by it.

05:37:46.795 --> 05:37:50.775
Even the attractiveness of her person had undergone a similar change.

05:37:51.395 --> 05:37:55.335
It might be partly owing to the studied austerity of her dress,

05:37:55.715 --> 05:37:58.455
and partly to the lack of demonstration in her manners.

05:37:59.395 --> 05:38:01.715
It was a sad transformation, too,

05:38:01.835 --> 05:38:05.615
that her rich and luxuriant hair had either been cut off,

05:38:05.795 --> 05:38:07.935
or was so completely hidden by a cap,

05:38:08.355 --> 05:38:12.695
that not a shining lock of it ever once gushed into the sunshine.

05:38:13.855 --> 05:38:16.115
It was due in part to all these causes,

05:38:16.495 --> 05:38:18.475
but still more to something else,

05:38:18.475 --> 05:38:22.135
that there seemed to be no longer anything in Hester's face

05:38:22.135 --> 05:38:23.915
for love to dwell upon,

05:38:24.495 --> 05:38:28.255
nothing in Hester's form, though majestic and statue-like,

05:38:28.775 --> 05:38:32.295
that passion would ever dream of clasping in its embrace,

05:38:33.095 --> 05:38:37.755
nothing in Hester's bosom to make it ever again the pillow of affection.

05:38:39.235 --> 05:38:41.755
Some attribute had departed from her,

05:38:42.015 --> 05:38:45.335
the permanence of which had been essential to keep her a woman.

05:38:46.495 --> 05:38:48.235
Such is frequently the fate,

05:38:48.415 --> 05:38:52.255
and such the stern development of the feminine character and person,

05:38:52.595 --> 05:38:54.035
when the woman has encountered,

05:38:54.115 --> 05:38:57.775
and lived through, an experience of peculiar severity.

05:38:59.375 --> 05:39:02.135
If she be all tenderness, she will die.

05:39:02.815 --> 05:39:07.055
If she survive, the tenderness will either be crushed out of her,

05:39:07.315 --> 05:39:09.895
or, and the outward semblance is the same,

05:39:09.895 --> 05:39:14.995
crushed so deeply into her heart that it can never show itself more.

05:39:15.755 --> 05:39:18.255
The latter is perhaps the truest theory.

05:39:19.295 --> 05:39:22.395
She who has once been a woman and ceased to be so,

05:39:22.635 --> 05:39:25.015
might at any moment become a woman again,

05:39:25.255 --> 05:39:28.755
if there were only the magic touch to affect the transformation.

05:39:29.915 --> 05:39:34.975
We shall see whether Hester Prynne were ever afterwards so touched and so transfigured.

05:39:36.035 --> 05:39:38.895
Much of the marble coldness of Hester's impression

05:39:38.895 --> 05:39:42.895
was to be attributed to the circumstance that her life had turned

05:39:42.895 --> 05:39:46.855
in a great measure from passion and feeling to thought.

05:39:47.935 --> 05:39:49.035
Standing alone in the world,

05:39:49.475 --> 05:39:51.895
alone as to any dependence on society,

05:39:52.315 --> 05:39:54.895
and with little pearl to be guided and protected,

05:39:55.595 --> 05:39:58.195
alone and hopeless of retrieving her position,

05:39:58.675 --> 05:40:01.535
even had she not scorned to consider it desirable,

05:40:02.255 --> 05:40:05.235
she cast away the fragment of a broken chain.

05:40:05.835 --> 05:40:08.895
The world's law was no law for her mind.

05:40:09.515 --> 05:40:13.235
It was an age in which the human intellect, newly emancipated,

05:40:14.095 --> 05:40:18.755
had taken a more active and a wider range than for many centuries before.

05:40:19.915 --> 05:40:23.055
Men of the sword had overthrown nobles and kings.

05:40:24.055 --> 05:40:27.475
Men bolder than these had overthrown and rearranged,

05:40:27.735 --> 05:40:30.675
not actually, but within the sphere of theory,

05:40:30.855 --> 05:40:32.715
which was their most real abode,

05:40:32.715 --> 05:40:35.455
the whole system of ancient prejudice,

05:40:35.935 --> 05:40:38.515
wherewith was linked much of ancient principle.

05:40:39.875 --> 05:40:41.935
Hester Prynne imbibed this spirit.

05:40:42.615 --> 05:40:44.695
She assumed a freedom of speculation,

05:40:45.015 --> 05:40:47.695
then common enough on the other side of the Atlantic,

05:40:48.275 --> 05:40:50.915
but which our forefathers, had they known it,

05:40:51.175 --> 05:40:53.095
would have held to be a deadlier crime

05:40:53.095 --> 05:40:55.975
than that stigmatized by the scarlet letter.

05:40:56.915 --> 05:40:59.635
In her lonesome cottage by the seashore,

05:40:59.635 --> 05:41:04.695
thoughts visited her such as dared to enter no other dwelling in New England.

05:41:05.115 --> 05:41:09.935
Shadowy guests that would have been as perilous as demons to their entertainer

05:41:09.935 --> 05:41:13.195
could they have been seen so much as knocking at her door.

05:41:14.635 --> 05:41:17.875
It is remarkable that persons who speculate the most boldly

05:41:18.495 --> 05:41:24.135
often conform with the most perfect quietude to the external regulations of society.

05:41:24.795 --> 05:41:26.775
The thought suffices them,

05:41:27.035 --> 05:41:30.135
without investing itself in the flesh and blood of action.

05:41:30.815 --> 05:41:33.095
So it seemed to be with Hester.

05:41:33.515 --> 05:41:37.055
Yet had little Pearl never come to her from the spiritual world,

05:41:37.415 --> 05:41:39.315
it might have been far otherwise.

05:41:39.895 --> 05:41:42.335
Then she might have come down to us in history,

05:41:42.735 --> 05:41:44.575
hand in hand with Anne Hutchinson,

05:41:45.195 --> 05:41:47.335
as the foundress of her religious sect.

05:41:47.995 --> 05:41:51.195
She might, in one of her phases, have been a prophetess.

05:41:51.195 --> 05:41:54.095
She might, and not improbably would,

05:41:54.515 --> 05:41:57.715
have suffered death from the stern tribunals of the period

05:41:57.715 --> 05:42:02.175
for attempting to undermine the foundations of the Puritan establishment.

05:42:03.395 --> 05:42:05.395
But in the education of her child,

05:42:05.755 --> 05:42:09.715
the mother's enthusiasm of thought had something to wreak itself upon.

05:42:11.215 --> 05:42:15.155
Providence in the person of this little girl had assigned to Hester's charge

05:42:15.155 --> 05:42:17.355
the German blossom of womanhood,

05:42:17.355 --> 05:42:21.215
to be cherished and developed amid a host of difficulties.

05:42:22.135 --> 05:42:23.995
Everything was against her.

05:42:24.355 --> 05:42:25.815
The world was hostile.

05:42:26.435 --> 05:42:29.195
The child's own nature had something wrong in it

05:42:29.195 --> 05:42:32.425
which continually betokened that she had been born amiss,

05:42:33.295 --> 05:42:35.755
the effluence of her mother's lawless passion,

05:42:36.355 --> 05:42:40.015
and often impelled Hester to ask, in bitterness of heart,

05:42:40.555 --> 05:42:45.115
whether it were for ill or good that the poor little creature had been born at all.

05:42:46.155 --> 05:42:49.695
Indeed, the same dark question often rose into her mind

05:42:49.695 --> 05:42:52.135
with reference to the whole race of womanhood.

05:42:52.855 --> 05:42:56.815
Was existence worth accepting, even to the happiest among them?

05:42:57.695 --> 05:43:00.315
As concerned her own individual existence,

05:43:00.735 --> 05:43:03.155
she had long ago decided in the negative

05:43:03.155 --> 05:43:05.475
and dismissed the point as settled.

05:43:06.515 --> 05:43:11.335
A tendency to speculation, though it may keep woman quiet, as it does man,

05:43:11.775 --> 05:43:13.175
yet makes her sad.

05:43:13.175 --> 05:43:17.635
She discerns it may be such a hopeless task before her.

05:43:19.195 --> 05:43:24.835
As a first step, the whole system of society is to be torn down and built up anew.

05:43:25.335 --> 05:43:29.595
Then the very nature of the opposite sex or its long hereditary habit,

05:43:29.995 --> 05:43:31.575
which has become like nature,

05:43:32.315 --> 05:43:36.155
is to be essentially modified before woman can be allowed to assume

05:43:36.155 --> 05:43:38.915
what seems a fair and suitable position.

05:43:39.715 --> 05:43:42.915
Finally, all other difficulties being obviated,

05:43:43.775 --> 05:43:47.255
woman cannot take advantage of these preliminary reforms

05:43:47.255 --> 05:43:51.815
until she herself shall have undergone a still mightier change,

05:43:52.115 --> 05:43:57.135
in which perhaps the ethereal essence wherein she has her truest life

05:43:57.135 --> 05:43:59.535
will be found to have evaporated.

05:44:00.835 --> 05:44:04.915
A woman never overcomes these problems by any exercise of thought.

05:44:04.915 --> 05:44:08.415
They are not to be solved, or only in one way.

05:44:09.275 --> 05:44:12.495
If her heart chants to come uppermost, they vanish.

05:44:13.515 --> 05:44:17.415
Thus Hester Prynne, whose heart had lost its regular and healthy throb,

05:44:17.895 --> 05:44:21.155
wandered without a clue in the dark labyrinth of mind,

05:44:21.675 --> 05:44:24.975
now turned aside by an insurmountable precipice,

05:44:25.195 --> 05:44:27.715
now starting back from a deep chasm.

05:44:28.655 --> 05:44:32.415
There was a wild and ghastly scenery all around her,

05:44:32.415 --> 05:44:34.715
and a home and comfort nowhere.

05:44:36.955 --> 05:44:40.195
At times a fearful doubt strove to possess her soul,

05:44:40.375 --> 05:44:43.335
whether it were not better to send Pearl at once to heaven,

05:44:43.695 --> 05:44:48.255
and go herself to such futurity as eternal justice should provide.

05:44:49.355 --> 05:44:52.115
The scarlet letter had not done its office.

05:44:53.355 --> 05:44:56.815
Now, however, her interview with the Reverend Mr Dimmesdale

05:44:56.815 --> 05:45:01.195
on the night of his vigil had given her a new theme of reflection,

05:45:01.195 --> 05:45:05.655
and held up to her an object that appeared worthy of any exertion

05:45:05.655 --> 05:45:07.655
and sacrifice for its attainment.

05:45:08.935 --> 05:45:12.915
She had witnessed the intense misery beneath which the minister struggled,

05:45:13.435 --> 05:45:16.495
or to speak more accurately, had ceased to struggle.

05:45:17.175 --> 05:45:19.975
She saw that he stood on the verge of lunacy,

05:45:20.395 --> 05:45:22.995
if he had not already stepped across it.

05:45:23.315 --> 05:45:27.395
It was impossible to doubt that whatever painful efficacy

05:45:27.395 --> 05:45:30.195
there might be in the secret sting of remorse,

05:45:30.195 --> 05:45:33.395
a deadly avenom had been infused into it

05:45:33.395 --> 05:45:35.475
by the hand that proffered relief.

05:45:36.695 --> 05:45:40.055
A secret enemy had been continually by his side

05:45:40.055 --> 05:45:42.755
under the semblance of a friend and helper,

05:45:43.275 --> 05:45:46.455
and had availed himself of the opportunities thus afforded

05:45:46.455 --> 05:45:50.335
for tampering with the delicate springs of Mr Dimmesdale's nature.

05:45:52.075 --> 05:45:55.455
Hester could not but ask herself whether there had not originally

05:45:55.455 --> 05:45:59.855
been a defect of truth, courage and loyalty on her own part

05:45:59.855 --> 05:46:03.115
in allowing the minister to be thrown into a position

05:46:03.115 --> 05:46:06.175
where so much evil was to be foreboded,

05:46:06.395 --> 05:46:08.515
and nothing auspicious to be hoped.

05:46:09.735 --> 05:46:13.715
Her only justification lay in the fact that she had been able to discern

05:46:13.715 --> 05:46:19.035
no method of rescuing him from a blacker ruin than had overwhelmed herself,

05:46:19.515 --> 05:46:23.735
except by acquiescing in Roger Chillingworth's scheme of disguise.

05:46:24.575 --> 05:46:27.115
Under that impulse she had made her choice,

05:46:27.115 --> 05:46:32.275
and had chosen, as it now appeared, the more wretched alternative of the two.

05:46:33.415 --> 05:46:37.595
She determined to redeem her error so far as it might yet be possible.

05:46:38.455 --> 05:46:41.135
Strengthened by years of hard and solemn trial,

05:46:41.255 --> 05:46:45.195
she felt herself no longer so inadequate to cope with Roger Chillingworth

05:46:45.195 --> 05:46:49.315
as on that night, abased by sin and half-maddened by the ignominy

05:46:49.315 --> 05:46:53.355
that was still new when they had talked together in the prison chamber.

05:46:53.975 --> 05:46:57.315
She had climbed her way since then to a higher point.

05:46:58.295 --> 05:47:02.035
The old man, on the other hand, had brought himself nearer to her level,

05:47:02.255 --> 05:47:06.355
or perhaps below it, by the revenge which he had stooped for.

05:47:07.295 --> 05:47:11.095
In fine Hester Prynne resolved to meet her former husband

05:47:11.095 --> 05:47:15.415
and do what might be in her power for the rescue of the victim

05:47:15.415 --> 05:47:18.395
on whom he had so evidently set his grip.

05:47:19.855 --> 05:47:21.835
The occasion was not long to seek.

05:47:21.835 --> 05:47:26.635
One afternoon, walking with Pearl in a retired part of the peninsula,

05:47:27.195 --> 05:47:32.995
she beheld the old physician with a basket on one arm and a staff in the other hand,

05:47:33.295 --> 05:47:38.475
stooping along the ground in quest of roots and herbs to concoct his medicine withal.

05:48:05.822 --> 05:48:09.262
The Scarlet Letter by Nathaniel Hawthorne

05:48:16.682 --> 05:48:22.002
Hester, bad little Pearl, run down to the margin of the water and play with the shells

05:48:22.002 --> 05:48:27.762
and tangled seaweed until she should have talked a while with the undergatherer of herbs.

05:48:28.802 --> 05:48:34.862
So the child flew away like a bird, and making bare her small white feet went pattering along

05:48:34.862 --> 05:48:41.282
the moist margin of the sea. Here and there she came to a full stop and peeped curiously

05:48:41.282 --> 05:48:48.162
into a pool left by the retiring tide as a mirror for Pearl to see her face in. Fourth

05:48:48.162 --> 05:48:54.742
peeped at her out of the pool with dark glistening curls around her head and an elf smile in

05:48:54.742 --> 05:49:01.142
her eyes, the image of a little maid whom Pearl, having no other playmate, invited to

05:49:01.142 --> 05:49:06.802
take her hand and run a race with her. But the visionary little maid on her part beckoned

05:49:07.222 --> 05:49:14.062
likewise, as if to say, This is a better place, come thou into the pool. And Pearl, stepping

05:49:14.062 --> 05:49:20.242
in mid-leg deep, beheld her own white feet at the bottom, while out of a still lower

05:49:20.242 --> 05:49:26.722
depth came a gleam of a kind of fragmentary smile floating to and fro in the agitated

05:49:26.722 --> 05:49:31.702
water. Meanwhile her mother had accosted the physician.

05:49:32.202 --> 05:49:36.862
I would speak a word with you, said she, a word that concerns us much.

05:49:37.922 --> 05:49:43.482
Aha! and is it Mistress Hester that has a word for old Roger Chillingworth? answered

05:49:43.482 --> 05:49:50.242
he, raising himself from his stooping posture, with all my heart. Why, Mistress, I hear good

05:49:50.242 --> 05:49:57.262
tidings of you on all hands. No longer ago than yester eve a magistrate, a wise and godly

05:49:57.262 --> 05:50:03.322
man, was discoursing of your affairs, Mistress Hester, and whispered me that there had been

05:50:03.322 --> 05:50:08.822
question concerning you in the council. It was debated whether or no, with safety to

05:50:08.822 --> 05:50:14.962
the commonweal, yonder scarlet letter might be taken off your bosom. On my life, Hester,

05:50:15.462 --> 05:50:19.942
I made my entreaty to the worshipful magistrate that it might be done forthwith.

05:50:21.322 --> 05:50:27.082
It lies not in the pleasure of the magistrates to take off the badge, calmly replied Hester.

05:50:27.262 --> 05:50:32.482
Were I worthy to be quit of it, it would fall away of its own nature, or be transformed

05:50:32.482 --> 05:50:35.302
into something that should speak a different purport.

05:50:36.502 --> 05:50:41.862
Nay, then, wear it, if it suit you better, rejoined he. A woman must needs follow her

05:50:41.862 --> 05:50:47.382
own fancy touching the adornment of her person. The letter is gaily embroidered, and shows

05:50:47.382 --> 05:50:48.982
right bravely on your bosom.

05:50:50.082 --> 05:50:55.562
All this while Hester had been looking steadily at the old man, and was shocked, as well as

05:50:55.562 --> 05:51:02.862
to discern what a change had been wrought upon him within the past seven years. It was

05:51:02.862 --> 05:51:08.102
not so much that he had grown older, for though the traces of advancing life were visible,

05:51:08.362 --> 05:51:14.702
he bore his age well, and seemed to retain a wiry vigour and alertness. But the former

05:51:14.702 --> 05:51:21.002
aspect of an intellectual and studious man, calm and quiet, which was what she best remembered

05:51:21.002 --> 05:51:27.482
in him, had altogether vanished, and been succeeded by an eager, searching, almost fierce,

05:51:27.702 --> 05:51:34.102
yet carefully guarded look. It seemed to be his wish and purpose to mask this expression

05:51:34.102 --> 05:51:40.402
with a smile, but the latter played him false, and flickered over his visage so derisively

05:51:40.402 --> 05:51:44.482
that the spectator could see his blackness all the better for it.

05:51:45.282 --> 05:51:51.702
Ever and on, too, there came a glare of red light out of his eyes, as if the old man's

05:51:51.702 --> 05:51:57.922
soul were on fire, and kept on smouldering duskily within his breast, until, by some

05:51:57.922 --> 05:52:05.122
casual puff of passion, it was blown into a momentary flame. This he repressed as speedily

05:52:05.122 --> 05:52:09.482
as possible, and strove to look as if nothing of the kind had happened.

05:52:10.742 --> 05:52:17.502
In a word, old Roger Chillingworth was a striking evidence of man's faculty of transforming

05:52:17.502 --> 05:52:24.162
himself into a devil, if he will only, for a reasonable space of time, undertake a devil's

05:52:24.162 --> 05:52:31.022
office. This unhappy person had effected such a transformation by devoting himself for seven

05:52:31.022 --> 05:52:37.342
years to the constant analysis of a heart full of torture, and deriving his enjoyment

05:52:37.342 --> 05:52:43.582
of events, and adding fuel to those fiery tortures which he analysed and gloated over.

05:52:44.542 --> 05:52:50.602
The scarlet letter burned on Hester Prynne's bosom. Here was another ruin, the responsibility

05:52:50.602 --> 05:52:52.922
of which came partly home to her.

05:52:53.962 --> 05:53:00.702
What see you in my face? asked the physician, that you look at it so earnestly. Something

05:53:00.702 --> 05:53:05.382
that would make me weep if there were any tears bitter enough for it, answered she,

05:53:05.382 --> 05:53:10.322
but let it pass. It is of yonder miserable man that I would speak.

05:53:10.962 --> 05:53:16.462
And what of him? cried Roger Chillingworth, eagerly, as if he loved the topic, and were

05:53:16.462 --> 05:53:21.662
glad of an opportunity to discuss it with the only person of whom he could make a confidant.

05:53:23.162 --> 05:53:28.202
Not to hide the truth, Mistress Hester, my thoughts happen just now to be busy with the

05:53:28.202 --> 05:53:31.842
gentleman, so speak freely, and I will make answer.

05:53:33.142 --> 05:53:38.882
When we last spake together, said Hester, now seven years ago, it was your pleasure

05:53:38.882 --> 05:53:44.782
to extort a promise of secrecy as touching the former relation betwixt yourself and me.

05:53:45.302 --> 05:53:50.642
As the life and good fame of yonder man were in your hands, there seemed no choice to me

05:53:50.642 --> 05:53:56.482
save to be silent in accordance with your behest. Yet it was not without heavy misgivings

05:53:56.482 --> 05:54:02.602
that I thus bound myself, for having cast off all duty towards other human beings, there

05:54:02.602 --> 05:54:07.942
remained a duty towards him, and something whispered me that I was betraying it in pledging

05:54:07.942 --> 05:54:09.622
myself to keep your counsel.

05:54:10.882 --> 05:54:16.582
Since that day no man is so near to him as you. You tread behind his every footstep.

05:54:16.782 --> 05:54:22.822
You are beside him, sleeping and waking. You search his thoughts. You burrow and rankle

05:54:22.822 --> 05:54:28.982
in his heart. Your clutch is on his life, and you cause him to die daily a living death,

05:54:29.282 --> 05:54:34.422
and still he knows you not. In permitting this, I have surely acted a false part by

05:54:34.422 --> 05:54:38.102
the only man to whom the power was left me to be true.

05:54:39.282 --> 05:54:45.842
What choice had you? asked Roger Chillingworth. My finger pointed that this man would have

05:54:45.842 --> 05:54:51.822
hurled him from his pulpit into a dungeon, thence peradventure to the gallows. It had

05:54:51.822 --> 05:54:54.502
been better so, said Hester Prynne.

05:54:54.902 --> 05:55:00.362
What evil have I done the man? asked Roger Chillingworth again. I tell thee, Hester Prynne,

05:55:00.762 --> 05:55:05.702
the richest fee that ever physician earned from monarch could not have bought such care

05:55:05.702 --> 05:55:11.462
as I have wasted on this miserable priest. But for my aid, his life would have burnt

05:55:11.462 --> 05:55:16.982
away in torment within the first two years after the perpetration of his crime and thine.

05:55:16.982 --> 05:55:22.982
For, Hester, his spirit lacked the strength that could have borne up as thine has beneath

05:55:22.982 --> 05:55:31.102
a burden like thy scarlet letter. Oh, I could reveal a goodly secret. But enough! What art

05:55:31.102 --> 05:55:37.302
can do? I have exhausted on him. That he now breathes and creeps about on earth is owing

05:55:37.302 --> 05:55:38.382
all to me.

05:55:39.042 --> 05:55:42.402
Better he had died at once, said Hester Prynne.

05:55:42.402 --> 05:55:49.022
Yea, woman, thou sayest truly, cried old Roger Chillingworth, letting the lurid fire of his

05:55:49.022 --> 05:55:55.922
heart blaze out before her eyes. Better had he died at once. Never did mortal suffer what

05:55:55.922 --> 05:56:02.242
this man has suffered, and all, all in sight of his worst enemy. He has been conscious

05:56:02.242 --> 05:56:09.222
of me. He has felt an influence dwelling always upon him like a curse. He knew by some spiritual

05:56:09.222 --> 05:56:15.222
sense, for the Creator never made another being so sensitive as this. He knew that no

05:56:15.222 --> 05:56:20.582
friendly hand was pulling at his heartstrings, and that an eye was looking curiously into

05:56:20.582 --> 05:56:27.082
him, which sought only evil, and found it. But he knew not that the eye and hand were

05:56:27.082 --> 05:56:32.822
mine. With the superstition common to his brotherhood, he fancied himself given over

05:56:32.822 --> 05:56:39.062
to a fiend to be tortured with frightful dreams and desperate thoughts. The sting of remorse

05:56:39.062 --> 05:56:45.962
and despair of pardon as a foretaste of what awaits him beyond the grave. But it was the

05:56:45.962 --> 05:56:52.062
constant shadow of my presence, the closest propinquity of the man whom he had most vilely

05:56:52.062 --> 05:56:57.882
wronged, and who had grown to exist only by this perpetual poison of the direst revenge.

05:56:59.262 --> 05:57:05.362
Yea, indeed, he did not err. There was a fiend at his elbow. A mortal man with once a human

05:57:05.362 --> 05:57:12.782
heart has become a fiend for his especial torment. The unfortunate physician, while

05:57:12.782 --> 05:57:18.262
uttering these words, lifted his hands with a look of horror, as if he had beheld some

05:57:18.262 --> 05:57:24.042
frightful shape which he could not recognize, usurping the place of his own image in a glass.

05:57:24.862 --> 05:57:30.202
It was one of those moments, which sometimes occur only at the interval of years, when

05:57:30.842 --> 05:57:37.442
aspect is faithfully revealed to his mind's eye. Not improbably, he had never before viewed

05:57:37.442 --> 05:57:39.222
himself as he did now.

05:57:40.422 --> 05:57:46.222
Hast thou not tortured him enough, said Hester, noticing the old man's look? Has he not paid

05:57:46.222 --> 05:57:46.882
thee all?

05:57:47.602 --> 05:57:54.082
No, no, he has but increased the debt, answered the physician, and as he proceeded his manner

05:57:54.382 --> 05:57:58.402
its fiercer characteristics, and subsided into gloom.

05:57:58.942 --> 05:58:04.382
Dost thou remember me, Hester, as I was nine years agone? Even then I was in the autumn

05:58:04.382 --> 05:58:11.262
of my days, nor was it the early autumn. But all my life had been made up of earnest, studious,

05:58:11.502 --> 05:58:16.962
thoughtful, quiet years, bestowed faithfully for the increase of mine own knowledge, and

05:58:16.962 --> 05:58:22.562
faithfully, too, though this latter object was but casual to the other, faithfully for

05:58:22.562 --> 05:58:28.642
the advancement of human welfare. No life had been more peaceful and innocent than mine,

05:58:28.962 --> 05:58:34.702
few lives so rich with benefits conferred. Dost thou remember me? Was I not, though you

05:58:34.702 --> 05:58:41.362
might deem me cold, nevertheless a man thoughtful for others, craving little for himself, kind,

05:58:41.522 --> 05:58:47.242
true, just, and of constant, if not warm, affections? Was I not all this?

05:58:48.042 --> 05:58:55.022
All this and more, said Hester. And what am I now? demanded he, looking into her face,

05:58:55.482 --> 05:59:00.882
and permitting the whole evil within him to be written on his features. I have already

05:59:00.882 --> 05:59:04.762
told thee what I am, a fiend who made me so.

05:59:05.962 --> 05:59:12.202
It was myself, cried Hester, shuddering. It was I, not less than he. Why hast thou not

05:59:12.202 --> 05:59:13.562
avenge thyself on me?

05:59:14.182 --> 05:59:20.042
I have left thee to the scarlet letter, replied Roger Chillingworth. If that has not avenged

05:59:20.042 --> 05:59:24.502
me, I can do no more. He laid his finger on it with a smile.

05:59:25.302 --> 05:59:32.322
It has avenged thee, answered Hester Prynne. I judged no less, said the physician. And

05:59:32.322 --> 05:59:35.042
now what wouldst thou with me touching this man?

05:59:36.002 --> 05:59:42.462
I must reveal the secret, answered Hester firmly. He must discern thee in thy true character.

05:59:42.922 --> 05:59:48.782
What may be the result, I know not. But this long debt of confidence, due from me to him,

05:59:49.082 --> 05:59:52.882
whose bane and ruin I have been, shall at length be paid.

05:59:53.782 --> 06:00:00.002
So far as concerns the overthrow or preservation of his fair name, and his earthly state, and

06:00:00.002 --> 06:00:06.002
perchance his life, he is in my hands. Nor do I, whom the scarlet letter has disciplined

06:00:06.002 --> 06:00:12.362
to truth, though it be the truth of red-hot iron entering into the soul, nor do I perceive

06:00:12.362 --> 06:00:18.442
such advantage in his living any longer a life of ghastly emptiness, that I shall stoop

06:00:18.442 --> 06:00:24.342
to implore thy mercy. Do with him as thou wilt. There is no good for him, no good for

06:00:24.342 --> 06:00:30.402
me, no good for thee. There is no good for little Pearl. There is no path to guide us

06:00:30.402 --> 06:00:32.062
out of this dismal maze.

06:00:33.222 --> 06:00:38.962
Woman, I could well-nigh pity thee, said Roger Chillingworth, unable to restrain the thrill

06:00:38.962 --> 06:00:44.382
of admiration too, for there was a quality almost majestic in the despair which she

06:00:44.382 --> 06:00:50.822
expressed. Thou hadst great elements. Peradventure, hadst thou met earlier with a better love

06:00:50.822 --> 06:00:56.762
than mine, this evil had not been. I pity thee for the good that has been wasted in

06:00:56.762 --> 06:01:03.242
thy nature. And I thee, answered Hester Prynne, for the hatred that has transformed a wise

06:01:03.242 --> 06:01:09.982
and just man to a fiend. Wilt thou yet purge it out of thee and be once more human? If

06:01:09.982 --> 06:01:15.682
not for his sake, then doubly for thine own. Forgive and leave his further retribution

06:01:15.682 --> 06:01:20.942
to the power that claims it. I said but now that there could be no good event for him

06:01:20.942 --> 06:01:27.322
or thee or me who are here wandering together in this gloomy maze of evil and stumbling

06:01:27.322 --> 06:01:34.062
step over the guilt wherewith we have strewn our path. It is not so. There might be good

06:01:34.062 --> 06:01:39.762
for thee and thee alone, since thou hast been deeply wronged and hast it at thy will

06:01:39.762 --> 06:01:46.002
to pardon. Wilt thou give up that only privilege? Wilt thou reject that priceless benefit?

06:01:47.402 --> 06:01:54.962
Peace has to peace, replied the old man with gloomy sternness. It is not granted me to

06:01:54.962 --> 06:02:01.802
pardon. I have no such power as thou tellest me of. My old faith, long forgotten, comes

06:02:01.802 --> 06:02:09.502
back to me and explains all that we do and all we suffer. By thy first step awry thou

06:02:09.502 --> 06:02:16.842
didst plant the germ of evil. But since that moment it has all been a dark necessity. Ye

06:02:16.842 --> 06:02:23.842
that have wronged me are not sinful save in a kind of typical illusion. Neither am I fiend-like

06:02:23.842 --> 06:02:30.262
who have snatched a fiend's office from his hands. It is our fate. Let the black flower

06:02:30.262 --> 06:02:38.322
blossom as it may. Now go thy ways and deal as thou wilt with yonder man. He waved his

06:02:38.322 --> 06:02:43.202
hand and betook himself again to his employment of gathering herbs.

06:03:14.520 --> 06:03:18.220
The Scarlet Letter by Nathaniel Hawthorne

06:03:18.220 --> 06:03:22.280
Hester and Pearl

06:03:23.520 --> 06:03:31.140
So Roger Chillingworth, a deformed old figure with a face that haunted men's memories longer than they liked,

06:03:31.820 --> 06:03:36.400
took leave of Hester Prynne and went stooping away along the earth.

06:03:36.880 --> 06:03:43.160
He gathered here and there a herb or grubbed up a root and put it into the basket on his arm.

06:03:44.040 --> 06:03:48.080
His grey beard almost touched the ground as he crept onward.

06:03:48.080 --> 06:03:54.200
Hester gazed after him a little while, looking with a half-fantastic curiosity

06:03:54.200 --> 06:04:00.100
to see whether the tender grass of early spring would not be blighted beneath him

06:04:00.100 --> 06:04:07.100
and show the wavering track of his footsteps, seer and brown, across its cheerful verdure.

06:04:07.680 --> 06:04:12.640
She wondered what sort of herbs they were which the old man was so sedulous to gather.

06:04:12.640 --> 06:04:17.760
Would not the earth, quickened to an evil purpose by the sympathy of his eye,

06:04:18.180 --> 06:04:24.920
greet him with poisonous shrubs of species hitherto unknown that would start up under his fingers?

06:04:25.760 --> 06:04:34.160
Or might it suffice him that every wholesome growth should be converted into something deleterious and malignant at his touch?

06:04:34.740 --> 06:04:39.840
Did the sun, which shone so brightly everywhere else, really fall upon him?

06:04:39.840 --> 06:04:49.440
Or was there, as it rather seemed, a circle of ominous shadow moving along with his deformity, whichever way he turned himself?

06:04:50.180 --> 06:04:51.920
And whither was he now going?

06:04:52.520 --> 06:04:57.620
Would he not suddenly sink into the earth, leaving a barren and blasted spot,

06:04:58.060 --> 06:05:03.740
where in due course of time would be seen deadly nightshade, dogwood, henbane,

06:05:03.740 --> 06:05:10.700
and whatever else of vegetable wickedness the climate could produce, all flourishing with hideous luxuriance?

06:05:11.720 --> 06:05:18.480
Or would he spread bat's wings and flee away, looking so much the uglier the higher he rose towards heaven?

06:05:19.940 --> 06:05:26.580
Be it sin or no, said Histoprine bitterly, as she still gazed after him, I hate the man.

06:05:27.480 --> 06:05:32.940
She upbraided herself for the sentiment, but could not overcome or lessen it.

06:05:32.940 --> 06:05:37.920
Attempting to do so, she thought of those long past days in a distant land,

06:05:38.320 --> 06:05:42.400
where he used to emerge at Eventide from the seclusion of his study,

06:05:42.880 --> 06:05:47.800
and sit down in the firelight of their home and in the light of her nuptial smile.

06:05:49.140 --> 06:05:58.560
He needed to bask himself in that smile, he said, in order that the chill of so many lonely hours among his books might be taken off the scholar's heart.

06:05:58.560 --> 06:06:02.440
Such scenes had once appeared not otherwise than happy,

06:06:02.840 --> 06:06:10.580
but now, as viewed through the dismal medium of her subsequent life, they classed themselves among her ugliest remembrances.

06:06:11.140 --> 06:06:13.880
She marvelled how such scenes could have been.

06:06:14.520 --> 06:06:18.300
She marvelled how she could ever have been wrought upon to marry him.

06:06:18.940 --> 06:06:27.760
She deemed it her crime most to be repented of, that she had ever endured and reciprocated the lukewarm grasp of his hand,

06:06:27.760 --> 06:06:32.820
and had suffered the smile of her lips and eyes to mingle and melt into his own.

06:06:34.060 --> 06:06:40.320
And it seemed a fowler offence committed by Roger Chillingworth than any which had since been done him.

06:06:40.600 --> 06:06:47.720
That, in the time when her heart knew no better, he had persuaded her to fancy herself happy by his side.

06:06:47.720 --> 06:06:52.600
Yes, I hate him, repeated Hester, more bitterly than before.

06:06:52.900 --> 06:06:56.700
He betrayed me. He has done me worse wrong than I did him.

06:06:58.480 --> 06:07:04.800
Let men tremble to win the hand of woman, unless they win along with it the utmost passion of her heart.

06:07:05.560 --> 06:07:09.900
Else it may be their miserable fortune, as it was Roger Chillingworth's,

06:07:09.900 --> 06:07:18.260
when some mightier touch than their own may have awakened all her sensibilities to be reproached even for the calm content,

06:07:18.560 --> 06:07:24.320
the marble image of happiness, which they will have imposed upon her as the warm reality.

06:07:25.420 --> 06:07:28.780
But Hester ought long ago to have done with this injustice.

06:07:29.360 --> 06:07:39.100
What did it betoken, had seven long years under the torture of the scarlet letter inflicted so much of misery and wrought out no repentance?

06:07:40.900 --> 06:07:47.260
The emotions of that brief space, while she stood gazing after the crooked figure of old Roger Chillingworth,

06:07:48.220 --> 06:07:55.240
threw a dark light on Hester's state of mind, revealing much that she might not otherwise have acknowledged to herself.

06:07:56.340 --> 06:07:59.100
He being gone, she summoned back her child.

06:07:59.660 --> 06:08:02.380
Pearl, little Pearl, where are you?

06:08:03.220 --> 06:08:11.260
Pearl, whose activity of spirit never flagged, had been at no loss for amusement while her mother talked with the old gatherer of herbs.

06:08:12.120 --> 06:08:20.000
At first, as already told, she had flirted fancifully with her own image in a pool of water, beckoning the phantom forth,

06:08:20.320 --> 06:08:28.740
and, as it declined to venture, seeking a passage for herself into its sphere of impalpable earth and unattainable sky.

06:08:29.440 --> 06:08:36.160
Soon finding, however, that either she or the image was unreal, she turned elsewhere for better pastime.

06:08:36.940 --> 06:08:46.420
She made little boats out of birch bark, and freighted them with snail-shells, and sent out more ventures on the mighty deep than any merchant in New England.

06:08:47.180 --> 06:08:50.200
But the larger part of them foundered near the shore.

06:08:51.080 --> 06:08:59.740
She seized a live horseshoe by the tail, and made prize of several five-fingers, and laid out a jellyfish to melt in the warm sun.

06:09:00.600 --> 06:09:06.780
Then she took up the white foam that streaked the line of the advancing tide, and threw it upon the breeze,

06:09:07.260 --> 06:09:12.700
scampering after it with winged footsteps to catch the great snowflakes ere they fell.

06:09:13.840 --> 06:09:21.240
Perceiving a flock of beech-birds that fed and fluttered along the shore, the naughty child picked up her apron full of pebbles,

06:09:21.720 --> 06:09:28.640
and, creeping from rock to rock after these small sea-fowl, displayed remarkable dexterity in pelting them.

06:09:29.320 --> 06:09:37.540
One little grey bird with a white breast, Pearl was almost sure, had been hit by a pebble, and fluttered away with a broken wing.

06:09:38.240 --> 06:09:49.840
But then the elf child sighed, and gave up her sport, because it grieved her to have done harm to a little being that was as wild as the sea-breeze, or as wild as Pearl herself.

06:09:51.880 --> 06:10:02.240
Her final employment was to gather seaweed of various kinds, and make herself a scarf or mantle, and a head-dress, and thus assume the aspect of a little mermaid.

06:10:02.240 --> 06:10:07.100
She inherited her mother's gift for devising drapery and costume.

06:10:08.000 --> 06:10:19.420
As the last touch to her mermaid's garb, Pearl took some eel-grass, and imitated, as best she could, on her own bosom, the decoration with which she was so familiar on her mother's,

06:10:20.000 --> 06:10:24.960
a letter, the letter A, but freshly green instead of scarlet.

06:10:24.960 --> 06:10:38.700
The child bent her chin upon her breast, and contemplated this device with strange interest, even as if the one only thing for which she had been sent into the world was to make out its hidden import.

06:10:39.560 --> 06:10:43.020
A wonder if mother will ask me what it means, thought Pearl.

06:10:43.840 --> 06:10:55.580
Just then she heard her mother's voice, and flitting along as lightly as one of the little sea-birds, appeared before Hester Prynne, dancing, laughing, and pointing her finger to the ornament upon her bosom.

06:10:56.340 --> 06:10:59.880
My little Pearl, said Hester, after a moment's silence.

06:11:00.380 --> 06:11:09.740
The green letter, and on thy childish bosom, has no purport. But dost thou know, my child, what this letter means, which thy mother is doomed to wear?

06:11:10.860 --> 06:11:16.460
Yes, mother, said the child, it is the great letter A, thou hast taught it me in the horn-book.

06:11:17.600 --> 06:11:31.380
Hester looked steadily into her little face, but though there was that singular expression which she had so often remarked in her black eyes, she could not satisfy herself whether Pearl really attached any meaning to the symbol.

06:11:32.080 --> 06:11:35.100
She felt a morbid desire to ascertain the point.

06:11:35.740 --> 06:11:38.860
Dost thou know, child, wherefore thy mother wears this letter?

06:11:39.440 --> 06:11:44.020
Truly do I, answered Pearl, looking brightly into her mother's face.

06:11:44.020 --> 06:11:48.860
It is for the same reason that the minister keeps his hand over his heart.

06:11:50.040 --> 06:12:00.520
And what reason is that? asked Hester, half smiling at the absurd incongruity of the child's observation, but, on second thoughts, turning pale.

06:12:01.280 --> 06:12:04.000
What has the letter to do with any heart save mine?

06:12:04.820 --> 06:12:10.280
Nay, mother, I have told all I know, said Pearl, more seriously than she was wont to speak.

06:12:10.280 --> 06:12:15.280
Ask yonder old man whom thou hast been talking with, it may be he can tell.

06:12:15.720 --> 06:12:24.880
But in good earnest now, mother dear, what does this scarlet letter mean, and why dost thou wear it on thy bosom, and why dost the minister keep his hand over his heart?

06:12:25.940 --> 06:12:35.060
She took her mother's hand in both her own, and gazed into her eyes with an earnestness that was seldom seen in her wild and capricious character.

06:12:35.060 --> 06:12:49.080
The thought occurred to Hester that the child might really be seeking to approach her with childlike confidence, and doing what she could, and as intelligently as she knew how, to establish a meeting point of sympathy.

06:12:49.080 --> 06:12:52.540
It showed Pearl in an unwanted aspect.

06:12:53.460 --> 06:13:16.520
Heretofore the mother, while loving her child with the intensity of a soul-affection, had schooled herself to hope for little other return than the waywardness of an April breeze, which spends its time in airy sport, and has its gusts of inexplicable passion, and is petulant in its best of moods, and chills oftener than caresses you when you take it to your bosom,

06:13:16.520 --> 06:13:33.980
in requital of which misdemeanours it will sometimes, of its own vague purpose, kiss your cheek with a kind of doubtful tenderness, and play gently with your hair, and then be gone about its other idle business, leaving a dreamy pleasure at your heart.

06:13:33.980 --> 06:13:38.780
And this, moreover, was a mother's estimate of the child's disposition.

06:13:38.780 --> 06:13:46.020
Any other observer might have seen few but unamiable traits, and have given them a far darker colouring.

06:13:46.320 --> 06:14:05.340
But now the idea came strongly into Hester's mind that Pearl, with her remarkable precocity and acuteness, might already have approached the age when she could be made a friend, and entrusted with as much of her mother's sorrows as could be imparted, without irreverence either to the parent or the child.

06:14:05.340 --> 06:14:30.500
In the little chaos of Pearl's character there might be seen emerging, and could have been from the very first, the steadfast principles of an unflinching courage, an uncontrollable will, a sturdy pride which might be disciplined into self-respect, and a bitter scorn of many things which, when examined, might be found to have the taint of falsehood in them.

06:14:30.500 --> 06:14:38.800
She possessed affections too, though hitherto acrid and disagreeable, as are the richest flavours of unripe fruit.

06:14:39.800 --> 06:14:50.680
With all these sterling attributes, thought Hester, the evil which she inherited from her mother must be great indeed, if a noble woman do not grow out of this elfish child.

06:14:51.820 --> 06:15:06.240
Pearl's inevitable tendency to hover about the enigma of the scarlet letter seemed an innate quality of her being. From the earliest epoch of her conscious life she had entered upon this as her appointed mission.

06:15:07.060 --> 06:15:26.900
Hester had often fancied that Providence had a design of justice and retribution in endowing the child with this marked propensity, but never until now had she bethought herself to ask whether, linked with that design, there might not likewise be a purpose of mercy and beneficence.

06:15:26.900 --> 06:15:53.340
If little Pearl were entertained with faith and trust, as a spirit messenger no less than an earthly child, might it not be her errand to soothe away the sorrow that lay cold in her mother's heart and converted it into a tomb, and to help her to overcome the passion once so wild, and even yet neither dead nor asleep, but only imprisoned within the same tomb-like heart?

06:15:54.560 --> 06:16:17.920
Such were some of the thoughts that now stirred in Hester's mind, with as much vivacity of impression as if they had actually been whispered into her ear. And there was little Pearl, all this while, holding her mother's hand in both her own, and turning her face upward while she put these searching questions once and again and still a third time.

06:16:17.920 --> 06:16:25.480
What does the letter mean, mother? And why dost thou wear it? And why dost the minister keep his hand over his heart?

06:16:25.480 --> 06:16:34.760
What shall I say? thought Hester to herself. No, if this be the price of the child's sympathy, I cannot pay it.

06:16:35.460 --> 06:16:36.740
Then she spoke aloud.

06:16:37.340 --> 06:16:52.000
Silly Pearl, said she, what questions are these? There are many things in this world that a child must not ask about. What know I of the minister's heart? And as for the scarlet letter, I wear it for the sake of its gold thread.

06:16:53.220 --> 06:17:18.680
In all the seven bygone years Hester Prynne had never before been false to the symbol on her bosom. It may be that it was the talisman of a stern and severe, but yet a guardian spirit, who now forsook her, as recognising that, in spite of his strict watch over her heart, some new evil had crept into it, or some old one had never been expelled.

06:17:19.540 --> 06:17:44.920
As for little Pearl, the earnestness soon passed out of her face. But the child did not see fit to let the matter drop, two or three times, as her mother and she went homeward, and as often at supper-time, and while Hester was putting her to bed, and once, after she seemed to be fairly asleep, Pearl looked up with mischief gleaming in her black eyes. Mother, said she, what does the scarlet letter mean?

06:17:44.920 --> 06:18:00.920
And the next morning the first indication the child gave of being awake was by popping up her head from the pillow and making that other inquiry which she had so unaccountably connected with her investigations about the scarlet letter.

06:18:00.920 --> 06:18:05.180
Mother, mother, why does the minister keep his hand over his heart?

06:18:05.900 --> 06:18:17.320
Hold thy tongue, naughty child, answered her mother, with an asperity that she had never permitted to herself before. Do not tease me, else I shall shut thee into the dark closet.

06:18:56.349 --> 06:19:01.929
Hester Prynne remained constant in her resolve to make known to Mr. Dimmesdale, at whatever

06:19:01.929 --> 06:19:07.289
risk of present pain or ulterior consequences, the true character of the man who had crept

06:19:07.289 --> 06:19:13.349
into his intimacy. For several days, however, she vainly sought an opportunity of addressing

06:19:13.349 --> 06:19:18.049
him in some of the meditative walks which she knew him to be in the habit of taking

06:19:18.049 --> 06:19:24.029
along the shores of the peninsula or on the wooded hills of the neighboring country. There

06:19:24.029 --> 06:19:29.129
would have been no scandal, indeed, nor peril to the holy whiteness of the clergyman's good

06:19:29.129 --> 06:19:35.029
fame had she visited him in his own study, where many a penitent heir now had confessed

06:19:35.029 --> 06:19:42.149
sins of perhaps as deep a die as the one betokened by the scarlet letter. But partly that she dreaded

06:19:42.149 --> 06:19:47.009
the secret or undisguised interference of old Roger Chillingworth, and partly that her

06:19:47.009 --> 06:19:52.269
conscious heart imparted suspicion where none could have been felt, and partly that both the

06:19:52.269 --> 06:19:56.189
minister and she would need the whole wide world to breathe in while they talked together.

06:19:56.729 --> 06:20:01.349
For all these reasons, Hester never thought of meeting him in any narrower privacy than

06:20:01.349 --> 06:20:07.789
beneath the open sky. At last, while attending a sick chamber, whether the Reverend Mr. Dimmesdale

06:20:07.789 --> 06:20:12.629
had been summoned to make a prayer, she learnt that he had gone, the day before, to visit

06:20:12.629 --> 06:20:19.089
the Apostle Elliot among his Indian converts. He would probably return by a certain hour

06:20:19.089 --> 06:20:25.149
in the afternoon of the morrow. Be times, therefore, the next day Hester took little Pearl,

06:20:25.689 --> 06:20:30.689
who was necessarily the companion of all her mother's expeditions, however inconvenient her

06:20:30.689 --> 06:20:37.989
presence, and set forth. The road, after the two wayfarers had crossed from the peninsula to the

06:20:37.989 --> 06:20:44.249
mainland, was no other than a footpath. It straggled onward into the mystery of the primeval forest.

06:20:44.249 --> 06:20:51.669
This hemmed it in so narrowly, and stood so black and dense on either side, and disclosed such

06:20:51.669 --> 06:20:57.729
imperfect glimpses of the sky above, that, to Hester's mind, it imaged not amiss the moral

06:20:57.729 --> 06:21:05.629
wilderness in which she had so long been wandering. The day was chill and somber. Overhead was a gray

06:21:05.629 --> 06:21:11.669
expanse of cloud, slightly stirred, however, by a breeze, so that a gleam of flickering sunshine

06:21:11.669 --> 06:21:18.209
might now and then be seen at its solitary play along the path. This flitting cheerfulness was

06:21:18.209 --> 06:21:24.509
always at the further extremity of some long vista through the forest. The sportive sunlight,

06:21:25.269 --> 06:21:31.569
feebly sportive at best in the predominant pensiveness of the day and scene, withdrew itself as they came

06:21:31.569 --> 06:21:36.629
nigh, and left the spots where it had danced the drearier, because they had hoped to find them

06:22:06.629 --> 06:22:13.089
Why not, mother? asked Pearl, stopping short, just at the beginning of her race. Will it not

06:22:13.089 --> 06:22:19.949
come of its own accord when I am a woman grown? Run away, child, answered her mother, and catch

06:22:19.949 --> 06:22:27.689
the sunshine. It will soon be gone. Pearl set forth at a great pace, and as Hester smiled to

06:22:27.689 --> 06:22:33.789
perceive, did actually catch the sunshine, and stood laughing in the midst of it, all brightened

06:22:33.789 --> 06:22:40.709
by its splendor, and scintillating with a vivacity excited by rapid motion. The light lingered about

06:22:40.709 --> 06:22:46.649
the lonely child, as if glad of such a playmate, until her mother had drawn almost nigh enough to

06:22:46.649 --> 06:22:55.509
step into the magic circle too. It will go now, said Pearl, shaking her head. See, answered Hester,

06:22:55.749 --> 06:23:02.649
smiling, now I can stretch out my hand, and grasp some of it. As she attempted to do so,

06:23:02.649 --> 06:23:07.709
the sunshine vanished. Or, to judge from the bright expression that was dancing on Pearl's

06:23:07.709 --> 06:23:13.129
features, her mother could have fancied that the child had absorbed it into herself, and would give

06:23:13.129 --> 06:23:18.789
it forth again, with a gleam about her path, as they should plunge into some gloomier shade.

06:23:19.849 --> 06:23:25.269
There was no other attribute that so much impressed her with a sense of new and untransmitted vigor in

06:23:25.269 --> 06:23:31.589
Pearl's nature as this never failing vivacity of spirits. She had not the disease of sadness,

06:23:31.589 --> 06:23:37.309
which almost all children in these latter days inherit, with the scruffula from the troubles of

06:23:37.309 --> 06:23:44.969
their ancestors. Perhaps this too was a disease, and but the reflex of the wild energy with which

06:23:44.969 --> 06:23:50.889
Hester had fought against her sorrows before Pearl's birth. It was certainly a doubtful charm,

06:23:51.369 --> 06:23:57.369
imparting a hard metallic luster to the child's character. She wanted what some people want

06:23:57.369 --> 06:24:02.829
throughout life, a grief that should deeply touch her, and thus humanize and make her capable of

06:24:02.829 --> 06:24:09.909
sympathy. But there was time enough yet for little Pearl. Come, my child, said Hester,

06:24:10.089 --> 06:24:15.089
looking about her from the spot where Pearl had stood still in the sunshine. We will sit down a

06:24:15.089 --> 06:24:21.829
little way within the wood, and rest ourselves. I am not a weary mother, replied the little girl,

06:24:21.829 --> 06:24:25.249
but you may sit down if you will tell me a story meanwhile.

06:24:26.989 --> 06:24:35.129
A story, child, said Hester, and about what? Oh, a story about the black man, answered Pearl,

06:24:35.489 --> 06:24:41.809
taking hold of her mother's gown and looking up half earnestly, half mischievously into her face.

06:24:43.049 --> 06:24:48.849
How he haunts this forest and carries a book with him, a big heavy book with iron clasps,

06:24:48.849 --> 06:24:54.569
and how this ugly black man offers his book and an iron pen to everybody that meets him here among

06:24:54.569 --> 06:25:00.049
the trees, and they are to write their names with their own blood, and then he sets his mark on

06:25:00.049 --> 06:25:07.749
their bosoms. Dost thou ever meet the black man, mother? And who told you this story, Pearl? asked

06:25:07.749 --> 06:25:14.389
her mother, recognizing a common superstition of the period. It was the old dame in the chimney

06:25:14.389 --> 06:25:20.329
corner at the house where you watched last night, said the child, but she fancied me asleep while

06:25:20.329 --> 06:25:26.089
she was talking of it. She said that a thousand and a thousand people had met him here, and had

06:25:26.089 --> 06:25:32.009
written in his book, and have his mark on them, and that ugly tempered lady, old Mistress Hibbons,

06:25:32.049 --> 06:25:37.749
was one. And, mother, the old dame said that this scarlet letter was the black man's mark on thee,

06:25:38.029 --> 06:25:42.669
and that it glows like a red flame when thou meetest him at midnight here in the dark wood.

06:25:43.209 --> 06:25:47.209
Is it true, mother, and dost thou go to meet him in the night time?

06:25:48.809 --> 06:25:52.269
Didst thou ever awake and find thy mother gone? asked Hester.

06:25:53.949 --> 06:25:58.769
Not that I remember, said the child. If thou fearest to leave me in our cottage,

06:25:59.089 --> 06:26:04.809
thou mightest take me along with thee. I would very gladly go. But, mother, tell me now,

06:26:05.229 --> 06:26:09.929
is there such a black man, and didst thou ever meet him, and is this his mark?

06:26:11.309 --> 06:26:15.909
Will thou let me be at peace, if I once tell thee? asked her mother.

06:26:17.289 --> 06:26:24.769
Yes, if thou tellest me all, answered Pearl. Once in my life I met the black man, said her mother.

06:26:25.429 --> 06:26:32.209
This scarlet letter is his mark. Thus conversing, they entered sufficiently deep into the wood to

06:26:32.209 --> 06:26:36.829
secure themselves from the observation of any casual passenger along the forest track.

06:26:37.749 --> 06:26:43.769
Here they sat down on a luxuriant heap of moss, which at some epoch of the preceding century had

06:26:43.769 --> 06:26:49.569
been a gigantic pine, with its roots and trunk in a darksome shade, and its head aloft in the upper

06:26:49.569 --> 06:26:56.069
atmosphere. It was a little dell where they had seated themselves, with a leaf-strewn bank rising

06:26:56.069 --> 06:27:02.049
gently on either side, and a brook flowing through the midst over a bed of fallen and drowned leaves.

06:27:02.769 --> 06:27:07.249
The trees impending over it had flung down great branches from time to time,

06:27:07.469 --> 06:27:12.489
which choked up the current, and compelled it to form eddies and black depths at some points,

06:27:13.089 --> 06:27:18.869
while in its swifter and livelier passages there appeared a channelway of pebbles and brown

06:27:18.869 --> 06:27:24.989
sparkling sand. Letting the eyes follow along the course of the stream, they could catch the

06:27:24.989 --> 06:27:30.609
reflected light from its water at some short distance within the forest, but soon lost all

06:27:30.609 --> 06:27:36.089
traces of it amid the bewilderment of tree trunks and underbrush, and here and there a huge rock

06:27:36.089 --> 06:27:42.369
covered over with gray lichens. All these giant trees and boulders of granite seemed intent on

06:27:42.369 --> 06:27:48.149
making a mystery of the course of this small brook, fearing perhaps that, with its never-ceasing

06:27:48.149 --> 06:27:53.549
loquacity, it should whisper tales out of the heart of the old forest whence it flowed, or

06:27:53.549 --> 06:27:59.789
mirror its revelations on the smooth surface of a pool. Continually, indeed, as it stole

06:27:59.789 --> 06:28:07.189
onward, the streamlet kept up a babble, kind, quiet, soothing, but melancholy, like the voice

06:28:07.189 --> 06:28:12.589
of a young child that was spending its infancy without playfulness, and knew not how to be merry

06:28:12.589 --> 06:28:20.409
among sad acquaintance and events of somber hue. Oh brook, oh foolish and tiresome little brook,

06:28:20.569 --> 06:28:26.789
cried Pearl after listening a while to its talk. Why art thou so sad? Pluck up the spirit,

06:28:26.789 --> 06:28:32.889
and do not be all the time sighing and murmuring. But the brook, in the course of its little

06:28:32.889 --> 06:28:38.209
lifetime among the forest trees, had gone through so solemn an experience that it could not help

06:28:38.209 --> 06:28:45.149
talking about it, and seemed to have nothing else to say. Pearl resembled the brook in as much as

06:28:45.149 --> 06:28:50.529
the current of her life gushed from a wellspring as mysterious, and had flowed through scenes

06:28:50.529 --> 06:28:56.709
shadowed as heavily with gloom. But unlike the little stream, she danced and sparkled,

06:28:56.929 --> 06:29:04.209
and prattled airily along her course. What does this sad little brook say, mother? inquired she.

06:29:06.169 --> 06:29:10.729
If thou hadst a sorrow of thine own, the brook might tell thee of it, answered her mother,

06:29:11.229 --> 06:29:17.129
even as it is telling me of mine. But now, Pearl, I hear a footstep along the path,

06:29:17.129 --> 06:29:22.569
and the noise of one putting aside the branches. I would have thee betake thyself to play,

06:29:22.929 --> 06:29:29.029
and leave me to speak with him that comes yonder. Is it the black man? asked Pearl.

06:29:30.829 --> 06:29:36.449
Wilt thou go and play, child? repeated her mother. But do not stray far into the wood,

06:29:37.189 --> 06:29:44.989
and take heed that thou come in my first call. Yes, mother, answered Pearl. But if it be the black

06:29:44.989 --> 06:29:49.869
man, wilt thou not let me stay a moment and look at him with his big book under his arm?

06:29:51.189 --> 06:29:58.209
Go, silly child, said her mother impatiently. It is no black man. Thou canst see him now through

06:29:58.209 --> 06:30:06.909
the trees. It is the minister. And so it is, said the child. And, mother, he has his hand over his

06:30:06.909 --> 06:30:12.909
heart. Is it because, when the minister wrote his name in the book, the black man set his mark in

06:30:12.909 --> 06:30:20.469
place? But why does he not wear it outside his bosom, as thou dost, mother? Go now, child,

06:30:20.789 --> 06:30:26.569
and thou shalt tease me as thou wilt another time, cried Hester Prynne. But do not stray far.

06:30:27.169 --> 06:30:33.989
Keep where thou canst hear the babble of the brook. The child went singing away, following up the

06:30:33.989 --> 06:30:39.049
current of the brook, and striving to mingle a more alightsome cadence with its melancholy voice.

06:30:39.929 --> 06:30:45.309
But the little stream would not be comforted, and still kept telling its unintelligible secret

06:30:45.309 --> 06:30:51.229
of some very mournful mystery that had happened, or making a prophetic lamentation about something

06:30:51.229 --> 06:30:58.289
that was yet to happen within the verge of the dismal forest. So Pearl, who had enough of shadow

06:30:58.289 --> 06:31:02.949
in her own little life, chose to break off all acquaintance with this repining brook.

06:31:03.589 --> 06:31:10.009
She set herself, therefore, to gathering violets and wood anemones and some scarlet columbines that

06:31:10.009 --> 06:31:16.969
she found growing in the crevice of a high rock. When her elf child had departed, Hester Prynne made

06:31:16.969 --> 06:31:21.989
a step or two towards the track that led through the forest, but still remained under the deep shadow

06:31:21.989 --> 06:31:29.289
of the trees. She beheld the minister advancing along the path entirely alone, and leaning on a

06:31:29.289 --> 06:31:35.689
which he had cut by the wayside. He looked haggard and feeble, and betrayed a nerveless

06:31:35.689 --> 06:31:41.049
despondency in his air, which had never so remarkably characterized him in his walks about

06:31:41.049 --> 06:31:46.109
the settlement, nor in any other situation where he deemed himself liable to notice.

06:31:47.269 --> 06:31:53.189
Here it was woefully visible in this intense seclusion of the forest, which of itself would

06:31:53.189 --> 06:31:59.169
have been a heavy trial to the spirits. There was a listlessness in his gait, as if he saw

06:31:59.169 --> 06:32:05.649
no reason for taking one step further, nor felt any desire to do so, but would have been glad,

06:32:05.869 --> 06:32:10.409
could he be glad of anything, to fling himself down at the root of the nearest tree

06:32:10.409 --> 06:32:17.349
and lie there passive for evermore. The leaves might bestrew him, and the soil gradually accumulate

06:32:17.349 --> 06:32:22.389
and form a little hillock over his frame, no matter whether there were life in it or no.

06:32:23.189 --> 06:32:29.229
Death was too definite an object to be wished for or avoided. To Hester's eye,

06:32:29.389 --> 06:32:35.309
the Reverend Mr. Dimmesdale exhibited no symptom of positive and vivacious suffering, except that,

06:32:35.369 --> 06:32:42.469
as Little Pearl had remarked, he kept his hand over his heart.

06:32:47.909 --> 06:32:53.189
The Scarlet Letter by Nathaniel Hawthorne.

06:33:15.109 --> 06:33:20.509
The Pastor and His Parishioner.

06:33:20.729 --> 06:33:29.109
Slowly as a minister walked, he had almost gone by before Hester Prynne could gather voice enough to attract his observation.

06:33:30.169 --> 06:33:32.049
At length she succeeded.

06:33:33.109 --> 06:33:40.429
Arthur Dimmesdale, she said, faintly at first, then louder but hoarsely.

06:33:40.849 --> 06:33:42.249
Arthur Dimmesdale.

06:33:43.529 --> 06:33:45.649
Who speaks? answered the minister.

06:33:46.509 --> 06:33:56.769
Gathering himself quickly up, he stood more erect, like a man taken by surprise in a mood to which he was reluctant to have witnesses.

06:33:57.689 --> 06:34:19.329
Throwing his eyes anxiously in the direction of the voice, he indistinctly beheld a form under the trees, clad in garments so somber and so little relieved from the gray twilight into which the clouded sky and heavy foliage had darkened the noontide that he knew not whether it were a woman or a shadow.

06:34:19.329 --> 06:34:28.689
It may be that his pathway through life was haunted thus by a specter that had stolen out from among his thoughts.

06:34:29.449 --> 06:34:33.409
He made a step nigher and discovered the scarlet letter.

06:34:34.529 --> 06:34:37.589
Hester, Hester Prynne, said he.

06:34:37.589 --> 06:34:40.589
Is it thou, art thou in life?

06:34:41.349 --> 06:34:46.949
Even so, she answered, in such life as has been mine these seven years past.

06:34:47.709 --> 06:34:50.609
And thou, Arthur Dimmesdale, dost thou yet live?

06:34:51.509 --> 06:34:59.009
It was no wonder that they thus questioned one another's actual and bodily existence and even doubted of their own.

06:34:59.009 --> 06:35:28.069
So strangely did they meet in the dim wood, that it was likely the first encounter in the world beyond the grave of two spirits who had been intimately connected in their former life, but now stood coldly, shuddering in mutual dread, as not yet familiar with their state, nor wanted to the companionship of disembodied beings, each a ghost and awestricken at the other ghost.

06:35:28.069 --> 06:35:44.809
They were awestricken likewise at themselves, because the crisis flung back to them their consciousness and revealed to each heart its history and experience, as life never does, except at such breathless epics.

06:35:45.529 --> 06:35:49.869
The soul beheld its features in the mirror of the passing moment.

06:35:49.869 --> 06:36:06.869
It was with fear and tremulously, and as it were by a slow reluctant necessity, that Arthur Dimmesdale put forth his hand, chill as death, and touched the chill hand of Hester Prynne.

06:36:08.569 --> 06:36:14.649
The grasp, cold as it was, took away what was dreariest in the interview.

06:36:14.649 --> 06:36:21.009
They now felt themselves, at least, inhabitants of the same sphere.

06:36:21.589 --> 06:36:39.249
Without a word more spoken, neither he nor she, assuming the guidance, but with an unexpressed consent, they glided back into the shadow of the wood when Hester had emerged, and sat down on the heap of moss where she and Pearl had been sitting.

06:36:39.889 --> 06:36:55.549
When they found voice to speak, it was at first only to utter remarks and inquiries, such as any two acquaintances might have made, about the gloomy sky, the threatening storm, and next, the health of each.

06:36:55.549 --> 06:37:05.769
Thus they went onward, not boldly, but step by step, into the themes that were brooding deepest in their hearts.

06:37:05.769 --> 06:37:25.769
So long estranged by fate and circumstances, they needed something slight and casual to run before and throw open the doors of intercourse, so that their real thoughts might be led across the threshold, and after a while the minister fixed his eyes on Hester Prynne.

06:37:27.109 --> 06:37:34.649
Hester, said he, hast thou found peace? She smiled drearily, looking down upon her bosom.

06:37:35.169 --> 06:37:40.629
Hast thou, she asked? None, nothing but despair, he answered.

06:37:41.169 --> 06:37:46.429
What else could I look for, being what I am, and leading such a life as mine?

06:37:46.889 --> 06:37:54.489
Were I an atheist, a man devoid of conscience, a wretch, with coarse and brutal instincts?

06:37:54.489 --> 06:38:00.389
I might have found peace long ere now, nay, I never should have lost it.

06:38:00.669 --> 06:38:14.289
But as matters stand with my soul, whatever of good capacity there originally was in me, all of God's gifts, that were the choicest, have become the ministers of spiritual torment.

06:38:15.649 --> 06:38:18.009
Hester, I am most miserable.

06:38:19.009 --> 06:38:27.769
The people reverence thee, said Hester, and surely thou workest good among them. Does this bring thee no comfort?

06:38:29.009 --> 06:38:35.069
More misery, Hester, only the more misery, answered the clergyman with a bitter smile.

06:38:35.589 --> 06:38:43.369
As concerns the good which I may appear to do, I have no faith in it. It must needs be a delusion.

06:38:43.369 --> 06:38:53.429
What can a ruined soul, like mine, affect towards the redemption of other souls, or a polluted soul, towards their purification?

06:38:54.989 --> 06:39:00.369
And as for the people's reverence, would that it would turn to scorn and hatred.

06:39:00.369 --> 06:39:14.029
Canst thou deem it, Hester, a consolation that I must stand up in my pulpit, and meet so many eyes turned upward to my face, as if the light of heaven were beaming from it?

06:39:14.029 --> 06:39:29.529
Must see my flock hungry for the truth, and listening to my words, as if a tongue of Pentecost were speaking, and then look inward and discern the black reality of what they idolize?

06:39:30.429 --> 06:39:41.669
I have laughed in bitterness and agony of heart, at the contrast between what I seem and what I am, and Satan laughs at it.

06:39:41.669 --> 06:39:53.089
You wrong yourself in this, said Hester gently. You have deeply and sorely repented. Your sin is left behind you in days long past.

06:39:53.889 --> 06:39:59.749
Your present life is not less holy and very truth than it seems in people's eyes.

06:40:00.249 --> 06:40:08.169
Is there no reality in the penitence thus sealed and witnessed by good works? And wherefore should it not bring you peace?

06:40:08.169 --> 06:40:22.129
No, Hester, no, replied the clergyman. There is no substance in it. It is cold and dead and can do nothing for me. Of penance I have had enough.

06:40:22.129 --> 06:40:36.429
Of penitence there has been none, else I should long ago have thrown off these garments of mock holiness, and have shown myself to mankind as they will see me at the judgment seat.

06:40:36.429 --> 06:40:56.569
Happy are you, Hester, that where the scarlet letter openly upon your bosom, mine, burns in secret. Thou little knowest what a relief it is, after the torment of a seven year's cheat, to look into an eye that recognizes me for what I am.

06:40:56.569 --> 06:41:15.529
Had I one friend, or were it my worst enemy, to whom when sickened with the praises of all other men, I could daily betake myself, and known as the vilest of all sinners, methinks my soul might keep itself alive thereby.

06:41:16.509 --> 06:41:30.849
Even thus much of truth would save me, but now it is all falsehood, all emptiness, all death. Hester Prynne looked into his face, but hesitated to speak.

06:41:30.849 --> 06:41:49.089
Yet, uttering his long restrained emotions so vehemently as he did, his words here offered her the very point of circumstances in which to interpose what she came to say. She conquered her fears and spoke.

06:41:49.089 --> 06:42:03.149
Such a friend as thou hast even now wished for, said she, with whom to weep over thy sin, thou hast in me the partner of it.

06:42:03.149 --> 06:42:17.369
Again she hesitated, but brought out the words with an effort. Thou hast long had such an enemy, and dwellest with him under the same roof.

06:42:18.189 --> 06:42:25.689
The minister started to his feet, gasping for breath, and clutching at his heart as if he would have torn it out of his bosom.

06:42:26.609 --> 06:42:34.109
What sayest thou, cried he, an enemy, and under mine own roof? What mean you?

06:42:35.389 --> 06:42:54.309
Hester Prynne was now fully sensible of the deep injury for which she was responsible to this unhappy man, and permitting him to lie for so many years, or indeed for a single moment, at the mercy of one whose purposes could not be other than malevolent.

06:42:54.309 --> 06:43:08.789
The very contiguity of his enemy, beneath whatever mask the latter might conceal himself, was enough to disturb the magnetic sphere of a being so sensitive as Arthur Dimmesdale.

06:43:09.729 --> 06:43:25.029
There had been a period when Hester was less alive to this consideration, or perhaps, in the misanthropy of her own trouble, she left the minister to bear what she might picture to herself as a more tolerable doom.

06:43:25.029 --> 06:43:35.889
But of late, since the night of his vigil, all her sympathies towards him had been softened and invigorated.

06:43:35.889 --> 06:44:03.069
She now read his heart more accurately. She doubted not that the continual presence of Roger Chillingworth, the secret poison of his malignity infecting all their air about him, and his authorized interference as a physician with the minister's physical and spiritual infirmities, that these bad opportunities had been turned to a cruel purpose.

06:44:03.069 --> 06:44:19.849
By means of them, the sufferer's conscience had been kept in an irritated state, the tendency of which was not to cure by wholesome pain, but to disorganize and corrupt his spiritual being.

06:44:19.849 --> 06:44:33.369
Again, its result on earth could hardly fail to be insanity, and hereafter that eternal alienation from the good and true of which madness is perhaps the earthly type.

06:44:34.289 --> 06:44:45.709
Such was the ruin to which she had brought the man once. Hey, why should we not speak of it? Still so passionately loved.

06:44:45.709 --> 06:45:02.349
Hester felt that the sacrifice of the clergyman's good name and death itself, as she had already told Roger Chillingworth, would have been infinitely preferable to the alternative which she had taken upon herself to choose.

06:45:02.349 --> 06:45:15.289
And now, rather than have had this grievous wrong to confess, she would gladly have laid down on the forest leaves and died there at Arthur Dimmesdale's feet.

06:45:15.289 --> 06:45:37.249
Oh, Arthur cried she. Forgive me, in all things else I have striven to be true. Truth was the one virtue which I might have held fast, and did hold fast through all extremity, save when thy good, thy life, thy fame were put in question.

06:45:37.249 --> 06:45:59.529
Then I consented to a deception. But a lie is never good, even though death threatened on the other side. Dost thou not see what I would say? That old man, the physician, he whom they call Roger Chillingworth, he was my husband.

06:46:00.789 --> 06:46:21.389
The minister looked at her for an instant. With all that violence of passion which intermixed in more shapes than one with his higher, purer, softer qualities, was in fact the portion of him which the devil claimed, and through which she sought to win the rest.

06:46:21.389 --> 06:46:44.089
Never was there a blacker or fiercer frown than Hester now encountered. For the brief space that it lasted, it was a dark transfiguration. But his character had been so much enfeebled by suffering that even its lower energies were incapable of much more than a temporary struggle.

06:46:44.089 --> 06:46:48.489
He sank down on the ground and buried his face in his hands.

06:46:48.489 --> 06:47:07.749
I might have known it, murmured he. I didn't know it was not the secret told me in the natural recoil of my heart at the first sight of him. And as often as I have seen him since, why did I not understand?

06:47:07.749 --> 06:47:28.269
Oh, Hester Prynne, thou little, little knowest all the horror of this thing, and the shame, the indelicacy, the horrible ugliness of this exposure of a sick and guilty heart to the very eye that would gloat over it.

06:47:28.269 --> 06:47:46.529
Woman, woman, thou art accountable for this. I cannot forgive thee. Thou shalt forgive me, cried Hester, flinging herself on the fallen leaves beside him. Let God punish. Thou shalt forgive.

06:47:47.349 --> 06:48:04.569
With sudden and desperate tenderness, she threw her arms around him and pressed his head against her bosom, little caring, though his cheek rested on the scarlet letter. He would have released himself, but strove in vain to do so.

06:48:05.749 --> 06:48:26.409
Hester would not set him free, lest he should look her sternly in the face. All the world had frowned on her for seven long years had it frowned upon this lonely woman, and still she bore it all, nor ever once turned away her firm, sad eyes.

06:48:26.409 --> 06:48:42.449
Heaven, likewise, had frowned upon her, and she had not died. But the frown of this pale, weak, sinful and sorrow-stricken man was what Hester could not bear and live.

06:48:42.449 --> 06:48:51.509
Wilt thou yet forgive me, she repeated over and over again? Wilt thou not frown? Wilt thou forgive?

06:48:51.509 --> 06:49:08.569
I do forgive you, Hester, replied the minister at length, with a deep utterance out of an abyss of sadness but no anger. I freely forgive you now. May God forgive us both.

06:49:08.569 --> 06:49:27.409
We are not, Hester, the worst sinners in the world. There is one worse than even the polluted priest. That old man's revenge has been blacker than my sin. He has violated in cold blood the sanctity of a human heart.

06:49:27.409 --> 06:49:46.889
Thou and I, Hester, never did so. Never, never, whispered she. What we did had a consecration of its own. We felt it so. We said so to each other. Hast thou forgotten it?

06:49:48.009 --> 06:49:57.429
Hush, Hester, said Arthur Dimmesdale, rising from the ground. No, I have not forgotten.

06:49:58.989 --> 06:50:19.469
They sat down again side by side and hand clasped in hand on the mossy trunk of a fallen tree. Life had never brought them a gloomier hour. It was a point whither their pathway had so long been tending and darkening ever as it stole along.

06:50:19.469 --> 06:50:33.529
And yet it enclosed a charm that made them linger upon it and claim another and another, and after all, another moment.

06:50:33.529 --> 06:50:58.269
The forest was obscure around them and creaked with a blast that was passing through it. The boughs were tossing heavily above their heads while one solemn old tree groaned dolefully to another as if telling the sad story of the pair that sat beneath or constrained to forebode evil to come.

06:50:59.049 --> 06:51:15.969
And yet they lingered. How dreary looked the forest track that led backward to the settlement where Hester Prynne must take up again the burden of her ignominy and the minister the hollow mockery of his good name.

06:51:15.969 --> 06:51:35.029
So they lingered an instant longer. No golden light had ever been so precious as the gloom of this dark forest. Here, seen only by his eyes, the scarlet letter need not burn into the bosom of the fallen woman.

06:51:36.389 --> 06:51:51.129
Here, seen only by her eyes, Arthur Dimmesdale, false to God and man, might be, for one moment, true. He started at a thought that suddenly occurred to him.

06:51:51.129 --> 06:52:06.189
Hester, cried he, here's a new horror. Roger Chillingworth knows your purpose to reveal his true character. Will he continue then to keep our secret? What will now be the course of his revenge?

06:52:07.969 --> 06:52:28.029
There is a strange secrecy in his nature, replied Hester thoughtfully, and it has grown upon him by the hidden practices of his revenge. A demon not likely that he will betray the secret. He will doubtless seek other means of satiating his dark passion.

06:52:28.029 --> 06:52:44.829
And I, how am I to live longer breathing the same air with this deadly enemy? exclaimed Arthur Dimmesdale, shrinking within himself and pressing his hand nervously against his heart, a gesture that had grown involuntary with him.

06:52:44.829 --> 06:52:59.569
Think for me, Hester. Thou art strong. Resolve for me. Thou must dwell no longer with this man, said Hester slowly and firmly. Thy heart must be no longer under his eye.

06:52:59.569 --> 06:53:20.529
It were far worse than death, replied the minister. But how to avoid it? What choice remains to me? Shall I lie down again on these withered leaves where I cast myself when thou didst tell me what he was? Must I sink down there and die at once?

06:53:22.109 --> 06:53:35.229
Alas, what a ruin has befallen thee, said Hester, with the tears gushing into her eyes. Wilt thou die for very weakness? There is no other cause.

06:53:35.229 --> 06:53:58.109
The judgment of God is on me, answered the conscient stricken priest. It is too mighty for me to struggle with. Heaven would show mercy, rejoined Hester. Hest thou but the strength to take advantage of it? Be thou strong for me, answered he. Advise me what to do.

06:53:58.109 --> 06:54:17.189
Is the world, then, so narrow, exclaimed Hester Prynne, fixing her deep eyes on the minister's and instinctively exercising a magnetic power over a spirit so shattered and subdued that it could hardly hold itself erect?

06:54:18.809 --> 06:54:34.689
Doth the universe lie within the compass of yonder town, which only a little time ago was but a leaf-strewn desert, as lonely as this around us, wither leads yonder forest track?

06:54:34.689 --> 06:54:55.849
Backward to the settlement, thou sayest yes, but onward, too, deeper it goes, and deeper into the wilderness, less plainly to be seen at every step, until some few miles hence the yellow leaves will show no vestige of the white man's tread.

06:54:55.849 --> 06:55:08.509
There thou art free. So brief a journey would bring thee from a world where thou hast been most wretched to one where thou mayest still be happy.

06:55:08.509 --> 06:55:17.549
Is there not shade enough in all this boundless forest to hide thy heart from the gaze of Roger Chillingworth?

06:55:18.469 --> 06:55:24.929
Yes, Hester, but only under the fallen leaves, replied the minister with a sad smile.

06:55:26.549 --> 06:55:36.869
Then there is the broad pathway of the sea, continued Hester. It brought thee hither. If thou so choose, it will bear thee back again.

06:55:37.629 --> 06:55:52.309
In our native land, whether in some remote, rural village, or in vast London, or surely in Germany, in France, in pleasant Italy, thou wouldst be beyond his power and knowledge.

06:55:52.309 --> 06:56:01.729
And what hast thou to do with all these iron men and their opinions? They have kept thy better part in bondage too long already.

06:56:02.569 --> 06:56:08.869
It cannot be, answered the minister, listening as if he were called upon to realize a dream.

06:56:09.529 --> 06:56:21.369
I am powerless to go, wretched and sinful as I am. I have no other thought than to drag on my earthly existence in the sphere where Providence hath placed me.

06:56:21.649 --> 06:56:27.169
Lost as my own soul is, I would still do what I may for other human souls.

06:56:27.169 --> 06:56:38.649
I dare not quit my post, though an unfaithful sentinel, who sure reward his death and dishonor, when his dreary watch shall come to an end.

06:56:39.069 --> 06:56:49.989
Thou art crushed under the seven years' weight of mystery, replied Hester Prynne, fervently resolved to buoy him up with her own energy.

06:56:49.989 --> 06:56:59.449
But thou shalt leave it all behind thee. It shall not cumber thy steps as thou treadest along the forest path.

06:56:59.989 --> 06:57:04.669
Neither shalt thou freight the ship with it, if thou prefer to cross the sea.

06:57:05.629 --> 06:57:13.649
Leave this wreck and ruin here where it hath happened. Metal no more with it. Begin all anew.

06:57:13.649 --> 06:57:24.309
Hast thou exhausted possibility in the failure of this one trial? Not so. The future is yet full of trial and success.

06:57:25.469 --> 06:57:30.129
There is happiness to be enjoyed. There is good to be done.

06:57:30.729 --> 06:57:41.169
Exchange this false life of thine for a true one. Be, if thy spirit summoned thee to such a mission, the teacher and apostle of the red men.

06:57:42.089 --> 06:57:51.049
Or, as is more by thy nature, be a scholar and a sage among the wisest and the most renowned of the cultivated world.

06:57:51.049 --> 06:57:59.109
Preach, write, act to anything save to lie down and die.

06:57:59.829 --> 06:58:08.609
Give up this name of Arthur Dimmesdale and make thyself another, a high one, such as thou canst wear without fear or shame.

06:58:09.389 --> 06:58:24.189
Why shouldst thou tarry so much as one other day in the torments that have so gnawed into thy life, that have made thee feeble to will and to do, that will leave thee powerless even to repent?

06:58:24.189 --> 06:58:38.029
Up and away! Oh, Hester! cried Arthur Dimmesdale, in whose eyes a fitful light kindled by her enthusiasm flashed up and died away.

06:58:39.269 --> 06:58:47.249
Thou tellest of running a race to a man whose knees are tottering beneath him. I must die here.

06:58:47.249 --> 06:58:53.969
There is not the strength or courage left to me to venture into the wide, strange, difficult world alone.

06:58:55.689 --> 06:59:07.469
It was the last expression of the despondency of a broken spirit. He lacked energy to grasp the better fortune that seemed within his reach.

06:59:07.469 --> 06:59:23.349
He repeated the word, Alone, Hester, thou shalt not go alone, answered she in a deep whisper. Then all was spoken.

06:59:52.414 --> 06:59:53.554
A FLOOD OF SUNSHINE

06:59:55.314 --> 07:00:01.294
Arthur Dimmesdale gazed into Hester's face with a look in which hope and joy shone out,

07:00:01.414 --> 07:00:07.074
indeed, but with fear betwixt them, and a kind of horror at her boldness, who had spoken

07:00:07.074 --> 07:00:10.134
what he vaguely hinted at, but dared not speak.

07:00:11.054 --> 07:00:17.134
But Hester Prynne, with a mind of native courage and activity, and for so long a period not

07:00:17.134 --> 07:00:23.094
merely estranged, but outlawed from society, had habituated herself to such latitude of

07:00:23.094 --> 07:00:26.614
speculation as was altogether foreign to the clergyman.

07:00:27.114 --> 07:00:33.954
She had wandered, without rule or guidance, in a moral wilderness, as vast, as intricate,

07:00:34.354 --> 07:00:39.634
and shadowy as the untamed forest, amid the gloom of which they were now holding a colicky

07:00:39.634 --> 07:00:41.394
that was to decide their fate.

07:00:42.054 --> 07:00:47.754
Her intellect and heart had their home, as it were, in desert places, where she roamed

07:00:47.754 --> 07:00:50.154
as freely as the wild Indian in his woods.

07:00:50.754 --> 07:00:57.114
For years past she had looked from this estranged point of view at human institutions, and whatever

07:00:57.114 --> 07:01:03.354
priests or legislators had established, criticizing all with hardly more reverence than the Indian

07:01:03.354 --> 07:01:10.574
would feel for the clerical band, the judicial robe, the pillory, the gallows, the fireside,

07:01:10.574 --> 07:01:11.554
or the church.

07:01:12.234 --> 07:01:15.514
The tendency of her fate and fortunes had set her free.

07:01:16.214 --> 07:01:20.974
The scarlet letter was her passport into regions where other women dared not tread.

07:01:21.594 --> 07:01:28.134
Shame, despair, solitude, these had been her teachers, stern and wild ones, and they had

07:01:28.134 --> 07:01:30.934
made her strong, but taught her much amiss.

07:01:32.134 --> 07:01:37.634
The minister, on the other hand, had never gone through an experience calculated to lead

07:01:37.634 --> 07:01:43.914
him beyond the scope of generally received laws, although, in a single instance, he had

07:01:43.914 --> 07:01:47.094
so fearfully transgressed one of the most sacred of them.

07:01:47.594 --> 07:01:52.034
But this had been a sin of passion, not of principle, nor even purpose.

07:01:52.474 --> 07:01:58.174
Since that wretched epoch, he had watched with morbid zeal and minuteness, not his acts,

07:01:58.414 --> 07:02:03.614
for those it was easy to arrange, but each breath of emotion and his every thought.

07:02:04.274 --> 07:02:10.414
At the head of the social system, as the clergyman of that day stood, he was only the more trammeled

07:02:10.414 --> 07:02:14.754
by its regulations, its principles, and even its prejudices.

07:02:15.354 --> 07:02:19.494
As a priest, the framework of his order inevitably hemmed him in.

07:02:19.814 --> 07:02:25.474
As a man who had once sinned, but who kept his conscience all alive and painfully sensitive

07:02:25.474 --> 07:02:30.874
by the fretting of an unhealed wound, he might have been supposed safer within the line of

07:02:30.874 --> 07:02:33.414
virtue than if he had never sinned at all.

07:02:34.834 --> 07:02:41.134
Thus we seem to see that, as regarded Hester Prynne, the whole seven years of outlaw and

07:02:41.134 --> 07:02:45.174
ignominy had been little other than a preparation for this very hour.

07:02:45.614 --> 07:02:51.314
But Arthur Dimmesdale, were such a man once more to fall, what plea could be urged in

07:02:51.314 --> 07:02:52.794
extenuation of his crime?

07:02:53.434 --> 07:02:58.954
None, unless it avail him somewhat that he was broken down by long and exquisite suffering,

07:02:59.234 --> 07:03:04.654
that his mind was darkened and confused by the very remorse which harrowed it, that,

07:03:04.874 --> 07:03:09.994
between fleeing as an avowed criminal and remaining as a hypocrite, conscience might

07:03:09.994 --> 07:03:15.334
find it hard to strike the balance, that it was human to avoid the peril of death and

07:03:15.334 --> 07:03:22.294
infamy and the inscrutable machinations of an enemy, that, finally, to this poor pilgrim

07:03:22.294 --> 07:03:29.414
on his dreary and desert path, faint, sick, miserable, there appeared a glimpse of human

07:03:29.414 --> 07:03:34.794
affection and sympathy, a new life and a true one, in exchange for the heavy doom which

07:03:34.794 --> 07:03:36.314
he was now expiating.

07:03:36.834 --> 07:03:41.774
And be the stern and sad truth spoken, that the breach which guilt has once made into

07:03:41.774 --> 07:03:45.194
the human soul is never, in this mortal state, repaired.

07:03:45.834 --> 07:03:50.554
It may be watched and guarded, so that the enemy shall not force his way again into the

07:03:50.554 --> 07:03:56.014
Citadel, and might even, in his subsequent assaults, select some other avenue in preference

07:03:56.014 --> 07:03:57.934
to that where he had formerly succeeded.

07:03:58.474 --> 07:04:03.894
But there is still the ruined wall, and near it the stealthy tread of the foe that would

07:04:03.894 --> 07:04:06.514
win over again his unforgotten triumph.

07:04:07.634 --> 07:04:11.314
The struggle, if there were one, need not be described.

07:04:11.754 --> 07:04:16.194
Let it suffice that the clergyman resolved to flee, and not alone.

07:04:17.654 --> 07:04:23.294
If in all these past seven years, thought he, I could recall one instant of peace or

07:04:23.294 --> 07:04:27.734
hope, I would yet endure, for the sake of that earnest of Heaven's mercy.

07:04:28.074 --> 07:04:34.594
But now, since I am irrevocably doomed, wherefore should I not snatch the solace allowed to

07:04:34.594 --> 07:04:36.874
the condemned culprit before his execution?

07:04:37.434 --> 07:04:43.414
Or, if this be the path to a better life, as Hester would persuade me, I surely give

07:04:43.414 --> 07:04:45.954
no fairer prospect by pursuing it.

07:04:46.434 --> 07:04:51.694
Neither can I any longer live without her companionship, so powerful is she to sustain,

07:04:51.914 --> 07:04:53.374
so tender to soothe.

07:04:53.914 --> 07:04:58.614
O, thou to whom I dare not lift mine eyes, wilt thou yet pardon me?

07:04:59.894 --> 07:05:04.174
Thou wilt go, said Hester calmly, as he met her glance.

07:05:05.534 --> 07:05:10.514
The decision once made, a glow of strange enjoyment through its flickering brightness

07:05:10.514 --> 07:05:12.194
over the trouble of his breast.

07:05:12.194 --> 07:05:17.874
It was the exhilarating effect, upon a prisoner just escaped from the dungeon of his own heart,

07:05:18.274 --> 07:05:24.514
of breathing the wild, free atmosphere of an unredeemed, unchristianized, lawless religion.

07:05:25.054 --> 07:05:30.014
His spirit rose, as it were, with a bound, and attained a nearer prospect of the sky

07:05:30.014 --> 07:05:33.894
than throughout all the misery which had kept him groveling on the earth.

07:05:34.494 --> 07:05:39.834
Of a deeply religious temperament, there was inevitably a tinge of the devotional in his

07:05:39.834 --> 07:05:40.174
mood.

07:05:41.254 --> 07:05:45.894
Do I feel joy again? cried he, wondering at himself.

07:05:46.554 --> 07:05:48.514
Methought the germ of it was dead in me.

07:05:48.834 --> 07:05:51.334
O, Hester, thou art my better angel.

07:05:51.774 --> 07:05:57.774
I seem to have flung myself, sick, sin-stained, and sorrow-blackened, down upon these forest

07:05:57.774 --> 07:06:02.954
leaves, and who have risen up all made anew, and with new powers to glorify him that hath

07:06:02.954 --> 07:06:03.654
been merciful.

07:06:04.194 --> 07:06:06.214
This is already the better life.

07:06:06.474 --> 07:06:08.034
Why did we not find it sooner?

07:06:08.594 --> 07:06:11.994
Let us not look back, answered Hester Brynne.

07:06:12.074 --> 07:06:13.334
The past is gone.

07:06:13.594 --> 07:06:15.574
Wherefore should we linger upon it now?

07:06:16.014 --> 07:06:21.134
See, with this symbol I undo it all, and make it as if it had never been.

07:06:22.274 --> 07:06:28.754
So speaking, she undid the clasp that fastened the scarlet letter, and, taking it from her

07:06:28.754 --> 07:06:32.194
bosom, threw it to a distance among the withered leaves.

07:06:32.694 --> 07:06:35.974
The mystic token alighted on the hither verge of the stream.

07:06:36.324 --> 07:06:40.754
With a hand's breadth further flight it would have fallen into the water, and have given

07:06:40.754 --> 07:06:46.254
the little brook another woe to carry onward, besides the unintelligible tale which it still

07:06:46.254 --> 07:06:47.474
kept murmuring about.

07:06:48.014 --> 07:06:53.854
But there lay the embroidered letter, glittering like a lost jewel, which some ill-fated wanderer

07:06:53.854 --> 07:06:59.434
might pick up, and thenceforth be haunted by strange phantoms of guilt, sinkings of

07:06:59.434 --> 07:07:02.014
the heart, and unaccountable misfortune.

07:07:03.154 --> 07:07:09.774
The stigma gone, Hester heaved a long, deep sigh, in which the burden of shame and anguish

07:07:09.774 --> 07:07:11.054
departed from her spirit.

07:07:11.774 --> 07:07:13.194
O exquisite relief!

07:07:13.434 --> 07:07:16.154
She had not known the weight until she felt the freedom.

07:07:16.774 --> 07:07:22.174
By another impulse she took off the formal cap that confined her hair, and down it fell

07:07:22.174 --> 07:07:27.754
upon her shoulders, dark and rich, with at once a shadow and a light in its abundance,

07:07:28.214 --> 07:07:30.874
and imparting the charm of softness to her features.

07:07:30.874 --> 07:07:36.574
There played around her mouth, and beamed out of her eyes, a radiant and tender smile,

07:07:36.874 --> 07:07:39.594
that seemed gushing from the very heart of womanhood.

07:07:40.094 --> 07:07:44.214
A crimson flash was glowing on her cheek that had been long so pale.

07:07:44.574 --> 07:07:50.254
Her sex, her youth, and the whole richness of her beauty came back from what men call

07:07:50.254 --> 07:07:56.054
the irrevocable past, and clustered themselves with her maiden hope, and a happiness before

07:07:56.054 --> 07:07:59.014
unknown within the magic circle of this hour.

07:07:59.654 --> 07:08:05.114
And, as if the gloom of the earth and sky had been but the effluence of these two mortal

07:08:05.114 --> 07:08:07.534
hearts, it vanished with their sorrow.

07:08:07.954 --> 07:08:14.414
All at once, as with a sudden smile of heaven, forth burst the sunshine, pouring a very flood

07:08:14.414 --> 07:08:20.134
into the obscure forest, gladdening each green leaf, transmuting the yellow fallen ones to

07:08:20.134 --> 07:08:23.974
gold, and gleaming adown the gray trunks of the solemn trees.

07:08:24.364 --> 07:08:28.814
The objects that had made a shadow hitherto embodied the brightness now.

07:08:29.234 --> 07:08:34.214
The course of the little brook might be traced by its merry gleam afar into the wood's heart

07:08:34.214 --> 07:08:37.314
of mystery, which had become a mystery of joy.

07:08:38.394 --> 07:08:44.834
Such was the sympathy of nature, that wild, heathen nature of the forest, never subjugated

07:08:44.834 --> 07:08:50.054
by human law, nor illumined by higher truth, with the bliss of these two spirits.

07:08:50.054 --> 07:08:56.774
Love, whether newly born or aroused from a death-like slumber, must always create a sunshine,

07:08:57.074 --> 07:09:01.274
filling the heart so full of radiance that it overflows upon the outward world.

07:09:01.754 --> 07:09:06.874
Had the forest still kept its gloom, it would have been bright in Hester's eyes, and bright

07:09:06.874 --> 07:09:08.514
in Arthur Dimmesdale's.

07:09:09.074 --> 07:09:12.154
Hester looked at him with a thrill of another joy.

07:09:13.114 --> 07:09:16.454
"'Thou must know Pearl,' said she, "'our little Pearl.

07:09:16.674 --> 07:09:17.694
Thou hast seen her.

07:09:17.694 --> 07:09:21.254
Yes, I know it, but thou wilt see her now with other eyes.

07:09:21.494 --> 07:09:22.934
She is a strange child.

07:09:23.134 --> 07:09:24.574
I hardly comprehend her.

07:09:24.734 --> 07:09:28.614
But thou wilt love her dearly as I do, and wilt advise me how to deal with her.'

07:09:30.034 --> 07:09:35.514
"'Tost thou think the child will be glad to know me?' asked the minister, somewhat uneasily.

07:09:35.814 --> 07:09:40.754
I have long shrunk from children, because they often show a distrust, a backwardness,

07:09:40.754 --> 07:09:42.114
to be familiar with me.

07:09:42.174 --> 07:09:44.094
I have even been afraid of little Pearl.'

07:09:45.174 --> 07:09:50.614
"'Ah, that was sad,' answered the mother, "'but she will love thee dearly, and thou

07:09:50.614 --> 07:09:50.974
her.

07:09:51.174 --> 07:09:52.314
She is not far off.

07:09:52.434 --> 07:09:56.054
I will call her Pearl, Pearl.'

07:09:56.794 --> 07:10:02.614
"'I see the child,' observed the minister, yonder she is, standing in a streak of sunshine

07:10:02.614 --> 07:10:05.334
a good way off, on the other side of the brook.

07:10:05.554 --> 07:10:09.274
So thou thinkest the child will love me?'

07:10:09.274 --> 07:10:14.714
Hester smiled, and again called to Pearl, who was visible at some distance, as the minister

07:10:14.714 --> 07:10:20.214
had described her, like a bright appareled vision in a sunbeam which fell down upon her

07:10:20.214 --> 07:10:21.654
through an arch of boughs.

07:10:22.234 --> 07:10:28.654
The ray quivered to and fro, making her figure dim or distinct, now like a real child, now

07:10:28.654 --> 07:10:32.614
like a child's spirit, as the splendour went and came again.

07:10:33.054 --> 07:10:36.634
She heard her mother's voice, and approached slowly through the forest.

07:10:37.714 --> 07:10:43.274
Pearl had not found the hour pass wearisomely while her mother sat talking with the clergyman.

07:10:43.714 --> 07:10:48.334
The great black forest, stern as it showed itself to those who brought the guilt and

07:10:48.334 --> 07:10:53.514
troubles of the world into its bosom, became the playmate of the lonely infant, as well

07:10:53.514 --> 07:10:54.354
as it knew how.

07:10:54.894 --> 07:10:59.154
Somber as it was, it put on the kindest of its moods to welcome her.

07:10:59.474 --> 07:11:04.474
It offered her the partridge-berries, the growth of the preceding autumn, but ripening only

07:11:04.474 --> 07:11:08.674
in the spring, and now red as drops of blood upon the withered leaves.

07:11:09.294 --> 07:11:12.714
These Pearl gathered, and was pleased with their wild flavour.

07:11:13.354 --> 07:11:17.374
The small denizens of the wilderness hardly took pains to move out of her path.

07:11:17.934 --> 07:11:23.774
A partridge, indeed, with a brood of tin behind her, ran forward threateningly, but soon repented

07:11:23.774 --> 07:11:27.234
of her fierceness, and clucked to her young ones not to be afraid.

07:11:27.914 --> 07:11:33.874
A pigeon, alone on a low branch, allowed Pearl to come beneath, and uttered a sound as much

07:11:33.874 --> 07:11:35.294
of greeting as alarm.

07:11:35.834 --> 07:11:41.434
A squirrel, from the lofty depths of his domestic tree, chattered either in anger or merriment,

07:11:41.654 --> 07:11:46.634
for the squirrel is such a choleric and humorous little personage that it is hard to distinguish

07:11:46.634 --> 07:11:47.974
between his moods.

07:11:47.974 --> 07:11:51.534
So he chattered at the child, and flung down a nut upon her head.

07:11:51.974 --> 07:11:55.414
It was a last year's nut, and already gnawed by his sharp tooth.

07:11:55.974 --> 07:12:01.034
A fox, startled from his sleep by her light footstep on the leaves, looked inquisitively

07:12:01.034 --> 07:12:06.554
at Pearl, as doubting whether it were better to steal off, or renew his nap on the same

07:12:06.554 --> 07:12:06.934
spot.

07:12:07.434 --> 07:12:13.054
A wolf, it is said, but here the tale has surely lapsed into the improbable, came up

07:12:13.054 --> 07:12:17.654
and smelt of Pearl's robe, and offered his savage head to be patted by her hand.

07:12:18.094 --> 07:12:23.574
The truth seems to be, however, that the mother forest, and these wild things which it nourished,

07:12:23.894 --> 07:12:27.314
all recognized a kindred wilderness in the human child.

07:12:28.514 --> 07:12:33.474
And she was gentler here than in the grassy margined streets of the settlement, or in

07:12:33.474 --> 07:12:34.394
her mother's cottage.

07:12:35.034 --> 07:12:39.434
The bowers appeared to know it, and one and another whispered as she passed,

07:12:40.094 --> 07:12:44.254
Adorn thyself with me, thou beautiful child, adorn thyself with me.

07:12:44.814 --> 07:12:51.034
And to please them, Pearl gathered the violets, and anemones, and columbines, and some twigs

07:12:51.034 --> 07:12:54.894
of the freshest green which the old trees held down before her eyes.

07:12:55.414 --> 07:13:00.754
With these she decorated her hair and her young waist, and became a nymph-child, or

07:13:00.754 --> 07:13:06.054
an infant-dryad, or whatever else was in closest sympathy with the antique wood.

07:13:06.674 --> 07:13:12.074
In such guise had Pearl adorned herself when she heard her mother's voice, and came slowly

07:13:12.074 --> 07:13:12.674
back.

07:13:13.254 --> 07:13:16.314
Slowly, for she saw the clergyman.

07:13:24.894 --> 07:13:27.194
March 19th, 2007.

07:13:53.308 --> 07:13:57.348
XIX Thou wilt, lover dearly, repeated as to Brynn,

07:13:57.488 --> 07:14:00.188
As she and the minister sat watching little Pearl.

07:14:00.188 --> 07:14:06.008
Dost thou not think her beautiful, and see with what natural skill she has made those simple

07:14:06.008 --> 07:14:11.048
flowers adorn her? Had she gathered pearls and diamonds and rubies in the wood,

07:14:11.368 --> 07:14:18.088
they could not have become her better. She is a splendid child, but I know whose brow she has.

07:14:18.328 --> 07:14:25.048
Dost thou know, Esther, said Arthur Dimmesdale with an unquiet smile, that this, dear child,

07:14:25.048 --> 07:14:32.388
tripping about always at thy side, hath caused me many an alarm? Methought, O Esther, what a

07:14:32.388 --> 07:14:38.368
thought is that, and how terrible to dread it, that my own features were partly repeated in her

07:14:38.368 --> 07:14:44.288
face, and so strikingly that the world might see them. But she is mostly thine.

07:14:44.548 --> 07:14:51.408
No, no, not mostly, answered the mother with a tender smile. A little longer, and thou needest

07:14:51.408 --> 07:14:58.108
not be afraid to trace whose child she is. But how strangely beautiful she looks with those wild

07:14:58.108 --> 07:15:05.368
flowers in her hair. It is as if one of the fairies whom we left in dear old England had decked her

07:15:05.368 --> 07:15:10.908
out to meet us. It was with a feeling which neither of them had ever before experienced,

07:15:11.128 --> 07:15:16.948
that they sat and watched Pearl's slow advance. In her was visible the tie that united them.

07:15:16.948 --> 07:15:22.788
She had been offered to the world these seven past years as the living hieroglyphic in which

07:15:22.788 --> 07:15:30.048
was revealed the secret they so darkly sought to hide, all written in this symbol, all plainly

07:15:30.048 --> 07:15:36.388
manifest. Had there been a prophet or magician skilled to read the character of flame, and Pearl

07:15:36.388 --> 07:15:42.488
was the oneness of their being, be the foregone evil what it might, how could they doubt that

07:15:42.488 --> 07:15:49.248
their earthly lives and future destinies were conjoined when they beheld at once the material

07:15:49.248 --> 07:15:55.848
union and the spiritual idea in whom they met, and what did well immortally together, thoughts

07:15:55.848 --> 07:16:02.128
like these and perhaps other thoughts which they did not acknowledge or define, threw an awe about

07:16:02.128 --> 07:16:08.668
the child as she came onward. Let us see nothing strange, no passion or eagerness in thy way of

07:16:08.668 --> 07:16:15.288
casting her, whispered Esther. Although it's a fitful and fantastic little elf sometimes,

07:16:15.888 --> 07:16:21.928
especially she is generally intolerant of emotion when she does not fully comprehend the why and

07:16:21.928 --> 07:16:29.368
wherefore, but the child hath strong affections. She loves me and will love thee. Thou canst not

07:16:29.368 --> 07:16:35.328
think, said the minister, glancing aside at Hester Prynne. How my heart dreads this interview and

07:16:35.328 --> 07:16:41.848
yearns for it, but in truth, as I already told thee, children are not readily won to be familiar

07:16:41.848 --> 07:16:49.968
with me. They will not climb my knee, nor prattle in my ear, nor answer to my smile, but stand apart

07:16:49.968 --> 07:16:57.028
and eye me strangely. Even little babes, when I take them in my arms, weep bitterly. Yet Pearl,

07:16:57.228 --> 07:17:03.888
twice in her little lifetime, hath been kind to me. The first time thou knowest it well, the last

07:17:03.888 --> 07:17:09.888
was when thou let'st her with thee to the house of yonder stern old governor, and thou didst

07:17:09.888 --> 07:17:16.188
plead so bravely in her behalf and mine, answered the mother. I remember it, and so shall little Pearl

07:17:16.188 --> 07:17:21.868
fear nothing. She may be strange and shy at first, but will soon learn to love thee.

07:17:22.168 --> 07:17:28.188
By this time Pearl had reached the margin of the brook and stood on the further side, gazing silently

07:17:28.188 --> 07:17:34.228
at Hester and the clergyman, who still sat together on the mossy tree trunk waiting to receive her.

07:17:34.488 --> 07:17:40.808
Just where she had paused, the brook danced to form a pool, so smooth and quiet that it reflected

07:17:40.808 --> 07:17:46.188
a perfect image of her little figure, with all the brilliant picturesqueness of her beauty.

07:17:46.388 --> 07:17:52.288
In its adornment of flowers and wreathed foliage, but more refined in spiritual eyes than the

07:17:52.948 --> 07:17:59.768
This image, so nearly identical with the living Pearl, seemed to communicate somewhat of its own

07:17:59.768 --> 07:18:06.728
shadowy and intangible quality to the child herself. It was strange, the way in which Pearl stood,

07:18:07.148 --> 07:18:13.628
looking so steadfastly at them through the dim medium of the forest gloom. Herself, meanwhile,

07:18:14.108 --> 07:18:19.568
all glorified with a ray of sunshine that was attracted through the wood as by a certain

07:18:19.568 --> 07:18:26.308
sympathy. In the brook beneath stood another child, another and the same, but likewise its ray of

07:18:26.308 --> 07:18:33.488
golden light. Hester felt herself in some indistinct and tantalizing manner, estranged from Pearl,

07:18:33.848 --> 07:18:39.628
as if the child in her lonely ramble through the forest had strayed out of the sphere in which she

07:18:39.628 --> 07:18:46.168
and her mother dwelt together and was now vainly seeking to return to it. There was both truth and

07:18:46.168 --> 07:18:52.808
in the impression the child and mother were estranged, but through Hester's fault, not Pearl's.

07:18:53.548 --> 07:18:58.788
Since the latter rambled from her side, another inmate had been admitted within the circle of

07:18:58.788 --> 07:19:05.648
the mother's feelings and so modified the aspect of them all that Pearl, the returning wanderer,

07:19:05.808 --> 07:19:09.548
could not find her wanted place and hardly knew where she was.

07:19:09.548 --> 07:19:15.668
I have a strange fancy, observed the sensitive minister, that this brook is the boundary between

07:19:15.668 --> 07:19:23.328
two worlds and that thou canst never meet thy Pearl again. Or is she an elfish spirit who,

07:19:23.408 --> 07:19:29.148
as the legends of our childhood taught us, is forbidden to cross a running stream? Pray hasten

07:19:29.148 --> 07:19:35.008
her, for this delay has already imparted a tremor to my nerves. Come, dearest child,

07:19:35.008 --> 07:19:42.508
said Hester encouragingly, and stretching out both her arms. How slow thou art! When hast thou been

07:19:42.508 --> 07:19:49.568
so sluggish before now? Here is a friend of mine who must be thy friend also. Thou wilt have twice

07:19:49.568 --> 07:19:55.868
as much love henceforward as thy mother alone could give thee. Leap across the brook and come to us.

07:19:56.208 --> 07:20:02.508
Thou canst leap like a young deer. Pearl, without responding in any manner to these honey-sweet

07:20:02.508 --> 07:20:08.788
expressions, remained on the other side of the brook. Now she fixed her bright, wild eyes on her

07:20:08.788 --> 07:20:15.488
mother, now on the minister, and now included them both in the same glance, as if to detect and

07:20:15.488 --> 07:20:21.508
explain to herself the relation which they bore to one another. For some unaccountable reason,

07:20:21.548 --> 07:20:28.848
as Arthur Dimmesdale felt the child's eyes upon himself, his hand, with that gesture so habitual

07:20:28.848 --> 07:20:37.308
as to have become involuntary, stole over his heart. At length, assuming a singular air of

07:20:37.308 --> 07:20:44.028
authority, Pearl stretched out her hand with the small forefinger extended, and pointing evidently

07:20:44.028 --> 07:20:49.508
towards her mother's breast. And beneath, in the mirror of the brook, there was a flower girdled

07:20:49.508 --> 07:20:57.328
and sunny image of little Pearl pointing her small forefinger to. Thou strange child, why dost thou

07:20:57.328 --> 07:21:03.948
not come to me? exclaimed Esther. Pearl still pointed with her forefinger, and a frown gathered

07:21:03.948 --> 07:21:10.348
on her brow, the more impressive from the childish, the almost baby-like aspect of the features that

07:21:10.348 --> 07:21:16.308
conveyed it. As her mother still kept beckoning to her and arraying face in a holiday suit of

07:21:16.308 --> 07:21:22.148
unaccustomed smiles, the child stamped her foot with a yet more imperious look and gesture.

07:21:22.148 --> 07:21:27.308
In the brook again was the fantastic beauty of the image, with its reflected frown,

07:21:27.568 --> 07:21:34.148
its pointed finger, and imperious gesture, giving emphasis to the aspect of little Pearl.

07:21:34.488 --> 07:21:39.668
Hasten, Pearl, or I shall be angry with thee, cried Esther Brin, who, however,

07:21:40.408 --> 07:21:46.348
inured to such behavior on the elf child's part at other seasons, was naturally anxious for a

07:21:46.348 --> 07:21:53.548
deportment now. Leap across the brook, naughty child, and run hither, else I must come to thee.

07:21:54.308 --> 07:22:00.628
But Pearl, not a whit startled at her mother's threats any more than mollified by her entreaties,

07:22:00.888 --> 07:22:06.108
now suddenly burst into a fit of passion, gesticulating violently and throwing her small

07:22:06.108 --> 07:22:12.428
figure into the most extravagant contortions. She accompanied this wild outbreak with piercing

07:22:12.428 --> 07:22:18.888
shrieks, which the woods reverberated on all sides, so that alone as she was in her childish

07:22:18.888 --> 07:22:24.948
and unreasonable wrath, it seemed as if a hidden multitude were lending her their sympathy and

07:22:24.948 --> 07:22:30.368
encouragement. Seen in the brook once more was the shadowy wrath of Pearl's image,

07:22:30.368 --> 07:22:36.028
crowned and girdled with flowers, but stamping its foot, wildly gesticulating,

07:22:36.028 --> 07:22:41.548
and in the midst of all still pointing its small forefinger at Esther's bosom.

07:22:42.148 --> 07:22:48.688
I see what else the child whispered Esther into the clergyman, and turning pale in spite of a strong

07:22:48.688 --> 07:22:54.528
effort to conceal her trouble and annoyance. Children will not abide any, the slightest

07:22:54.528 --> 07:22:59.608
change in the accustomed aspect of things that are dearly before their eyes.

07:23:00.348 --> 07:23:03.308
Pearl misses something that she has always seen me wear.

07:23:03.308 --> 07:23:09.708
I pray you, answer the minister, if thou hast any means of pacifying the child.

07:23:10.428 --> 07:23:16.648
Do it forthwith, save it were the cankered wrath of an old witch like Mistress Ibbons,

07:23:16.808 --> 07:23:23.368
addity, attempting to smile. I know nothing that I would not sooner encounter than this passion

07:23:23.368 --> 07:23:29.988
in a child. In Pearl's young beauty, as in the wrinkled witch, it has a preternatural effect.

07:23:29.988 --> 07:23:37.408
Pacify her, if thou lovest me. Esther turned again towards Pearl with a crimson blush upon

07:23:37.408 --> 07:23:45.188
her cheek, a conscious glance, a sigh, clergyman, and then a heavy sigh, while even before she had

07:23:45.188 --> 07:23:53.068
time to speak the blush yielded to a deadly pallor. Pearl, said she sadly, looked down at thy feet

07:23:53.068 --> 07:23:59.128
there before thee on the hither side of the brook. The child turned her eyes to the point indicated

07:23:59.128 --> 07:24:05.988
in their lay, the scarlet letter, so close upon the margin of the stream that the gold embroidery

07:24:05.988 --> 07:24:12.788
was reflected in it. Bring it hither, said Esther. Come thou and take it up, answered Pearl.

07:24:13.348 --> 07:24:19.448
Was ever such a child, observed Esther's sigh to the minister. Oh, I have much to tell thee about

07:24:19.448 --> 07:24:26.588
her. But in very truth, she is right as regards this hateful token. I must bear its torture yet

07:24:27.348 --> 07:24:33.988
only a few days longer until we shall have left this region and looked back hither as to a land

07:24:33.988 --> 07:24:40.188
which we have dreamed of. The forest cannot hide it. The mid-ocean shall take it from my hand and

07:24:40.188 --> 07:24:46.568
swallow it up forever with these words. She advanced to the margin of the brook, took up the

07:24:46.568 --> 07:24:54.368
scarlet letter, and fastened it again into her bosom. Hopefully but a moment ago, as Esther had

07:24:54.368 --> 07:25:01.248
spoken of drowning it in the deep sea, there was a sense of inevitable doom upon her as she thus

07:25:01.248 --> 07:25:07.488
received back this deadly symbol from the hand of fate. She had flung it into infinite space.

07:25:07.868 --> 07:25:14.628
She had drawn an hour's free breath, and here again was the scarlet misery glittering on the old

07:25:14.628 --> 07:25:22.448
spot. So it ever is, whether thus typified or no, that an evil deed invests itself with the character

07:25:22.448 --> 07:25:28.988
of doom. Hester next gathered up the heavy tresses of her hair and confined them beneath her cap,

07:25:29.388 --> 07:25:35.108
as if there were a withering spell in the sad letter. Her beauty, the warmth and richness of

07:25:35.108 --> 07:25:41.828
her womanhood, departed like fading sunshine, and a gray shadow seemed to fall across her.

07:25:42.008 --> 07:25:46.228
When the dreary change was wrought, she extended her hand to Pearl.

07:25:46.228 --> 07:25:53.188
Does thou know thy mother now, child, as she reproachfully, but with a subdued tone?

07:25:53.608 --> 07:25:58.908
Wilt thou come across the brook and own thy mother, now that she has her shame upon her,

07:25:59.228 --> 07:26:05.888
now that she is sad? Yes, now I will, answered the child, bounding across the brook

07:26:05.888 --> 07:26:12.008
and clasping Hester in her arms. Now thou art my mother indeed, and I am thy little Pearl,

07:26:12.008 --> 07:26:18.128
in a mood of tenderness that was not usual with her. She drew down her mother's head and kissed

07:26:18.128 --> 07:26:25.248
her brow and both her cheeks. But then, by a kind of necessity that always impelled this child to

07:26:25.248 --> 07:26:31.108
alloy whatever comfort she might chance to give with a throb of anguish, Pearl put up her mouth

07:26:31.108 --> 07:26:41.988
and kissed the scarlet letter too. That was not kind, said Hester. When thou hast shown me a

07:26:41.988 --> 07:26:48.048
wonder, asked Pearl. He waits to welcome thee, replied her mother. Come thou and entreat his

07:26:48.048 --> 07:26:54.988
blessing. He loves thee, my little Pearl, and loves thy mother too. Wilt thou not love him?

07:26:55.408 --> 07:27:01.548
Come, he longs to greet thee. Doth he love us, said Pearl, looking up with acute intelligence

07:27:01.548 --> 07:27:07.148
into her mother's face. Will he go back with us, hand in hand, we three together into the town?

07:27:07.868 --> 07:27:13.648
Not now, my child, answered Hester. But in days to come he will walk hand in hand with us.

07:27:13.968 --> 07:27:19.688
We will have a home and fireside of our own, and thou shalt sit upon his knee, and he will

07:27:19.688 --> 07:27:27.288
teach thee many things, and love thee dearly. Thou wilt love him, wilt thou not? And will he

07:27:27.288 --> 07:27:33.448
always keep his hand over his heart, inquired Pearl? Foolish child, what a question is that,

07:27:33.448 --> 07:27:40.508
exclaimed our mother. Come, and ask his blessing. But whether influenced by the jealousy that seems

07:27:40.508 --> 07:27:46.928
instinctive with every petted child towards a dangerous rival, or from whatever caprice of

07:27:46.928 --> 07:27:53.648
her freakish nature, Pearl would show no favour to the clergyman. It was only by an exertion of

07:27:53.648 --> 07:27:58.908
force that our mother brought her up to him, hanging back and manifesting her reluctance by

07:27:58.908 --> 07:28:05.608
grimaces, of which, ever since her babyhood, she had possessed a singular variety, and could

07:28:05.608 --> 07:28:11.868
transform her mobile physiognomy into a series of different aspects, with a new mischief in them

07:28:11.868 --> 07:28:19.108
each and all. The minister, painfully embarrassed but hoping that a kiss might prove a talisman

07:28:19.108 --> 07:28:25.508
to admit him into the child's kindly regards, bent forward and impressed one on her brow.

07:28:26.748 --> 07:28:32.028
Hereupon, Pearl broke away from her mother, and running to the brook, stooped over it and

07:28:32.028 --> 07:28:38.468
bathed her forehead, until the unwelcome kiss was quite washed off and diffused through a long lapse

07:28:38.468 --> 07:28:44.528
of the gliding water. She then remained apart, silently watching Esther and the clergyman,

07:28:44.688 --> 07:28:48.828
while they talked together and made such arrangements as were suggested by their new

07:28:48.828 --> 07:28:55.228
position, and the purposes soon to be fulfilled, and now this fateful interview had come to a close.

07:28:55.508 --> 07:29:02.668
The dell was to be left in solitude among its dark old trees, which with their multitudinous tongues

07:29:02.668 --> 07:29:09.168
would whisper long of what had passed there, and no mortal be the wiser, and the melancholy brook

07:29:09.168 --> 07:29:14.788
would add this other dell to the mystery with which its little heart was already overburdened,

07:29:15.668 --> 07:29:22.408
and whereof it still kept up a murmuring babble, with not a whit more cheerfulness of tone than

07:29:22.408 --> 07:29:24.008
age is heretofore.

07:30:14.644 --> 07:30:15.204
XX.

07:30:18.904 --> 07:30:20.304
The Minister in a Maze.

07:30:21.044 --> 07:30:25.324
As the minister departed, in advance of Hester Prynne and Little Pearl, he threw a backward

07:30:25.324 --> 07:30:30.584
glance, half expecting that he should discover only some faintly traced features or outline

07:30:30.584 --> 07:30:34.364
of the mother and the child, slowly fading into the twilight of the woods.

07:30:34.884 --> 07:30:38.784
So great of a sictitude of his life could not at once be received as real.

07:30:39.204 --> 07:30:44.384
But there was Hester, clad in her grey robe, still standing beside the tree trunk, which

07:30:44.384 --> 07:30:49.344
some blast had overthrown a long antiquity ago, and which time had ever since been covering

07:30:49.344 --> 07:30:54.564
with moss, so that these two fated ones, with earth's heaviest burden on them, might there

07:30:54.564 --> 07:30:58.124
sit down together and find a single hour's rest and solace.

07:30:58.124 --> 07:31:03.044
And there was Pearl too, lightly dancing from the margin of the brook, now that the intrusive

07:31:03.044 --> 07:31:06.484
third person was gone and taking her old place by her mother's side.

07:31:06.904 --> 07:31:09.544
So the minister had not fallen asleep and dreamed.

07:31:10.944 --> 07:31:15.624
In order to free his mind from this indistinctness and duplicity of impression which vexed it

07:31:15.624 --> 07:31:20.184
with a strange disquietude, he recalled and more thoroughly defined the plans which Hester

07:31:20.184 --> 07:31:22.224
and himself had sketched for their departure.

07:31:22.744 --> 07:31:27.604
It had been determined between them that the old world, with its crowds and cities, offered

07:31:27.604 --> 07:31:32.364
them a more eligible shelter and concealment than the wilds of New England or all America,

07:31:32.624 --> 07:31:37.044
with its alternatives of an Indian wigwam where the few settlements of Europeans scattered

07:31:37.044 --> 07:31:38.364
thinly along the seaboard.

07:31:38.764 --> 07:31:43.084
Not to speak of the clergyman's health, so inadequate to sustain the hardships of a forest

07:31:43.084 --> 07:31:48.464
life, his native gifts, his culture, and his entire development would secure him a home

07:31:48.464 --> 07:31:51.224
only in the midst of civilization and refinement.

07:31:52.004 --> 07:31:55.404
The higher the state, the more delicately adapted to it the man.

07:31:56.054 --> 07:32:00.684
In furtherance of this choice, it so happened that a ship lay in the harbor, one of those

07:32:00.684 --> 07:32:06.104
unquestionable cruisers frequent at that day, with, without being absolutely outlaws of

07:32:06.104 --> 07:32:10.844
the deep, yet roamed over its surface with a remarkable irresponsibility of character.

07:32:11.344 --> 07:32:15.644
This vessel had recently arrived from the Spanish main, and within three days' time

07:32:15.644 --> 07:32:16.744
would sail for Bristol.

07:32:17.364 --> 07:32:22.644
Hester Prynne, whose vocation, as a self-enlisted sister of charity, had brought her acquainted

07:32:22.644 --> 07:32:26.864
with the captain and crew, could take upon herself to secure the passage of two individuals

07:32:26.864 --> 07:32:31.424
and a child with all the secrecy which circumstances rendered more than desirable.

07:32:32.904 --> 07:32:37.464
The minister had inquired of Hester, with no little interest, the precise time at which

07:32:37.464 --> 07:32:39.204
the vessel might be expected to depart.

07:32:39.524 --> 07:32:42.044
It would probably be on the fourth day from the present.

07:32:42.304 --> 07:32:47.184
This is most fortunate, he had said to himself, now, why the Reverend Mr. Dimseyle considered

07:32:47.184 --> 07:32:49.404
it so very fortunate we hesitate to reveal.

07:32:49.984 --> 07:32:54.084
Nevertheless, to hold nothing back from the reader, it was because, on the third day from

07:32:54.084 --> 07:32:59.044
the present, he was to preach the election sermon, and, as such an occasion formed an

07:32:59.044 --> 07:33:03.184
honorable epoch in the life of a New England clergyman, he could not have chanced upon

07:33:03.184 --> 07:33:06.744
a more suitable mode and time of terminating his professional career.

07:33:07.024 --> 07:33:12.464
At last they shall say of me, thought this exemplary man, that I leave no duty unperformed

07:33:12.464 --> 07:33:13.344
or ill-performed.

07:33:13.824 --> 07:33:18.604
Sad, indeed, that an introspection so profound and acute as this poor minister's should be

07:33:18.604 --> 07:33:19.644
so miserably deceived.

07:33:19.984 --> 07:33:24.984
We have had, and may still have, worse things to tell of him, but none, we apprehend, so

07:33:24.984 --> 07:33:30.104
pitably weak, no evidence, at once so slight and irrefragable, of a subtle disease that

07:33:30.104 --> 07:33:33.384
had long since begun to eat into the real substance of his character.

07:33:33.884 --> 07:33:38.764
No man, for any considerable period, can wear one face to himself and another to the multitude,

07:33:39.184 --> 07:33:42.504
without finally getting bewildered as to which may be the true.

07:33:43.664 --> 07:33:48.224
The excitement of Mr. Dimseyle's feelings as he returned from his interview with Hester

07:33:48.224 --> 07:33:52.544
lent him an unaccustomed physical energy, and hurried him townward at a rapid pace.

07:33:53.064 --> 07:33:58.064
The pathway along the woods seemed wilder, more uncouth with its rude natural obstacles,

07:33:58.424 --> 07:34:01.924
and less trodden by the foot of man than he remembered it on his outward journey.

07:34:02.364 --> 07:34:07.424
But he leaped across the plashy places, thrust himself through the clinging underbrush, climbed

07:34:07.424 --> 07:34:13.104
the ascent, plunged into the hollow, and overcame, in short, all of the difficulties of the track,

07:34:13.424 --> 07:34:16.544
with an unwaryable activity that astonished him.

07:34:16.544 --> 07:34:21.544
He could not but recall how feebly, and with what frequent pauses for breath, he had toiled

07:34:21.544 --> 07:34:23.644
over the same ground only two days before.

07:34:24.124 --> 07:34:28.524
As he drew near the town, he took an impression of change from the series of familiar objects

07:34:28.524 --> 07:34:29.584
that presented themselves.

07:34:29.984 --> 07:34:35.124
It seemed not yesterday, not one, not two, but many days, or even years ago, since he

07:34:35.124 --> 07:34:35.804
had quitted them.

07:34:36.224 --> 07:34:41.104
There indeed was each former trace of the street as he remembered it, and all the peculiarities

07:34:41.104 --> 07:34:46.204
of the house, with the due multitude of gabled peaks, and a weathercock at every point where

07:34:46.204 --> 07:34:47.504
his memory suggested one.

07:34:48.084 --> 07:34:52.024
Not the less, however, came this importunately obtrusive sense of change.

07:34:52.404 --> 07:34:57.824
The same was true as regarded the acquaintances whom he met, and all the well-known shapes

07:34:57.824 --> 07:34:59.664
of human life, about the little town.

07:34:59.924 --> 07:35:01.724
They looked neither old nor young now.

07:35:01.864 --> 07:35:05.944
The beards of the aged were no whiter, nor could the creeping babe of yesterday walk

07:35:05.944 --> 07:35:06.764
on his feet today.

07:35:07.124 --> 07:35:11.824
It was impossible to describe in what respect they differed from the individuals on whom

07:35:11.824 --> 07:35:13.984
he had so recently bestowed a parting glance.

07:35:13.984 --> 07:35:18.544
And yet the minister's deepest sense seemed to inform him of their mutability.

07:35:19.404 --> 07:35:23.984
A similar impression struck him most remarkably as he passed under the walls of his own church.

07:35:24.404 --> 07:35:29.384
The edifice had so very strange, and yet so familiar an aspect, that Mr. Dimmesdale's

07:35:29.384 --> 07:35:35.124
mind vibrated between two ideas, either that he had seen it only in a dream hitherto, or

07:35:35.124 --> 07:35:36.904
that he was merely dreaming about it now.

07:35:37.364 --> 07:35:42.264
This phenomenon, in the various shapes which it assumed, indicated no external change,

07:35:42.264 --> 07:35:47.584
but so sudden and important a change in the spectator of the familiar scene that the intervening

07:35:47.584 --> 07:35:51.984
space of a single day had operated on his consciousness like the lapse of years.

07:35:52.464 --> 07:35:57.184
The minister's own will, and Hester's will, and the fate that grew between them, had wrought

07:35:57.184 --> 07:35:58.064
this transformation.

07:35:58.544 --> 07:36:03.164
It was the same town as Heretofore, but the same minister returned not from the forest.

07:36:03.484 --> 07:36:07.344
He might have said to the friends who greeted him, I am not the man for whom you take me.

07:36:07.344 --> 07:36:12.624
I left him yonder in the forest, withdrawn into a secret dell by a mossy tree-trunk and

07:36:12.624 --> 07:36:13.904
near a melancholy brook.

07:36:14.024 --> 07:36:19.964
Go seek your minister, and see if his emaciated figure, his thin cheek, his white, heavy,

07:36:20.164 --> 07:36:23.664
pain-wrinkled brow, be not flung down there like a cast-off garment.

07:36:24.084 --> 07:36:29.184
His friends, no doubt, would still have insisted with him, Thou art thyself the man!

07:36:29.524 --> 07:36:32.704
But this error would have been their own, not his.

07:36:33.064 --> 07:36:37.724
Before Mr. Dimmesdale reached home, his inner man gave him other evidences of a revolution

07:36:37.724 --> 07:36:39.264
in the sphere of thought and feeling.

07:36:39.664 --> 07:36:45.064
In truth, nothing short of a total change of dynasty and moral code in that interior

07:36:45.064 --> 07:36:50.744
kingdom was adequate to account for the impulses now communicated to the unfortunate and startled

07:36:50.744 --> 07:36:51.164
minister.

07:36:51.604 --> 07:36:57.124
At every step he was incited to do something strange, wild, wicked thing or other, with

07:36:57.124 --> 07:37:04.324
at once, involuntary and intentional, in spite of himself, yet growing out of a profounder

07:37:04.324 --> 07:37:06.384
self than that which opposed the impulse.

07:37:06.704 --> 07:37:08.924
For instance, he met one of his own deacons.

07:37:09.324 --> 07:37:13.444
The good old man addressed himself with the paternal affection and patriarchal privilege

07:37:13.444 --> 07:37:18.724
which his venerable age, his upright and holy character, and his station in the church entitled

07:37:18.724 --> 07:37:24.004
him to use, and, conjoined with this, the deep, almost worshipping respect which the

07:37:24.004 --> 07:37:26.504
minister's professional and private claims alike demanded.

07:37:27.224 --> 07:37:32.144
Never was there a more beautiful example of how the majesty of age and wisdom may comport

07:37:32.144 --> 07:37:38.464
with this obscenes and respect enjoined upon it, as from the lower social rank and inferior

07:37:38.464 --> 07:37:40.484
order of endowment towards a higher.

07:37:41.084 --> 07:37:45.764
Now, during a conversation of some two or three moments between the Reverend Mr. Dimmesdale

07:37:45.764 --> 07:37:50.644
and this excellent and hoary-bearded deacon, it was only by the most careful self-control

07:37:50.644 --> 07:37:54.824
that the former could refrain from uttering certain blasphemous suggestions that rose

07:37:54.824 --> 07:37:57.304
into his mind, respecting the communion supper.

07:37:57.684 --> 07:38:02.184
He absolutely trembled and turned pale as ashes, lest his tongue should wag itself

07:38:02.184 --> 07:38:06.644
in utterance of these horrible matters, and plead his own consent for so doing without

07:38:06.644 --> 07:38:11.324
his having fairly given it, and, even with this terror in his heart, he could hardly

07:38:11.324 --> 07:38:16.604
avoid laughing to imagine how the sanctified old patriarchal deacon would have been petrified

07:38:16.604 --> 07:38:17.964
by his minister's impiety.

07:38:18.964 --> 07:38:21.244
Again, another incident of the same nature.

07:38:21.604 --> 07:38:25.804
Hurrying along the street, the Reverend Dimmesdale encountered the eldest female member of his

07:38:25.804 --> 07:38:31.604
church, a most pious and exemplary old dame, poor, widowed, lonely, and with a heart full

07:38:31.604 --> 07:38:36.864
of reminisces about her dead husband and children, and her dead friends of long ago, as a burial

07:38:36.864 --> 07:38:38.864
ground is full of stored gravestones.

07:38:39.164 --> 07:38:43.864
Yet all this, which would else have been such heavy sorrow, was made almost a solemn joy

07:38:43.864 --> 07:38:49.664
to her devout old soul by religious consolations and the truth of scripture, wherewith she

07:38:49.664 --> 07:38:54.044
had fed herself continually for more than thirty years, and since Mr. Dimmesdale had

07:38:54.044 --> 07:38:58.744
taken her in charge, the good grandam's chief earthly comfort, which, unless it had been

07:38:58.744 --> 07:39:03.204
likewise a heavenly comfort, could have been none at all, was to meet her pastor, with

07:39:03.204 --> 07:39:08.604
her casually or of set purpose, and be refreshed with a word of warm, fragrant, heaven-breathing

07:39:08.604 --> 07:39:13.564
gospel truth from his beloved lips into her dulled but rapturously attentive ear.

07:39:14.184 --> 07:39:18.564
But on this occasion, up to the moment of putting his lips to the old woman's ear,

07:39:18.784 --> 07:39:23.324
Mr. Dimmesdale, as the great enemy of souls would have it, could recall no text of scripture,

07:39:23.584 --> 07:39:29.844
nor aught else, except a brief pithy and, as it then appeared to him, unanswerable argument

07:39:29.844 --> 07:39:31.984
against the immortality of the human soul.

07:39:32.584 --> 07:39:37.104
The instillment thereof into her mind would probably have caused this aged sister to drop

07:39:37.104 --> 07:39:41.104
dead at once, as by the effect of an intensely poisonous infusion.

07:39:41.464 --> 07:39:44.824
What he really did whisper, the minister could never afterwards recollect.

07:39:45.004 --> 07:39:49.344
There was perhaps a fortunate disorder in his utterance, which failed to impart any

07:39:49.344 --> 07:39:54.224
distinct idea to the good widow's comprehension, or which Providence interpreted after a method

07:39:54.224 --> 07:39:54.764
of its own.

07:39:55.524 --> 07:39:59.704
Assuredly, as the minister looked back, he beheld an expression of divine gratitude and

07:39:59.704 --> 07:40:04.564
ecstasy that seemed like the shine of a the celestial city on her face, so wrinkled and

07:40:04.564 --> 07:40:05.104
ashy pale.

07:40:05.704 --> 07:40:10.044
Again, a third instance, after parting from the old church member, he met the youngest

07:40:10.044 --> 07:40:10.944
sister of them all.

07:40:11.164 --> 07:40:15.984
It was a maiden newly won, and won by the reverend Mr. Dimmesdale's own sermon, on

07:40:15.984 --> 07:40:20.044
the Sabbath after his vigil, to barter the transitory pleasures of the world for the

07:40:20.044 --> 07:40:24.904
heavenly hope that was to assume brighter substance as life grew dark around her, and

07:40:24.904 --> 07:40:27.364
which would gild the utter gloom with final glory.

07:40:27.764 --> 07:40:31.184
She was fair and pure, as a lily that had bloomed in paradise.

07:40:31.184 --> 07:40:36.084
The minister knew well that he was himself enshrined with the stainless sanctity of her

07:40:36.084 --> 07:40:40.844
heart, which hung its snowy curtains about his image, imparting to religion the warmth

07:40:40.844 --> 07:40:43.224
of love, and to love a religious purity.

07:40:43.904 --> 07:40:48.324
Satan that afternoon had surely led the poor young girl away from her mother's side, and

07:40:48.324 --> 07:40:53.504
thrown her into the pathway of this sorely tempted, or, shall we not rather say, this

07:40:53.504 --> 07:40:54.824
lost and desperate man.

07:40:55.004 --> 07:41:00.524
As she drew nigh, the archfiend whispered him to condense into small compass, and drop

07:41:00.524 --> 07:41:05.864
into her tender bosom a germ of evil that would be sure to blossom darkly soon, and

07:41:05.864 --> 07:41:07.424
bear black fruit at times.

07:41:07.744 --> 07:41:12.984
Such was his sense of power over this virgin soul, trusting him as she did, that the minister

07:41:12.984 --> 07:41:18.384
felt potent to blight all the fields of innocence with but one wicked look, and develop all

07:41:18.384 --> 07:41:19.804
its opposite with but a word.

07:41:20.144 --> 07:41:24.684
So with a mightier struggle than he had yet sustained, he held his Jennifer cloak before

07:41:24.684 --> 07:41:29.404
his face, and hurried onward, making no sign of recognition, and leaving the young sister

07:41:29.404 --> 07:41:31.224
to digest his rudeness as she might.

07:41:31.824 --> 07:41:36.104
She ransacked her conscience, which was full of harmless little matters, like her pocket

07:41:36.104 --> 07:41:40.904
or her work-bag, and took herself to task, poor thing, for a thousand imaginary faults,

07:41:41.164 --> 07:41:44.544
and went about her household duties with swollen eyelids the next morning.

07:41:45.004 --> 07:41:49.204
Before the minister had time to celebrate his victory over this last temptation, he

07:41:49.204 --> 07:41:52.804
was conscious of another impulse, more ludicrous and almost as horrible.

07:41:52.984 --> 07:41:58.164
It was, we blush to tell it, it was to stop short in the road, and teach some very wicked

07:41:58.164 --> 07:42:03.224
words to a knot of little Puritan children, who were playing there, and had just begun

07:42:03.224 --> 07:42:03.664
to talk.

07:42:04.164 --> 07:42:08.884
Denying himself this freak, as unworthy of his cloth, he met a drunken seaman, one of

07:42:08.884 --> 07:42:10.544
the ship's crew from the Spanish main.

07:42:10.844 --> 07:42:15.864
And here, since he had so valiantly forebode all other wickedness, poor Mr. Dimmesdale

07:42:15.864 --> 07:42:21.204
longed at last to shake hands with this tarry black guard, and recreate himself with a

07:42:21.204 --> 07:42:26.684
few improper jests, such as dissolute sailors so abound with, and a volley of good, round,

07:42:26.684 --> 07:42:29.544
solid, satisfactory, and heaven-defying oaths.

07:42:29.544 --> 07:42:34.104
It was not so much a better principle, as partly his natural good taste, and still more

07:42:34.104 --> 07:42:38.304
his buck-rammed habit of clerical decorum, that carried him safely through the latter

07:42:38.304 --> 07:42:38.764
crisis.

07:42:39.564 --> 07:42:44.504
"'What is it that hurts and tempts me thus?' cried the minister to himself at length, pausing

07:42:44.504 --> 07:42:46.884
in the street, and striking his hand against his forehead.

07:42:47.184 --> 07:42:50.664
"'Am I mad, or am I giving over utterly to the fiend?

07:42:50.904 --> 07:42:54.284
Did I make a contract with him in the forest, and sign it with my blood?

07:42:54.284 --> 07:42:58.944
And does he now summon me to its fulfilment, by suggesting the performance of every wickedness

07:42:58.944 --> 07:43:01.944
which his most foul imagination can conceive?'

07:43:01.944 --> 07:43:06.264
At the moment, when the reverend Mr. Dimmesdale thus communed with himself, and struck his

07:43:06.264 --> 07:43:11.364
forehead with his hand, old Mistress Hibbins, the reputed witch-lady, is said to have been

07:43:11.364 --> 07:43:12.004
passing by.

07:43:12.264 --> 07:43:17.584
She made a very grand appearance, having on a high head-dress a rich gown of velvet, and

07:43:17.584 --> 07:43:22.644
a rough done-up with a famous yellow starch, of which Anne Turner, her especial friend,

07:43:22.644 --> 07:43:27.824
had taught her the secret, before the last good lady had been hanged for Sir Thomas Overbury's

07:43:27.824 --> 07:43:28.264
murder.

07:43:28.984 --> 07:43:33.224
Whether the witch had read the minister's thoughts or no, she came to a full stop, looking

07:43:33.224 --> 07:43:38.484
shrewdly in his face, smiled craftily, and, though little given to converse with clergymen,

07:43:38.664 --> 07:43:39.624
began a conversation.

07:43:40.124 --> 07:43:44.704
"'So, reverend sir, you have made a visit into the forest,' observed the witch-lady,

07:43:44.904 --> 07:43:46.444
nodding her high head-dress to him.

07:43:46.704 --> 07:43:51.264
"'The next time, I pray, you allow me only a fair warning, and I shall be proud to bear

07:43:51.264 --> 07:43:51.684
you company.

07:43:52.024 --> 07:43:56.924
Without taking over much upon myself, my good word will go far towards gaining any strange

07:43:56.924 --> 07:44:00.904
gentleman a fair reception from younger potente you want off.'

07:44:01.764 --> 07:44:06.724
"'I profess, madam,' answered the clergyman, with a grave obscience, such as the lady's

07:44:06.724 --> 07:44:11.524
rank demanded, and his own good breeding made imperative, "'I profess on my conscience

07:44:11.524 --> 07:44:15.724
and character that I am utterly bewildered as touching the purport of your words.

07:44:15.824 --> 07:44:18.444
I went not into the forest to seek a potentate.

07:44:18.444 --> 07:44:23.464
Neither do I, at any future time, design a visit thither, with a view of gaining the

07:44:23.464 --> 07:44:24.664
favour of such personage.

07:44:25.024 --> 07:44:29.304
My one sufficient object was to greet that pious friend of mine, the apostle Elliot,

07:44:29.604 --> 07:44:33.304
and rejoice with him over the many precious souls he hath won from heathen-dom.

07:44:33.624 --> 07:44:38.984
"'Ha, ha, ha!' cackled the old witch-lady, still nodding her high head-dress at the minister.

07:44:39.504 --> 07:44:42.404
"'Well, well, we must talk thus in the daytime.

07:44:42.724 --> 07:44:47.364
You carry it off like an old hand, but at midnight in the forest we shall have other

07:44:47.364 --> 07:44:48.684
talk together.'

07:44:48.684 --> 07:44:53.544
She passed on with her aged stateliness, but often turning back her head and smiling at

07:44:53.544 --> 07:44:57.264
him, like one willing to recognize a secret intimacy of connection.

07:44:57.984 --> 07:45:02.684
"'Have I then sold myself,' thought the minister, to the fiend whom, if men say true,

07:45:02.884 --> 07:45:06.904
this yellow-starched and velveted old hag has chosen for her prince and master?

07:45:07.364 --> 07:45:08.724
The wretched minister!

07:45:08.864 --> 07:45:10.744
He had made a bargain very like it.

07:45:10.864 --> 07:45:15.984
Tempted by a dream of happiness, he had yielded himself with deliberate choice, as he had

07:45:15.984 --> 07:45:16.944
never done before.

07:45:17.324 --> 07:45:23.304
To what he knew was deadly sin, and the infectious poison of that sin had been thus rapidly diffused

07:45:23.304 --> 07:45:24.564
throughout his moral system.

07:45:25.164 --> 07:45:30.084
It had stupefied all blessed impulses, and awakened into vivid life the whole brotherhood

07:45:30.084 --> 07:45:30.644
of bad ones.

07:45:31.124 --> 07:45:37.184
Scorn, bitterness, unprovoked malignity, gratuitous desire of ill, ridicule of whatever was good

07:45:37.184 --> 07:45:40.704
and holy, all awoke to tempt, even while they frightened him.

07:45:41.064 --> 07:45:45.724
And his encounter with old mistress Hibbins, if it were a real incident, did but show its

07:45:45.724 --> 07:45:49.944
sympathy and fellowship with wicked mortals, and the world of perverted spirits.

07:45:51.084 --> 07:45:55.604
He had by this time reached his dwelling on the edge of the burial ground, and, hastening

07:45:55.604 --> 07:45:57.564
up the stairs, took refuge in his study.

07:45:58.084 --> 07:46:02.124
The minister was glad to have reached this shelter without first betraying himself to

07:46:02.124 --> 07:46:07.264
the world by any of those strange and wicked eccentricities to which he had been continually

07:46:07.264 --> 07:46:09.304
impelled while passing through the streets.

07:46:09.824 --> 07:46:14.424
He entered the accustomed room and looked around him on its books, its windows, its

07:46:14.424 --> 07:46:19.544
fireplace, and the tapestrid comfort of the walls, with the same perception of strangeness

07:46:19.544 --> 07:46:24.224
that had haunted him throughout his walk from the forest dell into the town and thitherward.

07:46:24.824 --> 07:46:26.124
Here he had studied and written.

07:46:26.704 --> 07:46:30.044
Here gone through fast and vigil, and come forth half alive.

07:46:30.504 --> 07:46:31.604
Here striven to pray.

07:46:31.924 --> 07:46:34.064
Here borne a hundred thousand agonies.

07:46:34.324 --> 07:46:38.884
There was the Bible in its rich old Hebrew, with Moses and the prophets speaking to him,

07:46:39.144 --> 07:46:40.424
and God's voice through all.

07:46:40.744 --> 07:46:45.244
There on the table, with the inky pen beside it, was an unfinished sermon, with a sentence

07:46:45.244 --> 07:46:49.724
broken in the midst, where his thoughts had ceased to gush upon the page two days before.

07:46:50.184 --> 07:46:54.444
He knew that it was himself, the thin and white-cheeked minister, who had done and suffered

07:46:54.444 --> 07:46:57.624
these things, and written thus far into the election sermon.

07:46:58.004 --> 07:47:03.024
But he seemed to stand apart and eye this former self with scornful pity, but half envious

07:47:03.024 --> 07:47:03.664
curiosity.

07:47:04.064 --> 07:47:05.024
That self was gone.

07:47:05.304 --> 07:47:09.844
Another man had returned out of the forest, a wiser one, with a knowledge of hidden mysteries

07:47:09.844 --> 07:47:15.004
which the simplicity of the former never could have reached, a bitter kind of knowledge that.

07:47:15.564 --> 07:47:19.704
While occupied with these reflections, a knock came at the door of the study, and the minister

07:47:19.704 --> 07:47:24.764
said, Come in, not wholly devoid of an idea that he might behold an evil spirit.

07:47:25.004 --> 07:47:25.944
And so he did.

07:47:26.324 --> 07:47:28.384
It was old Roger Chillingworth that entered.

07:47:28.724 --> 07:47:32.904
The minister stood white and speechless, with one hand on the Hebrew scriptures, and the

07:47:32.904 --> 07:47:34.184
other spread upon his breast.

07:47:34.984 --> 07:47:37.164
Welcome home, reverend sir, said the physician.

07:47:37.574 --> 07:47:40.024
And how found you that godly man, the apostle Elliot?

07:47:40.404 --> 07:47:44.404
But methinks, dear sir, you look pale, as if the travel through the wilderness had been

07:47:44.404 --> 07:47:45.304
too sore for you.

07:47:45.684 --> 07:47:49.604
Will not my aid be requisite to put you in heart and strength to preach your election

07:47:49.604 --> 07:47:49.964
sermon?

07:47:50.504 --> 07:47:53.424
Nay, I think not so, rejoined the reverend Mr. Dimmesdale.

07:47:53.704 --> 07:47:58.464
My journey and the sight of the holy apostle yonder, and the free air which I have breathed,

07:47:58.644 --> 07:48:01.704
have done me good, after so long confinement in my study.

07:48:02.144 --> 07:48:06.644
I think to need no more of your drugs, my kind physician, good though they be, and administered

07:48:06.644 --> 07:48:07.744
by a friendly hand.

07:48:08.444 --> 07:48:12.684
At this time Roger Chillingworth was looking at the minister with the grave and intent

07:48:12.684 --> 07:48:14.924
regard of a physician towards his patient.

07:48:15.464 --> 07:48:20.324
But in spite of this outward show, the latter was almost convinced of the old man's knowledge,

07:48:20.624 --> 07:48:25.744
or at least his confident suspicion, with respect to his own interview with Hester Prynne.

07:48:26.104 --> 07:48:30.644
The physician knew then that in the minister's regard he was no longer a trusted friend,

07:48:30.924 --> 07:48:32.164
but his bitterest enemy.

07:48:32.664 --> 07:48:36.624
So much being known, it would appear natural that a part of it should be expressed.

07:48:36.844 --> 07:48:42.444
It is singular, however, how long a time often passes before words embody things, and with

07:48:42.444 --> 07:48:47.564
what security two persons, who chose to avoid a certain subject, may approach its very verge

07:48:47.564 --> 07:48:49.364
and retire without disturbing it.

07:48:49.484 --> 07:48:54.004
Thus the minister felt no apprehension that Roger Chillingworth would touch and express

07:48:54.004 --> 07:48:57.664
words upon the real position which they sustained towards one another.

07:48:58.184 --> 07:49:01.864
Yet did the physician, in his dark way, creep frightfully near the secret.

07:49:02.744 --> 07:49:07.624
Were it not better, he said, that you use my poor skill tonight, verily dear sir, we

07:49:07.624 --> 07:49:11.844
must take pains to make you strong and vigorous for this occasion of the election discourse.

07:49:12.304 --> 07:49:16.684
The people look for great things from you, apprehending that another year may come about

07:49:16.684 --> 07:49:18.104
and find their master gone.

07:49:18.784 --> 07:49:23.604
Yes, to another world replied the minister, with pious resignation, heaven granted that

07:49:23.604 --> 07:49:28.764
better one, for, in good sooth, I hardly think to tarry with my flock through the fleeting

07:49:28.764 --> 07:49:29.844
seasons of another year.

07:49:30.164 --> 07:49:34.404
But touching your medicine, kind sir, in my present frame of body, I need it not.

07:49:34.764 --> 07:49:36.904
I joy to hear it, administered the physician.

07:49:37.204 --> 07:49:41.944
It may be that my remedies, so long administered in vain, begin now to take due effect.

07:49:42.324 --> 07:49:46.764
Happy man were I, and well deserving of New England's gratitude, could I achieve this

07:49:46.764 --> 07:49:47.044
cure.

07:49:47.524 --> 07:49:52.424
I thank you from my heart, most watchful friend, said Reverend Mr. Dimmesdale, with a solemn

07:49:52.424 --> 07:49:52.744
smile.

07:49:53.204 --> 07:49:56.604
I thank you, and can but requite your good deeds with my prayers.

07:49:57.304 --> 07:50:01.924
A good man's prayers are golden recompense, rejoined old Roger Chillingworth, as he took

07:50:01.924 --> 07:50:02.344
his leave.

07:50:02.804 --> 07:50:07.384
Yea, they are the current gold coin of the New Jerusalem, with the King's own mint mark

07:50:07.384 --> 07:50:07.984
on them.

07:50:09.084 --> 07:50:13.924
Left alone, the minister summoned a servant of the house, and requested food, which, being

07:50:13.924 --> 07:50:16.604
set before him, he ate with ravenous appetite.

07:50:16.884 --> 07:50:21.484
Then flinging the already written pages of the election sermon into the fire, he forthwith

07:50:21.484 --> 07:50:25.904
began another, which he wrote with such an impulsive flow of thought and emotion, that

07:50:25.904 --> 07:50:30.484
he fancied himself inspired, and only wondered that heaven should see fit to transmit the

07:50:30.484 --> 07:50:34.784
grand and solemn music of its oracles through so foul an organ-pipe as he.

07:50:35.264 --> 07:50:40.364
However, leaving that mystery to solve itself, or go unsolved for ever, he drove his task

07:50:40.364 --> 07:50:42.404
onward with earnest haste and ecstasy.

07:50:43.204 --> 07:50:47.584
Thus the night fled away, as if it were a winged steed, and he careering on it.

07:50:47.954 --> 07:50:52.944
Morning came and peeped, blushing, through the curtains, and at last sunrise through

07:50:52.944 --> 07:50:57.464
a golden beam into the study, and laid it right across the minister's bedazzled eyes.

07:50:57.824 --> 07:51:02.324
There he was, with the pen still between his fingers, and a vast immeasurable tract of

07:51:02.324 --> 07:51:04.144
written space behind him.

07:51:35.152 --> 07:51:37.212
THE NEW ENGLAND HOLIDAY.

07:51:38.132 --> 07:51:47.492
The times in the morning of the day on which the new governor was to receive his office at the hands of the people, Hester Prynne and Little Pearl came into the market place.

07:51:48.552 --> 07:52:04.892
It was already thronged with the craftsmen and other plebeian inhabitants of the town, in considerable numbers, among whom, likewise, were many rough figures, whose attire of deer skins marked them as belonging to some of the forest settlements which surrounded the little metropolis of the colony.

07:52:05.892 --> 07:52:14.072
On this public holiday, as on all other occasions for seven years past, Hester was clad in a garment of coarse gray cloth.

07:52:14.932 --> 07:52:32.152
Not more by its hue than by some indescribable peculiarity in its fashion, it had the effect of making her fade personally out of sight and outline, while again the scarlet letter brought her back from this twilight indistinctness and revealed her under the moral aspect of its own illumination.

07:52:32.812 --> 07:52:40.072
Her face, so long familiar to the townspeople, showed the marble quietude which they were accustomed to behold there.

07:52:40.972 --> 07:52:56.032
It was like a mask, or rather like the frozen calmness of a dead woman's features, owing this dreary resemblance to the fact that Hester was actually dead in respect to any claim of sympathy, and had departed out of the world with which she still seemed to mingle.

07:52:56.892 --> 07:53:13.392
It might be, on this one day, that there was an expression unseen before, nor indeed vivid enough to be detected now, unless some preternaturally gifted observer should have first read the heart, and have afterwards sought a corresponding development in the countenance and mean.

07:53:14.392 --> 07:53:35.772
Such a spiritual seer might have conceived that, after sustaining the gaze of the multitude through several miserable years as a necessity, a penance, and something which it was a stern religion to endure, she now, for one last time more, encountered it freely and voluntarily, in order to convert what had so long been agony into a kind of triumph.

07:53:36.792 --> 07:53:44.712
Look your last on the scarlet letter and its wearer, the people's victim and life-long bond-slave, as they fancied her, might say to them.

07:53:45.672 --> 07:53:55.632
Yet a little while, and she will be beyond your reach. A few hours longer, and the deep mysterious ocean will quench and hide forever the symbol which ye have caused to burn on her bosom.

07:53:56.552 --> 07:54:10.252
Nor were it an inconsistency too improbable to be assigned to human nature, should we suppose a feeling of regret in Hester's mind at the moment when she was about to win her freedom from the pain which had been thus deeply incorporated with her being.

07:54:10.912 --> 07:54:21.192
Might there not be an irresistible desire to quaff a last long, breathless draft of the cup of wormwood and aloes with which nearly all her years of womanhood had been perpetually flavored?

07:54:21.912 --> 07:54:38.932
The wine of life, henceforth to be presented to her lips, must be indeed rich, delicious, and exhilarating in its chaste and golden beaker, or else leave an inevitable and weary languor after the leaves of bitterness wherewith she had been drugged, as with a cordial of intensest potency.

07:54:39.932 --> 07:55:03.272
Pearl was decked out with airy gaiety. It would have been impossible to guess that this bright and sunny apparition owed its existence to the shape of gloomy gray, or that a fancy, at once so gorgeous and so delicate as must have been requisite to contrive the child's apparel, was the same that had achieved a task perhaps more difficult in imparting so distinct a peculiarity to Hester's simple robe.

07:55:03.932 --> 07:55:20.612
The dress, so proper was it to little Pearl, seemed an effluence or inevitable development and outward manifestation of her character, no more to be separated from her than the many-hued brilliancy from a butterfly's wing, or the painted glory from the leaf of a bright flower.

07:55:21.392 --> 07:55:26.872
As with these, so with the child. Her garb was all of one idea with her nature.

07:55:27.952 --> 07:55:40.872
On this eventful day, moreover, there was a certain singular inquietude and excitement in her mood, resembling nothing so much as the shimmer of a diamond that sparkles and flashes with the varied throbbing of the breast on which it is displayed.

07:55:41.692 --> 07:56:04.892
Children have always a sympathy in the agitations of those connected with them, always especially a sense of any trouble or impending revolution of whatever kind in domestic circumstances, and therefore Pearl, who is the gem on her mother's unquiet bosom, betrayed by the very dance of her spirits, the emotions which none could detect in the marble passiveness of Hester's brow.

07:56:06.252 --> 07:56:11.352
This effervescence made her flit with a bird-like movement rather than walk by her mother's side.

07:56:12.552 --> 07:56:31.192
She broke continually into shouts of a wild, inarticulate, and sometimes piercing music. When they reached the market-place, she became still more restless on perceiving the stir and bustle that enlivened the spot, for it was usually more like the broad and lonesome green before a village meeting-house than the center of a town's business.

07:56:32.572 --> 07:56:51.032
Why, what is this, mother? cried she. Wherefore have all the people left their work to-day? Is it a play-day for the whole world? See, there is the blacksmith. He has washed his sooty face and put on his Sabbath-day clothes, and looks as if he would gladly be merry if any kind body would only teach him how.

07:56:51.832 --> 07:56:57.532
And there is Master Bracket, the old jailer, nodding and smiling at me. Why does he do so, mother?

07:56:58.912 --> 07:57:02.572
He remembers thee a little babe, my child, answered Hester.

07:57:04.132 --> 07:57:09.732
He should not nod and smile at me for all that, the black, grim, ugly-eyed old man, said Pearl.

07:57:10.672 --> 07:57:24.332
He may nod at thee, if he will, for thou art clad in gray, and wearest the scarlet letter. But see, mother, how many faces of strange people, and Indians among them, and sailors. What have they all come to do here in the market-place?

07:57:25.972 --> 07:57:37.072
They wait to see the procession pass, said Hester, for the governor and the magistrates are to go by, and the ministers and all the great people and good people, with the music and the soldiers marching before them.

07:57:37.972 --> 07:57:45.712
And will the minister be there? asked Pearl. And will he hold out both his hands to me, as when thou letst me to him from the brookside?

07:57:46.852 --> 07:57:53.372
He will be there, child, answered her mother. But he will not greet thee to-day, nor must thou greet him.

07:57:54.632 --> 07:58:00.152
What a strange, sad man is he, said the child, as of speaking partly to herself.

07:58:00.732 --> 07:58:07.352
In the dark night-time he calls us to him, and holds thy hand and mine, as when we stood with him on the scaffold yonder.

07:58:08.072 --> 07:58:14.932
And in the deep forest, where only the old trees can hear, and the strip of sky see it, he talks with thee, sitting on a heap of moss.

07:58:15.332 --> 07:58:19.852
And he kisses my forehead, too, so that the little brook would hardly wash it off.

07:58:20.232 --> 07:58:25.772
But here, in the sunny day, and among all the people, he knows us not, nor must we know him.

07:58:26.392 --> 07:58:29.932
A strange, sad man is he, with his hand always over his heart.

07:58:31.172 --> 07:58:35.492
Be quiet, Pearl, thou understandest not these things, said her mother.

07:58:36.392 --> 07:58:41.692
Think not now of the minister, but look about thee, and see how cheery is everybody's face to-day.

07:58:42.252 --> 07:58:48.132
The children have come from their schools, and the grown people from their workshops and their fields, on purpose to be happy.

07:58:48.592 --> 07:58:56.532
For today a new man is beginning to rule over them, and so, as has been the custom of mankind ever since a nation was first gathered,

07:58:56.972 --> 07:59:02.852
they make merry and rejoice, as if a good and golden year were at length to pass over the poor old world.

07:59:04.092 --> 07:59:09.252
It was, as Hester said, in regard to the unwanted jollity that brightened the faces of the people.

07:59:09.832 --> 07:59:16.612
Into this festal season of the year, as it already was, and continued to be during the greater part of two centuries,

07:59:17.312 --> 07:59:21.812
the Puritans compressed whatever mirth and public joy they deemed allowable to human infirmity,

07:59:22.752 --> 07:59:27.592
thereby so far dispelling the customary cloud that, for the space of a single holiday,

07:59:28.032 --> 07:59:32.732
they appeared scarcely more grave than most other communities at a period of general affliction.

07:59:33.272 --> 07:59:40.372
But we perhaps exaggerate the gray or sable tinge, which undoubtedly characterized the mood and manners of the age.

07:59:41.312 --> 07:59:46.792
The persons now in the marketplace of Boston had not been born to the inheritance of Puritanic gloom.

07:59:47.232 --> 07:59:52.612
They were native Englishmen, whose fathers had lived in the sunny richness of the Elizabethan epoch,

07:59:52.832 --> 08:00:01.412
a time when the life of England, viewed as one great mass, would appear to have been as stately, magnificent, and joyous as the world has ever witnessed.

08:00:01.972 --> 08:00:08.512
Had they followed their hereditary taste, the New England settlers would have illustrated all events of public importance

08:00:08.512 --> 08:00:14.832
by bonfires, banquets, pageantries, and processions, nor would it have been impracticable,

08:00:15.152 --> 08:00:20.712
in the observance of majestic ceremonies, to combine mirthful recreation with solemnity,

08:00:21.252 --> 08:00:28.512
and give, as it were, a grotesque and brilliant embroidery to the great robe of state which a nation at such festivals puts on.

08:00:29.152 --> 08:00:35.932
There was some shadow of an attempt of this kind in the mode of celebrating the day on which the political year of the colony commenced.

08:00:36.852 --> 08:00:44.192
The dim reflection of a remembered splendor, a colorless and manifold diluted repetition of what they had beheld in proud old London,

08:00:44.712 --> 08:00:48.352
we will not say at a royal coronation, but at a Lord Mayor's show,

08:00:48.932 --> 08:00:55.012
might be traced in the customs which our forefathers instituted with reference to the annual installation of magistrates.

08:00:55.592 --> 08:01:00.892
The fathers and founders of the commonwealth, the statesmen, the priest, and the soldier,

08:01:01.572 --> 08:01:06.852
seemed it a duty then to assume the outward state and majesty which, in accordance with antique style,

08:01:07.412 --> 08:01:10.712
was looked upon as the proper garb of public and social eminence.

08:01:11.552 --> 08:01:14.732
All came forth to move in procession before the people's eye,

08:01:15.232 --> 08:01:20.052
and thus impart a needed dignity to the simple framework of a government so newly constructed.

08:01:21.072 --> 08:01:24.292
Then, too, the people were countenanced, if not encouraged,

08:01:24.572 --> 08:01:29.092
in relaxing the severe and close application to their various modes of rugged industry,

08:01:29.512 --> 08:01:33.372
which at all other times seemed of the same piece and material with their religion.

08:01:34.572 --> 08:01:40.992
Here, it is true, were none of the appliances which popular merriment would so readily have found in the England of Elizabeth's time,

08:01:41.232 --> 08:01:42.412
or that of James.

08:01:42.872 --> 08:01:45.192
No rude shows of a theatrical kind,

08:01:45.752 --> 08:01:48.552
no minstrel with his harp and legendary ballad,

08:01:48.552 --> 08:01:51.292
nor Gleeman with an ape dancing to his music,

08:01:51.912 --> 08:01:54.572
no juggler with his tricks of mimic witchcraft,

08:01:55.132 --> 08:01:58.292
no Mary Andrew to stir up the multitude with jests,

08:01:58.412 --> 08:02:00.972
perhaps a hundred years old, but still effective,

08:02:01.432 --> 08:02:04.892
by their appeals to the very broadest sources of mirthful sympathy.

08:02:05.712 --> 08:02:10.792
All such professors of the several branches of jocularity would have been sternly repressed,

08:02:11.172 --> 08:02:16.412
not only by the rigid discipline of law, but by the general sentiment which gave law its vitality.

08:02:17.232 --> 08:02:20.992
Not the less, however, the great honest face of the people smiled,

08:02:21.652 --> 08:02:23.972
grimly perhaps, but widely too.

08:02:24.712 --> 08:02:29.232
Nor were sports wanting, such as the colonists had witnessed in Sheridan long ago,

08:02:29.512 --> 08:02:31.952
at the country fairs and on the village greens of England,

08:02:32.512 --> 08:02:35.332
in which it was thought well to keep alive on this new soil,

08:02:35.572 --> 08:02:38.872
for the sake of the courage and manliness that were essential in them.

08:02:39.752 --> 08:02:43.352
Wrestling matches, in the different fashions of Cornwall and Devonshire,

08:02:43.752 --> 08:02:45.832
were seen here and there about the marketplace,

08:02:46.392 --> 08:02:49.432
in one corner there was a friendly bout at quarterstaff,

08:02:49.692 --> 08:02:52.052
and, what attracted most interest of all,

08:02:52.392 --> 08:02:55.912
on the platform of the pillory, already so noted in our pages,

08:02:56.092 --> 08:03:00.272
two masters of defense were commencing an exhibition with the buckler and broadsword.

08:03:00.892 --> 08:03:02.952
But, much to the disappointment of the crowd,

08:03:03.212 --> 08:03:06.892
this latter business was broken off by the interposition of the town beetle,

08:03:07.272 --> 08:03:10.172
who had no idea of permitting the majesty of the law

08:03:10.172 --> 08:03:13.892
to be violated by such an abuse of one of its consecrated places.

08:03:14.652 --> 08:03:17.852
It may not be too much to affirm, on the whole,

08:03:18.252 --> 08:03:21.592
the people being then in the first stages of joyless deportment,

08:03:21.932 --> 08:03:25.292
and the offspring of sires who had known how to be merry in their day,

08:03:25.732 --> 08:03:28.652
that they would compare favorably, in point of holiday keeping,

08:03:28.772 --> 08:03:32.152
with their descendants, even at so long an interval as ourselves.

08:03:32.972 --> 08:03:36.672
Their immediate posterity, the generation next to the early immigrants,

08:03:37.152 --> 08:03:39.092
wore the blackest shade of Puritanism,

08:03:39.512 --> 08:03:41.612
and so darkened the national visage with it,

08:03:41.612 --> 08:03:44.612
that all the subsequent years have not sufficed to clear it up.

08:03:45.492 --> 08:03:48.232
We have yet to learn again the forgotten art of gaiety.

08:03:49.612 --> 08:03:51.592
The picture of human life in the marketplace,

08:03:52.192 --> 08:03:56.352
though its general tint was the sad gray, brown, or black of the English immigrants,

08:03:56.712 --> 08:03:59.072
was yet enlivened by some diversity of hue.

08:03:59.972 --> 08:04:05.132
A party of Indians, in their savage finery of curiously embroidered deer-skin robes,

08:04:05.372 --> 08:04:08.172
wampum belts, red and yellow ochre, and feathers,

08:04:08.732 --> 08:04:11.372
and armed with the bow and arrow and stone-headed spear,

08:04:11.612 --> 08:04:14.412
stood apart with countenances of inflexible gravity,

08:04:14.992 --> 08:04:17.452
beyond what even the Puritan aspect could attain.

08:04:18.552 --> 08:04:20.952
Nor, wild as were these painted barbarians,

08:04:21.092 --> 08:04:22.932
were they the wildest feature of the scene.

08:04:23.772 --> 08:04:27.012
This distinction could more justly be claimed by some mariners,

08:04:27.472 --> 08:04:29.872
a part of the crew of the vessel from the Spanish main,

08:04:30.252 --> 08:04:32.752
who had come ashore to see the humours of election day.

08:04:33.332 --> 08:04:36.672
They were rough-looking desperados, with sun-blackened faces,

08:04:36.992 --> 08:04:38.332
and an immensity of beard.

08:04:38.972 --> 08:04:42.572
Their wide, short trousers were confined about the waist by belts,

08:04:42.992 --> 08:04:45.012
often clasped with a rough plate of gold,

08:04:45.432 --> 08:04:47.432
and sustaining always a long knife,

08:04:47.672 --> 08:04:49.532
and in some instances a sword.

08:04:50.452 --> 08:04:53.572
From beneath their broad-brimmed hats of palm-leaf gleamed eyes,

08:04:53.832 --> 08:04:57.692
which, even in good nature and merriment, had a kind of animal ferocity.

08:04:58.492 --> 08:05:00.812
They transgressed without fear or scruple,

08:05:01.112 --> 08:05:03.512
the rules of behaviour that were binding on all others,

08:05:03.872 --> 08:05:06.292
smoking tobacco under the beetle's very nose,

08:05:06.592 --> 08:05:09.092
although each whiff would have cost a townsman a shilling,

08:05:09.672 --> 08:05:11.152
and quaffing, at their pleasure,

08:05:11.692 --> 08:05:14.512
draughts of wine or aquavite from pocket flasks,

08:05:14.672 --> 08:05:17.372
which they freely tendered to the gaping crowd around them.

08:05:18.012 --> 08:05:21.512
It remarkably characterised the incomplete morality of the age,

08:05:22.052 --> 08:05:23.372
rigid as we call it,

08:05:23.572 --> 08:05:26.112
that a licence was allowed for the seafaring class,

08:05:26.752 --> 08:05:28.412
not merely for their freaks on shore,

08:05:28.512 --> 08:05:31.172
but for far more desperate deeds on their proper element.

08:05:32.292 --> 08:05:35.772
The sailor of that day would go near to be arraigned as a pirate in our own.

08:05:36.292 --> 08:05:39.612
There could be little doubt, for instance, that this very ship's crew,

08:05:39.892 --> 08:05:42.872
though no unfavourable specimens of the nautical brotherhood,

08:05:43.352 --> 08:05:45.152
had been guilty, as we should phrase it,

08:05:45.272 --> 08:05:47.252
of depredations on the Spanish commerce,

08:05:47.652 --> 08:05:50.852
such as would have periled all their necks in a modern court of justice.

08:05:51.832 --> 08:05:55.572
But the sea in those old times heaved, swelled, and foamed,

08:05:55.792 --> 08:05:57.152
very much at its own will,

08:05:57.592 --> 08:05:59.872
or subject only to the tempestuous wind,

08:06:00.212 --> 08:06:03.212
with hardly any attempts at regulation by human law.

08:06:03.772 --> 08:06:06.632
The buccaneer on the wave might relinquish his calling,

08:06:06.892 --> 08:06:08.592
and become, at once, if he chose,

08:06:08.972 --> 08:06:11.572
a man of probity and piety on land.

08:06:12.152 --> 08:06:15.032
Nor, even in the full career of his reckless life,

08:06:15.192 --> 08:06:17.492
was he regarded as a personage with whom it was

08:06:17.492 --> 08:06:20.352
disreputable to traffic or casually associate.

08:06:21.332 --> 08:06:23.832
Thus the Puritan elders in their black cloaks,

08:06:24.152 --> 08:06:26.312
starched bands, and steeple-crowned hats,

08:06:26.832 --> 08:06:29.592
smiled not unbenignedly at the clamour and rude

08:06:29.592 --> 08:06:31.872
deportment of these jolly seafaring men,

08:06:33.212 --> 08:06:35.692
and provided neither surprise nor anemed version

08:06:35.692 --> 08:06:38.872
when so reputable a citizen as old Roger Chillingworth,

08:06:39.052 --> 08:06:41.692
the physician, was seen to enter the market place

08:06:41.692 --> 08:06:45.292
in close and familiar talk with the commander of the questionable vessel.

08:06:46.372 --> 08:06:49.592
The latter was by far the most showy and gallant figure,

08:06:49.912 --> 08:06:51.292
so far as apparel went,

08:06:51.692 --> 08:06:53.552
anywhere to be seen among the multitude.

08:06:54.572 --> 08:06:56.932
He wore a profusion of ribbons on his garment,

08:06:57.352 --> 08:06:58.792
and gold lace on his hat,

08:06:59.092 --> 08:07:01.392
which was also encircled by a gold chain,

08:07:03.332 --> 08:07:05.352
there was a sword at his side,

08:07:05.452 --> 08:07:07.052
and a sword cut on his forehead,

08:07:07.512 --> 08:07:09.452
which, by the arrangement of his hair,

08:07:09.792 --> 08:07:12.472
he seemed anxious rather to display than hide.

08:07:13.572 --> 08:07:16.932
A landsman could hardly have worn this garb and shown this face,

08:07:17.392 --> 08:07:20.292
and worn and shown them both with such a galleyard air

08:07:20.292 --> 08:07:23.512
without undergoing stern question before a magistrate,

08:07:23.992 --> 08:07:26.552
and probably incurring a fine or imprisonment,

08:07:26.732 --> 08:07:28.812
or perhaps an exhibition in the stocks.

08:07:29.912 --> 08:07:31.872
As regarded the shipmaster, however,

08:07:33.212 --> 08:07:34.772
he was not shown as pertaining to the character

08:07:34.772 --> 08:07:36.852
as to a fish his glistening scales.

08:07:38.292 --> 08:07:39.692
After parting from the physician,

08:07:40.052 --> 08:07:43.392
the commander of the Bristol ship strolled idly through the market place

08:07:43.392 --> 08:07:47.032
until, happening to approach the spot where Hester Prynne was standing,

08:07:47.252 --> 08:07:50.672
he appeared to recognize, and did not hesitate to address her.

08:07:51.532 --> 08:07:54.052
As was usually the case wherever Hester stood,

08:07:54.492 --> 08:07:57.492
a small vacant area, a sort of magic circle,

08:07:57.872 --> 08:07:59.412
had formed itself about her,

08:07:59.832 --> 08:08:02.432
into which, though the people were elbowing one another

08:08:03.212 --> 08:08:05.972
in the absence, none ventured or felt disposed to intrude.

08:08:06.672 --> 08:08:09.472
It was a forcible type of the moral solitude

08:08:09.472 --> 08:08:12.712
in which the scarlet letter enveloped its faded wearer,

08:08:12.892 --> 08:08:14.312
partly by her own reserve,

08:08:14.632 --> 08:08:18.032
and partly by the instinctive, though no longer so unkindly,

08:08:18.492 --> 08:08:20.032
withdrawal of her fellow creatures.

08:08:21.212 --> 08:08:24.212
Now, if never before, it answered a good purpose

08:08:24.212 --> 08:08:27.032
by enabling Hester and the seaman to speak together

08:08:27.032 --> 08:08:28.932
without risk of being overheard.

08:08:29.532 --> 08:08:32.692
And so changed was Hester Prynne's repute before the public

08:08:33.212 --> 08:08:35.972
that the matron in town, most eminent for rigid morality,

08:08:36.932 --> 08:08:38.472
could not have held such intercourse

08:08:38.472 --> 08:08:40.652
with less result of scandal than herself.

08:08:41.992 --> 08:08:44.152
So, mistress, said the mariner,

08:08:44.712 --> 08:08:47.252
I must bid the steward make ready for one more berth

08:08:47.252 --> 08:08:48.292
than you bargained for.

08:08:48.712 --> 08:08:51.092
No fear of scurvy or ship fever this voyage.

08:08:51.912 --> 08:08:53.972
What with the ship surgeon and this other doctor,

08:08:54.372 --> 08:08:56.472
our only danger will be from drug or pill,

08:08:56.892 --> 08:09:00.192
more by token as there is a lot of apothecary stuff aboard,

08:09:03.692 --> 08:09:05.832
what mean you, inquired Hester,

08:09:06.152 --> 08:09:07.992
startled more than she permitted to appear.

08:09:08.672 --> 08:09:09.732
Have you another passenger?

08:09:11.612 --> 08:09:13.932
Why, no you not, cried the shipmaster,

08:09:14.432 --> 08:09:17.132
that this physician here, Chillingworth, he calls himself,

08:09:17.532 --> 08:09:19.952
is minded to try my cabin fare with you?

08:09:20.432 --> 08:09:24.052
Ay, ay, you must have known it, for he tells me he is of your party

08:09:24.052 --> 08:09:26.792
and a close friend to the gentleman you spoke of,

08:09:26.932 --> 08:09:30.092
he that is in peril from these sour old Puritan rulers.

08:09:31.392 --> 08:09:33.192
They know each other well indeed,

08:09:33.512 --> 08:09:36.032
replied Hester, with a mean of calmness,

08:09:36.252 --> 08:09:38.112
though in the utmost consternation.

08:09:38.472 --> 08:09:40.392
They have long dwelt together.

08:09:41.752 --> 08:09:44.872
Nothing further passed between the mariner and Hester Prynne,

08:09:45.112 --> 08:09:48.812
but at that instant she beheld old Roger Chillingworth himself

08:09:48.812 --> 08:09:51.652
standing in the remotest corner of the market place

08:09:51.652 --> 08:09:53.052
and smiling on her,

08:09:53.472 --> 08:09:56.592
a smile which, across the wide and bustling square

08:09:56.592 --> 08:09:58.572
and through all the talk and laughter

08:09:58.572 --> 08:10:01.852
and various thoughts, moods and interests of the crowd,

08:10:03.212 --> 08:10:04.212
and fearful meaning.

08:10:33.267 --> 08:10:36.987
Send email to ScholarCat.com.

08:10:36.987 --> 08:10:41.807
The Scarlet Letter.

08:10:45.327 --> 08:10:54.527
Before Hester Prynne could call together her thoughts and consider what was practicable to be done in this new and startling aspect of affairs,

08:10:54.747 --> 08:10:58.927
the sound of military music was heard approaching along a contiguous street.

08:10:59.667 --> 08:11:06.987
It denoted the advance of the procession of magistrates and citizens on its way toward the meeting house,

08:11:07.447 --> 08:11:12.867
where, in compliance with a custom thus early established and ever since observed,

08:11:13.647 --> 08:11:17.447
the Reverend Mr. Dimmesdale was to deliver an election sermon.

08:11:19.187 --> 08:11:29.287
Soon the head of the procession showed itself with a slow and stately march, turning a corner and making its way across the marketplace.

08:11:30.487 --> 08:11:40.827
First came the music. It comprised a variety of instruments, perhaps imperfectly adapted to one another and placed with no great skill,

08:11:40.827 --> 08:11:48.087
but yet attaining the great object for which the harmony of drum and clarion addresses itself to the multitude,

08:11:48.467 --> 08:11:54.587
that of imparting a higher and more heroic air to the scene of life that passes before the eye.

08:11:55.047 --> 08:12:05.467
Little Pearl at first clapped her hands, but then lost, for an instant, the restless agitation that had kept her in a continual effervescence throughout the morning.

08:12:05.467 --> 08:12:13.567
She gazed silently and seemed to be borne upward like a floating seabird on the long heaves and swells of sound,

08:12:14.107 --> 08:12:21.547
but she was brought back to her former mood by the shimmer of the sunshine on the weapons and bright armor of the military company,

08:12:21.747 --> 08:12:26.587
which followed after the music and formed the honorary escort of the procession.

08:12:26.587 --> 08:12:37.587
This body of soldiery, which still sustains a corporate existence and marches down from past ages with an ancient and honorable fame,

08:12:38.067 --> 08:12:50.287
was composed of no mercenary materials. Its ranks were filled with gentlemen who felt the stirrings of martial impulse and sought to establish a kind of college of arms,

08:12:50.287 --> 08:13:02.087
whereas in an association of Knights Templars they might learn the science and so far as peaceful exercise would teach them the practices of war.

08:13:03.087 --> 08:13:11.447
The high estimation then placed upon the military character might be seen in the lofty port of each individual member of the company.

08:13:11.447 --> 08:13:23.527
Some of them, indeed, by their services in the low countries and on other fields of European warfare, had fairly won their title to assume the name and pomp of soldiership.

08:13:24.067 --> 08:13:36.987
The entire array, moreover, clad in burnished steel and with plumage nodding over their bright morians, had a brilliancy of effect which no modern display can aspire to equal.

08:13:36.987 --> 08:13:47.307
And yet, the men of civil eminence, who came immediately behind the military escort, were better worth a thoughtful observer's eye.

08:13:47.527 --> 08:13:56.407
Even in outward demeanor, they showed a stamp of majesty that made the warrior's haughty stride look vulgar, if not absurd.

08:13:56.407 --> 08:14:09.347
It was an age what we call talent had far less consideration than now, but the mass of materials which produced stability and dignity of character a great deal more.

08:14:09.347 --> 08:14:25.827
The people possessed by hereditary right the quality of reverence which in their descendants, if it survive at all, exists in smaller proportion and with a vastly diminished force in the selection and estimate of public men.

08:14:26.627 --> 08:14:32.047
The change may be for good or ill, and is partly perhaps for both.

08:14:32.047 --> 08:14:47.867
In that old day, the English settler, on these rude shores, having left king, nobles, and all degrees of awful rank behind, while still the faculty and necessity of reverence were strong in him,

08:14:47.867 --> 08:15:11.727
bestowed it on the white hair and venerable brow of age, on long-tried integrity, on solid wisdom and sad colored experience, on endowments of that grave and weighty order which gives the idea of permanence and comes under the general definition of respectability.

08:15:11.727 --> 08:15:35.947
These primitive statesmen, therefore, Bradstreet, Endicott, Dudley, Bellingham, and their calm peers, who were elevated to power by the earthly choice of the people, seem to have been not often brilliant, but distinguished by a ponderous sobriety rather than activity of intellect.

08:15:35.947 --> 08:15:49.147
They had fortitude in self-reliance and, in time of difficulty or peril, stood up for the welfare of the state like a line of cliffs against a tempestuous tide.

08:15:50.587 --> 08:16:02.107
The traits of character here indicated were well represented in the square cast of continents and large physical development of the new colonial magistrates.

08:16:02.107 --> 08:16:18.907
So far as the demeanor of natural authority was concerned, the mother country need not have been ashamed to see these foremost men of an actual democracy adopted into the house of peers or made the privy council of the sovereign.

08:16:19.267 --> 08:16:30.287
Next, in order to the magistrates came the young and eminently distinguished divine, from whose lips the religious discourse of the anniversary was expected.

08:16:30.287 --> 08:16:39.227
His was the profession at that era in which intellectual ability displayed itself far more than in political life.

08:16:39.367 --> 08:16:54.087
For leaving a higher motive out of the question, it offered inducements powerful enough in the almost worshipping respect of the community to win the most aspiring ambition into its service.

08:16:54.087 --> 08:17:00.427
Even political power, as in the case of increased matter, was within the grasp of a successful priest.

08:17:00.707 --> 08:17:18.447
It was the observation of those who beheld him now that never since Mr. Dimmesdale first set his foot on the New England shore had he exhibited such energy as was seen in the gait and air with which he kept his pace in the procession.

08:17:18.547 --> 08:17:21.887
There was no feebleness of step as at other times.

08:17:21.887 --> 08:17:28.067
His frame was not bent, nor did his hand rest ominously upon his heart.

08:17:28.527 --> 08:17:35.407
Yet if the clergymen were rightly viewed, his strength seemed not of the body.

08:17:35.627 --> 08:17:40.157
It might be spiritual and imparted to him by angelic ministrations.

08:17:40.747 --> 08:17:51.387
It might be the exhilaration of that potent cordial which is distilled only in the furnace glow of earnest and long continued thought.

08:17:51.387 --> 08:18:03.427
Or, perchance, his sensitive temperament was invigorated by the loud and piercing music that swelled heavenward and uplifted him on its ascending wave.

08:18:04.047 --> 08:18:11.687
Nevertheless, so abstracted was his look, it might be questioned whether Mr. Dimmesdale even heard the music.

08:18:12.687 --> 08:18:17.407
There was his body, moving onward, and with an unaccustomed force.

08:18:17.407 --> 08:18:33.627
But where was his mind? Far and deep in its own region, busying itself with preternatural activity to marshal a procession of stately thoughts that were soon to issue thence.

08:18:33.627 --> 08:18:39.007
And so he saw nothing, heard nothing, knew nothing of what was around him.

08:18:39.007 --> 08:18:50.127
But the spiritual element took up the feeble frame and carried it along, unconscious of the burden and converting it to spirit like itself.

08:18:51.707 --> 08:19:05.747
Men of uncommon intellect who have grown morbid possess this occasional power of mighty effort into which they throw the life of many days and then are lifeless for as many more.

08:19:05.747 --> 08:19:23.507
Hester Prynne, gazing steadfastly at the clergyman, felt a dreary influence come over her, but wherefore or whence she knew not, unless that he seemed so remote from her own sphere and utterly beyond her reach.

08:19:24.447 --> 08:19:33.947
One glance of recognition she had imagined must needs pass between them, she thought of the dim forest.

08:19:34.107 --> 08:19:49.387
With its little dell of solitude and love and anguish and the mossy tree trunk where, sitting hand in hand, they had mingled their sad and passionate talk with the melancholy murmur of the brook.

08:19:49.387 --> 08:19:54.647
How deeply had they known each other then, and was this the man?

08:19:55.167 --> 08:20:16.227
She hardly knew him now, he moving proudly past, enveloped as it were in the rich music with the procession of majestic and venerable fathers, he so unattainable in his worldly position and still more so in that far vista of his unsympathizing thought, through which she now beheld him.

08:20:16.227 --> 08:20:35.647
Her spirit sank with the idea that all must have been a delusion and that vividly, as she had dreamed it, there could be no real bond betwixt the clergyman and herself, and thus much of woman was there in Hester, that she could scarcely forgive him.

08:20:35.647 --> 08:20:57.087
Least of all now, when the heavy footstep of their approaching fate might be heard, nearer, nearer, nearer, for being able so completely to withdraw himself from their mutual world, while she groped darkly and stretched forth her cold hands and found him not.

08:20:57.087 --> 08:21:07.687
Pearl either saw and responded to her mother's feelings or herself, felt the remoteness and intangibility that had fallen around the minister.

08:21:09.067 --> 08:21:15.827
While the procession passed, the child was uneasy, fluttering up and down like a bird on the point of taking flight.

08:21:15.827 --> 08:21:21.007
When the whole had gone by, she looked up into Hester's face.

08:21:46.587 --> 08:21:55.947
Else I would have run to him and bid him kiss me now before all the people, even as he did yonder among the dark old trees.

08:21:56.167 --> 08:22:04.947
What would the minister have said, mother? Would he have clapped his hands over his heart and scowled on me and bid me be gone?

08:22:05.987 --> 08:22:21.287
What should he say, Pearl? answered Hester, saying that it was no time to kiss and that kisses are not to be given in the marketplace. Well for thee, foolish child, that thou didst not speak to him.

08:22:23.127 --> 08:22:34.467
Another shade of the same sentiment in reference to Mr. Dimmesdale was expressed by a person whose eccentricities, or insanity as we should term it,

08:22:34.647 --> 08:22:43.847
led her to do what few of the townspeople would have ventured on, to begin a conversation with the wearer of the scarlet letter in public.

08:22:43.847 --> 08:22:58.847
It was Mistress Hibbins, who arrayed in great magnificence, with a triple ruff, a broidered stomacher, a gown of rich velvet and a gold-headed cane, had come forth to see the procession.

08:22:58.847 --> 08:23:13.707
As this ancient lady had the renown, which subsequently cost her no less a price in her life of being a principal actor in all the works of necromancy that were continually going forward,

08:23:14.487 --> 08:23:23.747
the crowd gave way before her and seemed to fear the touch of her garment as if it carried the plague among its gorgeous folds.

08:23:23.747 --> 08:23:41.387
Seen in conjunction with Hester Prynne, kindly as so many now felt towards the latter, the dread inspired by Mistress Hibbins was doubled and caused a general movement from that part of the marketplace in which the two women stood.

08:23:41.387 --> 08:23:52.567
Now, what mortal imagination could conceive it? whispered the old lady confidentially to Hester.

08:23:52.567 --> 08:24:08.387
Yonder, divine man, that saint on earth as the people uphold him to be, and as I must need say, he really looks.

08:24:08.387 --> 08:24:29.687
Who now that saw him pass in the procession would think how little while it is since he went forth out of his study, chewing a Hebrew text of scripture in his mouth, I warrant, to take an airing in the forest.

08:24:29.687 --> 08:24:37.807
Aha, we know what that means, Hester Prynne.

08:24:37.807 --> 08:24:44.687
But truly forsooth, I find it hard to believe him the same man.

08:24:45.667 --> 08:24:59.107
Many a church member saw I walking behind a music that is danced in the same measure with me when somebody was fiddler,

08:24:59.107 --> 08:25:06.627
and it might be an Indian powwow or a Lapland wizard changing hands with us.

08:25:07.327 --> 08:25:12.567
That is but a trifle when a woman knows the world.

08:25:12.567 --> 08:25:27.427
But this, minister, couldst thou surely tell, Hester, whether he was the same man that encountered thee on the forest path?

08:25:28.927 --> 08:25:50.787
Madam, I know not of what you speak, answered Hester Prynne, feeling Mistress Hibbins to be of infirm mind, yet strangely startled and awe-stricken by the confidence with which she affirmed a personal connection between so many persons, herself among them, and the evil one.

08:25:51.787 --> 08:25:59.087
It is not for me to talk lightly of a learned and pious minister of the word like the Reverend Mr. Dimmesdale.

08:26:00.627 --> 08:26:06.227
Fie, woman, fie, cried the old lady, shaking her finger at Hester.

08:26:06.227 --> 08:26:17.147
Dost thou think I have been to the forest so many times, and have yet no skill to judge who else has been there?

08:26:17.507 --> 08:26:25.727
Yea, though no leaf of the wild garlands which they wore while they danced be left in their hair.

08:26:25.727 --> 08:26:30.527
I know thee, Hester, for I behold the token.

08:26:31.287 --> 08:26:37.827
We may all see it in the sunshine, and it glows like a red flame in the dark.

08:26:38.527 --> 08:26:44.507
Thou wearest it openly, so there need be no question about that.

08:26:45.387 --> 08:26:52.047
But this, minister, let me tell thee in thine ear.

08:26:52.047 --> 08:27:06.947
When the black man sees one of his own servants signed and sealed, so shy of owning to the bond as is the Reverend Mr. Dimmesdale,

08:27:07.787 --> 08:27:19.867
he hath a way of ordering matters so that the mark shall be disclosed in open daylight to the eyes of the world.

08:27:20.887 --> 08:27:33.067
What is it that the minister seeks to hide with his hand always over his heart, ha, Hester Prynne?

08:27:34.587 --> 08:27:41.027
What is it, good Mistress Hibbins, eagerly asked little Pearl, hast thou seen it?

08:27:42.267 --> 08:27:52.287
No matter, darling, responded Mistress Hibbins, making Pearl a profound reverence.

08:27:53.367 --> 08:27:58.407
Thou thyself will see it one time or another.

08:27:59.827 --> 08:28:06.967
They say, child, thou art the lineage of the prince of the air.

08:28:06.967 --> 08:28:13.367
Will thou ride with me some fine night to see thy father?

08:28:14.467 --> 08:28:21.387
Then thou shalt know wherefore the minister keeps his hand over his heart.

08:28:23.607 --> 08:28:31.267
Laughing so shrilly that all the marketplace could hear her, the weird old gentlewoman took her departure.

08:28:32.567 --> 08:28:42.287
By this time the preliminary prayer had been offered in the meeting-house, and the accents of the Reverend Mr. Dimmesdale were heard commencing his discourse.

08:28:43.107 --> 08:28:46.467
An irresistible feeling kept Hester near the spot.

08:28:47.287 --> 08:28:56.547
As the sacred edifice was too much thronged to admit another auditor, she took up her position close beside the scaffold of the pillory.

08:28:57.307 --> 08:29:09.827
It was in sufficient proximity to bring the whole sermon to her ears in the shape of an indistinct but varied murmur and flow of the minister's very peculiar voice.

08:29:10.767 --> 08:29:25.767
This vocal organ was in itself a rich endowment, insomuch that a listener, comprehending nothing of the language in which the preacher spoke, might still have been swayed to and fro by the mere tone and cadence.

08:29:26.807 --> 08:29:37.267
Like all other music, it breathed passion and pathos, and emotions high or tender in a tongue native to the human heart, were ever educated.

08:29:37.267 --> 08:29:54.647
Muffled as the sound was by its passage through the church walls, Hester Prynne listened with such intentness and sympathized so intimately that the sermon had throughout a meaning for her entirely apart from its indistinguishable words.

08:29:54.907 --> 08:30:02.227
These perhaps, if more distinctly heard, might have been only a grosser medium and have clogged the spiritual sense.

08:30:02.227 --> 08:30:22.027
Now she caught the low undertone as if the wind sinking down to repose itself, then ascended with it as it rose through progressive gradations of sweetness and power, until its volume seemed to envelop her with an atmosphere of awe and solemn grandeur.

08:30:22.027 --> 08:30:43.087
And yet, majestic as a voice sometimes became, there was forever in it an essential character of plaintiveness, a low, loud expression of anguish, the whisper or shriek as it might be conceived of suffering humanity that touched the sensibility in every bosom.

08:30:43.087 --> 08:30:54.027
At times, this deep strain of pathos was all that could be heard, and scarcely heard, sighing amid a desolate silence.

08:30:54.767 --> 08:31:12.147
But even when the minister's voice grew high and commanding, when it gushed irrepressibly upward, when it assumed its utmost breadth and power, so overfilling the church as to burst its way through the solid walls and diffuse itself in the open air,

08:31:12.147 --> 08:31:21.527
still if the auditor listened intently and for the purpose he could detect the same cry of pain, what was it?

08:31:21.527 --> 08:31:42.007
The complaint of a human heart, sorrow-laden, perchance guilty, telling its secret, whether of guilt or sorrow, to the great heart of mankind, beseeching its sympathy or forgiveness at every moment, in each accent and never in vain.

08:31:42.327 --> 08:31:50.687
It was this profound and continual undertone that gave the clergyman his most appropriate power.

08:31:50.687 --> 08:31:55.207
During all this time Hester stood statue-like at the foot of the scaffold.

08:31:55.967 --> 08:32:07.247
If the minister's voice had not kept her there, there would nevertheless have been an inevitable magnetism in that spot, once she dated the first hour of her life of ignominy.

08:32:07.247 --> 08:32:26.847
There was a sense within her, too ill-defined to be made a thought, but weighing heavily on her mind, that her whole orb of life, both before and after, was connected with this spot, as with the one point that gave it unity.

08:32:29.207 --> 08:32:35.787
Little Pearl, meanwhile, had quitted her mother's side and was playing at her own about the marketplace.

08:32:35.787 --> 08:32:50.947
She made the somber crowd cheerful by her erratic and glistening ray, even as a bird of bright plumage illuminates a whole tree of dusky foliage by darting to and fro, half seen and half concealed amid the twilight of the clustering leaves.

08:32:50.947 --> 08:32:55.687
She had an undulating, but oftentimes a sharp and irregular movement.

08:32:55.927 --> 08:33:06.957
It indicated the restless vivacity of her spirit, which today was doubly indefatigable in its tiptoe dance, because it was played upon and vibrated with her mother's disquietude.

08:33:06.957 --> 08:33:22.677
Whenever Pearl saw anything to excite her ever-active and wandering curiosity, she flew thitherward and, as we might say, seized upon that man or thing as her own property, so far as she desired it.

08:33:22.677 --> 08:33:44.257
But without yielding the minutest degree of control over her motions and requital, Puritans looked on, and if they smiled, were nonetheless inclined to pronounce the child a demon offspring from the indescribable charm of beauty and eccentricity that shone through her little figure and sparkled with activity.

08:33:44.577 --> 08:33:51.457
She ran and looked the wild Indian in the face, and he grew conscious of a nature wilder than his own.

08:33:52.437 --> 08:34:20.377
Thence, with native audacity, but still with reserve as characteristic, she flew into the midst of a group of mariners, the swarthy-cheeked wild men of the ocean, as the Indians were of the land, and they gazed wonderingly and admiringly at Pearl as if a flake on the sea foam had taken the shape of a little maid and were gifted with a soul of the sea fire that flashes beneath the prow in the night-time.

08:34:20.377 --> 08:34:32.137
One of these seafaring men, the shipmaster indeed, who had spoken to Hester Prynne, was so smitten with Pearl's aspect that he attempted to lay hands upon her with purpose to snatch a kiss.

08:34:32.337 --> 08:34:41.577
Finding it as impossible to touch her as to catch a hummingbird in the air, he took from his hat the gold chain that was twisted about it and threw it to the child.

08:34:41.577 --> 08:34:52.037
Pearl immediately twined it around her neck and waist with such happy skill that once seen there it became a part of her, and when it was difficult to imagine her without it.

08:34:52.037 --> 08:34:55.597
"'Thy mother is yonder woman with the scarlet letter,' said the seaman.

08:34:56.497 --> 08:34:59.197
"'Wilt thou carry her a message from me?'

08:34:59.197 --> 08:35:03.117
"'If the message pleases me, I will,' answered Pearl.

08:35:03.837 --> 08:35:05.697
"'Then tell her,' rejoined her,

08:35:05.877 --> 08:35:16.057
"'that I spake again with the black-a-visaged hump-shouldered old doctor, and he engages to bring his friend, the gentleman she watts of, aboard with him.

08:35:16.057 --> 08:35:20.217
"'So let thy mother take no thought save for herself and thee.

08:35:20.757 --> 08:35:24.337
"'Wilt thou tell her this, thou witch-baby?'

08:35:24.337 --> 08:35:30.337
"'Mistress Heaven says my father is the prince of the air,' cried Pearl with a naughty smile.

08:35:30.477 --> 08:35:38.197
"'If thou callest me that ill name, I shall tell him of thee, and he will chase thy ship with a tempest.'

08:35:39.557 --> 08:35:47.477
Pursuing a zig-zag course across the market-place, the child returned to her mother and communicated what the mariner had said.

08:35:47.797 --> 08:35:58.597
Hester's strong, calm, steadfastly enduring spirit almost sank, at last unbeholding the stark and grim continence of an inevitable doom,

08:35:58.597 --> 08:36:12.237
which at the moment when a passage seemed to open for the minister and herself out of their labyrinth of misery showed itself with an unrelenting smile right in the midst of their path.

08:36:12.297 --> 08:36:23.497
With her mind harassed by the terrible perplexity in which the shipmaster's intelligence involved her, she was also subjected to another trial.

08:36:23.497 --> 08:36:29.217
There were many people present from the country round about who had often heard of the scarlet letter,

08:36:29.817 --> 08:36:37.477
and to whom it had been made terrific by a hundred false or exaggerated rumors who had never beheld it with their own pavly eyes.

08:36:38.137 --> 08:36:46.417
These, after exhausting other modes of amusement, now thronged about Hester Prynne with rude and boorish intrusiveness.

08:36:46.937 --> 08:36:52.657
Unscrupulous as it was, however, you could not bring them nearer than a circuit of several yards.

08:36:52.657 --> 08:37:02.577
At that distance they accordingly stood fixed there by centrifugal force of the repugnance which the mystic symbol inspired.

08:37:03.617 --> 08:37:10.837
A whole gang of sailors likewise, observing the press of spectators and learning the purport of the scarlet letter,

08:37:11.377 --> 08:37:16.297
came and thrust their sunburnt and desperado-looking faces into the ring.

08:37:16.297 --> 08:37:22.317
Even the Indians were affected by a sort of cold shadow of the white man's curiosity,

08:37:23.257 --> 08:37:28.897
and gliding through the crowd fastened their snake-like black eyes on Hester's bosom,

08:37:29.197 --> 08:37:38.077
conceiving perhaps that the wearer of this brilliantly embroidered badge must needs be a personage of high dignity among her people.

08:37:38.077 --> 08:37:49.257
Lastly, the inhabitants of the town, their own interest in this worn-out subject languidly reviving itself by sympathy with what they saw others feel,

08:37:49.877 --> 08:37:54.397
lounged idly to the same quarter and tormented Hester Prynne,

08:37:54.637 --> 08:38:00.517
perhaps more than all the rest with their cool, well-acquainted gaze at her familiar shame.

08:38:01.597 --> 08:38:13.377
Hester saw and recognized the self-same faces of that group of matrons who had awaited her forthcoming from the prison door seven years ago,

08:38:13.577 --> 08:38:21.797
all save one, the youngest and only compassionate among them whose burial robe she had since made.

08:38:22.097 --> 08:38:26.777
At the final hour, when she was so soon to fling aside the burning letter,

08:38:26.777 --> 08:38:32.637
it had strangely become the center of more remark and excitement,

08:38:33.597 --> 08:38:42.837
and was thus made to sear her breast more painfully than at any time since the first day she put it on.

08:38:43.917 --> 08:38:53.257
While Hester stood in that magic circle of ignominy where the cunning cruelty of her sentence seemed to have fixed her forever,

08:38:53.257 --> 08:39:04.397
the admirable preacher was looking down from the sacred pulpit upon an audience whose very inmost spirits had yielded to his control,

08:39:05.037 --> 08:39:10.837
the sainted minister in the church, the woman of the scarlet letter in the marketplace.

08:39:11.517 --> 08:39:21.657
What imagination would have been irreverent enough to surmise that the same scorching stigma was on them both?

08:39:50.364 --> 08:39:52.244
THE REVELATION OF THE SCARLET LETTER.

08:39:53.444 --> 08:40:01.364
The eloquent voice on which the souls of the listening audience had been borne aloft as on the swelling waves of the sea, at length, came to a pause.

08:40:01.664 --> 08:40:05.684
There was a momentary silence, profound as what should follow the utterance of oracles.

08:40:06.084 --> 08:40:18.184
Then ensued a murmur, and half hushed tumult, as if the auditors, released from the high spell that had transported them into the region of another's mind, were returning into themselves with all their awe and wonder still heavy on them.

08:40:18.184 --> 08:40:22.124
In a moment more the crowd began to gush forth from the doors of the church.

08:40:22.384 --> 08:40:34.324
Now that there was an end, they needed more breath, more fit to support the gross and earthly life into which they relapsed, than that atmosphere which the preacher had converted into words of flame and had burdened with the rich fragrance of his thought.

08:40:35.104 --> 08:40:37.424
In the open air their rapture broke into speech.

08:40:37.784 --> 08:40:42.504
The street and the marketplace absolutely babbled from side to side with the plazas of the minister.

08:40:42.504 --> 08:40:48.924
His hearers could not rest until they had told one another of what each knew better than he could tell or hear.

08:40:49.524 --> 08:41:02.424
According to their united testimony, never had man spoken in so wise, so high, and so holy a spirit as he that spake this day, nor had inspiration ever breathed through mortal lips more evidently than it did through his.

08:41:02.424 --> 08:41:15.284
Its influence could be seen, as it were, descending upon him and possessing him and continually lifting him up out of the written discourse that lay before him and filling him with ideas that must have been as marvelous to himself as to his audience.

08:41:16.124 --> 08:41:25.344
His subject, it appeared, had been the relation between the deity and the communities of mankind, with a special reference to the New England which they were here planting in the wilderness.

08:41:25.344 --> 08:41:36.324
And, as he drew towards the close, a spirit of prophecy had come upon him constraining him to its purpose as mightily as the old prophets of Israel were constrained, only with this difference.

08:41:36.584 --> 08:41:46.464
That, whereas the Jewish seers had denounced judgments and ruin on their country, it was his mission to foretell a high and glorious destiny for the newly gathered people of the Lord.

08:41:46.464 --> 08:41:58.444
But, throughout it all, and through the whole discourse, there had been a certain deep, sad undertone of pathos, which could not be interpreted otherwise than as the natural regret of one soon to pass away.

08:41:59.084 --> 08:42:09.844
Yes, their minister, whom they so loved and who so loved them all, that he could not depart heavenward without a sigh, had the foreboding of untimely death upon him and would soon leave them in their tears.

08:42:10.484 --> 08:42:16.064
This idea of his transitory stay on earth gave the last emphasis to the effect which the preacher had produced.

08:42:16.364 --> 08:42:27.064
It was as if an angel, in his passage to the skies, had shaken his bright wings over the people for an instant, at once a shadow and a splendor, and had shed down a shower of golden truths upon them.

08:42:27.064 --> 08:42:41.224
Thus there had come to the Reverend Mr. Dimmesdale, as to most men in their various spheres, though seldom recognized until they see it far behind them, an epoch of life more brilliant and full of triumph than any previous one, or than any which could hereafter be.

08:42:41.224 --> 08:42:58.024
He stood at this moment on the very proudest eminence of superiority, to which the gifts of intellect, rich lore, prevailing eloquence, and a reputation of whitest sanctity, could exult a clergyman in New England's earliest days, when the professional character was of itself a lofty pedestal.

08:42:58.424 --> 08:43:05.404
Such was the position which the minister occupied, as he bowed his head forward on the cushions of the pulpit at the close of his election sermon.

08:43:06.484 --> 08:43:12.644
Meanwhile, Hester Pryne was standing beside the scaffold of the pillory, with the scarlet letter still burning on her breast.

08:43:13.684 --> 08:43:19.004
Now was heard again the clamor of the music, and the measured tramp of the military escort issuing from the church door.

08:43:19.544 --> 08:43:25.644
The procession was to be marshaled thence to the town hall, where a solemn banquet would complete the ceremonies of the day.

08:43:25.644 --> 08:43:42.164
Once more, therefore, the train of venerable and majestic fathers were seen moving through a broad pathway of the people, who drew back reverently on either side as the governor and magistrates, the old and wise men, the holy ministers, and all that were eminent and renowned, advanced into the midst of them.

08:43:42.164 --> 08:43:46.104
When they were fairly in the market place, their presence was greeted by a shout.

08:43:46.804 --> 08:44:01.324
This, though doubtless it might acquire additional force and volume from the childlike loyalty which the age awarded to its rulers, was felt to be an irrepressible outburst of enthusiasm kindled in the auditors by that high strain of eloquence which was yet reverberating in their ears.

08:44:01.684 --> 08:44:05.424
Each felt the impulse in himself, and in the same breath caught it from his neighbor.

08:44:05.424 --> 08:44:10.964
Within the church it had hardly been kept down. Beneath the sky it peeled upward to the zenith.

08:44:11.184 --> 08:44:29.044
There were human beings enough, and enough of highly wrought and symphonious feeling, to produce that more impressive sound than the organ tones of the blast, or the thunder, or the roar of the sea, even that mighty swell of many voices, blended into one great voice by the universal impulse which makes likewise one vast heart out of the many.

08:44:29.044 --> 08:44:37.784
Never from the soil of New England had gone up such a shout. Never on New England soil had stood the man so honored by his mortal brethren as the preacher.

08:44:38.464 --> 08:44:53.124
How fared it with him, then? Were there not the brilliant particles of a halo in the air about his head, so etherealized by spirit as he was, and so apotheosized by worshipping admirers, did his footsteps in the procession really tread upon the dust of the earth?

08:44:53.124 --> 08:45:01.124
As the ranks of military men and civil fathers moved onward, all eyes were turned towards the point where the minister was seen to approach among them.

08:45:01.504 --> 08:45:06.524
The shout died into a murmur, as one portion of the crowd after another obtained a glimpse of him.

08:45:06.864 --> 08:45:21.704
How feeble and pale he looked amid all his triumph. The energy, or say rather the inspiration which had held him up until he should have delivered the sacred message that had brought its own strength along with it from heaven, was withdrawn now that it had so faithfully performed its office.

08:45:21.704 --> 08:45:30.364
The glow, which they had just before beheld burning on his cheek, was extinguished like a flame that sinks down hopelessly among the late decaying embers.

08:45:30.824 --> 08:45:41.424
It seemed hardly the face of a man alive, with such a death-like hue. It was hardly a man with life in him that tottered on his path so nervously, yet tottered and did not fall.

08:45:41.424 --> 08:45:52.724
One of his clerical brethren, it was the venerable John Wilson, observing the state in which Mr. Dimmesdale was left by the retiring wave of intellect and sensibility, stepped forward hastily to offer his support.

08:45:53.184 --> 08:46:07.544
The minister, tremulously, but decidedly, repelled the old man's arm. He still walked onward, if that movement could be so described, which rather resembled the wavering effort of an infant with its mother's arms in view, outstretched to tempt him forward.

08:46:07.544 --> 08:46:22.604
And now, almost imperceptible as were the latter steps of his progress, he came opposite the well-remembered and weather-darkened scaffold where, long since, with all that dreary lapse of time between, Hester Pryne had encountered the world's ignominious stare.

08:46:23.284 --> 08:46:28.484
There stood Hester, holding little Pearl by the hand, and there was the scarlet letter on her breast.

08:46:29.164 --> 08:46:41.344
The minister here made a pause, although the music still played the stately and rejoicing march to which the procession moved. It summoned him onward, inward to the festival, but here he made a pause.

08:46:41.924 --> 08:46:53.364
Bellingham, for the last few moments, had kept an anxious eye upon him. He now left his own place in the procession and advanced to give assistance, judging from Mr. Dimmesdale's aspect that he must otherwise inevitably fall.

08:46:53.364 --> 08:47:05.544
But there was something in the latter's expression that warned back the magistrate, although a man not readily obeying the vague intimations that pass from one spirit to another. The crowd, meanwhile, looked on with awe and wonder.

08:47:06.124 --> 08:47:20.424
This earthly faintness was, in their view, only another phase of the minister's celestial strength, nor would it have seemed a miracle too high to be wrought for one so holy had he ascended before their eyes waxing dimmer and brighter and fading at last into the light of heaven.

08:47:20.424 --> 08:47:24.104
He turned towards the scaffold and stretched forth his arms.

08:47:24.744 --> 08:47:28.604
Hester, said he, come hither, come, my little pearl.

08:47:29.424 --> 08:47:35.644
It was a ghastly look with which he regarded them, but there was something at once tender and strangely triumphant in it.

08:47:35.964 --> 08:47:41.584
The child, with the birdlike motion which was one of her characteristics, flew to him and clasped her arms about his knees.

08:47:41.584 --> 08:47:51.004
Hester Prine, slowly, as if impelled by inevitable fate and against her strongest will, likewise drew near, but paused before she reached him.

08:47:51.584 --> 08:48:02.264
At this instant, old Roger Killingworth thrust himself through the crowd, or, perhaps, so dark, disturbed, and evil was his look he rose up out of some nether region to snatch back his victim from what he sought to do.

08:48:02.604 --> 08:48:06.984
Be that as it might, the old man rushed forward and caught the minister by the arm.

08:48:06.984 --> 08:48:10.784
Madam, hold. What is your purpose? whispered he.

08:48:10.944 --> 08:48:19.844
Wave back that woman. Cast off this child. All shall be well. Do not blacken your fame and perish in dishonor. I can yet save you. Would you bring infamy on your sacred profession?

08:48:20.644 --> 08:48:26.644
Ha, tempter, methinks thou art too late, answered the minister, encountering his eye fearfully but firmly.

08:48:27.044 --> 08:48:30.944
Thy power is not what it was. With God's help, I shall escape thee now.

08:48:31.384 --> 08:48:34.864
He again extended his hand to the woman of the scarlet letter.

08:48:35.644 --> 08:48:51.404
Hester Pryne, cried he with a piercing earnestness, in the name of him, so terrible and so merciful, who gives me grace at this last moment to do what, for my own heavy sin and miserable agony I withheld myself from doing seven years ago, come hither now and twine thy strength about me.

08:48:51.884 --> 08:49:01.964
Thy strength, Hester, but let it be guided by the will which God hath granted me. This wretched and wronged old man is opposing it with all his might, with all his own might, and the fiend's.

08:49:01.964 --> 08:49:05.264
Come, Hester, come, support me up yonder scaffold.

08:49:06.044 --> 08:49:24.544
The crowd was in a tumult. The men of rank and dignity who stood there immediately around the clergymen were so taken by surprise and so perplexed as to the purport of what they saw, unable to receive the explanation which most readily presented itself, or to imagine any other, that they remained silent and inactive spectators of the judgment which Providence seemed about to work.

08:49:24.544 --> 08:49:35.524
They beheld the minister leaning on Hester's shoulder and, supported by her arm around him, approached the scaffold and ascended steps, while still the little hand of the sin-born child was clasped in his.

08:49:35.944 --> 08:49:45.764
Old Roger Chillingworth followed, as one intimately connected with the drama of guilt and sorrow in which they had all been actors, and well entitled, therefore, to be present at its closing scene.

08:49:45.764 --> 08:49:57.284
Hath thou sought the whole earth over, said he, looking darkly at the clergymen, there was no one place so secret, no high place, nor lowly place, where thou couldst have escaped me save on this very scaffold.

08:49:58.284 --> 08:50:10.444
Thanks be to him who hath led me hither, answered the minister. Yet he trembled and turned to Hester with an expression of doubt and anxiety in his eyes, not the less evidently betrayed that there was a feeble smile upon his lips.

08:50:10.444 --> 08:50:15.044
Is not this better, murmured he, than what we dreamed of in the forest?

08:50:15.544 --> 08:50:18.404
I know not, I know not, she hurriedly replied.

08:50:18.664 --> 08:50:22.364
Better? Yea, so we may both die, and little Pearl die with us.

08:50:22.724 --> 08:50:27.584
For thee and Pearl be it as God shall order, said the minister, and God is merciful.

08:50:27.944 --> 08:50:36.324
Let me now do the will which he hath made plain before my sight, for, Hester, I am a dying man, so let me make haste to take my shame upon me.

08:50:37.464 --> 08:51:01.104
Partly supported by Hester Pryne and holding one hand of little Pearl's, the reverend Mr. Dimmesdale turned to the dignified and venerable rulers, to the holy ministers who were his brethren, to the people whose great heart was thoroughly appalled, yet overflowing with tearful sympathy, as knowing that some deep life-matter which, if full of sin, was full of anguish and repentance likewise, was now to be laid open to them.

08:51:01.604 --> 08:51:12.804
The sun, but little past its meridian, shone down upon the clergyman, and gave a distinctness to his figure, as he stood out from all the earth, to put in his plea of guilty at the bar of eternal justice.

08:51:13.404 --> 08:51:25.284
People of New England, he cried with a voice that rose over them high, solemn, and majestic, yet had always a tremor through it, and sometimes a shriek struggling up out of the fathomless depths of remorse and woe.

08:51:25.284 --> 08:51:31.084
Ye that loved me, ye that have deemed me holy, behold me here, the one sinner of the world.

08:51:31.364 --> 08:51:45.344
At last, at last, I stand upon the spot where, seven years since, I should have stood, here, with this woman, whose arm, more than the little strength wherewith I have crept hitherward, sustains me at this dreadful moment from groveling down upon my face.

08:51:45.344 --> 08:52:00.024
Lo, the scarlet letter which Hester wears, ye have all shuddered at it. Wherever her walk hath been, wherever so miserably burdened she may have hoped to find repose, it hath cast a lurid gleam of awe and horrible repugnance round about her.

08:52:00.064 --> 08:52:05.444
But there stood one in the midst of you, at whose brand of sin and infamy ye have not shuddered.

08:52:06.424 --> 08:52:22.144
It seemed, at this point, as if the minister must leave the remainder of his secret undisclosed, but he fought back the bodily weakness and, still more, the faintness of heart that was striving for the mastery of him. He threw off all assistance and stepped passionately forward apace before the woman and the child.

08:52:22.144 --> 08:52:45.244
It was on him, he continued with a kind of fierceness, so determined was he to speak out the whole. God's eye beheld it, the angels were forever pointing at it, the devil knew it well and fretted it continually with the touch of his burning finger, but he hid it cunningly from men and walked among you with the mean of a spirit, mournful, because so pure in his sinful world, and sad because he missed his heavenly kindred.

08:52:45.244 --> 08:53:03.164
Now, at the death hour, he stands up before you, he bids you look again at Hester's scarlet letter. He tells you that, with all its mysterious horror, it is but the shadow of what he bears on his own breast, and that even this, his own red stigma, is no more than the type of what has seared his inmost heart.

08:53:03.164 --> 08:53:08.904
Stand any here that question God's judgment on a sinner? Behold, behold, a dreadful witness of it!

08:53:09.264 --> 08:53:29.064
With a convulsive motion he tore away the ministerial band from before his breast. It was revealed, but it were irreverent to describe that revelation. For an instant, the gaze of the horror-stricken multitude was concentrated on the ghastly miracle, while the minister stood with a flush of triumph in his face as one who, in the crisis of acutest pain, had won a victory.

08:53:29.064 --> 08:53:40.844
Then, down he sank upon the scaffold. Hester partly raised him and supported his head against her bosom. Old Roger Chillingworth knelt down beside him with a blank, dull countenance, out of which the life seemed to have departed.

08:53:41.404 --> 08:53:45.784
Thou hast escaped me, he repeated more than once. Thou hast escaped me!

08:53:46.184 --> 08:53:50.844
May God forgive thee, said the minister. Thou too hast deeply sinned.

08:53:51.164 --> 08:53:54.964
He withdrew his dying eyes from the old man and fixed them on the woman and the child.

08:53:55.544 --> 08:54:07.964
My little Pearl, said he feebly, and there was a sweet and gentle smile over his face, as of a spirit sinking into deeper pose. Nay, now that the burden was removed, it seemed almost as if he would be supportive with the child.

08:54:07.964 --> 08:54:14.424
Dear little Pearl, wilt thou kiss me now? Thou wouldst not yonder in the forest, but now thou wilt?

08:54:15.104 --> 08:54:17.604
Pearl kissed his lips. A spell was broken.

08:54:18.084 --> 08:54:32.924
The great scene of grief in which the wild infant bore apart had developed all her sympathies, and as her tears fell upon her father's cheek, they were the pledge that she would grow up amid human joy and sorrow, nor forever do battle with the world but be a woman in it.

08:54:32.924 --> 08:54:37.284
Towards her mother too, Pearl's errand as a messenger of anguish was fulfilled.

08:54:38.264 --> 08:54:40.764
Hester, said the clergyman, farewell.

08:54:41.724 --> 08:54:45.524
Shall we not meet again? whispered she, bending her face down close to his.

08:54:46.004 --> 08:54:56.824
Shall we not spend our immortal life together? Surely, surely we have ransomed one another with all this woe. Thou lookest far into eternity with those bright dying eyes. Then tell me what thou seest.

08:54:56.824 --> 08:55:04.084
Hush, Hester, hush, said he with tremulous solemnity. The law we broke, the sin here awfully revealed.

08:55:04.624 --> 08:55:18.504
Let these alone be in thy thoughts. I fear, I fear, it may be that when we forgot our God, when we violated our reverence each for the other's soul, it was thence forth vain to hope that we could meet hereafter in an everlasting and pure reunion.

08:55:18.504 --> 08:55:36.044
God knows, and he is merciful. He hath proved his mercy most of all in my afflictions, by giving me this burning torture to bear upon my breast, by sending yonder dark and terrible old man to keep the torture always at red heat, by bringing me hither to die this death of triumphant ignominy before the people.

08:55:36.384 --> 08:55:43.764
Had either of these agonies been wanting, I had been lost forever. Praised be his name, his will be done. Farewell.

08:55:43.764 --> 08:56:01.144
That final word came forth with the minister's expiring breath. The multitude, silent till then, broke out in a strange, deep voice of awe and wonder, which could not as yet find utterance save in this murmur that rolled so heavily after the departed spirit.

08:56:30.713 --> 08:56:35.373
After many days, when time sufficed for the people to arrange their thoughts in reference

08:56:35.373 --> 08:56:40.913
to the foregoing scene, there was more than one account of what had been witnessed on the scaffold.

08:56:41.553 --> 08:56:46.633
Most of the spectators testified to having seen, on the breast of the unhappy minister,

08:56:47.153 --> 08:56:54.693
a scarlet letter, the very semblance of that worn by Hester Brynn, imprinted in the flesh,

08:56:55.113 --> 08:57:00.933
as regarded its origin. There were various explanations, all of which must necessarily

08:57:00.933 --> 08:57:07.533
have been conjectural. Some affirm that the Reverend Mr. Dimmesdale, on the very day when

08:57:07.533 --> 08:57:14.693
Hester Brynn first wore her ignominious badge, had begun a course of penance, which he afterwards,

08:57:14.893 --> 08:57:20.613
in so many futile methods, followed out by inflicting a hideous torture on himself.

08:57:21.153 --> 08:57:26.193
Others contended that the stigma had not been produced until a long time subsequent,

08:57:26.833 --> 08:57:32.833
when old Roger Chillingworth, being a potent necromancer, had caused it to appear through

08:57:32.833 --> 08:57:39.913
the agency of magic and poisonous drugs. Others, again, and those best able to appreciate the

08:57:39.913 --> 08:57:46.553
minister's peculiar sensibility and the wonderful operation of his spirit upon the body, whispered

08:57:46.553 --> 08:57:51.893
their belief that the awful symbol was the effect of the ever-active tooth of remorse,

08:57:51.893 --> 08:57:58.013
gnawing from the inmost heart outwardly, and at last manifesting heaven's dreadful judgment

08:57:58.013 --> 08:58:03.333
by the visible presence of the letter. The reader may choose among these theories.

08:58:04.093 --> 08:58:08.933
We have thrown all the light we could acquire upon the portent and would gladly, now that it

08:58:08.933 --> 08:58:16.473
has done its office, erase its deep print out of our own brain. Where long meditation has fixed it

08:58:16.473 --> 08:58:22.913
very undesirable distinctness, it is singular nevertheless that certain persons who were

08:58:22.913 --> 08:58:27.833
spectators of the whole scene and professed never once to have removed their eyes from the Reverend

08:58:27.833 --> 08:58:33.913
Mr. Dimmesdale, denied that there was any mark whatever on his breast more than on a newborn

08:58:33.913 --> 08:58:41.233
infant's, neither by their report had his dying words acknowledged nor even remotely implied any,

08:58:41.233 --> 08:58:47.593
the slightest connection on his part with the guilt for which Hester Prynne had so long worn

08:58:47.593 --> 08:58:53.553
the scarlet letter. According to these highly respectable witnesses, the minister, conscious

08:58:53.553 --> 08:58:59.213
that he was dying, conscious also that the reverence of the multitude placed him already

08:58:59.213 --> 08:59:05.733
among saints and angels, had desired by yielding up his breath in the arms of that fallen woman

08:59:05.733 --> 08:59:11.973
to express to the world how utterly new Katori is the choicest of man's own righteousness.

08:59:12.953 --> 08:59:19.093
After exhausting life in his efforts for mankind's spiritual good, he had made the manner of his

08:59:19.093 --> 08:59:25.953
death a parable in order to impress on his admirers the mighty and mournful lesson that,

08:59:26.033 --> 08:59:33.633
in the view of infinite purity, we all sinners all alike, it was to teach them that the holiest

08:59:33.633 --> 08:59:39.973
amongst us has but attained so far above his fellows as to discern more clearly the mercy

08:59:39.973 --> 08:59:47.033
which looks down and repudiate more utterly the phantom of human merit which would look

08:59:47.033 --> 08:59:52.973
aspiringly upward. Without disputing a truth so momentous, we must be allowed to consider

08:59:52.973 --> 08:59:59.573
this version of Mr. Dimmesdale's story as only an instance of that stubborn fidelity with which

08:59:59.573 --> 09:00:07.313
man's friends, and especially a clergyman's, will sometimes uphold his character when proofs

09:00:07.313 --> 09:00:13.733
clear as the midday sunshine on the scarlet letter establish him a false and sin-stained creature

09:00:13.733 --> 09:00:20.473
of the dust. The authority which we have chiefly followed, a manuscript of old date drawn up from

09:00:20.473 --> 09:00:26.773
the verbal testimony of individuals, some of whom had known as Duprin, while others had heard the

09:00:26.773 --> 09:00:33.613
from contemporary witnesses, fully confirms the view taken in the foregoing pages. Among many

09:00:33.613 --> 09:00:40.413
morals which press upon us from the poor minister's miserable experience, we put only this into a

09:00:40.413 --> 09:00:48.053
sentence. Be true, be true, be true. Show freely to the world, if not your worst, yet some trait

09:00:48.053 --> 09:00:53.853
whereby the worst may be inferred. Nothing was more remarkable than the change which took place

09:00:53.853 --> 09:00:59.873
almost immediately after Mr. Dimmesdale's death in the appearance and demeanor of the old man

09:00:59.873 --> 09:01:05.893
known as Roger Chillingworth. All his strength and energy, all his vital and intellectual force

09:01:05.893 --> 09:01:11.973
seemed at once to desert him in so much that he positively withered up, shriveled away and

09:01:11.973 --> 09:01:18.973
almost vanished from mortal sight like an uprooted weed that lies wilting in the sun. This unabby

09:01:18.973 --> 09:01:24.593
man had made the very principle of his life to consist in the pursuit and systematic exercise

09:01:24.593 --> 09:01:32.193
of revenge. And when, by its completest triumph, consummation, that evil principle was left with no

09:01:32.193 --> 09:01:37.873
further material to support it, when, in short, there was no more devil's work on earth for him

09:01:37.873 --> 09:01:44.573
to do, it only remained for the unhumanized mortal to but take himself, whether his master would find

09:01:44.573 --> 09:01:50.933
him task enough and pay him his wages duly. But to all these shadowy beings so long our

09:01:50.933 --> 09:01:57.073
near acquaintances, as well Roger Chillingworth as his companions, we would fain be merciful.

09:01:57.753 --> 09:02:04.133
It is a curious subject of observation and inquiry whether hatred and love be not the same thing at

09:02:04.133 --> 09:02:10.933
bottom. Each, in its utmost development, supposes a high degree of intimacy and heart knowledge.

09:02:10.933 --> 09:02:17.073
Each renders one individual dependent for the food of his affections and spiritual life upon

09:02:17.073 --> 09:02:24.773
another. Each leaves the passionate lover or the no less passionate hater forlorn and desolate by

09:02:24.773 --> 09:02:31.273
the withdrawal of his subject philosophically considered. Therefore the two passions seem

09:02:31.273 --> 09:02:37.553
essentially the same, except that one happens to be seen in a celestial radiance and the other

09:02:37.553 --> 09:02:43.353
in a dusky and lowered glow. In the spiritual world, the old physician and the minister,

09:02:43.773 --> 09:02:49.473
mutual victims as they have been, may unawares have found their earthly stalk of hatred and

09:02:49.473 --> 09:02:55.653
antipathy transmuted into gold and love. Leaving this discussion apart, we have a matter of business

09:02:55.653 --> 09:03:01.893
to communicate to the reader that old Roger Chillingworth's decease, which took place within

09:03:01.893 --> 09:03:07.013
the year, and by his last will and testament of which Governor Bellingham and the Reverend

09:03:07.013 --> 09:03:12.313
Mr. Wilson were executors, he bequeathed a very considerable amount of property,

09:03:12.553 --> 09:03:19.133
both here and in England, to little Burl, the daughter of Esther Brinn. So Burl, the elf child,

09:03:19.353 --> 09:03:24.893
the demon offspring, as some people up to that epoch persisted in considering her,

09:03:25.153 --> 09:03:31.213
became the richest heiress of her day in the New World. Not improbably, this circumstance brought

09:03:31.213 --> 09:03:36.973
very material change in the public estimation, and had the mother and child remained here.

09:03:37.553 --> 09:03:43.193
Little Burl, at a marriageable period of life, might have mingled her wild blood with the lineage

09:03:43.193 --> 09:03:50.093
of the devoutest Puritan among them all, but no time after the physician's death, the wearer of

09:03:50.093 --> 09:03:56.553
the scarlet letter disappeared, and Burl along with her. For many years, though a vague report,

09:03:56.553 --> 09:04:02.233
would now and then find its way across the sea, like a shapeless piece of driftwood tossed ashore

09:04:02.233 --> 09:04:07.933
with the initials of a name upon it, yet no tidings of them unquestionably authentic were

09:04:07.933 --> 09:04:14.213
received. The story of the scarlet letter grew into a legend. Its spell, however, was still potent,

09:04:14.593 --> 09:04:21.133
and kept the scaffold awful where the poor minister had died, and likewise the cottage by the seashore

09:04:21.133 --> 09:04:27.033
where Esther Brann had dwelt. Near this latter spot, one afternoon, some children were at play,

09:04:27.513 --> 09:04:32.973
when they beheld a tall woman in a gray robe approach the cottage door. In all those years,

09:04:33.133 --> 09:04:38.993
it had never once been opened, but either she unlocked it, or the decaying wooden iron yielded

09:04:38.993 --> 09:04:45.393
to her hand, or she glided shadow-like through these impediments, and at all events went in.

09:04:45.393 --> 09:04:51.613
On the threshold she paused, turning partly round, for perchance the idea of entering alone

09:04:51.613 --> 09:04:57.293
and all so changed, the home of so intense a former life, was more dreary and desolate

09:04:57.293 --> 09:05:03.513
than even she could bear, but her hesitation was only for an instant, though long enough to display

09:05:03.513 --> 09:05:10.253
a scarlet letter on her breast. And Esther Brann had returned and taken up her long forsaken shame,

09:05:10.253 --> 09:05:15.313
but where was little Pearl? If still alive, she must now have been in the flush and bloom

09:05:15.313 --> 09:05:21.033
of early womanhood. None knew, nor ever learned, with the fullness of perfect certainty,

09:05:21.453 --> 09:05:27.433
whether the elf-child had gone thus untimely to a maiden grave, or whether her wild, rich nature

09:05:27.433 --> 09:05:32.333
had been softened and subdued and made capable of a woman's gentle happiness.

09:05:32.513 --> 09:05:37.993
But through the remainder of Esther's life, there were indications that the recluse of the scarlet

09:05:37.993 --> 09:05:44.673
letter was the object of love and interest with some inhabitant of another land. Letters came

09:05:44.673 --> 09:05:51.553
with armorial seals upon them, though of bearings unknown to English heraldry. In the cottage there

09:05:51.553 --> 09:05:57.013
were articles of comfort and luxuries such as Esther never cared to use, but which only wealth

09:05:57.013 --> 09:06:03.373
could have purchased and affection have imagined for her. There were trifles, too, little ornaments,

09:06:03.373 --> 09:06:09.293
beautiful tokens of a continual remembrance that must have been wrought by delicate fingers

09:06:09.293 --> 09:06:16.253
at the impulse of a fond heart. And once, Esther was seen embroidering a baby garment

09:06:16.253 --> 09:06:22.673
with such a lavish richness of golden fancy as would have raised a public tumult at any

09:06:22.673 --> 09:06:29.193
infant thus apparel had been shown to our sober-youthed community. In fine, the gossips

09:06:29.193 --> 09:06:34.293
of that day believed, and Mr. Surveyor Pugh, who made investigations a century later,

09:06:34.713 --> 09:06:40.093
believed, and one of his recent successors in office, moreover, faithfully believes,

09:06:40.593 --> 09:06:46.593
that Pearl was not only alive but married and happy and mindful of her mother, and that she

09:06:46.593 --> 09:06:52.893
would most joyfully have entertained that sad and lonely mother at her fireside. But there was a

09:06:52.893 --> 09:06:58.933
more real life for Esther brainier in New England than in that unknown region where Pearl had found

09:06:58.933 --> 09:07:06.213
her home. Here had been her sin, here her sorrow and here was yet to be her penitence.

09:07:06.453 --> 09:07:13.293
She had returned, therefore, and resumed of her own free will, for not the sternest magistrate

09:07:13.293 --> 09:07:20.373
of that iron period would have imposed it, resumed the symbol of which we have related so dark a tale.

09:07:21.013 --> 09:07:27.413
Never afterwards did it quit her bosom, but in the lapse of the toilsome, thoughtful and

09:07:27.413 --> 09:07:33.473
self-devoted years that made up Hester's life, the scarlet letter ceased to be a stigma which

09:07:33.473 --> 09:07:39.013
attracted the world's scorn and bitterness, and became a type of something to be sorrowed over

09:07:39.013 --> 09:07:47.553
and looked upon with awe, yet with reverence, too. And, as Hester Brinn had no selfish ends,

09:07:47.913 --> 09:07:53.993
nor lived in any measure for her own profit and enjoyment, people brought all their sorrows and

09:07:53.993 --> 09:08:00.633
complexities, and besought her counsel as one who had herself gone through a mighty trouble,

09:08:01.273 --> 09:08:07.693
women more especially, in the continually recurring trials of wounded, wasted, wronged,

09:08:07.873 --> 09:08:15.633
misplaced, or erring in sinful passion, or with the dreary burden of a heart unyielded. Because

09:08:15.633 --> 09:08:21.613
unvalued and unsought came to Hester's cottage, demanding why they were so wretched, and what

09:08:21.613 --> 09:08:28.993
the remedy. Hester comforted and counseled them as best she might. She assured them, too, of a

09:08:28.993 --> 09:08:35.133
firm belief that at some brighter period, when the world should have grown ripe for it in heaven's

09:08:35.133 --> 09:08:41.833
own time, a new truth would be revealed in order to establish the whole relation between man and

09:08:41.833 --> 09:08:48.413
woman on a surer ground of mutual happiness. Earlier in life, Hester had vainly imagined

09:08:48.413 --> 09:08:54.433
that she herself might be the destined prophetess, but had long since recognized the

09:08:54.433 --> 09:09:00.693
impossibility that any mission of divine and mysterious truth should be confided to a woman

09:09:00.693 --> 09:09:07.593
stained with sin, bowed down with shame, or even burdened with a lifelong sorrow. The angel and

09:09:07.593 --> 09:09:15.953
apostle of the coming revelation must be a woman, indeed, but lofty, pure, and beautiful, and wise.

09:09:15.953 --> 09:09:23.033
Moreover, not through dusky grief, but the ethereal medium of joy and showing how sacred

09:09:23.033 --> 09:09:30.393
love should make us happy by the truest test of a life successful to such an end. So said Hester

09:09:30.393 --> 09:09:36.773
Brin, and glanced her sad eyes downward at the scarlet letter, and after many, many years,

09:09:37.213 --> 09:09:43.953
a new grave was delved near an old and sunken one in that burial ground beside which King's chapel

09:09:43.953 --> 09:09:50.773
has since been built. It was near that old and sunken grave, yet with a space between, as if the

09:09:50.773 --> 09:09:57.873
dust of the two sleepers had no right to mingle, yet one tombstone served for both. All around,

09:09:58.373 --> 09:10:03.553
there were monuments carved with ormorial bearings, and on this simple slab of slate,

09:10:04.073 --> 09:10:11.033
as the curious investigator may still discern, and perplex himself with the porport, there appeared

09:10:11.033 --> 09:10:17.793
the semblance of an engraved escutcheon. It bore a device, a herald's wording, of which may serve

09:10:17.793 --> 09:10:25.153
for a motto and brief description of our now concluded legend. So sombre is it, and relieved

09:10:25.153 --> 09:10:34.153
only by one ever-glowing point of light, gloomier than the shadow on a field, sable. The letter A,

09:10:35.013 --> 09:10:41.893
Gules.

09:10:41.893 --> 09:10:43.793
by Nathaniel Orthorn.
